1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Bc5 { This is the Busch-Gass Gambit, Black sacrifices the e-pawn for very little compensation as we will see soon. In 99% of all cases this isn't played intentionally. It's just a beginner mistake. } 3. Nxe5 { We take this pawn. Of course. There are a few options for Black now. The most important lines are Qe7, an attempt to get the pawn back, and Bxf2, going all in. } 3... Qe7 (3... Bxf2+ 4. Kxf2 (4. Ke2?? Bb6 $17) 4... Qh4+ 5. Kg1 Qxe4 (5... d6 6. Nf3 { [%cal Gf3h4] } 6... Qxe4 7. d4 Bg4 8. Be2)) (3... Qh4 4. d4 Qxe4+ 5. Be3 Nf6 (5... Bb6 6. Nd2 { [%cal Gd2e4] } 6... Qf5 7. Bc4 { [%cal Gc4f7,Ge5f7] } 7... Nh6 { [%cal Rd7d6,Bh6g4] } 8. Rg1) 6. Nd2 Qf5 7. Bd3 Qe6 8. Nxf7! Qxf7 9. dxc5 $16 O-O 10. Bc4 d5 11. cxd6 Be6 12. Bxe6 Qxe6 13. dxc7 Nc6 14. O-O) (3... d6) (3... Nf6) (3... Qf6) (3... Nc6) 4. d4 Nf6 5. dxc5 Qxe5 *


[Event "Busch-Gass Gambit: 1.e4 e5 2.Nf3 Bc5: 3…Bxf2"]
