[ChapterName "3…Bxf2"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/lH2hMGkp/xmz6S581"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/fuxia"]
[UTCDate "2019.06.17"]
[UTCTime "20:12:34"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Bc5 3. Nxe5 Bxf2+ { The point here is that Black hopes for a mistake on White's side, and then this can actually be a bit dangerous. } 4. Kxf2 { We take again. Of course. } 4... Qh4+ { g3 looks like a natural move here, but Kg1 is even better. } { [%cal Rh4e4,Rh4f2] } 5. Kg1 (5. g3 Qxe4 { Nf3 is safe now, but there is also the interesting Bh3! } { [%cal Re4h1,Re4e5] } 6. Bh3 { [%cal Gh3d7,Ge5d7,Gh1e1] } (6. Nf3 Nf6 { Black wants to castle and get the rook into the game. We don't allow that. } 7. Bd3 Qb4 8. Re1+ Kd8 (8... Kf8 9. Kg2 $18) 9. b3 $18 { [%cal Gc1b2] }) 6... Ne7 (6... Qd4+ 7. Kg2 { The knight is safe on e5: Black can't take it because of Re1. } 7... Ne7 8. Nf3 { [%cal Gf3d4] } 8... Qb6 $18)) (5. Ke3? { This is what Black is hoping for. } 5... Qg5+! { [%cal Gg5e5,Gg5e3] } 6. Kf2 (6. Kd4?? c5+! 7. Kc3 (7. Kd3 Qxe5 $17) (7. Kd5?? { Funnily enough: This is the main move in the lichess online database. } 7... Nf6+ $19) 7... Qxe5+ $17) 6... Qxe5 { And Black is okay. }) 5... Qxe4 (5... d6 6. Nf3 Qxe4 7. d4 Bg4 8. Be2 (8. Nc3 { is also fine } 8... Bxf3 9. gxf3 Qg6+ 10. Kf2)) 6. d4 { White also wants to get some pieces out. } 6... Nc6 7. Nf3 $18 { [%cal Gb1c3] } *


