1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Bc4 { Scotch Gambit } 4... Nf6 { Scotch Gambit/Dubois Réti Defense } (4... Bc5 { Haxo Gambit } 5. O-O (5. Ng5 { Scotch Gambit/Saratt Variation } 5... Nh6 6. Nxf7 Nxf7 7. Bxf7+ Kxf7 8. Qh5+ g6 (8... Kg8) 9. Qxc5! d6) 5... d6 6. c3 Bg4 { Scotch Gambit/Cochrane-Anderssen Variation }) (4... Bb4+ { Scotch Gambit/London Defense } 5. c3! dxc3 6. Bxf7+?? (6. bxc3 Ba5 7. Qb3 (7. O-O d6 8. Qb3 { [%cal Rc4f7] } 8... Qf6 9. e5) 7... Qe7 8. O-O) 6... Kxf7 7. Qd5+ Kf8 8. bxc3 Nf6 9. Qb5 Be7 $19) 5. e5 { Scotch Gambit/Advance Variation } (5. O-O Nxe4 $15 { Double Gambit Accepted. Note that White is down TWO pawns. This will change soon. } 6. Re1 d5 (6... f5? 7. Bg5 Be7 8. Bxe7 Qxe7 9. Bd5 Nb4 10. Bb3 d5 11. Nxd4 c5 12. c3 Na6 13. Nxf5 Bxf5 14. Qxd5 { [%cal Gd5f5,Gf2f3] } 14... g6 15. f3 Rd8 16. Qc4 { [%cal Gc4b5,Gb5e8,Gf3e4] } 16... Nc7 { [%cal Gf5e6] } 17. Qe2 Qg5 { [%cal Rf5h3,Rh3g2] } 18. fxe4 $16) 7. Bxd5 { Get one pawn back. Give the bishop for that. } 7... Qxd5 8. Nc3 Qa5 9. Nxe4 { Get the piece back. Still ONE pawn down. } 9... Be6 (9... Be7 10. Bg5 f6 11. Nxf6+ gxf6 12. Bxf6 { [%cal Gf6h8] } 12... O-O 13. Bxe7 Rf7 14. Bh4 $10) 10. Bd2 Qb5 11. Neg5 O-O-O 12. Nxe6 fxe6 $10 13. Ng5 { [%cal Gg5f7,Gg5e6,Bf7h8,Bf7d8] } 13... Rd7 14. Nxe6 { Get the last pawn back. } 14... Qxb2 $15 { And one pawn down again. }) 5... d5 (5... Ng4 { Scotch Gambit/Kingside Variation } 6. O-O Be7 (6... Ngxe5? 7. Nxe5 Nxe5 8. Re1 Qe7 9. f4 Nxc4 10. Rxe7+ Bxe7 11. Qxd4 d5) 7. Re1 d6 8. exd6) (5... Ne4) 6. Bb5 (6. exd6? Bxd6 7. Qe2+ Be7 8. O-O O-O $15) 6... Ne4 (6... Nd7 7. O-O Be7 8. Bxc6 bxc6 9. Nxd4 Nxe5 (9... Nb8) 10. Bf4 c5 11. Bxe5 cxd4 12. Bxg7 Rg8 13. Be5 (13. Bxd4?! { Very dangerous. White has to keep an eye on the g-file. } 13... Bh3 14. g3 Bxf1) 13... c5 (13... Kf8 { Otherwise White has the plan Re1 and Bf6. This is would win the bishop on e7. } { [%cal Rf1e1,Re5f6,Ye1e8] }) 14. Re1 { [%cal Re5f6,Re1e8] } 14... Rg6 { [%csl Rf6] } (14... Qb6 { [%cal Rb6f6,Rb6b2] } 15. Nd2 (15. b4? { Pap, Misa - Krstic, Uros, 1-0, Pula op 17th, 2003, https://lichess.org/9UrZUqRL }) 15... Qg6 16. Bg3)) 7. Nxd4 Bd7 (7... Bc5) 8. Bxc6 bxc6 9. O-O Bc5 10. Be3 (10. f3) 10... Qe7 (10... Bb6 11. Nd2 Nxd2 (11... O-O) 12. Qxd2 O-O 13. Nb3 a5 $10 { [%cal Rc2c3,Ra2a4,Rf2f4] } (13... f6 14. exf6 Qxf6 { [%cal Rf6b2] } 15. Nc5 { [%cal Rc5d7] } 15... Bf5 16. Bd4 (16. c3) 16... Qg6 { [%cal Rf5c2] } 17. Rae1 { [%cal Re1e3,Re3g3,Rg3g7,Rd4g7] } 17... Rfe8 (17... Bxc2?! 18. Re6 { [%cal Re6g6,Re6c6,Rd2c2] } 18... Qg4 { [%cal Rg4d4] } 19. h3 Qf4 { [%cal Rf4d2,Rf4d4] } 20. Be3 Qf7 21. Rxc6 Bf5 22. Rd1 Rad8 23. Bd4 $14) 18. c3 $14)) 11. Re1 (11. f3 Nd6 { [%cal Rc5e3,Re7e3] } 12. Bf2 Nf5 13. c3 O-O 14. Re1 Qg5 15. Qd2 Qe7 $10) (11. f4?! O-O) 11... O-O 12. f3 Ng5 13. f4 Ne6 (13... Ne4) 14. c3 Bb6 15. a4 a5 16. Kh1 g6 17. Nd2 Rab8 18. N2f3 Ng7 19. f5 Nxf5 20. Bg5 Qc5 21. Nxf5 Bxf5 22. Nd4 Be4 23. Bf6 Rfe8 24. Qd2 Rb7 25. Qf4 Qf8 26. Rxe4 dxe4 27. Nf5 h5 28. Bg7 Qxg7 29. Nxg7 Kxg7 30. Qf6+ Kg8 31. Rf1 Rf8 32. e6 Bc5 33. exf7+ Kh7 34. Qxc6 e3 35. Qxb7 e2 36. Re1 Rxf7 37. Qb5 { Jones, Gawain C - Gupta, Abhijeet, 1-0, Commonwealth-ch RSA op, 2011, https://lichess.org/AvHP0WDL } *


