{ White to move and win. }
1. g6 { Yes! If Black doesn't take White's rook, White will take Black's. } { [%cal Gh5a5] } (1. Rxh7 { This allows Black to equalize immediately per Rxa2, followed by Rxb2. } 1... Rxa2 2. Rxc7 Rxb2) (1. Bb3 { That's the second best move. Still winning, but it requires quite some work and very accurate play. } 1... Ra1 2. Rxh7 { [%cal Gh7c7] } 2... Kd8 3. g6 Ne8 { [%cal Re8g7,Re8f6] } 4. Kf5 Rf1+) (1. Bf7+ { Looks clever, but Black doesn't have to take. Ke7 holds the game. } 1... Ke7 2. Rxh7 Ne6 3. Bg6+ Kd6 { This is almost equal, with only a slight edge for White. }) 1... Rxh5 (1... hxg6 2. Rxa5) 2. g7 { Exactly! This pawn cannot be stopped anymore. } (2. Kxh5 { Too greedy! Now Black is slightly better. after hxg6+ Kxg6 a5! } 2... hxg6+ 3. Kxg6 a5 { [%cal Ga5a3,Gb4b3] }) 2... Rc5 3. g8=Q+ { Well done! } *


