1. Be3+ (1. e7 { This allows Black to capture the e-pawn via Re1! And the a-pawn has the wrong color: it can't be supported by White's bishop. } 1... Re1+! 2. Kd6 Rxe7 3. Kxe7 Ka8 { And White's bishop has the wrong corner to support the a-pawn. Draw. }) 1... Kb7 2. e7 Rxa3 3. Ba7 Ra1 4. Kf4 { Correct. Now the king supports the bishop's way back to e3. } 4... Rf1+ 5. Bf2 Rxf2+ 6. Ke3 Rf1 7. Ke2 Kc7 8. e8=Q { Well done! } *


