1. e4 e5 2. d4 exd4 3. Qxd4 Nc6 { Center Game: Normal Variation. The following moves are the most commonly played. } 4. Qe3 (4. Qa4 { A motif from the Scandinavian defense. Low success rate for White so far. } 4... Nf6 5. Nf3 Bc5 6. Bg5 (6. Bb5) (6. Bd3) 6... O-O (6... h6 7. Bh4 { [%cal Ge4e5] } 7... d6 8. Nc3 Bd7 9. O-O-O O-O) (6... d6) 7. Nc3 h6 8. Bh4 Bb4 { Discourage White from castling long. } 9. Bd3 d6 10. O-O Bxc3 11. bxc3 g5 (11... Bd7 { [%cal Rd7a4] } 12. Rab1 { [%cal Gb1b7] } 12... b6 13. Bb5 a6 14. Bxc6 b5 15. Qd4 { [%cal Gd4f6,Gh4f6] } 15... Bxc6 { [%cal Rc6e4] } 16. Rfe1 Re8 $10) 12. Nxg5 hxg5 13. Bxg5 Ne5 14. f4 Nxd3 15. cxd3 Qd7 { [%cal Rd7a4,Rf6g4] } 16. Qd1 Nh7 $10) (4. Qc4) 4... Nf6 { White's main problem is the protection of the e-pawn. } 5. Nc3 (5. Bd3 { This might better in the long run. It avoids the usual pin of the knight on c3, and maybe White can even castle short. } 5... g6 6. Ne2 Bg7 7. Nbc3 d6 8. Qg3 Bd7 9. Qh4 h6 10. O-O a5 $10) 5... Bb4 6. Bd2 O-O 7. O-O-O Re8 { And here comes the weak e-pawn problem. Qg3 is the main move, giving the pawn away, and making this opening actually a gambit. I don't like that. } { [%cal Re8e4,Rf6e4,Rb4c3] } 8. Qg3 (8. Bd3? d5 { [%cal Rd5d4,Re8e3] }) (8. f3 d5 { White has to avoid the fork, protect the pawn, and keep a retreat square for the knight. It's a bit tricky to get out of this situation. } { [%csl Rd4][%cal Re8e3,Rd5d4,Rd4c3,Rd4e3] } 9. Qf2 { The best and most commonly played move. Black is already better. } (9. Qe1?! Bd7 { Avoiding a discovered attack on Black's queen. } { [%cal Gd1d8] } (9... dxe4 10. Nxe4 { [%cal Gd2b4,Gd1d8] } 10... Bxd2+ 11. Rxd2 { [%cal Gd2d8] } 11... Bd7 12. Bd3 Ne5 13. Ne2 { [%cal Ge2g3,Gg3e4] } 13... Nxd3+ 14. Rxd3 Nxe4 15. fxe4 Qg5+ 16. Qd2 Qxd2+ 17. Rxd2 Bc6 { [%cal Rc6e4,Re8e4,Ba8d8] } (17... Rxe4? 18. Nc3 { [%cal Gc3e4,Gd2d7] } 18... Re7 19. Nd5 { [%cal Gd5e7,Gd5c7] } 19... Re4 20. Nxc7 Rd8 21. Rhd1 Re7 $16) 18. Nc3 f6 { The real fight here is about d7. That's why Black can't just take the e-pawn. } { [%csl Bd7] } (18... Bxe4?! 19. Nxe4 Rxe4 20. Rd7 Rc8 21. Rf1 { [%cal Gf1f7,Gd7f7] } 21... f6 $15 { Black is still slightly better here due to the extra pawn. But it will be very hard to convert that into a victory. }) 19. Rhd1 $15 { [%cal Gd2d7] }) (9... d4)) 9... d4 (9... dxe4) 10. Na4 (10. Nb5) 10... Qe7 11. Bb5 Rd8 12. Bxc6 bxc6 13. Nh3) 8... Rxe4 9. a3 Bd6 10. f4 Re8 11. Bd3 Bf8 12. Nf3 d5 $15 *


