[UTCTime "11:42:30"]

1. e4 e5 2. d4 exd4 3. Nf3 { Kieseritzky Variation. The basic idea is that you recapture the pawn with the knight, not with the queen. We know this decision from Black's side in the Scandinavian. This also enables king-side castling earlier. } { [%cal Gd1d4,Gf3d4] } 3... Nc6 { Most common move } (3... Bc5 { Best move, according to SF. The idea is not to protect the d-pawn (not possible anyway), but to keep pressure on f2 for a long time. } { [%csl Bf2][%cal Rc5f2] } 4. Nxd4 (4. c3 { Gambit line } 4... dxc3 5. Nxc3 d6 6. Bg5 (6. Bc4 { Zezulkin, Jurij - Plachetka, Jan, 1-0, CZE-chT 9899, 2016, https://lichess.org/9lu5P5l5 }) 6... Ne7 7. Bc4 h6 $15) (4. Bc4 Nf6 5. e5 d5 6. exf6 dxc4 7. Qe2+ (7. fxg7) 7... Be6 8. fxg7 Rg8 9. Bg5 Be7 10. Bxe7 { d4 must be kept protected } { [%csl Rd4] } 10... Kxe7 11. Qe4 { [%cal Ge4h7,Ge4d4,Gf3d4] } 11... Nc6 $10) 4... Nf6 (4... d6 5. Be2 (5. Nc3) (5. Bc4 Nf6 6. O-O { Don't worry about that pawn. If Black takes it, White gets a really nice attack. } { [%csl Ge4] } 6... O-O (6... Nxe4? 7. Nd2 Bxd4 8. Nxe4 { [%cal Gd1d4] } 8... Bf6 9. Qh5 { [%cal Gc4f7,Gh5f7] } 9... O-O 10. Ng5 Bxg5 11. Bxg5 Qd7 12. Rae1 { [%cal Ge1e7,Gg5e7] } 12... Nc6 13. Bd3 $14 { [%cal Gd3h7,Gh5h7] }))) (4... Qf6?! 5. Nf3 (5. Be3 { Pavkovic, Mario - Orak, Ljubomir, 0-1, Omis op, 2006, https://lichess.org/vdKg76t9 }) 5... d6 6. Nc3 { [%cal Gc3d5,Bd5f6,Bd5c7] } 6... Nc6 7. Nd5 (7. Bg5 Qg6 { [%cal Rg6e4] } 8. Nd5 { [%cal Gd5c7] } 8... Bb6 $10) 7... Qd8 $14) 5. Nc3 (5. e5?! Qe7 6. Be2 Qxe5 7. Nf3 Qe7 $15) 5... O-O 6. Bg5 Re8 7. Be2 Nc6 $15 { Illingworth, Max - Kovacs, Gabor H, 0-1, Budapest FS08 GM, 2011, https://lichess.org/e1ZKBEYB }) (3... Bb4+ 4. Bd2 Bc5 (4... Bxd2+) (4... Qe7) 5. Bg5 { [%cal Gf3d4,Gd1d4] } 5... f6 6. Bh4 Nc6 { [%cal Rc6d4,Rc5d4,Gf3d4,Gd1d4] } 7. Bc4 h5 { [%cal Rg7g5] } 8. Bg3 d6 9. c3 dxc3 10. Nxc3) (3... Nf6 { Transposition: C43 Petrov/Modern Attack } 4. e5 Ne4 5. Qxd4 (5. Qe2 Bb4+ 6. Nbd2 Nxd2 7. Bxd2 Bxd2+ 8. Qxd2 O-O 9. Nxd4 $10) 5... d5 6. exd6 Nxd6 7. Nc3 Nc6 8. Qf4) (3... c5 4. c3 { Morra gambit style! } 4... Nc6 (4... d5) (4... dxc3) 5. cxd4 cxd4 6. Nxd4 Nf6 (6... Bb4+ 7. Bd2 Qe7 8. Nb5 { [%cal Gb5c7] } 8... d5 { [%csl Bc7][%cal Re7c7] }) (6... Bc5) 7. Nc3 (7. Nxc6) 7... Bb4 8. Nxc6 dxc6 (8... bxc6 9. Bd3 d5 10. exd5 Qe7+ 11. Qe2 Qxe2+ 12. Kxe2!? { Unpin the knight } 12... cxd5 $10) (8... Bxc3+ 9. bxc3 bxc6 10. Bd3 $10) 9. Qxd8+ Kxd8 10. f3 Ke7 11. Be3 $10) 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nxc6 bxc6 6. e5 Qe7 7. Qe2 Nd5 8. c4 Ba6 9. b3 g6 10. f4 d6 11. Qf2 Nf6 12. Be2 dxe5 13. O-O Ne4 14. Qe1 O-O-O 15. Nc3 Nc5 16. fxe5 Bg7 17. Na4 Nxa4 18. Bg4+ Kb7 19. bxa4 Qxe5 20. Rb1+ Ka8 21. Bf3 Qc5+ 22. Kh1 Rhe8 23. Qh4 Rd6 24. Bf4 Rde6 25. Rfd1 Bf6 *


