1. e4 e5 2. d4 d5 { C21 King's Pawn Game/Beyer Gambit. This sacrifices the e5-pawn. Overall, this is not a sound gambit. White is just better from the start, and there are little chances for Black to equalize. Don't play this. } 3. dxe5 { The only useful move here. Everything else gives Black an equal game. } 3... Be6 { Avoid the queen trade. } (3... dxe4?! { The engine thinks this is the best move. But it costs Black an essential tempo, and after the queen trade, White is even ahead in development. } 4. Qxd8+ Kxd8 5. Nc3 Bf5 (5... Nc6 6. Bg5+ f6 7. O-O-O+ Bd7 8. exf6 gxf6 9. Bh4 { Abakoumkin, Georgios - Grivas, Efstratios, 1-0, Kallithea-ch U18, 2016, https://lichess.org/stAudxat }) 6. Bf4 Kc8 { Every other move is answered with White's long castling and a check. } 7. Bc4) 4. exd5 Bxd5 5. Nc3 { [%cal Rc3d5] } 5... Bb4 6. Bd2 Be6 7. Nf3 Nc6 8. Bd3 Nge7 9. Qe2 Qd7 $16 *


