1. e4 e5 2. d4 exd4 3. Qxd4 Nc6 4. Qe3 { C22 Center Game: Paulsen Attack Variation } 4... Bb4+ 5. Nc3 Nge7?! { (-0.34 → 0.51) Inaccuracy. Best move was Nf6. I guess the knight has been put there to avoid a pin from g5. However it is very limited by White's e4 pawn, and it's blocking Black's own queen. It will stay there for a very long time. } { [%csl Gd5][%cal Re7d5] } (5... Nf6 6. Bd2 O-O 7. O-O-O Re8 8. Bc4 d6 9. f3 Na5 10. Bd3 d5 11. Qe1 d4 12. Na4) 6. Bd2 O-O 7. O-O-O d6 8. Qg3 { g3 is the natural place of White's queen in this line. Puts pressure on g7 and makes room for the dark-square bishop. } { [%csl Gg7][%cal Gg3g7] } 8... Kh8 { Preparation for f7-f5. Once that has been played, the c4-f7 diagonale is an invitation for White's light-square bishop. } { [%cal Gc4f7,Gf1c4] } 9. f4 { Forces Black to play f5 now. Otherwise White will play it and own the entire king side. } 9... f5 10. e5 { Developing pieces might have been better. Also, the e4 pawn was blocking Black's knight on e7 so nicely. } (10. Bd3 fxe4 11. Bxe4 Bf5 12. Bxf5 Nxf5 13. Qd3 Nfd4 $14) 10... dxe5 11. fxe5 { [%cal Gd1d8] } (11. Nge2 { Black can't take the f-pawn, that would lead to a discovered attack on the queen. } { [%cal Gd1d8] } 11... Bd6 (11... exf4? 12. Nxf4 { [%csl Gd5][%cal Gc3d5,Gf4d5] } 12... Qe8 13. Bc4 { [%cal Gh1e1,Ge1e8] } 13... Ne5 14. Bb3 Bd6 $16)) 11... Qe8 12. Nf3 (12. Nh3 { [%cal Gg3c3] } 12... Qf7 { [%cal Rf7a2] } 13. Ng5 { [%cal Gg5f7] } 13... Qg8 14. a3 Bc5 $14) 12... f4 { That pawn is safe for now. It also illustrates why Nf3 wasn't so good: The knight on c3 needs a second defender, but Nf3 is blocking White's own queen. } { [%cal Gg3c3] } 13. Qf2 (13. Bxf4? Bxc3 14. bxc3 Qf7 { [%cal Rf7a2] }) 13... Bg4 14. Re1 (14. Be2 Rd8 15. Rhe1 Ng6 $10) 14... Rd8 15. Bd3 Qh5 { Here was an opportunity for a spectacular draw. } (15... Ba5 16. h3 Bb6 17. hxg4!? Bxf2 18. Rxh7+ Kg8 19. Rh8+ Kxh8 20. Rh1+ Kg8 21. Bh7+ Kh8 (21... Kf7?? 22. Ng5#) 22. Bf5+ Kg8 23. Bh7+) 16. Be4 Ba5 17. h3 Bf5 18. Rhf1 (18. e6!? { [%cal Ge1e6,Be4c6] } 18... Rde8) 18... Bb6 { [%cal Rb6f2] } (18... Qh6 { [%csl Re6][%cal Rh6f4,Rh6e6] } 19. Qh4 Qg6 20. Bxc6 { Now everything is hanging. } { [%cal Gh4e7,Gc6b7,Rf5c2,Ra5c3,Re7c6,Rd8d2,Gh4f4] } 20... Nxc6 21. Qxf4 Bxc2 { [%cal Rf8f4] } 22. Nh4 { [%cal Gh4g6,Rf8f4] } 22... Rxf4 23. Nxg6+ Bxg6 24. Rxf4 $10) 19. Qe2 Be6 { [%cal Re6a2] } 20. a3 a6 21. Bd3 (21. Nh2 { [%cal Ge2h5] } 21... Qg5 22. Kb1 h6 $10) 21... Ba7 (21... Ng6) 22. Ne4 (22. Nd4 { [%cal Ge2h5] } 22... Qxe2 23. Ndxe2 f3 24. gxf3 Bxh3 25. Rh1 { [%cal Gd3h7,Gh1h7] } 25... Rxd3 26. cxd3 Bg2 27. Rh2 Bxf3 28. Rf1 Ng6 $10) 22... Nd5 23. g4 Qe8 24. Neg5 { [%cal Gd3h7,Gg5h7] } 24... Bg8 { [%cal Gd3h7,Gg5h7] } (24... Ne3 { [%cal Re3f1] } 25. Bxh7 g6 26. Nh4 Bc4 $17) 25. Qe4 Ne3 26. e6 { The bishop on g8 has to protect h7. } { [%csl Bh7][%cal Ge4h7,Gd3e4,Rg8h7] } 26... Rxd3 (26... Nxf1) 27. Qxd3 h6? { (-0.21 → 1.53) Mistake. Best move was Nxf1. } (27... Nxf1 28. Rxf1 h6 29. Nf7+ Bxf7 30. exf7 Qxf7 31. Kb1 Kg8 32. g5 Rd8 33. Qe4 Re8 34. Qxf4) 28. Nf7+ Bxf7 29. exf7 Qxf7 30. Bxe3 Bxe3+ 31. Kb1 Rd8?! { (1.61 → 2.54) Inaccuracy. Best move was Kg8. } (31... Kg8 32. Rd1) 32. Qc3? { (2.54 → 1.46) Mistake. Best move was Ne5. } (32. Ne5 Qe8 33. Ng6+ Kh7 34. Nf8+ Kg8 35. Qc4+ Kxf8 36. Rxe3 Qxe3 37. Rxf4+ Ke7 38. Re4+ Qxe4) 32... Qd5 33. h4 Qe4?! { (1.24 → 1.77) Inaccuracy. Best move was Kg8. } (33... Kg8 34. Rd1) 34. h5 Rd5?! { (1.59 → 2.31) Inaccuracy. Best move was Qe7. } (34... Qe7 35. Rd1 Re8 36. Qb3 Rb8 37. Qd5 Rd8 38. Qf5 Rf8 39. Qd7 Re8 40. Qd5 Qe4 41. Qxe4) 35. g5 hxg5 36. h6 Qg6? { (2.29 → 3.41) Mistake. Best move was Qe7. } (36... Qe7 37. Rh1 Ne5 38. Rh5 Qc5 39. Nxe5 Qxc3 40. Nf7+ Kh7 41. bxc3 gxh6 42. Nxh6 Kg6 43. Rhh1) 37. hxg7+ Qxg7 38. Rh1+ Kg8 39. Qc4 Qf7 40. Qb3? { (1.65 → 0.00) Mistake. Best move was Qe4. } (40. Qe4 Rb5 41. Rh6 Rxb2+ 42. Kxb2 Qg7+ 43. Kb1 Qxh6 44. Qd5+ Kg7 45. Nxg5 Kf6 46. Ne4+ Ke7) 40... Nd8? { (0.00 → 1.96) Mistake. Best move was Na5. } (40... Na5 41. Qa4 Nc4 42. Qxc4 Rd1+ 43. Rxd1 Qxc4 44. Nxg5 Kg7 45. Rd8 Qe2 46. Rh7+ Kf6 47. Ne4+) 41. Rh5? { (1.96 → 0.52) Mistake. Best move was Rd1. } (41. Rd1 Rxd1+ 42. Rxd1 Qxb3 43. Rxd8+ Kg7 44. cxb3 g4 45. Nh2 g3 46. Nf3 g2 47. Rd7+ Kf6) 41... Qxh5 42. Qxd5+ Nf7 43. Qe4?! { (1.05 → 0.27) Inaccuracy. Best move was Rf1. } (43. Rf1 Kg7 44. Nd4 Bxd4 45. Qxd4+ Kf8 46. Qb4+ Kg7 47. Qd4+ Kf8 48. Qb4+ Kg7 49. Qxb7 Qe2) 43... Kf8? { (0.27 → 1.99) Mistake. Best move was g4. } (43... g4 44. Nd4 Qe5 45. Qg6+ Qg7 46. Qxg7+ Kxg7 47. Nf5+ Kg6 48. Nxe3 fxe3 49. Kc1 Kf5 50. Rxe3) 44. Rd1? { (1.99 → 0.63) Mistake. Best move was Ne5. } (44. Ne5 Nd6 45. Qd5 Kg7 46. Rh1 Qe8 47. a4 f3 48. Ng4 f2 49. Qd3 Qe4 50. Qxe4 Nxe4) 44... g4 45. Ne1 Nd6 46. Qe6 g3 47. Rd5 Qf7 48. Qh6+ Qg7?! { (1.03 → 1.82) Inaccuracy. Best move was Ke7. } (48... Ke7 49. Rg5) 49. Qh4 Nf7 50. Ng2? { (1.66 → -0.50) Mistake. Best move was Rd7. } (50. Rd7 Qg6 51. Ng2 Bc5 52. Nxf4 Qf5 53. Rxc7 Bd6 54. Rc4 b5 55. Rd4 Bc5 56. Rd1 Bd6) 50... Qg6? { (-0.50 → 1.59) Mistake. Best move was Qh6. } (50... Qh6 51. Rd8+ Kg7 52. Qe7 Bc5 53. Qxc5 Nxd8 54. Qxc7+ Nf7 55. Qxb7 Qf6 56. Qe4 f3 57. Nf4) 51. Rd7 Kg8?! { (1.75 → 2.68) Inaccuracy. Best move was b5. } (51... b5 52. Rxc7) 52. Qe7?! { (2.68 → 1.94) Inaccuracy. Best move was Rxc7. } (52. Rxc7 Qg5 53. Qh3 f3 54. Qd7 Qh5 55. Rc8+ Kg7 56. Nxe3 g2 57. Qd4+ Qe5 58. Qg4+ Qg5) 52... b6?? { (1.94 → 5.14) Blunder. Best move was f3. } (52... f3 53. Qxe3 fxg2 54. Rd2 g1=Q+ 55. Qxg1 Nd6 56. Qg2 c6 57. Rd3 Nf5 58. Rd8+ Kg7 59. Rd7+) 53. Nh4 Qh5? { (4.87 → 6.86) Mistake. Best move was g2. } (53... g2 54. Qe8+ Kg7 55. Nxg2 Qf6 56. Nh4 f3 57. Qe4 Bg5 58. Nxf3 Qg6 59. Nxg5 Qxg5 60. Rxc7) 54. Qf6 Bc5?? { (6.65 → 10.43) Blunder. Best move was Bd4. } (54... Bd4 55. Rxd4) 55. Ng6 g2?! { (10.20 → Mate in 1) Checkmate is now unavoidable. Best move was Qh1+. } (55... Qh1+ 56. Ka2 Qh7 57. Qe6 Qg7 58. Nxf4 g2 59. Nxg2 Qf8 60. Rxc7 a5 61. Rc8 Qxc8 62. Qxc8+) 56. Qxf7# { White wins by checkmate. } 1-0


