1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. exd5 cxd5 4. c4 Nf6 5. Nc3 g6 6. Bg5 { Starting position for this chapter.
This is a rare move, and it might lead to a very unique play. } 6... Bg7 (6... Be6) (6... dxc4) (6... Ne4?!) (6... Nbd7 7. Bd3 (7. Nf3) (7. cxd5 Bg7 8. Qb3 O-O 9. Be2 Nb6 10. Bf3) 7... h6) (6... e6? { Gives White a pressing initiative: } 7. cxd5 exd5 8. Bb5+ Nc6 9. Qe2+ Be6 10. Bxf6 Qxf6 11. Nxd5! { [%csl Be6][%cal Rd5f6,Be2e8] } 11... Qd8 12. Bxc6+ (12. Nf4 { Same as the 12.Bxc6 line. } 12... Qxd4 (12... Bb4+ { Same as Qxd4. } 13. Kf1 Qxd4 14. Bxc6+ bxc6 15. Nxe6 fxe6 16. Qxe6+ Kf8 17. Qb3 Qb6 $16) 13. Bxc6+ bxc6 14. Nxe6 Bb4+ 15. Kf1 fxe6 16. Qxe6+ Kf8 17. Qb3 { [%cal Ra1d1,Bb3d1,Bd1d4] } 17... Qb6 $16) 12... bxc6 13. Nf4 Qxd4 14. Nxe6 Bb4+ 15. Kf1 fxe6 16. Qxe6+ Kf8 17. Qb3 Qb6 $16 { Black is just a pawn down here without sufficient compensation. }) 7. Bxf6 { Removes a defender for d5. } (7. Nf3) (7. cxd5) 7... Bxf6 8. cxd5 O-O (8... Qb6) 9. Bc4 (9. Nf3) 9... Na6 (9... e6) (9... Nd7) (9... Qb6 { [%cal Gb6d4,Gb6b2] } 10. Nge2 Qxb2 11. Rb1 Qa3 12. O-O Nd7 13. Ne4 (13. Qd2?! Nb6 { [%cal Gb6c4] } 14. Bb3 Qa5 15. Ng3 Bd7 16. Nge4 { [%cal Re4f6] } 16... Rac8?! (16... Bg7 17. d6 exd6 18. Nxd6 { [%cal Rd6b7] } 18... Bc6 $10 { d4 is pinned and can't advance. } { [%csl Bd4][%cal Gg7c3,Ga5c3] }) 17. Rfc1?! { Aronian, Levon - Carlsen, Magnus, 0-1, Wch Blitz 5th, 2009, https://lichess.org/E4YUyFAu }) 13... Nb6 { [%cal Gb6c4] }) *


