1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. Nd2 dxe4 4. Nxe4 Bf5 5. Ng3 Bg6 6. h4 h6 7. Nf3 Nd7 8. h5 { Spassky Variation. This is probably the most played line in the Classical Variation. You have to learn it. } 8... Bh7 9. Bd3 Bxd3 10. Qxd3 { And here, on move 10, the actual game begins. Black has to make a decision now: play e6 to develop the dark-squared bishop, Qc7 to prevent Bf4, or Ngf6 to prevent Ne4. } 10... e6 (10... Ngf6 11. Bf4 (11. Bd2 e6 12. O-O-O Be7 { transposes back to the main line. }) 11... Qa5+ (11... e6 12. O-O-O Be7 13. Kb1 (13. Ne4 Nxe4 { Bareev played this a while. } 14. Qxe4 Nf6 15. Qd3 (15. Qe2 Qd5 { [%cal Gd5h5,Gd5a2] } 16. Kb1 (16. c4 Qa5 17. a3 b5 (17... Nxh5?! 18. Bd2 Qf5 19. Qe5 Nf6 20. Qc7! { And this is very uncomfortable for Black. } 20... Nd7 { Popov, Vladimir Valentinov - Agostini, Valerio, 1/2-1/2, CT15/pr21, 2006, https://lichess.org/LC7irGhF }))) (15. Qe5?! a5! 16. Kb1 a4 { White's best option here is probably something aggressive, like g4. } 17. c4 { is not a good idea: } 17... O-O 18. Bd2 Qb6 { Ljubojevic, Ljubomir - Anand, Viswanathan, 0-1, Amber-rapid 12th, 2003, https://lichess.org/yaB1JV1O }))) (11... Nd5 12. Bd2 e6 (12... Qc7 { Balogh, Csaba - Binder, Tamas, 1/2-1/2, HUN-chT 0304, 2004, https://lichess.org/t08o1kDo }) 13. O-O-O { [%cal Rf3e5] } (13. c4 Nb4?! 14. Qb3 a5 15. a3 a4 16. Qd1 Na6 { Tal, Mihail - Rodriguez Vargas, Orestes, 1-0, Las Palmas, 1975, https://lichess.org/OHpunZsy }) 13... Qc7 $10 { [%csl Be5][%cal Gc7e5,Gd7e5,Rf3e5] }) 12. Bd2 Qc7 13. O-O-O e6 (13... O-O-O)) (10... Qc7) 11. Bd2 { Prevents Qa5+. } (11. Bf4 { This is a very annoying move. } { [%cal Rf4b8] } 11... Qa5+ (11... Ngf6) 12. Bd2 Bb4 13. c3 (13. a3) (13. Bxb4) (13. Ne4 { Threat: Nd6! } { [%csl Rd6][%cal Re4d6] } 13... Ngf6 (13... Bxd2+) 14. Nd6+ Ke7 15. Nxb7 (15. Nc4 Bxd2+ 16. Nfxd2 (16. Qxd2 Qxd2+ 17. Ncxd2 (17. Nfxd2) (17. Kxd2 c5 $15 { [%cal Gc5d4] }))))) 11... Ngf6 (11... Qc7) 12. O-O-O Be7 { Lobron System } 13. Kb1 (13. Qe2 O-O 14. Ne5 (14. Nf1) (14. Kb1) (14. Rhe1 Rc8 (14... Qc7) (14... c5 15. Nf5 { [%csl Re7][%cal Re2e7] } 15... Rc8 (15... cxd4) (15... exf5 16. Qxe7) 16. Nxe7+ Qxe7))) (13. Ne4 Nxe4 14. Qxe4 Nf6 15. Qd3 (15. Qe2 Qd5 { [%cal Gd5a2] } 16. Kb1 (16. c4 Qe4 17. Qxe4 Nxe4 18. Be3 (18. Be1 $10) 18... f5 19. Rhe1 (19. Nd2) (19. Kc2 f4 { [%cal Gf4e3,Ge4f2] } (19... O-O-O) (19... O-O) 20. Kd3 fxe3 21. Kxe4 exf2 22. Rhf1 $10 (22. Rdf1 Rf8 23. Rxf2 { Anand, Viswanathan - Leko, Peter, 1/2-1/2, Amber-blindfold 17th, 2008, https://lichess.org/w96n9v06 }) 22... Rf8 (22... Bf6 23. Rxf2 Ke7 { Rublevsky, S. - Riazantsev, A., 1/2-1/2, Russian Rapid GP 2015, https://lichess.org/UnOyKoGi }) (22... Bd6 23. Rxf2 O-O { Belyakov, B. - Seger, R., 1-0, 25th Czech Open A 2014, https://lichess.org/AACbxMLX }) 23. Rxf2 { Mista, A. - Miton, K., 1/2-1/2, Bundesliga 2017-18, https://lichess.org/rWhqqFdz })) 16... Rd8 (16... O-O { transposes to the main line. })) 15... O-O 16. g4 { This might lead to a rather weird forced draw! } 16... Nxg4 17. Rhg1 Nxf2! { At a low depth, the engine thinks Black is better here. That's wrong. } 18. Qe3?! Nxd1 19. Qxh6 Bf6 20. Bf4 { [%cal Gf4e5] } 20... Bxd4 21. Be5 { Podvoysky, Evgeny Borisovich - Kazantsev, Renal Aleksandrovic, 1/2-1/2, RUS/C10/sf2 (RUS), 2010, https://lichess.org/IsPQxRyu } 21... Be3+ { [%cal Ge3c1,Ge3h6] } 22. Qxe3! Nxe3 23. Rxg7+ Kh8 24. Rxf7+ Kg8 25. Rg7+ $10 { Draw! }) 13... Qb6 (13... O-O 14. Ne4 c5 (14... Nxe4 15. Qxe4 Nf6 16. Qe2 Qd5 17. Ne5 Qe4 (17... c5) (17... Qxd4) 18. Qxe4 Nxe4 19. Be3 (19. Be1) 19... Rfd8 (19... Bd6) (19... a5) (19... Rac8) 20. g4 (20. c3) 20... c5 21. f3 cxd4 22. Bxd4 Bc5 23. Bxc5 Nxc5 24. c3 Kf8 (24... f6))) *


