1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 dxe4 4. Nxe4 { B15 Main Line } 4... Bf5 { B18 Classical Variation } 5. Ng3 Bg6 6. f4?! { B18 Maróczy Attack. This was played first in 1902 between Jacques Mieses and Geza Maróczy. https://lichess.org/Q32XTGW1 Maybe it should be called Mieses Attack. 20 years later Mieses tried this for the second, and last, time against Tartakower – and he lost again.
Maróczy however played it on the white side three times in 1929 and 1930. And that's probably why this line got his name.
I marked this move as dubious, because it has similar problems as the ➡ Bird Variation with 2.f4: White's kingside is weakened, the dark-squared bishop blocked temporarily, and it simply doesn't develop a piece. } 6... e6 7. Nf3 Nd7 8. Bd3 Bd6 9. O-O Ne7 10. Bxg6 hxg6 11. Ne4 Nf6 12. Neg5 O-O { Berthelot, Yannick - Khenkin, Igor, 0-1, FRA-chT1, 2002, https://lichess.org/cu5NxkVW } *


