Safarli, E., 1/2-1/2, World Rapid 2017, https://lichess.org/ni5S7rnp }) 14. Ne5 $146 { Novelty. } 14... Qd6 { Attack this knight immediately. } { [%cal Gg7e5,Gd6e5] }) 7... Nb6! { Main move and my recommendation if you follow the 8…Nc6 line.. The idea is to play Be6 next if possible, or just Bg7 and castle. } { [%cal Gc8e6,Gf8g7] } (7... e6 { Playable. } 8. Nf3 { White's threats are: Bc4 (which would win a pawn), Bb5 and even Nxd5. } { [%csl Rc4,Rb5][%cal Rf1c4,Rc4b5,Rc3d5] } 8... Bg7 (8... Nc6 { The problem with this move is that Bb5 and Bxc6 damages Black's pawn structure. } 9. Bb5 Bg7 10. O-O O-O 11. Bxc6 { Makes Black pawn structure a bit worse, but also gives up the bishop pair. } 11... bxc6 12. Na4 { It's not easy to recommend a move for Black now. The main moves are Qd6 and Ba6, the engine also likes Qa5 (a novelty!), Qc7 (6 games) and Nb6 (played only twice). } { [%cal Ra4c5] } 12... Qd6 { is the main move. The idea is to play Rb8. This a rather soft threat; White ignores that usually and just develops a rook. } { [%csl Bb8][%cal Bd6b8,Ga8b8,Gb8b3] } (12... Ba6?! { is one of the main moves, but I don't recommend it. Follow this line to see why. } { [%cal Ga6f1] } 13. Re1 Nb6 { supports the square c4 which would be a nice place for Black's light-squared bishop. White can either ignore that and just play Nc5 or activate their dark-squared bishop a tempo on Black's queen with Bg5. } { [%csl Bc4][%cal Ga6c4,Bb6c4] } 14. Bg5 { my recommendation for White. } (14. Nc5?! { The main move. But it allows Black a cute little maneuver: } 14... Bc4 15. Qc3 Bd5 { And this is a good blockader for the IQP now. } 16. Ne5 { White would like to play Bf4 next or Qh3 and Bh6. } { [%csl Rf4,Rh6][%cal Rc3h3,Rc1h6] } 16... Qh4 $10 { prevents that. And it pins the knight on e5 against the d-pawn. Black still wants to play Nc4 eventually. Two moves have been tried here: b3 and f3.
