1. e4 c6 2. Nc3 d5 3. Qf3 { Goldmann Variation. MVL, Short, and Smyslov tried this. The basic idea is an attack on f7. } { [%csl Bf7][%cal Rf3f7,Rf1c4,Rc4f7] } 3... dxe4 { is the main move. } 4. Nxe4 Nf6 { Block the queen's view on f7. } { [%cal Rf3f7] } 5. Bc4 Nbd7 { Threatening Ne5 with a fork. Bb3 is the best move now, but that has been played only once. Most people try d4. } { [%csl Be5][%cal Gd7e5,Be5c4,Be5f3] } 6. Bb3 { Krajnak, Martin - Petrik, Stanislav, 0-1, SVK-chT 9900, 1999, https://lichess.org/thQZhovs } (6. d4?! { this does cover e5, but … the d4-pawn is very vulnerable. } { [%csl Re5][%cal Rd4e5] } 6... Nb6! { Attack d4 and the bishop on c4. } { [%cal Gb6d5,Gf6d5,Gb6c4,Gd8d4] } 7. Nxf6+ gxf6 { Now we have a kind of improved ➡ Bronstein-Larsen Variation in which Black is a central pawn up. } 8. Bb3 Qxd4 { Threatening Bg4 with mate on d1! } { [%cal Gc8g4,Bd4d1,Bg4d1] } 9. h3 (9. Ne2 $146 { prevents that too. Has never been played. }) 9... Qe5+ 10. Ne2 { Now Black has to bring the light-squared bishop out and castle. } 10... Be6 $146 { Novelty! The point is that White has a serious weakness on g2, because Black has the open g-file. Trading off the light-squared bishops removes one potential defender for that square. } { [%csl Bg2][%cal Gh8g8,Gg8g2] } 11. Bxe6 Qxe6 12. O-O Qd5 { Black can now force a queen trade } { [%cal Gd5g2,Gh8g8,Gg8g2] } 13. Qxd5 cxd5 $17 { Black is just better here. Castling isn't necessary anymore, because the queens are gone. The doubled pawns on the f-file are actually a strength, because they can support the center pawns. The open g-file gives Black options for attacks. e6 should be played next to open up the dark-squared bishop. } { [%csl Bf7,Bf6][%cal Ga8c8,Gc8c2,Gh8g8,Gg8g2,Ge7e6,Gf8d6,Gd6h2] }) 6... e6 { [%cal Gd8f6,Gd7f6] } (6... a5 { is an engine suggestion. } { [%cal Ga5a4] } 7. a4 e6 8. d4 c5 { [%cal Gf8c5] } 9. Ne2 cxd4 10. Nxf6+ Nxf6 11. O-O Be7 12. Bf4 { [%csl Rb8][%cal Rf4b8] } 12... O-O $10 { This is equal. b7 is a problem now, Black should play Nd7 next and try to bring that knight to a better square. } { [%csl Bb7][%cal Ga8a6,Gf6d7] }) 7. d4 (7. Nxf6+ Qxf6 8. Qxf6 Nxf6 9. Nf3 Bd6 { Krajnak, Martin - Petrik, Stanislav, 0-1, SVK-chT 9900, 1999, https://lichess.org/thQZhovs }) 7... c5 (7... Nb6?! { Doesn't work anymore, because it doesn't come with a tempo on the bishop. } 8. c3 { And White is better. }) 8. Be3 Nxe4 9. Qxe4 Nf6 { This is okay for both sides. But nothing more. } *


