1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 dxe4 4. f3 { Rasa-Studier Gambit. This isn't very solid, but playable nevertheless in blitz and bullet. } 4... exf3 (4... Nf6 { Transposes to Blackmar-Diemer Gambit/Declined/O'Kelly Defense. This gives the advantage away almost completely. }) 5. Nxf3 { And this is the point of this gambit: White has two pieces developed, and both bishops have open diagonals. Black has to develop quickly now. } 5... Nf6 { Transposes to Blackmar-Diemer Gambit/Ziegler Defense. If you don't want to enter that line, play g6 and go for a slower game. } (5... g6 6. Bc4 Bg7 { [%cal Gg7d4,Gd8d4] } 7. O-O (7. Ng5 { [%cal Gg5f7,Gc4f7] } 7... Nh6 8. Be3 (8. Nce4 { Engine suggestion. }) 8... O-O 9. O-O)) 6. Bc4 Bf5 7. Ne5 { [%cal Ge5f7,Gc4f7] } (7. O-O) 7... e6 8. g4 { [%cal Ge5g4] } 8... Bg6 (8... Nfd7) 9. Nxg6 (9. h4) (9. g5) 9... hxg6 (9... fxg6? 10. Bxe6) *


