{ This is just an overview, listing the named and the main lines. For explanations see the theory chapters. }
1. e4 c5 { [%csl Be7][%cal Ga3f8] } 2. Nf3 d6 { B50 Sicilian Defense } 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 g6 { B70 Dragon Variation } 6. Be3 Bg7 (6... Ng4?? { This is a well-known trap: } 7. Bb5+! { Wins material. } 7... Nc6 (7... Nd7 8. Qxg4 $18) (7... Bd7 8. Qxg4 $18) 8. Nxc6 bxc6 9. Bxc6+ Bd7 10. Bxa8 Nxe3 11. fxe3 Qxa8 12. Nd5 $18) 7. f3 { B75 Dragon Variation, Yugoslav Attack. This makes Ng4 impossible, and it prepares g2-g4. We enter one of the sharpest lines against the Dragon. } { [%cal Gf3g4,Bg2g4] } 7... O-O (7... a6 { This line is often called "Dragadorf". } 8. Qd2 b5 (8... Nbd7 { Main move. }) 9. a4 b4 (9... bxa4) 10. Na2 a5) (7... Nc6 { B76 Dragon Variation, Yugoslav Attack, Belezky Line } 8. Qd2 { [%cal Ge3h6] } 8... O-O { B77 Dragon Variation, Yugoslav Attack } 9. Bc4 { B77 Dragon Variation, Yugoslav Attack, Main Line } 9... Bd7 10. O-O-O Rc8 { B78 Dragon Variation, Yugoslav Attack, Old Line } (10... Qa5 11. Bb3 (11. Kb1 Rfc8 12. Bb3 Ne5 13. h4 Nc4 14. Bxc4 Rxc4 15. Nb3 Qc7 16. Bd4 Be6 17. h5 a5 18. hxg6 hxg6 19. a4) 11... Rfc8 12. h4 (12. Kb1 Ne5 13. h4 Nc4 14. Bxc4 Rxc4) 12... h5 { B79 Dragon Variation, Yugoslav Attack, Soltis Variation } (12... Ne5 13. Kb1 Nc4 14. Bxc4 Rxc4 15. Nb3 Qc7 16. g4 Rc8 17. e5 $14)) 11. Bb3 Ne5 12. Kb1 Re8 13. h4 h5 14. Bh6 (14. g4 hxg4 15. h5 Nxh5 16. Bh6 e6 17. Rdg1 Qf6 18. fxg4 Bxh6 19. Qxh6 Qg7) 14... Nc4 15. Bxc4 Rxc4 16. Bxg7 Kxg7 17. Nd5 (17. g4 hxg4 18. h5 Rh8 19. hxg6 fxg6 20. b3 (20. f4) 20... Rc5 21. fxg4 Bxg4 22. Nd5 Nxd5 23. exd5 Rxd5 24. Rhg1 $14) 17... e5 (17... Nxd5 18. exd5) 18. Nxf6 Qxf6 19. Nb3 (19. Ne2 Rc6)) 8. Qd2 { White prepares to castle long. } { [%cal Ge1c1] } 8... Nc6 { And here White has three main options: The Main line with Bc4, the Modern line with O-O-O, and the very aggressive Panov variation with g4 immediately. } 9. Bc4 { B77 Dragon Variation, Yugoslav Attack, Main Line } (9. O-O-O { Modern Line }) (9. g4 { Panov Variation }) 9... Bd7 (9... Nd7 { Sosonko Variation }) (9... Nxd4 10. Bxd4 Be6 { Czerniak Variation } (10... Qa5!?)) 10. O-O-O (10. h4) (10. Bb3) 10... Rc8 { B78 Dragon Variation, Yugoslav Attack, Old Line } { [%csl Rc4][%cal Rc8c4] } (10... Qa5 11. Bb3 Rfc8 12. h4 Ne5 { Main move. } (12... h5 { B79 Dragon Variation, Yugoslav Attack, Soltis Variation }) 13. Kb1 Nc4 14. Bxc4 Rxc4 15. Nb3 Qc7 16. g4 (16. Bd4 Be6 17. h5) 16... Rc8 17. e5 { [%cal Gd2d7] } 17... Ne8 18. Nd5 Qd8 $14) (10... Ne5 { [%cal Ge5c4] } 11. Bb3) 11. Bb3 Nxd4 (11... Ne5 12. Kb1 Re8 13. h4 h5 14. Bh6 Nc4 15. Bxc4 Rxc4 16. Bxg7 Kxg7 17. Nd5 e5 18. Nxf6 Qxf6 19. Nb3 Rec8 20. Qxd6 Be6 21. c3 b5 22. Rd2 R4c6 23. Qd3 Qf4) 12. Bxd4 b5 { [%cal Rb5b4] } 13. Nd5 Nxd5 14. Bxg7 Kxg7 15. exd5 (15. Bxd5?! a5!) *


[Event "SicilianDragon/Yugoslav Attack: 7…O-O 8.Qd2 Nc6 9.Bc4 Bd7 10.O-O-O Rc8 - Main/Old Line"]
[Date "2008"]
[White "Peter Leko"]
[Black "Magnus Carlsen"]
[Result "1/2 - 1/2"]
