{ This is just an overview, listing the named and the main lines. For explanations see the theory chapters. }
1. e4 c5 { There are three main systems in which Black is fianchettoing the dark-squared bishop: the Dragon in various forms, the closed Sicilian (2.Nc3), and the Rossolimo.
They all have in common that Black shouldn't move the e-pawn prior to castling to avoid any pressure by White along the a3-f8 diagonal. } { [%csl Be7][%cal Ga3f8] } 2. Nf3 (2. Nc3 Nc6 3. g3 { B24 Closed Variation, Fianchetto Variation } (3. f4 { B23 Grand Prix Attack } 3... g6 4. Nf3 Bg7 5. Bc4 (5. Bb5 { Main move. } 5... Nd4 6. O-O Nxb5 7. Nxb5) 5... e6 6. f5 { B23 Grand Prix Attack, Schofman Variation }) 3... g6 4. Bg2 Bg7 5. d3 d6 6. f4 (6. Be3 { Main move } 6... Rb8 7. Qd2 b5 8. Nge2 b4 9. Nd1 Nd4 10. O-O e6) (6. Nge2 e5 { B25 Closed Variation, Botvinnik Defense II } (6... e6 { Main move. } 7. O-O Nge7 8. Be3 Nd4)) 6... e6 { Main move } (6... e5 { B25 Closed Variation, Botvinnik Defense I } 7. Nh3 Nge7 { B25 Closed Variation, Botvinnik Defense, Edge Variation }) 7. Nf3 Nge7 8. O-O O-O 9. Be3 Nd4 10. e5 Nef5 11. Bf2 Nxf3+ 12. Qxf3 Nd4 13. Qd1) 2... d6 { B50 Sicilian Defense } (2... Nc6 { B30 Old Sicilian } 3. d4 { B32 Sicilian Defense: Open } (3. Bb5 { B30 Nyezhmetdinov-Rossolimo Attack } 3... g6 { B31 Nyezhmetdinov-Rossolimo Attack, Fianchetto Variation } 4. O-O (4. Bxc6 dxc6 { Main line. Avoids an isolated a-pawn for Black. } (4... bxc6 5. O-O Bg7 6. Re1 Nh6 7. c3 O-O 8. d4 cxd4 9. cxd4 d5 10. e5 f6) 5. d3 Bg7 6. h3 Nf6 7. Nc3 O-O) 4... Bg7 5. Re1 e5 (5... Nf6 { Main move. } 6. e5 Nd5 7. Nc3 Nc7 8. Bxc6 dxc6 9. Ne4 { [%cal Ge4c5] } 9... Ne6 (9... b6)) 6. b4 { B31 Nyezhmetdinov-Rossolimo Attack, Gurgenidze Variation } (6. Bxc6 { Main move. } 6... dxc6 (6... bxc6 7. c3 Ne7 8. d4 cxd4 9. cxd4 exd4 10. Nxd4 O-O 11. Nc3) 7. d3 Qe7 8. Nbd2)) 3... cxd4 4. Nxd4 g6 { B36 Accelerated Dragon } (4... Nf6 5. Nc3 g6?! 6. Nxc6 bxc6 7. e5 Ng8) 5. c4 { B36 Accelerated Dragon, Maróczy Bind } (5. Nc3 { B34 Accelerated Dragon, Modern Variation } 5... Bg7 6. Be3 Nf6 7. Bc4 { B35 Accelerated Dragon, Modern Bc4 Variation }) (5. Nxc6?! { B34 Accelerated Dragon, Exchange Variation } 5... bxc6 6. Qd4 Nf6 7. e5 Nd5 8. e6 $15) 5... Bg7 { B37 Accelerated Fianchetto, Maróczy Bind, 5... Bg7 } (5... Nf6 6. Nc3 d6 { Main move. } (6... Nxd4 7. Qxd4 d6 { B36 Accelerated Dragon, Maróczy Bind, Gurgenidze Variation } 8. Be2 (8. Bg5 Bg7 9. Qd2 O-O 10. Bd3 Be6) 8... Bg7 9. Be3 O-O 10. Qd2 Be6) 7. Be2 Nxd4 8. Qxd4 Bg7 9. Be3 O-O 10. Qd2 Be6 11. Rc1 Qa5 12. f3 $14) 6. Be3 { B38 Accelerated Dragon, Maróczy Bind } 6... Nf6 7. Nc3 Ng4 { B39 Accelerated Dragon, Maróczy Bind, Breyer Variation } (7... O-O { Main move. } 8. Be2 d6 9. O-O Bd7 10. Qd2 { [%cal Ge3h6] } 10... Nxd4 11. Bxd4 Bc6 12. f3 a5 13. b3 $14) 8. Qxg4 Nxd4 9. Qd1 Ne6 10. Rc1 $14 Qa5 11. Bd3 b6 12. O-O Bb7 13. f4 O-O $14) (2... g6 { B27 Hyperaccelerated Dragon } 3. d4 { Transposition: Hyperaccelerated Fianchetto } (3. c4 Bg7 4. d4 cxd4 5. Nxd4 Nc6 { B37 Transposition: Accelerated Fianchetto, Maróczy Bind, 5... Bg7 } 6. Be3 { Transposition: Accelerated Dragon, Maróczy Bind }) 3... cxd4 (3... Bg7 { B27 Hyperaccelerated Pterodactyl } 4. Nc3 (4. d5 d6 5. Nc3 Nf6 6. Be2 O-O 7. O-O Na6) (4. dxc5 Qa5+ 5. Nc3 Bxc3+ 6. bxc3 Qxc3+ $10 { B27 Hyperaccelerated Pterodactyl, Exchange Variation }) 4... cxd4 5. Nxd4 Nc6 6. Be3 Nf6 7. Bc4 { Transposition: B35 Accelerated Dragon, Modern Bc4 Variation } (7. Be2 O-O 8. O-O (8. Nb3 d6 9. O-O { Transposition: B74 Dragon Variation, Classical Variation, Normal Line }) (8. f4 d6 9. Nb3 Be6) 8... d5 (8... d6 9. Nb3 { Transposition: B74 Dragon Variation, Classical Variation, Normal Line } (9. Qd2 { Transposition: B73 Dragon Variation, Classical Variation, Battery Variation })) 9. exd5 (9. Nxc6 bxc6 10. e5 Nd7 11. f4 e6 12. Na4) 9... Nxd5 10. Nxd5 Qxd5 11. Bf3 Qa5)) 4. Nxd4 Nc6 { Transposition: Accelerated Dragon } (4... Bg7 5. Nc3 (5. c4 Nc6 { B37 Accelerated Fianchetto, Maróczy Bind, 5... Bg7 }) 5... Nc6 6. Be3 Nf6)) 3. d4 (3. Bb5+ { Canal-Sokolsky Attack } 3... Bd7 4. Bxd7+ Qxd7 (4... Nxd7 5. O-O Ngf6 6. Qe2 g6?! 7. c3! { And this is the problem in this line: White has still the option to close the a1-h8 diagonal. }) 5. c4 { Canal-Sokolsky Attack, Sokolsky Variation } 5... Nf6 6