 Qd2 Nc6 9. Bc4 { B77 Dragon Variation, Yugoslav Attack, Main Line } 9... Bd7 10. O-O-O Rc8 { B78 Dragon Variation, Yugoslav Attack, Old Line } (10... Qa5 11. Bb3 Rfc8 12. h4 h5 { B79 Dragon Variation, Yugoslav Attack, Soltis Variation } (12... Ne5 { Main move. }))) 6... Bg7 7. Be3 { B72 Dragon, Classical Attack } (7. O-O { Main move. } 7... O-O 8. Bg5 (8. Be3 Nc6 9. Nb3 { B74 Dragon Variation, Classical Variation, Normal Line } (9. Qd2 { B73 Dragon Variation, Classical Variation, Battery Variation } 9... Ng4 (9... Bd7 10. Rad1 Rc8) 10. Bxg4 Bxg4) 9... Be6 (9... a6 10. f4 b5 11. Bf3 Bb7)) 8... Nc6 9. Nb3 Be6 10. Kh1) 7... Nc6 { B73 Dragon Variation, Classical Variation } (7... O-O 8. O-O Nc6 9. Nb3 { B74 Dragon Variation, Classical Variation, Normal Line }) 8. O-O (8. Nb3 { B72 Dragon Variation, Classical Variation }) 8... O-O 9. Nb3 { B74 Dragon Variation, Classical Variation, Normal Line } (9. Qd2 { B73 Dragon Variation, Classical Variation, Battery Variation }) 9... Be6 (9... a5 { B74 Dragon Variation, Classical Variation, Alekhine Line }) (9... a6 { The a-systems are sometimes also called Dragondorf, because a6 is the signature move of the Najdorf. It's probably a bit too passive here. } 10. f4 b5 11. Bf3 Bb7) 10. f4 Rc8 (10... Na5 { B74 Dragon Variation, Classical Variation, Maróczy Line (not a Maróczy Bind of course) } 11. f5 Bc4 (11... Bd7 { Rare, but playable. } 12. e5!?) 12. Nxa5 (12. Bd3 { Main move. } 12... Bxd3 13. cxd3 Nxb3 14. axb3 $14) 12... Bxe2 13. Qxe2 Qxa5 14. g4 { B74 Dragon Variation, Classical Variation, Stockholm Attack } (14. Bd4 { Main move. })) (10... Qc8 { B74 Dragon Variation, Classical Variation, Tartakower Line. Main move. } 11. Kh1 Rd8 { [%cal Rd8d1] } 12. Bg1 $10) 11. Kh1 a6 (11... Na5 { Now Black enters the Na5 line with better preparation. } 12. f5 Bc4 13. Bd3) *


