1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 g6 { Dragon Variation. Some people see a similarity between Blacks pawn structure and the star constellation Draco, hence the name. } 6. Be3 { Note that Ng4 doesn't work here, it loses material immediately. } (6. Be2 { Classical variation. Less challenging. } 6... Bg7 7. O-O O-O 8. Bg5 Nc6 9. Nb3) 6... Bg7 (6... Ng4? 7. Bb5+! { [%cal Gd1g4,Gb5e8] } 7... Nc6 (7... Nd7 8. Qxg4) 8. Nxc6 bxc6 9. Bxc6+ { [%cal Gc6a8,Gc6e8] } 9... Bd7 10. Bxa8 Nxe3 11. fxe3 Qxa8 12. Qd4 $18 { [%cal Gd4h8] }) 7. f3 { This is the starting point for the Yugoslav Attack. f3 protects e4 and prevents Black from playing Ng4.
This line is considered the most testing attempt for the Dragon. } { [%csl Bf3][%cal Gf3g4,Gf3e4,Rf6g4] } 7... O-O 8. Qd2 { Setting up the battery in order to trade off Black's dark-squared bishop. } { [%csl Bh6][%cal Bd2h6,Rh6g7] } 8... Nc6 { There are two main lines here: 0-0-0 and Bc4. The latter is a bit sharper. } (8... a6? { That's a wasted tempo. } 9. O-O-O Nc6) 9. Bc4 { Prevents d5 by Black. } { [%csl Gd5][%cal Gc4d5] } (9. O-O-O { And here Black really should use the opportunity to play d5. } 9... d5 10. exd5 (10. Kb1 { Here comes a famous queen sacrifice: } 10... Nxd4 11. e5! Nf5! 12. exf6 Bxf6 (12... exf6) 13. Nxd5 Qxd5!? 14. Qxd5! Nxe3 15. Qd3 (15. Qd2) 15... Nxd1 16. Qxd1 Be6 $14 { Technically White is still better, but Black does have some compensation for the queen. } 17. Bd3 (17. Bb5 { Scores better for White than Bd3, although the engine thinks it's an inferior move. } 17... Rad8) 17... Rfd8 18. Qe1 Rd6 19. Qa5 b6 20. Qe1 Rc8 21. a3?! (21. g4! Rc5 22. h4 h5 23. g5 Bg7 $14 { Houtman, Joop - Percze, Raymond, 1/2-1/2, WC.2006.S.00008, 2004, https://lichess.org/l0AcjsF2 }) 21... Rc5 22. g4 Rcd5 23. Qg3 h5 24. h3 h4 25. Qf2 Rxd3! 26. cxd3 Rxd3 27. Qe2?! Rb3 28. Rd1 g5?! (28... Rxb2+ 29. Qxb2 Bxb2 30. Kxb2 $13) 29. Rd2 Kg7 30. Qe4 a5 31. Kc1 b5 32. Kd1 a4 33. Ke1 Bc4 34. Kf2 e6 35. Qc2 Bd5 36. Qd1 b4 37. axb4 Rxb4 38. Qe2 Rb3 39. Kg2 Kg8 { Adams, Michael - Ivanchuk, Vassily, 1/2-1/2, Dortmund, 1998, https://lichess.org/Ci1cyukp }) 10... Nxd5 11. Nxc6 bxc6 12. Bd4 Bxd4 (12... e5 13. Bc5 Be6 14. Ne4 Re8 (14... Rb8 15. Bc4 Re8 16. h4 h5 $14) 15. h4 h6 (15... Nf4 16. Qe1 { [%cal Gd1d8] } 16... Bd5 (16... Qc7 17. h5 Nxh5 18. g4 Nf4 19. Qh4 { [%cal Gh4h7] } 19... h6 20. Nf6+ Kh8 21. Qg5 { [%cal Gh1h6] } 21... Nh5 22. Nxe8 Rxe8 23. Qe3 Nf4 24. a3? { Gave Black one free tempo – enough to secure the draw. } 24... Kg8 25. Bxa7 Nd5 26. Qf2 e4 27. fxe4 Nf6 28. Qb6 Qe5 29. Qd4 Qc7 30. g5 hxg5 31. Qb6 Qf4+ 32. Qe3 Nxe4 33. Bg2 Bg4 34. Rde1 f5 35. Rhg1 Bh5 36. c3 Be5 37