b6 17. Nc3 a5 18. Qe5 Qxe5 19. Rxe5 Be6 20. a4 Rfc8 21. Ne2 Kf8 22. Nf4 Bd7 23. Nd3 f6 24. Rc5 e5 25. Be2 Be6 26. Re1 Ke7 27. Bf1 Kd6 28. Rc3 Nd5 29. Rc4 Nf4 30. Rc3 Nd5 31. Rc4 Nf4 32. Rc3 Nd5 { Leko, Peter - Radjabov, Teimour, 1/2-1/2, Nanjing Pearl Spring 2nd, 2009, https://lichess.org/I29WsXZc }) 15. Bc4 Rd8 (15... Nb6 16. Bb3 Nxa4 17. Qxa4 c5 18. Rhe1 e6 19. Qe4 Ba6 20. Bxe6 Bb7 21. Bd5 Bxd5 22. Qxd5 Qxh2 23. Qg5 Rfe8 24. Rh1 Qe5 25. Qxe5 Rxe5 26. Rd7 h5 27. g4 hxg4 28. fxg4 Re4 29. Rf1 Rf8 30. Rxa7 Rxg4 31. Rc7 c4 32. Kd2 f5 33. a4 c3+ 34. Kxc3 Rxa4 35. b4 Rb8 36. Rd1 Raxb4 37. Rdd7 Rg4 38. Rg7+ Kh8 39. Rh7+ Kg8 40. Rhg7+ Kh8 41. Rh7+ { Caruana, F. - Nakamura, Hi, 1/2-1/2, KM FIDE GP 2015, https://lichess.org/qyfmgmFq }) 16. Bb3 (16. Nc5 Bf5 17. Bb3 Nf4 { [%csl Be2][%cal Gf4e2,Be2c1,Be2d4] } (17... Nb6 18. Qe3 (18. Qc3 h5 19. g3 Nd5 20. Qc4 e6 21. Rhe1 Qe7 (21... Nb6 { [%cal Gb6c4] } 22. Qc3 { Muzychuk, Anna - Cmilyte, Viktorija, 1/2-1/2, EU-Cup (Women) 17th, 2012, https://lichess.org/qbCk3w3Q }) 22. Nd3?! { Adams, Mi - Nakamura, Hi, 1/2-1/2, 9th London Classic 2017, https://lichess.org/ffzmMT9t }) 18... Nd5) (17... Rd6) 18. Qf2 (18. Qc4 Be6 19. Nxe6 Nxe6 20. g3 (20. h4!?) 20... Rd6 21. c3 (21. Rhe1) (21. Qc3 Ng7 (21... Rad8 22. Bxe6 Rxe6 23. b3 { Granski, Michael - Lecroq, Michel, 1/2-1/2, CCO18/F, 2012, https://lichess.org/BvzQdCce }) 22. a3 $10) 21... Qb6 (21... a5 22. f4 $10 { Serban, Florin - Haugen, Arild, 1/2-1/2, CCO17/F, 2009, https://lichess.org/vWXMIImt }) (21... Rad8 22. f4 (22. Qe2) 22... Rxd1+ 23. Rxd1 Rxd1+ (23... Qb6 24. Rxd8+ Nxd8 $14) 24. Bxd1 Qb6 $14 { Seelig, Jürgen - Muñiz Pardiño, Alberto, 1/2-1/2, GER/CM/04-D (GER), 2017, https://lichess.org/hM25Ut8H }) 22. Qe2 Nc5 { [%cal Gc5b3,Gb6b3] } 23. Bc4 Na4 { [%cal Ga8b8,Gb6b2] } 24. Rxd6 (24. Bxf7+! Kxf7 25. Rxd6 exd6 26. Qc4+ d5 27. Qxa4 $14) 24... exd6 25. Bxf7+ Kxf7 26. Qc4+ d5 27. Qxa4 $14) 18... Rxd1+ 19. Rxd1 Rd8 20. Re1 (20. Rxd8+ Qxd8 21. g4 Bc8 $14 { Lupo, Alfredo - Demchenko, Sergey Pavlovich, 1-0, WC40/pr05, 2016, https://lichess.org/oX7FPmsC })) 16... Bf5 17. g4 Nf4 18. Qe3 Be6 19. h4 Bxb3 20. axb3 Ng2 21. Rxd8+ Rxd8 22. Qe4 Qf4+ 23. Qxf4 Nxf4 24. Nc3 h5 25. Re1 hxg4 26. fxg4 Ne6 27. Ne4 Kg7 28. b4 Rh8 29. Ng5 Nxg5 30. hxg5 e6 31. Re4 Rb8 32. Rc4 Rb5 33. Rxc6 Rxb4 34. c4 a5 35. Kb1 e5 36. Rc5 e4 37. Rxa5 Rxc4 38. Re5 e3 39. Rxe3 Rxg4 40. Re5 f5 41. gxf6+ Kxf6 42. Re8 g5 43. Kc2 Rf4 44. Rf8+ Ke5 45. Rxf4 Kxf4 46. b4 g4 47. b5 Ke5 48. b6 Kd6 49. b7 Kc7 50. b8=Q+ Kxb8 51. Kd3 { Ivanchuk, Vassily - Carlsen, Magnus, 1/2-1/2, Leon 22nd, 2009, https://lichess.org/C3wSGyXI }) 9... Bd7 (9... d5?! { This gambit has been tried a few times, but it doesn't work. } 10. exd5 Na5 11. Bb3 Nxb3 12. Nxb3 Qc7 13. Bf4! Qc4 14. O-O-O Rd8 15. Rhe1 { Hanging pawn. } { [%csl Ge7][%cal Ge1e7] } 15... Be6 { Using the pin. } { [%csl Rd2][%cal Rd8d2] } 16. Qd4! Qxd4 17. Nxd4 { [%cal Gd4e6,Ge1e6] } 17... Bxd5 18. Rxe7 { [%cal Ge7b7] } 18... Bxa2! 19. Rxb7 $14 (19. Nxa2?! Nd5 { [%cal Gd5e7,Gd5f4] } 20. Re4 { [%cal Gd5f4] } 20... f5 { [%cal Gd5f4] } 21. Ne6 fxe4 22. Nxd8 Nxf4 $10)) 10. O-O-O { This is the real starting point for this line. Black has a number of options now. } 10... Rc8 { Threatening Nxd4. } { [%cal Gc6d4] } (10... Ne5) (10... Rb8) (10... Qa5) (10... Na5) (10... a6) 11. Bb3 (11. Be2) (11. Nxc6) 11... Ne5 (11... Nxd4 { anyway. This does break the battery for a while. } { [%cal Bd2h6] } 12. Bxd4 b5! 13. Nd5 Nxd5 14. Bxg7 Kxg7 15. exd5 a5 16. a3 Qb6 17. Rhe1 { [%csl Re7][%cal Re1e7] } 17... Rfe8 (17... h5!? { Prevents g4, which will be important after the next move: } { [%cal Gh5g4] } 18. Rxe7 Bf5! 19. c3 b4 20. axb4 axb4 21. Qe3 Qxe3+ 22. Rxe3 bxc3 23. Rxc3 $10) 18. g4 { Prevents Bf5. } { [%csl Rf5][%cal Rg4f5] }) 12. Kb1 Re8 (12... Nc4) (12... a6) 13. h4 h5 14. Bh6 (14. g4) (14. Bg5) 14... Nc4 (14... Bh8) 15. Bxc4 (15. Qc1 Bh8 16. g4 b5 { Rilberg, Stefan - Dahlström, Richard, 1/2-1/2, SWE/C2005 (SWE), https://lichess.org/bQaQbD7q }) 15... Rxc4 16. Bxg7 Kxg7 17. Nd5 (17. g4) 17... e5 (17... Nxd5) 18. Nxf6 (18. Nb3) (18. Ne2!?) 18... Qxf6 19. Nb3 (19. Ne2) 19... Rec8 (19... Be6) (19... Re6?!) (19... b6!?) 20. Qxd6 Be6 21. c3 b5 (21... R4c6) 22. Qd2 (22. Rd2 R4c6 (22... R4c7 { [%cal Ga7a5] })) 22... Qe7 (22... a5 23. Qg5? (23. Nxa5! Ra4 24. Nb3 $14) 23... Qxg5 24. hxg5 a4 $10 { Leko, Peter - Carlsen, Magnus, 1/2-1/2, Miskolc m, 2008, https://lichess.org/b5RQMwtm }) (22... Rb8) 23. Qd6 Qf6 $10 { Leko, Peter - Carlsen, Magnus, 1/2-1/2, Miskolc m, 2008, https://lichess.org/b5RQMwtm } *


[Event "Bg7 in the Sicilian: Accelerated Dragon/Maróczy Bind"]
