1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. c3 Nf6 4. d3 { Anti-Fraser System. This prevents the rather adventurous ➡Fraser Defense/Vukovic Gambit. It does however allow Black to play d5. } 4... d5 5. Nbd2 a5 { This is an important move. If Black doesn't play it, White should play b4, followed by b5, to drive the knight on c6 away. Once that happens, e5 is unprotected. } (5... Be7 6. b4 O-O 7. b5 Na5 8. Nxe5 dxe4 9. dxe4 Bc5 { [%cal Rc5f2,Rf6g4,Rg4f2] } 10. Be2 { [%csl Gg4][%cal Ge2g4] } 10... Re8 { [%csl Re5][%cal Re8e5] } 11. Nd3 { [%cal Gd3c5] } 11... Bb6 12. O-O $10) 6. Be2 (6. exd5 Nxd5 7. g3 g6 8. Bg2 Bg7 9. O-O O-O $10 { Jobava, Ba - Inarkiev, E., 1/2-1/2, 17th ch-EUR Indiv 2016, https://lichess.org/FoUsATSL }) 6... Bc5 { [%cal Rc5f2,Rf6g4,Rg4f2] } 7. O-O O-O $10 *


