[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/fuxia"]
[UTCDate "2018.04.24"]
[UTCTime "07:43:37"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. c3 d5 4. Qa4 f6 $10 { Steinitz Variation. f6 protects the pawn on e5, but it also weakens Black's king side a bit.
White can now either play Bb5 or the rather passive d3. } 5. Bb5 { Now Black has to add further protection to the knight. } (5. d3 Be6 (5... Ne7) (5... a6) 6. Nbd2 { [%cal Gd3d4,Gd4e5] } (6. Be3) (6. Be2) 6... Qd7 (6... Bd6 { Nepomniachtchi, Ian - Jakovenko, Dmitrij, 0-1, Novosibirsk Siberian Bank Cup, 2012, https://lichess.org/0sVRFfgY }) 7. b4! { [%csl Gc5] } (7. Be2) 7... a6 8. Rb1) (5. exd5?! { This helps Black's development by activating their queen. } 5... Qxd5 $15) 5... Ne7 6. exd5 $7 Qxd5 $7 { [%cal Re5e4] } 7. d4 Bg4 (7... e4 8. c4 Qd8 { [%cal Gd4d5] } 9. Nfd2 { The thread is now an exchange on c6 and then pushing the d-pawn. } { [%cal Gd4d5] } 9... Kf7! 10. Nxe4 Nxd4 { [%cal Rd4b5] } 11. c5 Nxb5 12. Qxb5) 8. c4 Qe4+ 9. Be3 $7 Bxf3 (9... exd4) (9... a6) 10. Nd2 $7 { [%cal Gd2e4,Gd2f3] } 10... Qg6 $7 { [%cal Rg6g2,Rf3g2] } 11. gxf3 (11. Nxf3?) 11... exd4 $7 12. Bxd4 $7 *


