1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. c3 d5 4. Qa4 { [%cal Ga4c6,Ga4e4] } 4... Qd6 { Meitner Variation*.
White has quite a few options here. The most common move is Bb5. } { [%cal Rd6c6,Rd6d5] } 5. Bb5 { Black needs another protector for the knight in order to avoid doubled pawns. But Nf6 is also a move. } (5. exd5 Qxd5 6. Bb5 e4 { Has been played only once: Srijit Paul - Saurabh, Mumbai 2016, ½-½ (not sure how correct the result is) https://chesstempo.com/gamedb/game/4079947 } (6... Ne7) (6... Bd7) 7. Ng5 $146 { Novelty. The Queen is bound to defend the knight and can't move away. } { [%cal Rd5c6] } 7... Ne7 { Unleashes the black queen. } { [%cal Re7c6] } 8. d3 { Protect the knight. } { [%cal Gd3e4,Bg5e4,Gc1g5] } (8. d4 f6 (8... exd3 { See the 8.d3 e3 line. })) (8. f4) 8... e3 { [%cal Rd5g2] } (8... exd3 { [%cal Rd5g2] } 9. O-O Bd7 10. Bc4 { [%cal Gc4d5] } 10... Ne5 { [%cal Rd7a4] } 11. Bxd5 Bxa4 12. Bxb7 Rb8 13. Be4 $10) 9. Bxe3 Qxg2 10. Qe4 Qxe4 11. dxe4 $10) (5. Na3) 5... Ne7 (5... Bd7) (5... Nf6) 6. d4! { [%cal Gf3d4,Gf3e5] } (6. exd5 { Playable, but not very ambitious. Not in the spirit of the Ponziani. } 6... Qxd5 7. d3 (7. d4 { Webb, L. - Hebden, M., 0-1, Polar Capital Jersey Open, 2016, https://lichess.org/beJ0EaVP })) 6... exd4 { The only good move, but it's not easy to why unless you look at the alternatives. } (6... dxe4?! { Gives the knight a very nice outpost. } 7. Nxe5 { [%csl Gd7][%cal Ge5d7,Ge5c6] } 7... a6 { The threat is not axb5. This move creates a square for the knight on c6! It also enables long castling. } 8. O-O Bd7 { And now the knights wants to go to a7. But White has the option to clean up the field a bit and win the pawn on e4. } { [%cal Rc6a7] } 9. Nxd7 Qxd7 10. Bxc6 Qxc6 11. Qxc6+ Nxc6 12. Re1 { Black cannot hold that pawn. } { [%cal Ge1e4] } 12... O-O-O (12... f5?! 13. f3) 13. Rxe4 $16) (6... Bd7?! 7. Nxe5 { [%cal Ge5d7] } 7... Nxe5 { [%cal Rd7b5,Re5d3] } 8. dxe5 { [%cal Ge5d6] } 8... Bxb5 9. Qxb5+ Qc6 10. Qxc6+ Nxc6 { [%cal Rc6e5] } 11. f4 $14) 7. O-O! (7. exd5?! Nxd5 8. Nxd4 Nb6 9. Qc2 (9. Qd1 Qe5+ 10. Be3 Bd6 11. Qd3 $15 { [%cal Gd3b5,Gd3d4] }) 9... Bd7 10. O-O Nxd4 11. Bxd7+ Qxd7 12. cxd4 O-O-O 13. Nc3 Kb8 14. Rd1 $15) 7... Bd7 8. e5! Qe6 9. cxd4 O-O-O 10. Bg5 (10. Bxc6 Nxc6) 10... f6 11. Bf4 fxe5 12. Nxe5 Nxe5 13. Bxe5 Bxb5 14. Qxb5 Nc6 { [%cal Rc6e5,Re6e5] } 15. f4 Bd6 { [%cal Rd6e5,Rc6e5,Re6e5,Gd4e5,Gf4e5] } 16. Nc3 { [%cal Gc3d5,Gb5d5] } (16. Re1? Nxd4 { [%csl Be5][%cal Rd4c2,Rd4f3,Re6e1] }) 16... Bxe5 17. dxe5 a6 18. Qb3 Na5 19. Qc2 $15 { [%cal Rg7g5,Rf4f5,Ga5c4,Ga1e1,Bd5d4,Bc3e4] } *


