1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. c3 d5 4. Qa4 Bd7 { Caro Gambit. Black is giving up the d-pawn. There is compensation: The white queen will be sent back to d1, and the only other developed white piece, the knight on f3, will be exchanged. } 5. exd5 { We accept it of course. } 5... Nd4 { The move that justifies the sacrifice. } { [%cal Rd7a4,Rd4f3,Rd4c2] } 6. Qd1 { The only move. } 6... Nxf3+ 7. Qxf3 Nf6 { Threatens to take on d5 or to push the e-pawn. } { [%cal Rf6d5,Rf6e4,Be5e4] } (7... Bd6 8. Na3 { [%cal Ga3c4,Gc4d6,Gc4e5] } 8... Ne7 9. Nc4 O-O 10. Nxd6 cxd6 11. b3 { [%cal Gc1b2] } 11... Re8 12. Bb2 $14 { [%cal Gf1e2,Ge1g1,Re5e4,Rb7b5,Re7g6] }) 8. Bc4 (8. c4 { Also playable, but not recommended. Also the engine doesn't like it. Frees the c3 square for the knight, but there's a price. } { [%csl Bc3] } 8... c6 { And here comes the price: After an exchange on d5, White has doubled pawns on the d-file and no pawn on the c-file to support them. } (8... Bc5 9. Nc3 O-O) 9. Nc3 Bc5 { [%cal Rd8b6,Bc5f2,Rd7g4,Rg4f3] } (9... cxd5) 10. Be2 cxd5 { White can't take with the knight, because then Black could pin that with the bishop on c6. } { [%cal Rd7c6] } 11. cxd5 O-O 12. d3 { This is overall a bit uncomfortable for White. }) 8... b5 (8... e4 { The main move, but Black can also play b5 first and win some space. } 9. Qe2 { The queen should stay on light squares, so the dark-squared bishop can move. Also, the e-pawn is now pinned and can't advance. } { [%cal Ge2e8] } 9... Bd6 { Prepare castling. } 10. d4 { [%cal Gc1g5] } 10... O-O (10... h6) (10... Bg4 { Not possible yet, because the e-pawn is pinned. } 11. f3 Bf5 $16) 11. h3 { Prevents Bf5. And here we can see the compensation: Black has almost completed their development, while White is far behind. That also means that Black should use this advantage and start attacking immediately. } { [%csl Gg4,Ba1,Bb1,Bc1,Be1][%cal Rd7g4,Gh3g4] } 11... Re8 (11... h6 { Return the favor. } { [%csl Rg5][%cal Rh6g5,Gc1g5] } 12. Bb3 { [%cal Gc3c4] } 12... b5 13. O-O) 12. Na3 { [%cal Ga3c2] } (12. Be3?! { [%cal Gb1d2] }) 12... a6 $10 { [%cal Rb7b5,Ga3c2,Gc4b3,Ge1g1] } (12... Bxa3 13. bxa3 Ba4 { [%cal Rd8d5,Rf6d5] } 14. Rb1 (14. Bg5 h6 15. Bh4 g5 16. Bg3 b5 { Exchange a flank pawn for a center pawn. } { [%csl Bb5,Bd5] } 17. Bxb5 (17. Bb3) 17... Bxb5 18. Qxb5 Nxd5 { [%cal Rd5c3] } 19. Qc5 { [%cal Gc5c7,Gg3c7,Rd5c7,Rd8c7] } 19... Rb8 $10) 14... b6 15. Bg5 Qd6 16. Bxf6 Qxf6 17. Rb4 { [%cal Gb4a4] } 17... Bd7 $10)) (8... Be7?! 9. d3 O-O 10. O-O $14) 9. Bb3 e4 *


