1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. c3 d5 4. Bb5 { Spanish variation. Not recommended. } 4... dxe4 { The only useful move. } (4... f6?! { Looks like a late Damiano Defense and should be treated like one. } 5. d4 dxe4 6. Bxc6+ bxc6 7. Nxe5! fxe5 8. Qh5+ Ke7 9. Qh4+ (9. Qxe5+? Kf7 10. Qxe4 Qd5 11. Nd2) 9... Ke8 10. Qh5+) 5. Nxe5 Qd5 { [%cal Rd5e5,Rd5b5] } 6. Qa4! Ne7 7. f4 Be6! (7... exf3 8. Nxf3 a6 (8... Qe6+ 9. Kf2 Bd7 10. d4 $10) (8... Bd7) (8... Be6) 9. Be2 (9. Na3 { [%csl Bb5,Bc7][%cal Ra3b5,Rb5c7,Rc7a8,Rc7e8] } 9... Bd7) 9... Ng6 10. Qb3 Qxb3 (10... Qh5 { Engine move. I don't think a human would play that. Threat is Nf4. } { [%cal Rg6f4] }) 11. axb3 Nf4 12. Bc4 (12. Bb5 Rb8 13. Bxc6+ bxc6 { Lu Shanglei - Ni Hua, 0-1, 6th Hainan Danzhou GM, 2015, https://lichess.org/PEQRGi4u }) 12... Nxg2+ 13. Kf2 Nf4 14. d4 Nh3+ 15. Kg2) *


