1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. c3 f5 { Ponziani Countergambit. This isn't as sharp as many other lines.
Black will usually put a pawn on e4, White will challenge it with f3, and Black will very likely get the pawn back.
I prefer d4 here, the declined variation. But accepting the gambit is also playable. } 4. d4 (4. exf5 { Also playable. } 4... Qf6 5. d4 (5. Bb5 e4 6. Qe2 Qe7 7. Bxc6 { [%cal Gc6f3] } 7... dxc6 8. Nd4 { [%cal Gd4f5] } 8... c5 9. Ne6 Bxe6 10. fxe6 Nf6 { [%cal Rf6g4,Rf6e4] } 11. d3 exd3 12. Qxd3 Qxe6+ 13. Qe3 Qxe3+ 14. Bxe3 Ng4 { [%cal Rg4e3,Rg4f2] } 15. Bf4 { [%cal Gf4c7] } 15... O-O-O 16. O-O $15) (5. g3 Qxf5 6. d4 { [%cal Gf1g2,Ge1g1] }) 5... e4 { [%cal Re4f3] } 6. Nfd2 (6. Ng5 d5 { The only good move here. } (6... Qxf5? 7. Qh5+ g6 8. Qe2 { [%cal Ge2e4,Gg5e4] } 8... Nf6 9. f3 { Signature move. } 9... d5 10. g4 Qd7 11. fxe4 Qe7 { [%cal Rc8g4,Rg4e2] } 12. h3 Nxe4 13. Nxe4 Qxe4 14. Qxe4+ dxe4 15. Bg2 $16) 7. Qh5+ g6 8. fxg6 hxg6 9. Qe2 Bf5 10. Bf4 { [%cal Gf4c7] } 10... O-O-O 11. Qd2 { Make room for the bishop. } 11... Kb8 $14) 6... Qxf5 7. Be2 d5 8. f3 { Signature move. } 8... Bd6 9. fxe4 dxe4 10. Nc4 $10) 4... fxe4 5. Nxe5 Nf6 { [%cal Rf6e4] } (5... Qf6 6. Nxc6 bxc6) 6. Bg5 d6 7. Nxc6 bxc6 8. Nd2 d5 9. f3 { Signature move. } 9... Be7 10. Be2 O-O (10... exf3 11. Bxf3 O-O 12. O-O { Popov, Vladimir Yurievich - Goffin, Peter B, 1/2-1/2, WS/MN/116, 2014, https://lichess.org/1JJumrkJ }) 11. O-O Nh5 12. Bxe7 Qxe7 13. fxe4 Nf4 $10 *


