1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. c3 d6?! { Neumann Variation. See [Rosenthal - Neumann].
Very passive. White has few comfortable options now. } 4. Bb5 { Pin the knight before d4 is played. } (4. d4 Nf6 (4... Be7 5. Bd3 Nf6 6. d5 Nb8 7. c4 Bg4 8. h3 Bh5 $14) (4... Bg4) 5. Bb5 Be7 6. d5 a6 7. Bd3 Nb8 8. O-O O-O $14) (4. Bc4 f5 5. exf5 (5. d3 { Wagener, Claude - Sokolov, Ivan, 0-1, Vienna op 18th, 2013, https://lichess.org/0AdcvlZZ }) 5... Bxf5 6. O-O e4 7. Re1 d5 8. Bb5 Nf6 9. Ne5 Bd7 10. Bxc6 Bxc6 11. d3 $10) 4... f5 (4... Nf6 5. O-O Nxe4 6. d4 Bd7 7. Re1 Nf6 8. Nbd2 (8. Bxc6 Bxc6 9. dxe5 dxe5 10. Qxd8+ Kxd8 11. Nxe5 Bd5 12. Nd2 $10) 8... Be7 9. Bxc6 Bxc6 10. dxe5 dxe5 11. Nxe5 Bd5 12. c4 Be6 13. Qc2 O-O $10) (4... Bd7 5. O-O { Transposition to Ruy Lopez/Steinitz Defense }) (4... g6) 5. exf5 Bxf5 6. d4 { Threatening d5. } { [%cal Gd4d5] } 6... Nf6 (6... a6) (6... Be7) (6... e4 7. d5 exf3 8. dxc6 Qe7+ 9. Be3 b6 10. Qxf3 $16 Qe4 (10... Be4 { Escofet Fernandez, Jaime - Bauza, Alejandro, 0-1, URU-ch, 1992, https://lichess.org/RWKAuiK8 }) 11. Nd2 Qxf3 12. Nxf3 Be4 13. Nd4 Bxg2 (13... Bd5 { The engine thinks Black should not take the pawn. } 14. O-O-O) 14. Rg1 Bd5 15. c4 Bf7 16. Ba6 Nf6 17. O-O-O $16) 7. O-O a6 8. Ba4 Bd7 9. Re1 Be7 10. dxe5 Nxe5 11. Bb3 Bg4 12. Nbd2 Qd7 13. h3 Nxf3+ 14. Nxf3 Bxf3 15. Qxf3 { [%cal Gf3b7,Gb3g8] } 15... d5 $16 *


