{ The following list of games is ordered by date, starting with the oldest game. }
1. e4 { The first part is a set of historical games from the 19th century that introduced important new lines. But be aware that the players of this time didn't play very accurately, and the core ideas of some lines have been worked out much later. } 1... e5 { The second part features modern games in which we can see the current state of the Ponziani theory. } *


