1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 { C27 Vienna Game. } 2... Nf6 { Falkbeer Variation } (2... d6 3. f4 $10 { Omaha Gambit }) (2... Bc5 $10 { Anderssen Defense } 3. Qg4 $10 { Giraffe Attack } (3. Na4?! $15 { Hamppe-Meitner Variation } 3... Bxf2+! 4. Kxf2 Qh4+ 5. Ke3 Qf4+ 6. Kd3 d5 $15 7. Qe1 (7. Kc3 d4+ 8. Kb3 Qxe4)) (3. f4 { First played by Carl Friedrich Jänisch in London 1851, so I call it the (other) Jänisch Gambit. There is also one in the Ruy Lopez. } 3... d6)) (2... Nc6 $10 { Max Lange Defense } 3. d4 $15 { Fyfe Gambit } (3. g3 $10 { Paulsen Variation } 3... Bc5 (3... Nf6 4. Bg2 Bc5 5. Nge2 d5 $14 { Paulsen Variation/Unnamed Gambit } 6. Nxd5) 4. Bg2 h5 5. Nf3 h4 $10 { Paulsen Variation/Mariotti Gambit }) (3. Bc4 Nf6 $10 { Stanley Variation/Three Knights Variation } (3... Bc5 4. Qg4 Qf6 5. Nd5 $14 { Stanley Variation/Meitner-Mieses Gambit } 5... Qxf2+ 6. Kd1 Kf8 7. Nh3 h5 8. Qg5 Qd4 9. d3 Be7 10. Qg3 $14 { Merry, Alan B - Webb, M., 0-1, Scarborough Congress 2017, https://lichess.org/YzzqWr51 }) 4. f4? Nxe4 5. Nf3 $15 { Stanley Variation/Bronstein Gambit }) (3. f4 $10 { Vienna Gambit } 3... Bc5 (3... exf4 $15 4. d4 $15 { Vienna Gambit/Steinitz Gambit } (4. Nf3 $15 { Vienna Gambit/Steinitz Gambit/Knight Variation } 4... Be7 $10 { Vienna Gambit/Cunningham Defense } (4... g5 5. h4 (5. Bc4 g4 6. O-O gxf3 $17 { Vienna Gambit/Hamppe-Muzio Gambit }) (5. d4 $17 { Vienna Gambit/Pierce Gambit }) 5... g4 6. Ng5 $15 { Vienna Gambit/Hamppe-Allgaier Gambit } 6... h6 7. Nxf7 Kxf7 8. d4 $15 { Vienna Gambit/Hamppe-Allgaier-Thorold Gambit })) 4... Qh4+ 5. Ke2 $10 { Vienna Gambit/Steinitz Gambit/Main Line } 5... d6 $10 { Vienna Gambit/Steinitz Gambit/Paulsen Defense } (5... b6 $15 { Vienna Gambit/Steinitz Gambit/Fraser-Minckwitz Defense }) (5... d5 $10 { Vienna Gambit/Steinitz Gambit/Zukertort Defense }) (5... g5 $15 { Vienna Gambit/Steinitz Gambit/Soerensen Defense })) 4. fxe5 d6 $10 { Vienna Gambit/Quelle Gambit }) 3... f5?! $16 { Philidor Countergambit }) (2... Bb4 3. Qg4 (3. Nd5 { Unnamed sideline. }) (3. f4 { First played by Ernst Karl Falkbeer in London 1855, so I call it the Falkbeer Gambit. That's not the official name. } 3... exf4 4. Qg4 { [%cal Gg4g7,Gg4f4] } 4... Nf6) 3... Nf6 $10 { Zhuravlev Countergambit }) (2... f5 { First played in Falkbeer - Anderssen, Berlin 1851, so I call it the Anderssen Gambit }) (2... c6 3. d4) 3. Bc4 $10 { Stanley Variation } (3. a3 $10 { Mengarini Variation }) (3. f4 $10 { Vienna Gambit } 3... d5 $10 { Vienna Gambit/Main Line } 4. d3 $15 { Vienna Gambit/Steinitz Variation } (4. fxe5 Nxe4 5. Nf3?! (5. d3?! $15 { Vienna Gambit/Modern Variation } 5... Qh4+?! $14 6. g3 Nxg3?! 7. Nf3 Qh5 8. Nxd5 $10 { Vienna Gambit/Wurzburger Trap }) (5. Qf3 $10 { Vienna Gambit/Paulsen Attack } 5... f5 $10 { Vienna Gambit/Bardeleben Variation }) 5... Bg4?! (5... Be7 $10 { Vienna Gambit/Breyer Variation }) 6. Qe2 $10 { Vienna Gambit/Kaufmann Variation })) (3. g3 { Mieses Variation } 3... d5 (3... Bc5 4. Bg2 Nc6 5. Nge2 d5?! $14 { Paulsen Variation/3…Nf6 4.Bg2 } 6. exd5 $14 { Paulsen Variation/Polluck Gambit }) 4. exd5 Nxd5 (4... c6 { Mieses Variation/Erben Gambit }) 5. Bg2 Nxc3 6. bxc3 Bd6 7. Nf3 O-O 8. O-O Nc6 9. Rb1 Rb8 10. d4 Bg4 $10 11. Qd3 Qd7 (11... Qf6) 12. dxe5 Nxe5) 3... Bb4 $10 { Stanley Variation/Reversed Spanish } (3... Bc5 4. Nge2 b5 $14 { Stanley Variation/Eifel Gambit }) (3... Nxe4 { Stanley Variation/Modern Variation } 4. Nf3 $15 { Bishop's Opening/Boden-Kieseritsky Gambit } (4. Qh5 Nd6 5. Bb3 Be7 $10 { Stanley Variation/Monster Declined } (5... Nc6?! 6. Nb5 g6 7. Qf3 f5?! 8. Qd5 Qe7 9. Nxc7+ Kd8 10. Nxa8 b6 $16 { Stanley Variation/Frankenstein-Dracula Variation }) 6. Nf3 Nc6 7. Nxe5 $10 { Stanley Variation/Alekhine Variation })) (3... Nc6 $10 { Stanley Variation/Three Knights Variation }) *


