1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. f4 { C26 Vienna Gambit } 3... d5 { Basically the only good move. } { [%cal Rf6e4] } (3... Nc6?! { Gives White everything they want. } 4. fxe5! Nxe5 5. d4 Nc6 (5... Ng6 6. e5 Ng8 7. Nf3 { Cover the entry square for Black's queen. } { [%csl Gh4][%cal Gf3h4] } 7... Bb4 8. Bc4 d5 9. exd6 Bxd6 10. Ng5 Nh6 (10... Qe7+ 11. Nce4 f5 12. O-O fxe4 13. Rf7 Qd8 (13... Bxh2+ 14. Kh1 (14. Kxh2 Qd6+ 15. Kg1 Nf6 16. Rxf6 gxf6 17. Nxe4 Qe7 18. Nc5 { [%cal Gd1h5,Gc1h6,Ga1e1] }))))) (3... exf4? { A serious mistake. And the most played move in this position on lichess. } 4. e5! Ng8 { The only move to keep a chance to equalize maybe later. } 5. Nf3) 4. fxe5 (4. exd5 { Possible, but rare. } 4... Nxd5 (4... exf4 5. d4 Nxd5 6. Nxd5 Qxd5 7. Bxf4 Bd6 8. Bxd6 Qxd6 9. Nf3 O-O 10. Be2) (4... e4 5. Bb5+) 5. Nxd5 Qxd5 6. fxe5 Qe4+ 7. Qe2 Qxc2) 4... Nxe4 5. Nf3 (5. d3 Qh4+?! 6. g3 Nxg3 7. Nf3 Qh5 8. Nxd5 { Würzburger Trap, named after the German banker Max Würzburger. } 8... Bg4 (8... Nxh1 9. Nxc7+ Kd8 10. Nxa8 $13) 9. Bg2 (9. Nf4 Bxf3 10. Nxh5 Bxd1 11. hxg3 Bxc2 12. b3) 9... Nxh1 (9... Bxf3? 10. Qxf3 Qxe5+ (10... Qxf3 11. Bxf3 Nxh1 12. Nxc7+ Kd7 13. Nxa8 Nc6 14. Bg4+ Kd8 15. d4 Nxd4 16. Bg5+ Be7 17. Rd1 Bxg5 18. Rxd4+ { [%csl Gd7][%cal Gd4d7,Gd7e7] } 18... Ke8 19. Rd7 Bh4+ 20. Kf1 Nf2 21. Nc7+ Kf8 22. Bf3 $16) 11. Kd1 Nxh1 12. Bf4 Qxb2 13. Qe4+ Kd8 14. Bxc7+ Kd7 15. Qf5+ Kc6 16. Qc8! Nf2+ (16... Qxa1+ 17. Ke2) 17. Kd2) 10. Nxc7+ Kd7 11. Nxa8 Nc6 12. Be3 $14) (5. Qf3 { Stockfish's preferred move. } { [%cal Gf3c3] } 5... Nxc3 6. dxc3 (6. bxc3) (6. Qxc3)) 5... Be7 6. Qe2 Nxc3 7. dxc3 c5 8. Bf4 Nc6 9. O-O-O Be6 10. h4 h6 *


