1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Bc5 { This does prevent White from castling short for now. } 3. f4 { First played by Carl Friedrich Jänisch in London 1851, so I call it the Jänisch Gambit. } 3... d6 { In contrast to the Omaha Gambit Black got the bishop out first, which makes this a better version. } { [%cal Rd8h4] } 4. Nf3 { Prevent the annoying check. } (4. fxe5?! { I don't recommend this. It's a bloody mess. } 4... dxe5 5. Qh5 { [%cal Gh5e5] } 5... Qd4! 6. Nf3 Qf2+ 7. Kd1 Nc6 8. Nd5 { [%cal Gd5c7] } 8... Nf6 9. Qg5 Nxd5 (9... Nxe4?? 10. Qxg7 Rf8 11. Nxc7+ Kd8 12. Nxa8 Nd4 13. Bd3 $16) 10. exd5 Ne7 (10... e4 11. dxc6 exf3 12. Qxg7 Bd4 13. Qg5 bxc6 14. c3 Ba6 15. cxd4 Bxf1 16. Qe5+ Kd8 17. Qf6+ Kc8 18. Qxf3 Qxf3+ 19. gxf3 Bg2 20. Re1 (20. Rg1 Bxf3+ 21. Kc2) 20... Bxf3+ 21. Kc2 Bd5 22. d3 $13) 11. Qxg7 Rg8 12. Qxe5) 4... Nf6 (4... Nc6 5. Na4 { One option is hunting the annoying black bishop. } 5... Bg4 (5... Bb6 { Main move on lichess. } 6. Nxb6 axb6 { And now White has the bishop pair and a slightly better pawn structure. } 7. Bb5 Bd7 8. d3 { [%cal Gc1f4] } 8... Nge7 (8... Nf6?! { That loses a pawn. } 9. Bxc6 Bxc6 10. fxe5 Ng4 11. exd6 Qxd6 12. O-O { Stockfish says it's still equal, but ... I like White here. h3 should be played soon to neutralize the mate threat on h2. } { [%cal Rd6h2,Rg4h2] }) 9. f5 { And here we close the position for a while. White has also ideas of a positional pawn sacrifice per f5-f6. } 9... O-O 10. O-O { [%cal Gf5f6] } 10... f6 11. Bc4+ Kh8 (11... d5?? 12. exd5 Na5 13. d6+ Nxc4 14. dxe7 Qxe7 15. dxc4 $18) 12. a3 { Create a retreat square for the bishop and prevent the knight coming to b4. } { [%cal Gc4a2,Rc6b4] } 12... Be8 { Black should now move some defending material to the king side. } 13. Be6 { Be annoying! }) 6. Nxc5 dxc5 7. d3 f5!? { A very rare move. Interesting nonetheless. } 8. Be2 fxe4 9. dxe4 Qxd1+ 10. Bxd1 exf4 (10... Nge7 11. f5 g6 12. fxg6 hxg6 $13) 11. Bxf4 O-O-O $10 { Technically equal, but White's bishop pair might be worth more in the endgame. On the other hand, the the isolated e-pawn is a liability. }) (4... Bg4) (4... a6?! { 4th most common move on lichess. It's just a wasted tempo. }) (4... exf4 5. d4 Bb4 6. Bxf4 $16) 5. Bc4 Nc6 (5... O-O) (5... Bg4) (5... a6) (5... Ng4 6. d4 exd4 7. Nxd4 Qh4+ 8. g3 Qh3?! { Main move on lichess. } 9. Bf1 Qh5) *


