1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. Bc4 { This position can also be reached per Bishop's opening: 1.e4 e5 2.Bc4 Nf6 3.Nc3 } 3... Nxe4 { This is the Frankenstein–Dracula Variation already. } 4. Qh5 (4. Nxe4? { Don't do that. } 4... d5 5. Bd3 dxe4 6. Bxe4 f5 $15) (4. Bxf7+ { Interesting very sharp sideline. Objectively better for Black, but requires accurate play. } 4... Kxf7 5. Nxe4 { [%cal Gd1f3] } 5... d5 (5... Nc6?! 6. Qf3+ Ke6 (6... Kg8?? 7. Ng5 { [%cal Gf3f7] } 7... Qe7 (7... Qxg5?? 8. Qd5#) 8. Qd5+ Qe6 9. Nxe6 dxe6 10. Qe4 $18) 7. d3) 6. Ng3 $15) 4... Nd6 5. Bb3 (5. Qxe5+ { [%cal Ge5g7] } 5... Qe7 6. Qxe7+ Bxe7 7. Be2) 5... Nc6 { Holding on to the pawn. } { [%cal Gc6e5] } (5... Be7 { Gives the pawn back. } 6. Qxe5 (6. Nf3 Nc6 7. Nxe5 O-O 8. O-O Nxe5 9. Qxe5 Bf6 10. Qf4 $10) 6... O-O 7. Nf3 Nc6 8. Qf4 Na5 9. O-O Nxb3 10. axb3 $10 { Black has the bishop pair, White open files for the rooks. }) 6. Nb5 g6 (6... Nxb5?? 7. Qxf7#) 7. Qf3 f5 8. Qd5 Qe7 (8... Qf6 9. Nxc7+ Kd8 10. Nxa8 b6 11. d3 Bb7 12. h4?? (12. Nf3 { [%cal Gf3e5,Gd5e5] }) 12... Ne7!) 9. Nxc7+ Kd8 10. Nxa8 b6 11. d3 Bb7 12. h4 { [%cal Gc1g5] } 12... f4 13. Qf3 Nd4 { [%cal Rb7f3] } 14. Qh3 Bxa8 15. c3 Nxb3 16. axb3 { [%cal Ga1a7] } *


