1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 { B12 Caro-Kann Defense: Advance Variation } 3... Bf5 4. Nd2 e6 5. Nb3 Nd7 6. Nf3 Qc7 7. Be2 c5 8. dxc5 Bxc5 9. Nxc5 Qxc5 10. c3 Ne7 11. Nd4 { White gives up the e5-pawn in favor of an attack. } 11... Nxe5 12. Qa4+ N5c6 13. Nb5 Qb6 14. Be3 (14. Nd6+ Kf8 15. Qb5) 14... Qd8 15. Nxa7 Qd7 16. Bb5 O-O 17. Qd1 Rfb8?! { (-0.96 → -0.28) Inaccuracy. Best move was d4. } (17... d4 18. Nxc6 bxc6 19. Be2 d3 20. Bf3 Nd5 21. Qd2 Nxe3 22. fxe3 e5 23. a4 e4 24. Bd1) 18. b4?! { (-0.28 → -0.78) Inaccuracy. Best move was Qd2. } (18. Qd2 Qc7 19. Nxc6 bxc6 20. Be2 e5 21. b4 Ra4 22. Bd1 Ra3 23. O-O Ng6 24. Bb3 Nf4) 18... d4 19. Nxc6 bxc6 20. Bc4 c5 21. O-O e5?! { (-0.60 → -0.08) Inaccuracy. Best move was cxb4. } (21... cxb4 22. cxd4 Rc8 23. Rc1 Be4 24. Re1 Nf5 25. Bb3 Rxc1 26. Bxc1 Bd5 27. Bb2 Ne7 28. Qd3) 22. Bd2 Be6 23. Bxe6 Qxe6 24. bxc5 d3 25. Be3 Qc4 26. Qh5 Nc6?! { (-0.92 → -0.36) Inaccuracy. Best move was f5. } (26... f5 27. Qg5 Rb7 28. a4 h6 29. Qg3 f4 30. Qf3 Nd5 31. Bd2 e4 32. Qg4 Rf7 33. a5) 27. Qf5 Rd8 28. Rfd1 Rxa2 29. Rab1 Ra7 30. h4 h6 31. Rb6 Rc7 32. Qf3?! { (-0.12 → -0.64) Inaccuracy. Best move was f3. } (32. f3 Qxc3 33. Qe4 Nd4 34. Rd6 Rxd6 35. cxd6 Rd7 36. Kf2 Qc5 37. Qa8+ Kh7 38. Qe4+ g6) 32... e4 33. Qg3 Rdc8?! { (-0.64 → -0.08) Inaccuracy. Best move was Rcc8. } (33... Rcc8 34. Bxh6 Qxc3 35. Qg5 Re8 36. Rc1 Qe5 37. Qxe5 Nxe5 38. Bf4 Ng6 39. Bg5 f6 40. h5) 34. Bxh6 Qxc3 35. Bf4? { (-0.29 → -1.58) Mistake. Best move was Rdb1. } (35. Rdb1 Re7) 35... Re7? { (-1.58 → -0.11) Mistake. Best move was Nd4. } (35... Nd4 36. Be5 f6 37. Bxd4 Qxd4 38. Kh2 Rxc5 39. Rd6 Rd5 40. Re6 Rf8 41. Kg1 Re5 42. Ra6) 36. Be3 Nd4 37. Qg4 Ne2+ 38. Kh1 Rce8 39. h5? { (-0.44 → -1.56) Mistake. Best move was g3. } (39. g3 Qe5 40. Qg5 Qxg5 41. hxg5 Nc3 42. Rc1 Nd5 43. Rd6 Nxe3 44. fxe3 Rc7 45. Kg2 Kf8) 39... Re6? { (-1.56 → -0.33) Mistake. Best move was Qe5. } (39... Qe5 40. Qh4) 40. h6 Qf6 41. Rdb1 g6? { (-0.08 → 1.37) Mistake. Best move was Qg6. } (41... Qg6 42. Qxg6 Rxg6 43. Rb8 Rxb8 44. Rxb8+ Kh7 45. Rf8 Rf6 46. c6 Rxc6 47. Rxf7 Rd6 48. Bd2) 42. Rxe6 Rxe6?? { (0.95 → Mate in 10) Checkmate is now unavoidable. Best move was Qxe6. } (42... Qxe6 43. Qxe6) 43. h7+ Kg7 44. h8=Q+ { Black resigns. } 44... Kxh8 45. Qh3+ Qh4 46. Qxh4+ Kg7 47. Bh6+ Kh7 48. Bg5+ Kg7 49. Qh6+ Kg8 50. Rb8+ Re8 51. Rxe8# 1-0


[Event "Tbilisi FIDE World Cup"]
[Site "https://lichess.org/WoRDze1I"]
[Date "2017.09.10"]
[Round "19"]
[White "Kramnik, Vladimir (2803)"]
[Black "Ivanchuk, Vassily (2727)"]
[Result "0-1"]
[TimeControl "-"]
[Termination "Normal"]
