1. e4 { lichess.org: https://lichess.org/XvgXJ2Tb } 1... c6 { chess24.com: https://chess24.com/en/watch/live-tournaments/arad-open-2017/7/1/2 } 2. d4 d5 3. e5 c5 4. dxc5 Nc6 5. a3 { Gives away the e-pawn in favor of an attack. But even with 5.f4 Black could capture a pawn: } (5. f4 Nh6 6. Nf3 e6 7. Be3 d4 8. Bxd4 Nxd4 9. Qxd4 Qxd4 10. Nxd4 Bxc5) 5... Nxe5 6. b4 { Gives the gained tempo away. } (6. Bb5+ Nc6 7. b4 Nf6 8. Bb2 e6) 6... g6 { The most common move in this position. } 7. Bb5+ Bd7 { Not sure why the engine discards Nc6. That doesn't look so bad. Actually, I'd prefer this move. } (7... Nc6 8. Bb2 Nf6 9. c4 Be6 10. Nf3 Bg7 11. O-O O-O 12. Nbd2 a5 13. Qb3 axb4 14. axb4 Rxa1 15. Rxa1 Qc7 16. Re1 Rd8 17. Ng5 Bf5 18. h3 dxc4 19. Nxc4 Nd5 20. Bxg7 Kxg7 21. Nd6 exd6 22. Qxd5 h6 23. Nf3 Be6 24. Qe4 dxc5 25. bxc5 Bd5 26. Qh4 h5 $10) 8. Qxd5 { A free pawn! This extra pawn will decide the game. } 8... Bxb5 { I think this exchange isn't good for Black. Bg7 looks better. } (8... Bg7 9. Bxd7+ Qxd7 10. Qxd7+ Nxd7 11. Ra2 Ngf6 12. Ne2 b6 13. cxb6 Nxb6 14. Nbc3 O-O 15. O-O) 9. Qxe5 Nf6 10. Nc3 Bc6 11. Nf3 { Missed the opportunity to get an open file with Bg5 and Rd1. } (11. Bg5 Bg7 12. Rd1 Qc8) 11... Bg7 12. Bb2 O-O { b6 immediately would have made Black's life a little bit easier. } (12... b6 13. O-O bxc5 14. Qxc5 Bxf3 15. gxf3 O-O) 13. Qe2 { Again a missed open file. } (13. Rd1 Qc8 14. O-O Re8) 13... Ne4?! { Novelty. Inviting an exchange that isn't good for Black. Qc8 would have been better for the fight for the center. Hard to see tough. } (13... Qc8 14. Nd1 e5 15. O-O Nd5 16. Nxe5 Re8 17. f4 Nxf4 18. Rxf4 Qc7 19. Qf2 Bxe5 20. Bxe5 Qxe5 21. Rb1 Re7 22. Rd4 b6 23. cxb6 axb6 24. Rd3 Qe1+ 25. Qxe1 Rxe1+ 26. Kf2 Rh1 27. Rd6 Be4 28. Nc3 Rxb1 29. Nxb1 Bxc2 30. Nd2 b5 31. Rd5 Rxa3 32. Rxb5 Ra2 33. Ke3 Bf5 34. Rb8+ Kg7 35. b5 Kf6 36. b6 Rb2 37. Ne4+ Bxe4 38. Kxe4 Rxg2) 14. Qe3 { Then engine wants to see Nd1 here, to enforce the bishop exchange. } (14. Nd1 Bxb2 15. Nxb2 b6 16. cxb6 axb6) 14... b6 15. Rd1 { Finally! } 15... Qc7 (15... Qe8 16. Nxe4 Bxb2 17. O-O Bxe4 18. Qxe4 bxc5 19. Rb1 Bf6 20. b5 Qb8) 16. O-O Bxc3 17. Bxc3 Nxc3 18. cxb6 { Opportunity for Black to equalize with a nice tactic: Qf4! } 18... Qxb6 (18... Qf4 19. Qxc3 Bxf3 20. Rd4 Qf6 21. gxf3 axb6 22. Rfd1 Rfc8 23. Qd3 b5 24. f4 Kg7 25. Qxb5 Rxc2 26. a4 e5 27. Qxe5 Rxa4 28. Qe3 Ra6 29. h3 Rb2 30. Rd8 Re6 31. Qc5 Qe7 32. Qc3+ Qf6 33. Qc5) 19. Qxc3 Rac8 20. Rfe1 Qb7? { Mistake. Ba4 would have been much better. } (20... Ba4 21. Qd4 Bxc2 22. Rd2 Rfe8 23. h4 Bf5 24. h5 Qxd4 25. Nxd4 Bd7 $10) 21. Rd2?! { Inaccuracy. } (21. Qb3 Bxf3 22. gxf3 Qc7 23. c4 Qxc4 24. Qxc4 Rxc4 25. Rxe7 a5 26. b5 Rb8 27. Rb1 a4 28. Re4 Rxe4 29. fxe4 Kf8) 21... Bxf3?! { Inaccuracy. } (21... a5 22. Qb3 Bxf3 23. gxf3 axb4 24. axb4 Qb5 25. Rd5 Qc4 26. Rxe7 Qxc2 27. Qxc2 Rxc2 28. Rdd7 Kg7) 22. Qxf3 Qxf3 23. gxf3 e6 24. Re5 Rc7 25. Ra5 Rfc8?! { Inaccuracy. This attacks the wrong pawn. } (25... Rb8 26. Kg2 Rb6 27. b5 Kg7 28. c4 Rbb7 29. Ra4) 26. c4 Rxc4 27. Rxa7 Rf4?! { Inaccuracy. Again, the wrong pawn. The passers must be stopped, not the doubled pawns. } (27... Rb8 28. Ra5 Rf4 29. Kg2 Rf5 30. Rxf5 exf5 31. Rd5 Kg7 32. Ra5 Kf6 33. b5 Ke5 34. a4 h5 35. Ra7 Kf4 36. Rc7 Ke5 37. Rc5+ Kd4 38. Rc6 h4 39. Kh3 Ke5 40. Rc5+ Kd4 41. Rc7 Ra8 42. b6 Rxa4 43. b7 Rb4 44. Kxh4 Kd5+ 45. Kg5) 28. Kg2? { Mistake. Should protect the passers instead. } (28. Rb2 Rb8 29. b5 Rb6 30. a4 Rf5 31. f4 Kg7) 28... Rc3?! { Inaccuracy. Again, Rb8 was needed. } (28... Rb8 29. Ra5 Kf8 30. b5 Rb6 31. Rb2 Ke7 32. a4 Kd6 33. Kg3 Rf5) 29. b5?! { Inaccuracy. Protect the passers instead … } (29. Rb2 Rc6 30. b5 Rb6 31. a4 Rf5 32. f4) 29... Rb3 30. a4 g5 { Maybe the king should travel north first: } (30... Kg7 31. Ra2 Rfb4 32. Rc7 g5 33. Kf1 Kf6 34. Ke2 e5) 31. h3 { This move doesn't do much. It's a pity that both players had to handle this endgame in zeitnot. } (31. Ra2 Rbb4 32. Ra6 Kg7 33. b6 Rb1 34. a5 Rd4 35. Ra7 h5 36. Rc7 Rdd1 37. Rac2 Ra1 38. R7c5 Rg1+ 39. Kh3 Ra4 40. R2c4 Ra2 41. Rb4 Rxf2 42. Rxg5+ Rxg5 43. b7 Rxf3+ 44. Kh4 Rxa5 45. b8=Q) 31... h5 { The engine found an interesting alternative: } (31... Kg7 32. Ra2 Rbb4 33. Ra6 h5 34. Ra1 g4 35. fxg4 Rb2 36. Kg3 Rfxf2 37. gxh5 Rf5 38. h6+ Kxh6 39. Ra3 Rg5+ 40. Kf3 Rh5 41. Kf4 Rb4+ 42. Kg3 Rg5+ 43. Kf3 Kg6 44. Rc6 Rh5 45. Ke2 Rhh4 46. a5 Rxb5 47. a6 Rb2+ 48. Kd1 Rd4+ 49. Kc1 Rb8 50. a7 Ra8 51. Kb2 Rd7 52. Rca6 Kf6 53. Kc3 Ke7 54. Kb4 Rd5 55. R6a5 Kd6 56. Rxd5+ Kxd5 57. h4 f5 58. h5 f4) 32. Re2 g4 33. hxg4? { Mistake. The attacked f-pawn should take here first. } (33. fxg4 hxg4 34. Re3 gxh3+ 35. Rxh3 Rbb4 36. Rg3+ Kh7 37. Ra3) 33... hxg4 34. Re3 Rxf3? { Mistake. } (34... gxf3+ 35. Kg3 Rbb4 36. Rb3 Rxa4 37. Rxa4 Rxa4 38. b6) 35. Rxf3 (35. Rxb3 Rxb3 36. Ra6 Kf8 37. b6 Ke7 38. Ra7+ Kd8 39. Ra8+ Kd7 40. a5 Kc6 41. a6 Rxb6 42. Rc8+ Kd7 43. a7 Kxc8 44. a8=Q+) 35... gxf3+ 36. Kg3 Kf8 37. Kf4?! { Inaccuracy. } (37. Ra6 Ke8 38. b6 Kd7 39. a5 Kc6 40. Ra8 e5 41. a6 Rxb6 42. Rc8+ Kd7 43. a7 Rg6+ 44. Kxf3 Kxc8 45. a8=Q+) 37... f6? { Mistake. } (37... e5+ 38. Kxe5 Rb2 39. Ke4 Rxf2 40. Ke3 Rb2 41. Kxf3 Rb4 42. Ke3 Ke8 43. Kd3 f5 44. Ra6 Kd7 45. Kc3 Re4 46. a5 Re3+ 47. Kc4 f4 48. Ra7+ Kd6 49. b6 f3 50. Rf7 Kc6 51. Rc7+ Kd6 52. a6 Re4+ 53. Kb5 Re5+ 54. Ka4 Re4+ 55. Ka5 Re1 56. a7 f2 57. Rf7 f1=Q 58. Rxf1 Rxf1 59. Kb4 Rb1+ 60. Kc4 Rc1+ 61. Kd4 Rd1+ 62. Ke4 Kc6 63. a8=Q+ Kxb6) 38. Rh7 Ke8?? { Now it's completely lost. Kg8 was necessary. } (38... Kg8 39. Rd7) 39. a5 Kd8?! { Inaccuracy. } (39... Rxb5 40. a6 Rf5+ 41. Kg3 Rg5+ 42. Kxf3 Rf5+ 43. Ke2 Re5+ 44. Kf1 Ra5 45. a7 Kd8 46. Rh8+ Kd7 47. a8=Q Rxa8 48. Rxa8 Kc6) 40. a6 Kc8? { Mistake. Now it's mate in 7. } (40... Rb4+ 41. Kg3 Rxb5 42. a7 Rg5+ 43. Kf4 Rf5+ 44. Ke3 Re5+ 45. Kd3 Rd5+ 46. Kc4 Ra5 47. a8=R+ Rxa8 48. Rh8+ Ke7 49. Rxa8 Kd6) 41. Rh8+ { Not the best mating sequence, but winning anyway. Black resigns. } (41. a7 Ra3 42. b6 Ra4+ 43. Kg3 Kd8 44. b7 Rg4+ 45. Kxg4 f5+ 46. Kh4 f4 47. a8=Q#) 1-0


