1. e4 c6 { The amazing thing about this game is that Quang Liem Le didn't make a single inaccuracy. See https://lichess.org/WAtglanu for an engine analysis. } 2. Nf3 d5 { chess24 URL: https://chess24.com/en/watch/live-tournaments/chinese-league-2017/10/3/2 } 3. Nc3 Bg4 4. h3 Bxf3 { B11 Caro-Kann Defense: Two Knights Attack, Mindeno Variation, Exchange Line } 5. Qxf3 Nf6 6. Be2 e6 7. O-O Bc5 8. d3 Nbd7 9. Qg3 O-O { Up to this move, they were still following the game [Mastrovasilis - Dreev, 2013] https://lichess.org/2g77xPlM/black#18 } 10. Bh6 { I think the idea here is not really a mating attack. This move forces the knight to e8, where it is blocking the rook from coming into the game. } 10... Ne8 11. Bf4 Kh8?! { Very passive. Bd4 looked interesting. } (11... Bd4 12. Rab1) 12. exd5 { White has the bishop pair; opening up the game is just consequent. } 12... cxd5 13. Na4 Be7 14. c4 Ndf6 { Makes sure that Nd6 is protected by the queen. } 15. Nc3 (15. c5 { This move could have prevented Nd6 for a while. } 15... Qa5 16. b3 b5 17. cxb6 axb6 18. Be5 { Create a safe square for the inevitable knight retreat. } 18... b5 19. Nc3 Nd7 $15 { Now Black is a little bit better. c5 was probably not the best option. }) 15... Nd6 16. Be5 { Frees f4 for the queen. } 16... Nf5 17. Qf4 Rc8 18. cxd5 { Maybe it would have been better to keep the tension for a while. Black has little interest in opening up the field. } (18. Rae1 b6 19. Nb5 Qd7) 18... Nxd5 19. Qe4 { A different order for the following moves would have been better for White. } (19. Nxd5 Qxd5 20. Bf3 Qd7 $10) 19... Bf6 (19... Nb4 { A sharper line. } 20. Qxb7 Nc6 21. d4 Nfxd4 22. Bxd4 Nxd4 23. Rfd1 Bf6 $10) 20. Nxd5 Bxe5 21. Qxe5 Rc5 22. Bf3 Nh4 23. Be4 exd5 24. Qd4?! { (0.16 → -0.36) Inaccuracy. Best move was g3. } (24. g3 b6 25. Bh1 d4 26. Qe2 Ng6 27. Rac1 Rxc1 28. Rxc1 f5 29. Qe6 f4 30. Re1 fxg3) 24... b6 25. b4 Rc7 26. Qxd5 f5 27. Bf3 Rd7 28. Qc6 Rd6 { Taking d3 first looks more natural. } (28... Rxd3 29. Be2 Rd6) 29. Qb7 Rd7 30. Qc6 Rxd3 31. Be2 Rd6 32. Qb7 Rd7 33. Qc6 Rf6 34. Qc4 Rg6 35. g3?? { (-1.07 → -5.15) Blunder. Best move was Rac1. } (35. Rac1 Rxg2+ 36. Kh1 Rg6 37. Rfd1 Rgd6 38. Rxd6 Rxd6 39. Qc8 h6 40. Kg1 Qxc8 41. Rxc8+ Kh7) 35... Rd4 36. Rad1 Qa8 37. Qc8+ Qxc8 38. Rxd4 Qc7 39. Kh2?! { (-4.26 → -5.16) Inaccuracy. Best move was Rfd1. } (39. Rfd1 h6) 39... Re6 40. Rc1 Qb8 41. Rdc4 Re8 42. Rc7 Ng6 43. Bb5 Rf8 44. Bd7?! { (-5.38 → -6.34) Inaccuracy. Best move was f4. } (44. f4) 44... f4 45. h4?! { (-6.19 → -6.81) Inaccuracy. Best move was a3. } (45. a3 Qd8 46. R1c2 fxg3+ 47. fxg3 Qe7 48. Bg4 Qe3 49. Rc8 Qxa3 50. b5 Qd6 51. Bf5 Rxc8) 45... fxg3+ 46. fxg3 Qa8 47. Bh3 Qd5 48. Rc8 h5 { White resigns. } 0-1


