1. c4 c6 { A11 English Opening: Caro-Kann Defensive System } 2. Nf3 d5 3. e3 Nf6 4. Nc3 e6 5. Qc2 Nbd7 6. b3 Bd6 7. Be2 O-O 8. Bb2 a6 9. d4 e5 { These first 9 moves are all very common, they have been played in a variety of move orders many times before. White still can castle either side, and they should open the center prior to this decision. cxd5 is the main move here. The lichess engine (SF 8/depth 21) suggests Nxd5! } 10. O-O-O (10. cxd5 cxd5 11. dxe5 Nxe5 12. O-O { And now castle short. } (12. O-O-O?! { Putting queen and king in line on an open file is not a good idea … } 12... Be6 13. Ng5 Rc8 14. Kb1 b5 15. Qd2 b4 16. Na4 Bf5+ $17) 12... Be6 13. Rac1 Rc8 14. Qb1 Nfg4 15. Nxe5 Bxe5 16. Bxg4 Bxg4 17. Na4 Bb8 18. Rxc8 Bxc8 19. Bd4 Re8 $10 { Portisch, Lajos - Kasparov, Garry, 1/2-1/2, Dubai ol (Men), 1986, https://lichess.org/bPjYf6oX }) (10. Nxd5 { Engine moves. The idea is a fork on e5. } 10... Nxd5 11. cxd5 e4 12. Qxe4 Qa5+ 13. Nd2 Nf6 14. Qc2 cxd5 { Romm, Mikhail Yakovlevich - Balabanov, Viktor Viktorovich, 1/2-1/2, MT-Sokolov (RUS), 2011, https://lichess.org/xCOcCXaF }) 10... e4?! { (0.00 → 0.51) Inaccuracy. Best move was exd4. } (10... exd4 11. Rxd4 Nb6 (11... Qe7 12. cxd5 cxd5 13. Kb1 Nb6 14. Rc1 Bg4 { Bischoff, Klaus - Antunes, Antonio, 1-0, Tunis op, 2017, https://lichess.org/nPrxMlbB }) 12. Kb1 Bd7 13. h3 h6 14. g4 Bc5 15. Rf4 Bd6 16. Rd4) 11. Nd2 Re8 12. g4 Nf8 13. Rdg1 Be6 14. h4 b5 15. c5 Bc7 16. g5 N6d7 17. f3 exf3 18. Nxf3 f5?! { (1.08 → 1.67) Inaccuracy. Best move was a5. } (18... a5 19. Bd3 a4 20. bxa4 bxa4 21. Nxa4 Qe7 22. h5 g6 23. Kb1 Reb8 24. Ka1 Rb7 25. Nc3) 19. Kb1 b4 20. Nd1 { This also protects e3 which was almost hanging. } 20... Ng6?! { (1.41 → 2.05) Inaccuracy. Best move was a5. } (20... a5 21. h5 a4 22. bxa4 Qb8 23. Bc1 f4 24. Nh4 fxe3 25. Nxe3 Bf4 26. Bd1 b3 27. axb3 Rxa4 $16) 21. h5 Ne7 22. Bd3 a5 23. Nf2 Nf8 24. Nh3 Qb8 25. Ne5? { (1.82 → 0.77) Mistake. Best move was Qd1. } (25. Qd1 Bc8 26. Nf4 Ne6 27. Nxe6 Bxe6) 25... a4 26. Nf4 axb3 27. axb3 Bxe5 28. dxe5 Bc8 29. e6 Nxe6 (29... Qa7 30. Rh4 Bxe6 31. Re1) 30. Nxe6 Bxe6 31. Bxg7 { Black cannot take the bishop. } 31... d4 (31... Kxg7?? 32. Qb2+ Kf8 33. Qf6+ Bf7 34. Qh6+ Kg8 35. g6 Ra1+ 36. Kc2 hxg6 37. hxg6 Qh2+ 38. Rxh2 Ra2+ 39. Kc1 Ra1+ 40. Bb1 Rxb1+ 41. Kxb1 Bxg6 42. Rxg6+ Nxg6 43. Qxg6+ Kf8 44. Qf6+ Kg8 45. Rh8#) 32. Bxd4 Ra3 33. Bc4 Nd5 34. h6?! { (1.50 → 0.80) Inaccuracy. Best move was g6. } (34. g6 h6 35. Qd3 Qd8 36. Bb2 Nc3+ 37. Kc2 Qxd3+ 38. Kxd3 Bxc4+ 39. bxc4 Ra5 40. Bxc3 bxc3) 34... Nc3+?! { (0.80 → 1.71) Inaccuracy. Best move was Nxe3. } (34... Nxe3 35. Bxe6+?! { This move was found as "best" in the automatic server side analysis. But g6 is so much stronger. It renders the whole Nxe3 suggestion invalid. } (35. g6! { Mate in 17 moves. } 35... Bxc4 36. gxh7+ Kf7 37. Rg7+ Ke6 38. Re1 Rxb3+ 39. Kc1 Bd5 40. Bxe3 Qe5 41. Bd2 Qxe1+ 42. Bxe1 Re3 43. Bh4 Be4 44. Qc4+ Ke5 45. h8=Q Rxh8 46. Bf6+ Kf4 47. Bg5+ Kg3 48. Bxe3+ Kf3 49. Bd2 Kf2 50. Qd4+ Ke2 51. Qe3+ Kf1 52. Rg1#) 35... Rxe6 36. Qd3 Qb5 37. Qxb5 cxb5 38. Rh3 Rxb3+ 39. Kc1 Nc2 40. Rxb3 Nxd4 41. Rb1) 35. Bxc3 Bxc4 36. Bb2 Bxb3 37. Qxf5 Qa7 38. Qxh7+!! { What a move! } 38... Qxh7+ 39. g6 Ba2+ 40. Kc1 { Black resigns. } 1-0


