1. e4 d6 { The basic idea is a setup with a knight on f6 and a fianchettoed bishop on g7. While White can occupy the center with pawns, Black tries to undermine it from the flanks. } { [%cal Gg8f6,Bf8g7,Rg7g6] } 2. d4 (2. f4 $10 { Rat Defense/Harmonist } 2... d5 3. exd5 Nf6 $14 { Rat Defense/Fuller Gambit }) (2. h4 $10 { Rat Defense/Petruccioli Attack }) (2. g4?! $15 { Rat Defense/Spike Attack }) 2... Nf6 { Pirc Defense/General.
Named after https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vasja_Pirc (pronounced Pirts)
In contrast to the Modern Defense (2…g6), Nf6 is slightly more active as it's attacking a pawn already. But note how many fields are under White's control and how many under Black's. } { [%csl Gg4,Rf5,Re5,Rd5,Rc5,Rb5,Rc4,Rg5,Rf4][%cal Gf6e4] } (2... e5 { King's Pawn Game/Maróczy Defense }) (2... Nd7?! $14 { Rat Defense/Antal Defense }) (2... f5?! $14 { Rat Defense/Balogh Defense }) (2... e6 $14 { Rat Defense/Small Center Defense }) (2... g6 { With a different move order, we get a Modern Defense – and the same ideas and problems. } 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. Be3 Nf6) 3. Nc3 (3. f3 { Lion Defense/Lion's Jaw } 3... e5 (3... g6 4. c4 Bg7 5. Nc3 { Transposition: King's Indian Defense/Sämisch Variation } 5... O-O 6. Be3 c5 7. Nge2 Nc6 8. d5 Ne5 9. Ng3 e6 10. Be2 exd5 11. cxd5 a6 12. a4 Bd7 13. h3 b5) 4. d5 (4. dxe5 { This is very uncomfortable for Black. } 4... dxe5 5. Qxd8+ Kxd8 6. Bc4 Ke8 7. Be3 Nbd7) 4... Be7 5. Be3 O-O) (3. Nf3?! $15 { Pirc Defense/Roscher Gambit }) 3... g6 (3... Nbd7 4. f4 { Lion Defense/Anti-Philidor } (4. g4 { Lion Defense/Bayonet Attack }) 4... e5 { Lion Defense/Anti-Philidor/Lion's Cave } 5. Nf3 exd4 6. Qxd4 c6 7. Bc4 d5 { Lion Defense/Anti-Philidor/Lion's Cave/Lion Claw Gambit }) (3... c6 { Czech Defense/General }) (3... e5 4. dxe5 dxe5 5. Qxd8+ Kxd8 6. Bg5 (6. Bc4 Be6 7. Bxe6 fxe6 8. Nf3 Bd6 9. Bg5 Ke7 10. O-O-O Nd7) 6... Be6 7. O-O-O+ Nd7 8. Nf3 Kc8) 4. f4 { Pirc Defense/Austrian Attack } (4. Be3 c6 5. Qd2 { Pirc Defense/150 Attack } (5. h3 { Pirc Defense/150 Attack/Sveshnikov-Jansa Attack }) 5... Bg4?! $16 { Pirc Defense/150 Attack/Inner Doll Defense }) (4. Be2 { Pirc Defense/Classical Variation } 4... Bg7 5. h4 { Pirc Defense/Bayonet Attack } (5. g4 { Pirc Defense/Chinese Variation })) (4. Nf3 { Pirc Defense/Classical Variation #2 } 4... Bg7 { Pirc Defense/Classical Variation/Two Knights System } 5. Be2 { Pirc Defense/Classical Variation/Quiet System } (5. h3 $10 { Pirc Defense/Classical Variation/Schlechter Variation }) 5... O-O 6. O-O Nc6 { Pirc Defense/Classical Variation/Quiet System/Chigorin Line } (6... c6 { Pirc Defense/Classical Variation/Quiet System/Czech Defense }) (6... Bg4 $14 { Pirc Defense/Classical Variation/Quiet System/Parma Defense })) (4. Bc4 $10 { Pirc Defense/Kholmov System }) (4. Bg5 { Pirc Defense/Byrne Variation }) 4... Bg7 (4... Nc6?! 5. Nf3) 5. Nf3 (5. Bc4 { Pirc Defense/Austrian Attack/Ljubojevic Variation }) (5. e5?! Nfd7 6. Nf3 c5 7. exd6 O-O! 8. Be3 exd6 9. Qd2 Nc6 10. O-O-O Qa5 11. Kb1 Nf6 $15) 5... O-O (5... c5 { Pirc Defense/Austrian Attack/Dragon Formation }) 6. Bd3 { Pirc Defense/Austrian Attack/Weiss Variation } (6. Be3 { Pirc Defense/Austrian Attack/Kurajica Variation }) (6. e5 { Pirc Defense/Austrian Attack/Unzicker Attack } 6... Nfd7 7. h4 $14 { Pirc Defense/Austrian Attack/Unzicker Attack/Bronstein Variation }) 6... Na6 (6... Nc6 7. e5 dxe5 8. fxe5 Nh5 9. Be3 Bg4 10. Be2 f6 11. exf6 exf6 $10) (6... c5 { Open the center early, otherwise Black's position will be very cramped. } 7. dxc5 (7. d5) 7... dxc5 8. e5 Nd5 9. Nxd5 Qxd5 10. Qe2 Nc6 (10... Bf5) (10... Qc6) 11. Be4 Qd8 (11... Qd7)) 7. O-O c5 (7... Nb4) 8. d5 Bg4 (8... Rb8 9. Kh1 Bg4 10. h3 Bxf3 11. Rxf3 Nc7 12. a4 a6 13. a5 e6) (8... Nc7 9. a4) 9. Bc4 (9. h3 Bxf3 10. Rxf3 (10. Qxf3) 10... Nc7 11. a4) 9... Nc7 10. h3 Bxf3 11. Qxf3 a6 $14 12. a4 b6 13. Qd3 e6 14. dxe6 fxe6 *


