1. e4 d6 2. d4 Nf6 3. Nc3 g6 4. f4 { Austrian Attack. The idea is similar to the Grand Prix Attack in the Sicilian: Bring the knight to g5, and start an attack on the king side. } { [%cal Gg1f3,Gf3g5] } 4... Bg7 5. Nf3 (5. e5 Nfd7 6. Nf3 c5 7. exd6 O-O 8. Be3 exd6 9. Qd2 Nc6 10. O-O-O Qa5 11. Kb1 Nf6) (5. Bd3 O-O 6. Nf3 Na6 { [%cal Ga6c5,Gc7c5] } 7. O-O c5 8. d5) 5... c5 { Dragon Formation. Very similar to the Sicilian/Dragon, hence the name. } (5... O-O 6. Be3 { Kurajica Variation } (6. e5 { Austrian Attack/Unzicker Attack } 6... Nfd7 7. h4 { Unzicker Attack/Bronstein Variation } 7... c5 8. h5 cxd4 9. hxg6 (9. Qxd4 dxe5 10. Qf2 e4 (10... exf4) 11. Ng5 { [%cal Gg5h7,Gh1h7,Gg5e4] } (11. Nxe4))) (6. Bd3 { Weiss Variation } 6... Na6 7. O-O c5 8. d5 Bg4 9. Bc4 Nc7 10. h3 Bxf3 11. Qxf3 a6 12. a4 b6 13. Qd3 e6 14. dxe6 fxe6 15. Rd1 d5 16. exd5 exd5 17. Qf3 Qe7 18. Nxd5 Nfxd5 19. Bxd5+ Nxd5 20. Qxd5+ Kh8)) 6. Bb5+ Bd7 7. e5 Ng4 8. e6 fxe6 9. Ng5 Bxb5 10. Nxe6 Bxd4! 11. Nxd8 (11. Nxb5 Qa5+ 12. Qd2 Bf2+ 13. Kd1 Ne3+ 14. Ke2 Qxb5+ 15. Kxf2 Ng4+ 16. Kg3 Na6 17. Re1 (17. Kxg4 Qd7 18. Re1 Nc7 19. Qe2 Kf7 20. Qc4 Nxe6 21. Qd5 Kf6 { Raut, Cristian - Verduyn, Frederic, 0-1, Condom op 2nd, 2003, https://lichess.org/3iayTswR }) 17... Nh6 18. b3 Nf5+) 11... Bf2+ 12. Kd2 Be3+ 13. Ke1 Bf2+ *


