... e5?! { Kennedy Variation } 3. d5 { Kennedy Variation/Linksspringer Variation } (3. dxe5 Nxe5 (3... Bc5 { Kennedy Variation/Bielefelder Gambit }) (3... f6 { Kennedy Variation/Hammer Gambit }) (3... Qh4 { Kennedy Variation/Herford Gambit }) (3... d6 { Kennedy Variation/de Smet Gambit }) 4. Nf3 { Kennedy Variation/Paulsen Attack } (4. Nc3 { Kennedy Variation/Keres Attack }) (4. f4 Nc6 { Kennedy Variation/Riemann Defense } (4... Ng6 { Kennedy Variation/Main Line })) 4... Nxf3+ 5. Qxf3 Qf6 6. Qg3) 3... Nce7 { Every normal move is good for White now. } (3... Nb8) (3... Nb4) 4. Nf3 Ng6 5. h4 h5 6. Bg5 { [%cal Rf3e5] } 6... Nf6 (6... f6 7. Be3)) 3. Nc3 $10 { Scandinavian Variation/Bogoljubow Variation } (3. Be3 $15 { Hornung Gambit. Not good for White, but playable. } 3... dxe4 { Just take the pawn and have a good game. } 4. d5 { This gives White an interesting initiative in the center and a good lead in development. Still, it's questionable if this is compensation enough. The engine doesn't like it, but what does that mean in a Blitz game? } 4... Ne5 5. Nc3 (5. Qd4 { [%cal Rd4e4,Rd4e5] } 5... Ng4 6. Bc4 (6. Qxe4? N8f6 7. Qa4+ Bd7 8. Bb5 Nxe3 9. Bxd7+ Qxd7 10. Qxd7+ Kxd7 11. fxe3 Nxd5 { [%cal Gd5e3] } 12. Ke2)) (5. Bb5+) 5... Nf6 6. Bd4 Ng6) (3. exd5 Nb4 { Scandinavian Variation/Aachen Gambit } (3... Qxd5 { Scandinavian Variation/Exchange Variation } 4. Nc3 { Scandinavian Variation/Exchange Variation/Marshall Gambit })) (3. e5 { Scandinavian Variation/Advance Variation. This is the line you'll most likely encounter in Blitz and Rapid games. } 3... Bf5 (3... a6) 4. c3 (4. Nf3 e6 5. c3) 4... f6 5. f4 Nh6 6. Nf3) 3... dxe4 (3... a6 { Scandinavian Variation/Bogoljubow Variation/Brandics Gambit }) (3... g6 { Scandinavian Variation/Bogoljubow Variation/Erben Gambit }) (3... e5 { Scandinavian Variation/Bogoljubow Variation/Heinola-Deppe Gambit }) (3... Nf6 { Scandinavian Variation/Bogoljubow Variation/Vehre Variation }) 4. d5 Ne5 { Scandinavian Variation/Bogoljubow Variation/Nimzowitsch Gambit } (4... Nb8 5. f3 { Scandinavian Variation/Bogoljubow Variation/Richter Gambit }) 5. Bf4 Ng6 6. Bg3 f5 *


