1. e4 Nc6 2. Nf3 f5 { This is called Lean Variation but most people know it as Colorado Gambit. } 3. exf5 { Best move actually. Called Colorado Counter Accepted. Whatever Counter means. } (3. e5) (3. d3) (3. Nc3 fxe4 4. Nxe4 d5 5. Ng3 (5. Nc3) 5... e5 6. Bb5 Bg4 7. h3 Bxf3 8. Qxf3 Nf6 (8... Qd6) (8... Ne7) 9. Nh5 (9. O-O) (9. Bxc6+) (9. Qc3) 9... Kf7 10. Nxf6 gxf6 11. O-O) (3. Bc4? fxe4 4. Bxg8 Rxg8 (4... exf3 5. Bd5 fxg2 6. Bxg2 { Racz, Zoltan - Majzik, Levente, 1/2-1/2, HUN-chT2 9495, 2017, https://lichess.org/yTkaWbj6 }) 5. Ng5 d5 $17) 3... d5 { Be as aggressive as possible and go towards the center. } { [%cal Gc8f5] } 4. d4 (4. g4? { Some people try to hold that pawn. Yummy! } 4... h5 5. gxh5 { The only thing you can do with that pawn. } (5. Bb5) (5. g5) (5. h3? hxg4 { White's rook is hanging, they can't take back. } { [%cal Gh8h1] } 6. Ng5 Bxf5 7. hxg4 { Trading the rook for the very active bishop is the best move here! } (7. d4) 7... Rxh1 8. gxf5 e5 9. d3 (9. Ne6) (9. fxe6) 9... Qf6 10. Be3 Bc5)) 4... Bxf5 5. Bb5 e6 6. Ne5 Ne7 7. Qh5+ g6 8. Qh4 Bg7 (8... a6 { Levacic, Patrick - Brumen, Dinko, 1/2-1/2, Zagreb, 2017, https://lichess.org/P8AEykjy }) 9. Bg5 { [%cal Rg5e7] } 9... Qd6 { [%csl Gb4][%cal Gd6b4,Gb4e1,Gb4b5] } 10. O-O a6 11. Nxc6 Nxc6 12. Bxc6+ Qxc6 *


