... Kf7 29. Qa6 Rxc2+?! { (-1.86 → -1.23) Inaccuracy. Best move was Rxh6. } (29... Rxh6 30. Kb1 Qb8 31. Ne4 Ra7 32. Nd6+ Kf8 33. Qc8+ Qxc8 34. Nxc8 Rc7 35. Nd6 Nf3 36. Rg4) 30. Kb1 Rxh6 31. Ne4? { (-1.41 → -2.57) Mistake. Best move was Rc1. } (31. Rc1 Rxc1+ 32. Rxc1 Ne7 33. Qb7 Rh4 34. Ne4 Rh5 35. Nd6+ Kg8 36. Rc7 Ndc6 37. Rxc6 Nxc6) 31... Qc7 32. Nd6+?! { (-2.57 → -3.18) Inaccuracy. Best move was Rc1. } (32. Rc1 Rxc1+ 33. Rxc1 Qxe5 34. Re1 Qc7 35. Ng5+ Kf6 36. Nxe6 Qc2+ 37. Ka1 Qc6 38. Qxc6 Nxc6) 32... Nxd6 33. exd6?? { White resigns. } { (-3.05 → Mate in 4) Checkmate is now unavoidable. Best move was Rxd4. } (33. Rxd4 Re2 34. Ka1 Nf5 35. Rb4 Rxe5 36. Rxb5 Rxb5 37. Qxb5 Rh2 38. Rd1 Qf4 39. Qb7+ Kf6) 33... Rxb2+ 34. Ka1 Ra2+ 35. Kxa2 Qc2+ 36. Ka1 Nb3# 0-1


