1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Bc4 { The gambit. Note that e4 is hanging. Black can just take it and go into the complications, or decline. } { [%csl Be4] } 5... Nxe4 { Accepted! } (5... e6 { Declined. Meh! } 6. Nc3 { Transposes into the Sozin Attack }) (5... a6 { Black wants to play a Najdorf. } 6. O-O { Black has equalized already, and there are many good moves, like e5, e6, or g6. } (6. Nc3 { Najdorf, Lipnitsky Attack } 6... e6) 6... Nxe4?! { is none of them } 7. Bxf7+! Kxf7 8. Qh5+ g6 9. Qd5+ e6 10. Qxe4) 6. Qh5 { And here Black has only one good move. Everything else will be punished with fire. } { [%cal Gc4f7,Gh5f7] } 6... e6 (6... d5? 7. Bxd5 g6 8. Qe5 { [%cal Ge5h8,Ge5e4] } 8... Nf6 9. Nb5 { [%cal Gb5c7,Ge5c7] } 9... Na6 10. Bf3 Bg7 11. N1c3 O-O 12. O-O $14) (6... g6?? 7. Qd5 { [%cal Gd5e4,Gd5f7] } 7... e6 8. Qxe4 $18 { White is a piece up. Note that d5 make things only worse: } 8... d5? 9. Bb5+ Bd7 10. Qe5 { [%cal Ge5h8] } 10... Rg8 $18) 7. Bb5+ Nd7 { Only move again. } (7... Bd7?! 8. Nxe6 { [%cal Ge6d8] } 8... Qf6 { [%cal Rf6f2,Re4f2] } (8... Qe7 9. Bxd7+ Nxd7 10. Nc7+! Kd8 11. Nd5 Qe5 (11... Ng3+ 12. Nxe7 Nxh5 13. Nd5 Nhf6 14. Nbc3 $14)) 9. Nf4 { [%cal Bc1f4] } 9... g5 10. Bd3 $14) (7... Nc6?? 8. Nxc6 bxc6 9. Bxc6+ Bd7 10. Bxe4 $18 { Piece up. Winning. }) 8. Nxe6! { White gets the pawn back. } { [%cal Ge6d8,Bh5e8] } 8... Nf6 { White has two equally good continuations: Bxd7 and Nxd8. } { [%cal Rf6h5,Ge6d8] } (8... Qa5+?? { A common blunder online. } 9. Nc3 d5 10. Qxd5) 9. Bxd7+ (9. Nxd8 Nxh5 10. Bxd7+ { [%csl Gf7][%cal Gd8f7] } 10... Bxd7 (10... Kxd7? 11. Nxf7 $16) 11. Nxb7 Bc6 { Transposes to the main line. }) 9... Bxd7 (9... Qxd7?! 10. Nxf8 Kxf8 11. Qe2 $14 { White is a bit better: Intact pawn structure, and the king can still castle. }) 10. Nxd8 Nxh5 11. Nxb7 Bc6 { [%cal Rc6b7,Rc6g2] } 12. Na5 Bxg2 13. Rg1 Be4 { [%cal Re4c2] } 14. Nc3 Bxc2 15. Be3 Be7 16. Rc1 *


