1. Nf3 { I played this with the intention to get a reversed Grünfeld on the board. } { [%clk 0:15:00] } 1... c5 { Looks like my opponent rather wanted to play a Sicilian. } { [%clk 0:15:00] } 2. g3 { I declined that invitation. Of course. } { [%clk 0:14:57] } 2... Nc6 { This is actually the Main move in this position! } { [%clk 0:14:57] } 3. Bg2 { Just wait for d5 … } { [%clk 0:14:55] } 3... d5 { … and there it is. } { [%clk 0:14:55] } (3... e5 { was possible, and then I wouldn't have any good plan besides playing a KIA with a space disadvantage. }) 4. d4 { [%clk 0:14:53] } 4... cxd4 { [%clk 0:14:48] } 5. Nxd4 { [%clk 0:14:53] } 5... Nf6 { [%clk 0:14:45] } 6. O-O { [%clk 0:14:48] } 6... e5 { [%clk 0:14:36] } 7. Nxc6 { Now we have the Exchange Variation/Modern Variation reversed. Lichess is still calling it "King's Indian Attack/French Variation". } { [%clk 0:14:47] } 7... bxc6 { [%clk 0:14:35] } 8. c4 { [%cal Gg2c6] [%clk 0:14:45] } 8... Be6 { [%clk 0:14:25] } 9. Nc3 { [%clk 0:14:42] } (9. Bg5 { Maybe I should have done this, before my opponent could play h6? } 9... Rc8 10. Qa4 Qd7 11. Bxf6 gxf6 { Not so clear. White has the better pawn structure, and the king is quite safe. But Black has the bishop pair, and the open g-file can become very useful. } 12. e3 d4 13. exd4 exd4 14. Nd2 (14. c5 Bxc5 15. Rc1 Qe7 16. Bxc6+ Kf8 17. Nd2 Kg7 $13 { Nakamura, Hi - Anand, V., 1/2-1/2, 5th Zurich CC 2016, https://lichess.org/dJ34SZSW }) 14... c5 15. Qa3 (15. Qb3 Bg7 16. Qd3 O-O 17. f4 Bf5 18. Be4 Bxe4 19. Nxe4 Rfe8 { Efimenko, Z. - Mekhitarian, K., 1/2-1/2, 23rd Abu Dhabi Masters, 2016, https://lichess.org/h16XpyFz }) 15... Be7 16. Qd3 h5 17. Nf3 Rb8 18. b3 { Efimenko, Z. - Cornette, M., 1/2-1/2, Bundesliga 2016-17, 2017, https://lichess.org/BlisvN1M }) (9. Qa4) 9... h6 { Prevents Bg5, but now I get an important tempo: } { [%clk 0:14:09] } 10. Qa4 { [%clk 0:14:27] } (10. cxd5 cxd5 11. Qa4+ Bd7 12. Qa6 { [%cal Gc3d5,Gg2d5] } 12... Bc8 13. Qb5+ Bd7 14. Qb7 { Mojzis, Jaroslav - Suran, Jan, 0-1, CZE-chT 9798, 1997, https://lichess.org/JyccWrCk } { [%cal Gb7a8] }) 10... Qd7 { [%clk 0:12:32] } (10... Bd7 { Transposes to the 10.cxd5 line. } 11. cxd5 cxd5 12. Qa6 Bc8 13. Qb5+) 11. Rd1?! { This gives Black time to play Rd8. I shouldn't allow that. } { [%clk 0:14:23] } (11. cxd5! cxd5 12. Qxd7+ Kxd7 $14) 11... Be7?! { I guess my opponent wanted to castle. But he didn't have time for that, because now I win a pawn. } { Inaccuracy. Best move was Rd8. } { [%clk 0:12:12] } (11... Rd8 12. b3 Bc5 13. Ba3 Bxa3 14. Qxa3 Qe7 15. Qa5 e4 16. cxd5 cxd5 17. Nb5 Rd7 18. Nd4) 12. cxd5 { [%clk 0:13:36] } 12... Nxd5 { [%clk 0:11:52] } 13. Nxd5 { [%clk 0:13:13] } 13... Bxd5?? { Blunder. Best move was cxd5. } { [%clk 0:11:46] } (13... cxd5 14. Qxd7+ Kxd7 15. Bxd5 Bxd5 16. Rxd5+ Ke6 17. e4 a5 18. Be3 a4 19. f4 exf4 20. gxf4) 14. Bxd5?? { I was so focused on that pawn, that I missed the pin on the queen. e4 would have ended the game immediately. } { Blunder. Best move was e4. } { [%clk 0:13:08] } (14. e4 Rd8 15. Be3 O-O 16. exd5 cxd5 17. Qxd7 Rxd7 18. Rxd5 Rxd5 19. Bxd5 Rd8 20. Bb3 a6) 14... cxd5 { [%clk 0:11:35] } 15. Qxd7+ { [%clk 0:13:06] } 15... Kxd7 { [%clk 0:11:32] } 16. Rxd5+ { [%clk 0:13:04] } 16... Ke6 { [%clk 0:11:21] } 17. e4 { [%clk 0:12:55] } 17... Rad8 { [%clk 0:11:12] } 18. Be3 { So I traded my e-pawn for Black's a-pawn. } { [%clk 0:12:25] } (18. Rxd8 { was also possible, but I liked the idea to get two connected passed pawns. } { [%csl Ga2,Gb2] } 18... Rxd8 19. Be3) 18... Rxd5 { [%clk 0:11:08] } 19. exd5+ { [%clk 0:12:25] } 19... Kxd5 { [%clk 0:11:07] } 20. Bxa7 { [%clk 0:12:16] } 20... Bc5?! { Inaccuracy. Best move was Ra8. } { [%clk 0:11:00] } (20... Ra8 21. Be3 f5 22. Kg2 f4 23. gxf4 exf4 24. Rd1+ Ke4 25. Bd4 f3+ 26. Kg3 Bd6+ 27. Kh3) 21. Bxc5 { [%clk 0:11:44] } 21... Kxc5 { [%clk 0:10:58] } 22. Rc1+ { [%clk 0:11:40] } 22... Kd4?! { The engine thinks I should go for pawns on the king side. But I thought, I could stop them easily and promote my pawns on the queen side in the mean time. } { Inaccuracy. Best move was Kd6. } { [%cal Gb2b4,Ga2a4] [%clk 0:10:54] } (22... Kd6 23. Kf1 g5 24. Ke2 Kd5 25. Rc7 Rb8 26. b3 Ra8 27. Rd7+ Kc5 28. a4 Rb8 29. Rxf7) 23. Kf1?! { Inaccuracy. Best move was Rc7. } { [%clk 0:11:36] } (23. Rc7) 23... Rb8 { [%clk 0:10:48] } 24. Rc2 { [%clk 0:11:25] } 24... Kd3 { [%clk 0:10:40] } 25. Re2 { [%clk 0:11:22] } 25... f6 { [%clk 0:10:21] } 26. Ke1 { [%clk 0:11:21] } 26... Rc8 { [%clk 0:09:24] } 27. Rd2+ { [%clk 0:11:18] } (27. Re3+ Kc2) 27... Ke4 { [%clk 0:09:23] } 28. Ke2 { [%clk 0:11:08] } 28... g5?! { Inaccuracy. Best move was Rc1. } { [%clk 0:08:39] } (28... Rc1 29. f3+ Kf5 30. Kd3 Rf1 31. b4 Rxf3+ 32. Kc4 e4 33. Rb2 e3 34. Kd3 Ke6 35. b5) 29. f3+?! { Inaccuracy. Best move was b4. } { [%clk 0:11:03] } (29. b4 Rb8 30. f3+ Kf5 31. Rb2 Ke6 32. a4 Kd5 33. Kd3 Ra8 34. a5 h5 35. Kc3 f5) 29... Kf5 { [%clk 0:08:32] } 30. a4?! { Inaccuracy. Best move was b4. } { [%clk 0:10:51] } (30. b4 Rc1 31. Kd3 Rb1 32. Kc4 Rc1+ 33. Kb3 Rf1 34. b5 Rxf3+ 35. Kb4 e4 36. Re2 Ke5) 30... e4?! { Inaccuracy. Best move was Rb8. } { [%clk 0:08:16] } (30... Rb8 31. a5) 31. Rd5+ { 1-0 Black resigns. } { [%clk 0:10:36] } (31. a5 exf3+ 32. Kxf3) 1-0


