1. d4 g6 2. c4 Bg7 3. Nc3 c5 4. d5 Bxc3+ 5. bxc3 f5 6. e3?! $17 { Opens the field for the white bishop, but blocks the black one. } 6... d6 7. Bd3 { Prepare e4. } (7. Be2 Nd7 8. f3 Ngf6 9. Nh3 O-O 10. O-O Ne5 { [%cal Gc8d7] }) 7... Nf6 8. Ne2 (8. Nf3 Nbd7 9. Qe2 Ne4 { [%cal Ge4c3] } 10. Qc2 Ndf6 11. O-O e5 12. dxe6 Bxe6) 8... e5 9. dxe6 Bxe6 10. O-O Nc6 11. Ng3 (11. Nf4 Bf7 { g5 is an option now to kick the knight away }) 11... O-O 12. Qe2 { Preparing e4 again. } (12. e4 { Open diagonale for the bishop on c1. } 12... fxe4 13. Nxe4 Nxe4 14. Bxe4 Bxc4 { Pawn sacrifice for White. } 15. Bd5+ Bxd5 16. Qxd5+ Kh8! 17. c4 Qf6 18. Rb1 Rae8 19. Bb2 (19. Rxb7?? { TRAP } 19... Qxf2+! 20. Rxf2 Re1+ 21. Rf1 Rfxf1#) 19... Nd4! 20. Qxb7 (20. Rbd1?? Ne2+ 21. Kh1 Qxb2) 20... Re2 21. f3) 12... Ng4 { Threat: Qh4 or Nge5. } 13. e4?! f4 14. Nh1 (14. Nf5 Nge5 15. Nh6+ Kg7 { Now the knight is trapped, the light square bishop attacked, and f3 opens the white position. }) 14... Qh4 15. h3 f3 16. gxf3 Nh2 { "Attraction sacrifice" } 17. f4 Bxh3 18. f3 Bxf1 19. Qxh2 Qxh2+ 20. Kxh2 Bxd3 21. Nf2 Bxc4 22. a3 d5 23. Be3 b6 *


