1. e4 c5 2. c3 d5 { This is a line with some forced moves. Easy to learn. } 3. exd5 Qxd5 (3... Nf6 4. Qa4+ Nbd7 5. c4) 4. d4 Nf6 (4... Nc6 5. Nf3 Bg4 6. Be2 cxd4 7. cxd4 e6 8. Nc3 Qa5 9. O-O Nf6) (4... cxd4 5. cxd4 (5. Nf3) 5... Nc6 6. Nf3 e5 7. Nc3 Bb4 8. Bd2 Bxc3 9. Bxc3 e4 10. Ne5 Nxe5 11. dxe5 Ne7 12. Qa4+ (12. Be2) (12. g3 { Israeli chess player Yochanan Afek has played this three times. 2 wins, 1 draw. } 12... O-O (12... e3!?) (12... Bf5) 13. Bg2 Bf5 14. O-O Rad8 $146 { Forcing White either to trade queens or to leave the d-file.
Novelty. } (14... Rfd8 { Afek - Plantet, 1999, 1-0 }) (14... Rac8 { Afek -Potze, 20016, 1-0 }) 15. Qe2 { [%cal Ge2e4,Gg2e4] } 15... Qd3 { The point is that Black can't really lose the grip on e4. } { [%csl Be4] } 16. Rfe1 $14)) 5. Nf3 Bg4 (5... e6) (5... Nc6) (5... cxd4 6. cxd4) *


