1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nf6 { C42 Petrov's Defense } 3. d4 { C43 Russian Game/Modern Attack. Here, Black has to make the first decision: take e4 or d4? } 3... Nxe4 { Modern Attack/Symmetrical Variation. The Main move. And now White has also a choice: } (3... d6?! { Transposition to C41 Philidor Defense/Nimzowitsch Variation. Not recommended, too passive. }) (3... d5?! { Symmetrical Variation. Not recommended. The basic problem with all symmetrical lines is that they are better for the side with the tempo advantage, and that is usually White. } 4. exd5 (4. Nxe5 Nxe4 5. Qf3 { [%cal Ge5f7,Gf3f7] }) (4. dxe5 Nxe4) 4... exd4 5. Bb5+ (5. Qxd4 Qxd5) 5... c6 6. dxc6 bxc6 (6... Qe7+ 7. Be2 Nxc6 8. Nxd4) (6... Nxc6 7. Nxd4) (6... Qa5+ 7. Nc3 bxc6 8. Nxd4 cxb5 9. Qf3 { [%cal Gf3a8] } 9... b4) 7. Be2 { The two hanging pawns aren't easy to defend, and Black can't even make use of the open e- and b-files . } { [%csl Gd4,Gc6][%cal Ge8e3,Gb8b3] }) (3... exd4 4. e5 (4. Bc4 { Transposition to Bishop's Opening/Urusov Gambit } 4... Nxe4 5. Qxd4 Nf6 6. Nc3 Be7 7. Bg5 c6 { [%csl Bd5,Bb5] } 8. O-O-O d5 9. Rhe1) 4... Ne4 5. Qxd4 { Modern Attack/Center Attack } { [%cal Gd4e4] } 5... d5 6. exd6 Nxd6 7. Nc3 Nc6 8. Qf4) 4. Bd3 { Modern Attack/Center Variation. Main move. } (4. Nxe5 d6 (4... d5) 5. Nf3 (5. Nd3?!) 5... d5 (5... Be7) (5... Bg4) (5... Bf5) (5... Nc6) 6. Bd3 (6. h3) 6... Nc6 (6... Bd6) (6... Be7) 7. O-O (7. Qe2) (7. Nc3) 7... Be7 (7... Bg4) 8. c4 (8. Nbd2 Nd6 9. c3 Bf5) 8... Nb4 (8... Nf6) 9. Be2 O-O 10. Nc3 Bf5 11. a3 Nxc3 12. bxc3 Nc6 13. Re1 Re8 14. cxd5 Qxd5 15. Bf4 Rac8 16. Bd3 Qd7 17. Rb1 b6 18. d5 Bxd3 19. Qxd3 Bxa3 20. Ng5 { [%cal Gd3h7,Gg5h7] } 20... g6 21. Ne4 Qf5 22. Bxc7 Rxc7 23. Nf6+ Qxf6 24. Rxe8+ Kg7 25. dxc6 Bc5 $14 26. Rb2 Rxc6) (4. Qe2 d5 5. Nbd2) (4. dxe5?! { This gives up the control over c5 and opens a very sharp line, maybe the sharpest line possible: } { [%csl Bc5] } 4... Bc5 { [%cal Rc5f2,Re4f2] } (4... d5 { A rather slow variation. } 5. Nbd2 Nxd2 6. Qxd2 c5 7. Bd3) 5. Bc4 { [%cal Gc4f7,Rc5f2,Re4f2] } 5... Nxf2 { [%cal Rf2h1,Rf2d1] } 6. Bxf7+! Kxf7 (6... Kf8) 7. Qd5+ { [%cal Gd5f7,Gd5c5] } 7... Kg6 8. Qxc5 { [%cal Gc5f2] } 8... Nxh1 $13 { Stockfish 9 says, the position is completely equal }) 4... d5 (4... Nc6 { is also playable! } 5. Bxe4 d5 6. Bd3 (6. Nxe5 dxe4 (6... Nxe5?!) 7. Nxc6 bxc6 8. O-O Be7 9. Nc3 f5 10. d5 O-O) 6... e4!) (4... exd4 5. Bxe4 Nc6) 5. Nxe5 Nd7 (5... Bd6 6. O-O O-O 7. c4 c6 (7... Bxe5 8. dxe5 Nc6 9. cxd5 Qxd5 10. Qc2 Nb4 11. Bxe4 Nxc2 12. Bxd5 Bf5 13. g4 Bxg4 14. Be4 Nxa1 15. Bf4 f6 (15... f5) 16. Nc3 (16. Nd2) 16... fxe5 17. Bg3 Rad8 18. Rxa1) 8. Nc3 Nxc3 9. bxc3 dxc4 10. Nxc4 Bc7) 6. Nxd7 Bxd7 7. O-O Bd6 8. c4 c6 9. cxd5 cxd5 10. Nc3 Nxc3 11. bxc3 O-O 12. Qh5 g6 13. Qxd5 Qc7 14. Bh6 Rfd8 15. Qg5 Qxc3 16. Rfd1 Bf8 17. Bxf8 Rxf8 18. Rac1 *


