1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Nxe5 d6 4. Nxf7 { C42 Russian Game/Cochrane Gambit.
White has two pawns for the knight, and Black's king is a little bit weak. Still not enough compensation. } 4... Kxf7 5. d4 { Center Variation.
The e4-pawn is not really hanging, because Black can't take it. } (5. Nc3 c5 6. Bc4+ Be6 7. Bxe6+ Kxe6 8. d4 Kf7 (8... cxd4 9. Qxd4 Kf7 (9... Nc6? 10. Qc4+ Kd7 11. Bf4 { [%csl Gd1][%cal Ge1c1,Ga1d1] })) 9. dxc5 { [%cal Gd1d8] } 9... Na6 { [%csl Gc4] } (9... Nc6 10. O-O dxc5 11. Qe2 Qd6 (11... Qe8) (11... Nd4? 12. Qc4+ Ke8 13. Bg5 { Depasquale, Chris - Solomon, Stephen J, 1-0, Australian Masters, 1998, https://lichess.org/IuWOK3gk }))) (5. Bc4+ { Bishop Check Line } 5... d5 (5... Be6?! { Most common move online, but it allows White to equalize. } 6. Bxe6+ Kxe6 7. d4 Kf7)) 5... c5 (5... Nxe4? { This is the move White is hoping for. } 6. Qh5+ g6 (6... Kg8?? { Mate in 2! } 7. Qd5+ Be6 8. Qxe6# { See [fuxia - WM2018ru] https://lichess.org/xez1Fpvt }) (6... Ke7 7. Qe2 { Two very nice threads. } { [%cal Ge2e4,Gc1g5,Gg5e7] } 7... Ke8 8. Qxe4+ $16) 7. Qd5+ Kg7 8. Qxe4 $16 { Reinderman, Dimitri - Van der Sterren, Paul, 1-0, Lost Boys, 1999, https://lichess.org/N3Duzm2Q }) (5... g6) (5... Qe8?! 6. Nc3) (5... c6?! 6. Bd3) *


