1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. d3 { King's Indian Attack. White goes for a rather quiet and more positional game without too many exchanges. This doesn't challenge Black seriously.
Look at Vadim Zvjaginsev's games, he is playing this quite often. } 3... Nc6 4. g3 Bc5 5. Bg2 d6 (5... d5 { Black opens the position immediately. White should take, because otherwise Black will. } 6. exd5 Nxd5 7. O-O O-O) 6. O-O (6. Nc3) 6... O-O (6... Bg4) 7. c3 { [%cal Gb2b4] } (7. Nc3 { Transposes to the Four Knights Game. } 7... a6 8. h3) (7. Re1 { Not a good move here: It weakens f2. } 7... Ng4 8. Re2 { [%cal Rc6d4,Rf7f5] }) 7... a5 { [%csl Rb4][%cal Ra5b4] } *


