1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Nxe5 d6 4. Nf3 Nxe4 5. Nc3 { Nimzowitsch Attack. This is a similar idea as in the ➡ Stafford Gambit, but without losing a pawn. White wants to open the d-file and get a free diagonal to develop the bishop on the c-file. } 5... Nxc3 (5... Nf6 { Too passive. } 6. d4 Be7 7. Bd3 O-O 8. h3 Re8 9. O-O Nbd7 10. Re1 Nf8 11. d5 Ng6 (11... c6 12. Bf4 Bd7 13. Bc4 Ng6 14. Bg3 Rc8 15. dxc6 Bxc6 16. Bb3 d5 17. Qd3 Qb6 { Anand, Viswanathan - Carlsen, Magnus, 1/2-1/2, Tata Steel-A 75th, 2013, https://lichess.org/YO7GGsin }) 12. Nd4 (12. Bxg6 hxg6 13. Nd4 Bd7 { Muzychuk, Mariya - Vazquez Igarza, Renier, 0-1, Gibraltar Masters 11th, 2013, https://lichess.org/Np4a6tPC }) 12... Bd7 13. Be3 c6 14. Bf1 Bf8 15. a4 cxd5 { Karjakin, Sergey - Wang, Hao, 1/2-1/2, Moscow Aeroflot rapid final, 2013, https://lichess.org/t8RQBDed }) 6. dxc3 { [%cal Gd1d6,Gc1g5,Gf1b5] } (6. bxc3 { A very rare line. } 6... Be7 7. d4 O-O 8. Bd3 $10) 6... Be7 7. Be3 (7. Bf4 O-O 8. Qd2 Nd7 9. O-O-O { Opposite castling, meaning that both sides will try a pawn storm against the enemy's king. } 9... Nc5 10. Be3 Re8 11. Bc4 Be6 12. Bxe6 Nxe6 13. h4 Qd7 14. Qd3 { [%cal Gd3h7,Gf3g5,Gg5h7] } 14... Qc6 { [%csl Gg2][%cal Gc6g2] } 15. Qf5 Qc4 { [%cal Gc4a2] } 16. Kb1 g6 17. Qh3 h5 18. Nd2 Qg4 (18... Qe2 19. Rde1 Qg4 20. Qh2 (20. Qxg4 hxg4 21. f3 (21. h5) 21... gxf3 22. Nxf3 Bf6 23. g4 Ng7 24. h5 gxh5 25. gxh5 { Quesada Perez, Yuniesky - Naumann, Alexander, 1/2-1/2, Dresden ol (Men) 38th, 2008, https://lichess.org/jCvnnvFt }) 20... d5 21. f3 Qa4 22. g4 Bd6)) (7. Bc4 O-O) 7... Nc6 8. Qd2 Be6 9. O-O-O { White almost always castles long in this line. } 9... Qd7 10. Kb1 (10. h4 h6 11. a3 Bf6 (11... Rg8 12. Ng1!? { [%cal Gg1e2,Gf2f3,Gg2g4] })) 10... Bf6 11. h4 O-O-O { Black can castle short, but that's rare. White has four pawns on the queenside, so a pawn storm on that side is rather difficult. } 12. Nd4 Nxd4 13. Bxd4 Be5 14. Qe3 { [%cal Gd4a7] } (14. Be2) (14. f4 Bxd4 15. Qxd4 { [%cal Gd4a7,Gd4g7] } 15... c5 16. Qxg7 (16. Qf2 { Anand, Viswanathan - Gashimov, Vugar, 1/2-1/2, Amber-blindfold 20th, 2011, https://lichess.org/CfaTtiG1 })) 14... Qa4 { [%cal Re6a2,Ra4a2,Ga4a7] } (14... Bxd4?! { Loses a pawn. } 15. Qxd4 $14 { [%cal Gd4g7,Gd4a7] }) 15. b3 Qa5 (15... Bxd4 16. cxd4 (16. Rxd4 Qc6 17. Be2 Qc5 18. Bf3 h5 19. Re1 Rhe8 { Vidit, S. - Wei Yi, 1/2-1/2, China vs World Team 2018, https://lichess.org/aktR2YGf }) 16... Qa5 17. Qg5 Qf5 (17... Qxg5 { Gives White the open h-file. } 18. hxg5 { [%cal Gh1h5] }) 18. d5 { Heer, Machiel de - Sánchez Ródenas, Antonio, 1/2-1/2, Rochade-25/TT, 2014, https://lichess.org/1vob1lWn }) 16. Bxe5 dxe5 17. Be2 { The black queen is a bit overworked, so either f6 or Kb8 should be played. } { [%cal Ga5a7,Ga5e5] } 17... f6 (17... Kb8 18. Kb2 f6) 18. Qg3 { [%cal Gg3g7] } *


