1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Nxe5 d6 4. Nd3 { The idea here is to bring the knight to f4. } { [%cal Rd3f4] } 4... Nxe4 5. Qe2 Qe7 6. Nf4 (6. Nc3 Nf6 (6... Nc5) (6... Nxc3 7. dxc3 Bg4 (7... Qxe2+ 8. Bxe2 Be7 9. Be3 O-O 10. O-O-O $14 { This is very equal, White is just a bit better developed. The opposite castling is a recipe for a good fighting game. }) 8. f3 Qxe2+ 9. Bxe2 Bd7)) *


