{ The Bishop's Opening with 2.Bc4 is one of these extremely flexible openings, similar to 2.Nf3. This opening will often transpose into other openings, but it can also be played in unique, fresh ways that don't require much theory. }
1. e4 e5 2. Bc4 { White attacks Black's weakest pawn. The strategic idea is not to block f3 with a piece, so that the queen can move there quickly and keep the pressure on that pawn. After d3, f4 is sometimes played to weaken Black's king side further. } { [%csl Gf3,Bf4][%cal Gc4f7,Gd1f3,Gf3f7,Bf2f4,Bc1f4] } *


