{ The main line here follows the most common moves according to the database. This is by no means a recommendation or even the best way to play this. }
1. e4 e5 2. Bc4 { C23 Bishop's Opening } 2... Nf6 { C24 Bishop's Opening, Berlin Defense } (2... Nc6 3. Nf3 { C50 Italian Game } (3. Nc3 Nf6 { C28 Vienna Game: Stanley Variation, Three Knights Variation } 4. d3 { C28 Bishop's Opening: Vienna Hybrid } 4... Na5 5. Nge2 Nxc4 6. dxc4 Bc5) (3. d3 Nf6 4. Nf3 { C 55 Italian Game: Two Knights Defense (→ https://lichess.org/study/9cAiplbq ), Modern Bishop's Opening. We are in the main line again, see move 4 there. }) (3. c3 Nf6 4. Qe2 Bc5 5. d3 h6) (3. f4 Nf6 4. Nf3 exf4 5. Nc3 Bb4 6. O-O O-O) (3. a3 Nf6 4. d3 Bc5 5. Nc3 d6 6. Na4 Bb6) (3. Qf3 Nf6 4. Ne2 Na5 5. d3 c6) (3. Qh5 g6 4. Qf3 Nf6 5. Ne2 Bg7) 3... Bc5 { C50 Giuoco Piano } (3... Nf6 { C55 Italian Game: Two Knights Defense (→ https://lichess.org/study/9cAiplbq ) } 4. d3 { C 55 Italian Game: Two Knights Defense (→ https://lichess.org/study/9cAiplbq ), Modern Bishop's Opening. See main line }) (3... Be7 { C50 Italian Game: Hungarian Defense } 4. d4 d6 5. dxe5 dxe5 6. Qxd8+ Bxd8) (3... d6 { C50 Italian Game } 4. c3 g6 5. d4 Bg7 6. O-O) 4. c3 { C53 Italian Game: Classical Variation #2 } 4... Nf6 5. d3 { C53 Italian Game: Classical Variation, Giuoco Pianissimo } 5... d6 6. Bb3 a6) (2... d5 { C23 Bishop's Opening: Khan Gambit } 3. exd5 Nf6 4. Nc3) (2... Bc5 3. b4 { C23 Bishop's Opening: McDonnell Gambit } 3... Bxb4 4. c3 { C23 Bishop's Opening: McDonnell Gambit, La Bourdonnais-Denker Gambit } 4... Ba5 5. Nf3 Nc6) (2... d6 3. Nf3 { C41 Philidor Defense #3 } 3... Be7 4. d4 exd4 5. Nxd4 Nf6 6. Nc3 { [%cal Rb8c6,Rc8d7] } 6... O-O $10) (2... c6 { C23 Bishop's Opening: Philidor Counterattack } 3. d4 d5 4. exd5 cxd5 5. Bb5+ Bd7 6. Bxd7+ Nxd7 7. dxe5 Nxe5 { Black has an IQP but is slightly better developed. } { [%csl Rd5] }) 3. d3 (3. d4 { C24 Bishop's Opening: Ponziani Gambit } 3... exd4 (3... Nxe4? 4. dxe5 { [%cal Gd1d5,Gd5f7,Bc4f7,Re8f7] } 4... c6 5. Bxf7+ Kxf7 6. Qf3+ Nf6 7. exf6 Qxf6) 4. Nf3 { C24 Bishop's Opening: Urusov Gambit. White offers the pawn on e4 in this gambit. https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dxUuueHFfFs } { [%csl Ge4][%cal Gf3d4] } (4. e5? { This is good for Black, no matter what White does now. } 4... d5 5. exd6 (5. Bb5+ Nfd7 (5... Bd7 6. exf6 (6. Bxd7+ Nfxd7 7. Qxd4 Nc6 { [%csl Ge5][%cal Gd7e5,Gc6e5,Gc6d4] }) 6... Bxb5 7. Qxd4 Qxf6 8. Qxf6 gxf6 9. Nc3 Bc6 $15) 6. Qxd4 c6 7. Be2)) 4... Nc6 { C44 Scotch Game: Scotch Gambit, Dubois Reti Defense. } (4... d5 { Decline the gambit. } 5. exd5 Bb4+ 6. c3 Qe7+ 7. Be2 dxc3 8. bxc3 (8. Nxc3 O-O) 8... Bd6 $10) (4... Nxe4 { Accept the gambit. } 5. Qxd4 Nf6 $15 { White will continue with Nc3, Bg5, Qh4, 0-0-0, and usually intends to meet ...0-0 and ...h6 with the piece sacrifice Bxh6, exposing the black king. Black has a solid position with no clear weaknesses but White has attacking chances and piece activity as compensation for the pawn. } (5... Nd6?! 6. O-O $16 { +1.4 White has a good attack now. }) (5... Nc5 $146 { Interesting line, not in the database. } 6. O-O Nc6 7. Re1+ Ne6 8. Qd3 Bb4 $10)) (4... Bb4+ 5. c3 dxc3 6. bxc3 Bc5 7. e5 d5 8. exf6 dxc4 9. Qxd8+ Kxd8 10. fxg7 Re8+ 11. Be3 Bxe3 12. fxe3 Rg8 13. Na3 { [%cal Ga3c4] } 13... c6 14. Nxc4 Kc7!? { [%csl Rd6] } 15. Nd4 Rxg7 { [%cal Rg7g2] } 16. Rf1 { [%cal Gc4e5,Ge5f7] } 16... Nd7 { [%cal Rd7e5] } 17. g3) 5. O-O { C55 Italian Game: Scotch Gambit } 5... Nxe4 { C55 Italian Game: Scotch Gambit, Double Gambit Accepted } 6. Re1 d5 7. Bxd5! Qxd5 8. Nc3!) 3... Nc6 4. Nf3 { C 55 Italian Game: Two Knights Defense (→ https://lichess.org/study/9cAiplbq ), Modern Bishop's Opening } 4... Be7 5. O-O O-O 6. Re1 d6 7. a4 Na5 8. Ba2 c5 9. c3 Nc6 10. Nbd2 Be6 11. Nc4 h6 12. Bd2 a6 13. b4 b5 14. Ne3 Bxa2 15. Rxa2 cxb4 16. axb5 axb5 17. Rxa8 Qxa8 18. cxb4 d5 19. exd5 Nxb4 20. Nf5 Nbxd5 21. Rxe5 Re8 22. Nxe7+ Rxe7 23. Rxe7 Nxe7 24. Qb3 Qd5 25. Qxd5 Nfxd5 { Swathi, Ghate - Mohota, Nisha | ½-½ | https://lichess.org/XIaNo7aP } *


