1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 { E10 Indian Game: Anti-Nimzo-Indian } (3. Nc3 { Main move online. This transposes the game to a Nimzo-Indian.
In the following line White's moves are taken from the lichess online database, Black's moves from the engine evaluation. In other words: It's a recipe against the most common responses. } 3... Bb4 (3... b6 { A rare attempt to stick to the QID set up. It's technically still a Nimzo though. The engine says this is good for White. } 4. e4 Bb7 5. Bd3 Bb4 6. f3 c5 7. d5) 4. Qc2 O-O 5. a3 Bxc3+ 6. Qxc3 b6 { Nimzo-Indian/Keres Defense } 7. Bg5 h6 8. Bh4 Bb7 9. e3 d6 10. Ne2 Nbd7 11. Qc2 Qe7 $10) 3... b6 { E10 Queen's Indian Defense } 4. g3 { E15 Fianchetto Variation } (4. Nc3 { Kasparov Variation } 4... Bb7 5. a3 { Kasparov-Petrosian Variation } (5. Bg5 h6 6. Bh4 Bb4 { Kasparov Variation/General } (6... g5 7. Bg3 Nh5 { Kasparov Variation/Botvinnik Attack })) 5... Be7 { Kasparov-Petrosian Variation/Marco Defense } (5... d5 { Kasparov-Petrosian Variation/Main Line } 6. cxd5 exd5 { Kasparov-Petrosian Variation/Classical Variation } (6... Nxd5 { Kasparov-Petrosian Variation/Modern Variation } 7. Bd2 { Kasparov-Petrosian Variation/Romanishin Attack } (7. e3 { Kasparov-Petrosian Variation/Petrosian Attack }) (7. e4 { Kasparov-Petrosian Variation/Polovodin Gambit }) (7. Qa4+ { Kasparov-Petrosian Variation/Rashkovsky Attack }) (7. Qc2 { Kasparov-Petrosian Variation/Kasparov Attack }))) (5... g6 { Kasparov-Petrosian Variation/Hedgehog Variation }) (5... Ne4 { Kasparov-Petrosian Variation/Andersson Variation })) (4. a3 { Petrosian Variation } 4... Ba6 5. Qc2 Bb7 { Petrosian Variation/Farago Defense }) (4. Bf4 { Miles Variation }) (4. e3 { Spassky System }) 4... Ba6 { Fianchetto Variation/Nimzowitsch Variation } { [%cal Ga6c4] } (4... Bb7 { Fianchetto Traditional } 5. Bg2 Bb4+ { Capablanca Variation } (5... Be7 { Traditional Variation } 6. Nc3 { Anti-Queen's Indian System } (6. O-O { Classical Variation } 6... O-O 7. b3 { Euwe Variation } (7. d5 exd5 8. Nd4 { Classical Variation/Taimanov Gambit } (8. Nh4 { Classical Variation/Polugayevsky Gambit } { [%cal Gh4f5] } 8... c6 9. cxd5 Nxd5 10. Nf5 Nc7 11. e4 d5)) (7. Nc3 { Classical Variation/Traditional Variation } 7... d5 { Classical Variation/Traditional Variation/Nimzowitsch Line } (7... Na6 { Classical Variation/Tiviakov Defense }) (7... Ne4 8. Qc2 Nxc3 9. Qxc3 { Classical Variation/Traditional Variation/Main Line })) (7. Re1 { Fianchetto Variation/Kramnik Variation })) 6... Ne4 7. Bd2 { Opocensky Variation }) (5... c5 { Fianchetto Variation/Saemisch Variation } 6. d5 exd5 7. Nh4 { Fianchetto Variation/Rubinstein Variation }) 6. Bd2 a5 { Yates Variation } (6... Be7 { Riumin Variation })) 5. b3 { Fianchetto Variation/Nimzowitsch Variation/Quiet Line } (5. Qa4 { Fianchetto Variation/Nimzowitsch Variation/Nimzowitsch Attack }) (5. Qb3 { Fianchetto Variation/Nimzowitsch Variation/Timman's Line }) (5. e3 d5) 5... Bb4+ { Fianchetto Variation/Nimzowitsch Variation/Check Variation } 6. Bd2 Be7 { Fianchetto Variation/Nimzowitsch Variation/Check Variation/Intermezzo Line } (6... Qe7 { Fianchetto Variation/Nimzowitsch Variation/Check Variation/Modern Line }) 7. Bg2 c6 { [%cal Gd7d5] } 8. Bc3 d5 9. Ne5 Nfd7 10. Nxd7 Nxd7 11. Nd2 O-O 12. O-O Rc8 *


