1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 b6 { E10 Queen's Indian Defense } 4. g3 { E15 Fianchetto Variation. Prepare to fianchetto the light-squared bishop. The standard response for Black through the 1970s was 4...Bb7 (see Fianchetto Traditional), but 4...Ba6 has since become the topical line. } { [%csl Rg2][%cal Rf1g2] } 4... Ba6 { Nimzowitsch Variation. White can defend the pawn at c4 with a piece by playing 5.Nbd2, 5.Qa4, 5.Qc2 or 5.Qb3, but these moves all diminish control of d4, making ...c7–c5 an effective reply for Black; therefore 5. b3 is White's most common response. } { [%csl Gc4,Rd4][%cal Ga6c4,Rb1d2,Rd1a4,Yd1c2,Bd1b3,Gc7c5] } 5. b3 { Quiet Line. Weakens the dark squares slightly, Black should take advantage of that with 5...Bb4+. } (5. Qa4 { Nimzowitsch Attack } 5... Bb7 { Main move. } (5... c5 6. Bg2 Bb7 7. dxc5 Bxc5) (5... c6 6. Nc3 d5 7. cxd5 exd5 $14) 6. Bg2 { Main move. } (6. Nc3 h6 7. Bg2 a5 8. Qb3 Bb4) 6... c5 { Main move. } (6... Qc8 { Preferred by SF8. } 7. Nc3 Ne4 8. Nxe4 Bxe4 9. O-O Be7 $10) (6... Be7 7. O-O O-O 8. Nc3) 7. dxc5 Bxc5 { Main move. Here Bf4, Nc3 and O-O can be played in any order by White, same for Black: O-O, Be7, h6. } (7... bxc5 8. O-O Be7 9. Nc3 O-O $10) (7... Qc8 8. Nc3 Bxc5 9. Bf4 Nh5 $10) (7... Bc6 8. Qc2 Be4!? { Qa4 Bc6 Qc2 Be4 … opportunity for a draw. } 9. Qd2 Bxc5 $10) 8. O-O O-O 9. Nc3 Be7 $10) (5. Qb3 { Timman's Line }) 5... Bb4+ { Check Variation } 6. Bd2 (6. Nbd2?? { This loses material: } 6... Bc3 7. Rb1 Bb7 { [%cal Gb7e4,Be4b1] } 8. Bh3 (8. Qc2 Bxd4 9. b4 a5 10. Rg1 { [%cal Re2e3] } 10... Nc6 { [%cal Gc6b4,Gc6a5] } 11. b5 Nb4 $15) (8. e3 Be4 9. Rb2 O-O 10. Bg2 Bxb2 $15) (8. Bb2 Ne4 9. Bg2 (9. Bc1 O-O 10. Bg2 Nxd2 11. Bxd2 Bxd4 $15) 9... Nxd2 { [%cal Gb7g2] } 10. Bxc3 Nxb1 $15) 8... Bxd4 { [%cal Gb7h1] } (8... Be4?! { Too early. Black now has to trade the two good bishops for a bad knight and a worse rook. } 9. O-O Bxd2 10. Bxd2 Bxb1 11. Qxb1 $10) 9. Nxd4 { The best move for White, according to SF8. I'm not so sure about that. } (9. e3?! Bc5 10. Bb2 O-O 11. O-O a5 $15) 9... Bxh1 10. f3 { Trap the bishop. } 10... Nc6 11. Bb2 Qe7) 6... Be7 { Check Variation/Intermezzo Line } (6... Qe7 { Check Variation/Modern Line }) 7. Bg2 *


