1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 f5 4. exf5?! { Some people don't know that this gambit should rather not be accepted. } 4... e4 5. Bxc6 (5. Qe2 { Pin the pawn. } 5... Qe7 { Unpin the pawn. } 6. Bxc6 { Otherwise the knight has to go back to g1. } 6... dxc6 { bxc6 should also be fine. But this structure allows Black to castle long into eternal safety. } { [%cal Ge8c8] } 7. Nd4 { [%cal Rd4f5] } 7... Qe5 { [%cal Gc8f5,Ge5f5,Ge5d4] } 8. c3 (8. Nf3 Qe7 { Invitation for a draw. } 9. Nd4 Qe5 { Draw by repetition. Not what we want. } (9... Nh6 10. Qh5+ Nf7 11. Ne2 Qc5 { [%cal Gc5c2,Gc5f5,Gc8f5] } 12. Ng3 { [%cal Rg3f5,Rh5f5] } 12... Qxc2 13. O-O Be7 14. Nc3 O-O 15. d3 Qxd3 16. Re1 Nd6 17. Bf4 Nxf5 18. Rad1 Nxg3 19. hxg3 Qc4 20. Rxe4 Qf7 $10)) 8... Bd6 { Stop white from castling short. } 9. Na3 (9. O-O?? Qxh2# { That's why white can't castle. }) 9... Bxa3 { Ruin white's structure. } 10. bxa3 Nf6 11. O-O Bxf5 12. d3 Bg6) 5... dxc6 6. Ne5 (6. Qe2 Bxf5 { best move } (6... Qe7) 7. Nc3 Qe7 8. Nd4 Bg6) 6... Bxf5 7. d4 (7. O-O Qd4 8. Ng4 Nf6 (8... O-O-O 9. Nc3 Nf6 { Narancic, Vlado - Todorovic, Goran N, 0-1, YUG-chT2, 1994, https://lichess.org/D9DWRQVc }) 9. Ne3 Bg6) 7... exd3 8. Nxd3 *


