1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 d5 4. Nf3 { Basic Catalan position. } 4... dxc4 { Open Catalan, because the h1-a8 diagonal is open. } 5. Bg2 (5. Qa4+? { Bad idea: } 5... Nbd7 { supports a later c5 } 6. Qxc4 a6 { prepares b5 and Bb7 } 7. Bg2 b5 8. Qc2 (8. Qc6 Rb8 9. Bf4 Nd5! { Black will still push the queen away via Bb7 and push c5 later. }) 8... Bb7 9. O-O c5 { Black is now ahead in development and saved his queen side, while White's queen has moved three times. }) 5... a6 { [%cal Gb7b5] } (5... c5 6. O-O Nc6 7. Ne5 Bd7 (7... Nxd4 8. e3 Nc6 9. Bxc6+ bxc6 10. Qxd8+ Kxd8 11. Nxf7+) (7... Nxe5 8. dxe5 Nd5 (8... Qxd1 9. Rxd1 Nd7 10. f4 Be7 11. Na3 Nb6 12. Nb5 { [%cal Gb5c7] } 12... Rb8 13. Nc7+ Kf8 14. a4) 9. Na3 { [%cal Ga3c4] } 9... c3 10. bxc3 Nxc3 11. Qc2 Nd5 12. Rd1 Bd7 13. Bxd5 exd5 14. Rxd5) 8. Na3 cxd4 9. Naxc4 Bc5 10. Qb3 O-O!? { Giving up b7 is the best option for Black! } (10... Rb8? 11. Bf4!) (10... Qc8 11. Bf4 O-O 12. Rac1 (12. Nd3 Be7 13. Nd6 Bxd6 14. Bxd6 Rd8 15. Rac1)) 11. Qxb7 { [%cal Gb7c6,Gg2c6] } 11... Nxe5 12. Nxe5 Rb8 13. Qf3) 6. O-O (6. a4? Nc6 { [%cal Gc6d4,Gd8d4] } 7. O-O Rb8 8. a5?! Bb4 { [%cal Gc6a5,Gb4a5,Gc6d4] }) *


