{ This chapter is based on https://chess24.com/en/learn/advanced/video/the-english-opening/1-c4-e6-2-g3-d5-3-bg2-nf6-4-nf3-be7-1 }
1. c4 e6 2. g3 d5 3. Bg2 Nf6 4. Nf3 Be7 { A14 English Opening/Neo-Catalan Declined } 5. O-O O-O 6. b3 (6. d4 { most testing move } 6... dxc4) 6... c5 (6... d4 { ambitious } 7. e3 Nc6 (7... c5 { Is better for Black. } 8. exd4 cxd4 9. Re1 Nc6 10. d3 { Leads to a reversed Modern Benoni. Black should try to prepare e5. } 10... Ne8 { Withe the idea of f6, e5. } { [%cal Rf7f6,Re6e5] } (10... Re8 11. Ne5 (11. Ba3) 11... Nxe5 12. Rxe5 Qc7 13. Re1 e5 14. Ba3 { Trades of minor pieces favor White. That makes it easier to advance on the queenside. } 14... Bf5 15. Bxe7 Rxe7 16. Na3 Rae8 17. b4) (10... Nd7 11. Na3 e5 12. Nc2 a5 13. a3 f6 14. Rb1 Nc5 15. b4 axb4 16. axb4 Na4 17. Bd2 Bf5? { is a serious mistake. } { [%cal Rf5d3] } (17... Bg4 { is better. }) 18. b5 Nb8 19. Nfxd4! { Piece sacrifice. } 19... exd4 20. Bxb7 Ra7 21. Bd5+ Kh8 22. Nxd4 { Nikolic, Predrag - Szabo, Krisztian, 1-0, EU-ch 10th, 2009, https://lichess.org/Ebklvct2 }) 11. a3 a5 12. Ne5 { White should try to trade one pair of minor pieces to help their coordination. } 12... Nxe5 13. Rxe5 f6 14. Re1 e5 15. f4 exf4 (15... Bd6 16. Qh5 { [%cal Gh5e5,Gf4e5,Ge1e5] } 16... g6 17. Qf3) 16. Bxf4) 8. exd4 Nxd4 9. Bb2 Bc5 10. Ne5 { Lubbe, N. - Skytte, R., 1-0, Sondex Cup GM/IM 1 2016, https://lichess.org/1sa5NIqD } { idea is to challenge the bishop on c5. } 10... c6 11. Nc3 Qd6 12. Re1 Ba3 13. Bxa3 Qxa3 14. Ne2 Rd8 15. Nxd4 Rxd4 16. Qc2 $14) (6... a5 7. Nc3! { [%cal Gc3a4] } (7. Bb2 a4) 7... c6 { Best for Black. } (7... d4 8. Nb5 Nc6 (8... c5 9. e3 Nc6 10. exd4 cxd4 11. Re1 $14 { [%csl Gb5] }) 9. e3 e5 10. Bb2 Bc5 11. exd4 exd4 12. Re1) 8. Bb2 (8. d4?! b6 9. Bb2 Ba6 $132) 8... Nbd7 (8... d4?! 9. Na4) 9. Qc2 b6 10. d3! { Important, because now White has e4 after Ba6. } 10... Ba6 11. e4) (6... c6 7. Bb2 Nbd7 8. d3 { [%cal Ge2e4] } (8. d4 { transposes to a closed Catalan. }) 8... b6 9. e4 Bb7 (9... dxe4?! 10. dxe4 Nxe4? 11. Nd4 { [%cal Gg2e4,Gd4c6,Be4c6] }) 10. e5) (6... b6 7. Bb2 Bb7 8. cxd5 { recommended by CS } (8. e3 { too complicated } { [%cal Gb1c3,Gd1e2] }) 8... Nxd5 (8... exd5 9. d4 Nbd7 10. Nc3 Re8 11. Rc1 c5 (11... a6 { Rerouting the knight to d3 is interesting in case of a6 and c6. } 12. Ne5 Bd6 13. Nd3 $10 { [%cal Ge2e3,Bc3e2,Bd1c2,Bd3e5,Rc1c7] }) (11... c6) 12. dxc5 bxc5 13. Ne1 { Hanging pawns setup } { [%cal Ge1d3,Gd3f4] } 13... Nb6 14. Nd3 $14) 9. d4 c5 10. dxc5 Bxc5 11. a3 a5 12. Nbd2 { Giri, A. - Kramnik, V., 1/2-1/2, 5th Norway Blitz 2017, https://lichess.org/QCOavkVy } { Yu Yangyi - Xu, Xiangyu, 1-0, CHN Team Men 2017, https://lichess.org/ZVyX3fuc }) *


