{ [%csl Gc3] }
1. Nf3 d5 2. c4 { A09 Réti Opening, named after Richard Réti (1889—1929)
https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/06/RichardReti.jpg } 2... d4 { Advance Variation } (2... dxc4 { Réti Accepted }) (2... c6 3. e3 (3. d4 { Slav Defense: Modern Line }) (3. b3 { Anglo-Slav Variation/Bogoljubow Variation.
This is now very close to a Nimzo-Larsen Attack. There is also a nice little trap after dxc4. } 3... Bg4 { Bogoljubow Variation II } (3... Nf6 4. Bb2 (4. g3 Bg4 { Torre System } (4... Bf5 { London Defensive System. Yes, a reversed London System. }) (4... d4 { Engine suggestion, rarely played. })) 4... Bg4 { Capablanca Variation } (4... Bf5 { New York System }) (4... g6 { Bled Variation }) (4... e6 5. g3 Be7 6. Bg2 O-O 7. O-O { Stonewall Line })) (3... dxc4 4. bxc4 e5! { A poisoned pawn. } 5. Nc3 (5. Nxe5?? Qd4! { Now White will lose a piece. } { [%csl Re5,Ra1][%cal Rd4a1,Rd4e5] }))) 3... Nf6 4. Nc3 e6 5. b3 Nbd7 6. Bb2) (2... b5? { Zilbermints Gambit }) (2... e6 { Transposition to English Opening/Agincourt Defense }) (2... Nf6?! { Transposition to A15 English Opening/Anglo-Indian Defense/Scandinavian Defense } 3. cxd5 Nxd5 4. e4 Nb6 5. d4) 3. e3 (3. Rg1 { Penguin Variation }) (3. d3?! { An attempt to play the reversed Benko. } 3... Nc6) (3. b4 c5 { Advance Variation/Michel Gambit } (3... f6)) (3. g3 c5 { Now we have a reversed Benoni with an extra tempo. } (3... Nc6 4. Bg2 e5 5. d3 Nf6 6. O-O a5 7. e3 Be7 (7... dxe3 8. Bxe3 Be7 9. Nc3 O-O 10. d4 exd4 11. Nxd4 Nxd4 12. Qxd4 c6 (12... Qxd4 13. Bxd4 c6 14. Rfe1 { Gustafsson, Jan - Bindrich, Falko, 1-0, GER-ch 82nd, 2011, https://lichess.org/YhPbgGhs })) (7... Bc5 8. exd4 Bxd4 9. Nxd4 Nxd4 10. Re1)) (3... g6 4. Bg2 Bg7 5. O-O) 4. Bg2 Nc6 5. O-O (5. d3) (5. e3) 5... e5 (5... Nf6) (5... g6) 6. d3 (6. e3) 6... Nf6 (6... Bd6 7. e3 Nge7 8. exd4 cxd4 (8... exd4?! 9. Nbd2))) 3... c5 (3... Nc6 { Main line } 4. exd4 Nxd4 5. Nxd4 Qxd4 6. Nc3 c6 7. d3) (3... dxe3 4. fxe3) (3... d3? 4. Qb3! { Prevents Bf5. } { [%csl Gb7][%cal Gb3d3,Gf1d3,Rc8f5,Gb3b7] } 4... Na6 { [%cal Ra6c5,Bc5b3,Bc5d3,Ra6b4] } 5. a3 { Prevents Nb4 } { [%cal Ga3b4] } (5. Qxd3?! Qxd3 6. Bxd3 Nb4 { [%cal Gb4c2,Gb4d3] } 7. Ke2 Nxd3 8. Kxd3 { White is still better here, but it's a position you probably don't want to go for. }) 5... Nf6 6. Qxd3) 4. b4 { Reversed Blumenfeld Gambit } *


[Event "Réti Opening: 1.Nf3 d5 2.c4: 2...dxc4 - Réti Accepted"]
