1. Nf3 d5 2. c4 Nf6?! { This is a rather dubious line. We just take the pawn here. } 3. cxd5 c6 { This gambit is one of Black's better options! } (3... Nxd5 { And here we have some options. One very aggressive is e4. } 4. e4 (4. d4 { This position is usually reached per Queen's Gambit Refused. See Najdorf - Ljubojevic, 1973 for an example: https://lichess.org/v9RTLQXa } 4... g6 (4... Bf5) (4... e6 5. e4 { Get a grip on the center. } 5... Nf6 { [%cal Rf6e4] } 6. Nc3 { [%cal Gc3e4,Rf6e4] } 6... c5) (4... Nc6 { This might get very sharp! } 5. e4 Nb6 (5... Nf6 6. Nc3 e6 (6... Bg4? 7. d5! Nb8 { The best move, surprisingly. } (7... Bxf3 8. gxf3! { The only move! } 8... Nb8 9. Qa4+ c6 10. Bf4 { [%cal Gd5d6] } 10... g6 11. Rd1 $16 { White is so much ahead in development that the pawn structure doesn't matter anymore. }) (7... Ne5? { This looks overwhelming. But … } 8. Nxe5! { We just give up the queen! } 8... Bxd1 9. Bb5+ Nd7 (9... c6 10. dxc6 { [%cal Gc6c7] } 10... a6 11. c7+ axb5 12. cxd8=Q+ Rxd8 13. Nxd1 Nxe4 14. Nc3 $18 { One piece up, and better developed. }) 10. Bxd7+ Qxd7 11. Nxd7 Kxd7 12. Nxd1 $18 { Still on piece up. }))))) 4... Nb6 (4... Nf6 { [%cal Rf6e4] } 5. Nc3 c5 (5... Nc6?! 6. d4 Bg4? 7. d5 Nb8 { Best move. A bit sad. } (7... Ne5?? 8. Nxe5! { Temporary queen sacrifice! } 8... Bxd1 9. Bb5+ Nd7 (9... c6?! 10. dxc6 a6 11. c7+ axb5 12. cxd8=Q+ Rxd8 13. Nxd1 Nxe4 14. Nc3 { Strikovic, Aleksa - Rodriguez Perez, Armiche Jose, 1-0, El Sauzal op 5th, 2004, https://lichess.org/Mz6KGfRt }) 10. Bxd7+ Qxd7 11. Nxd7 Kxd7 12. Nxd1)) 6. Bb5+ Bd7 7. e5 Bxb5 8. Nxb5) 5. d4 Bg4 (5... g6 6. h3 { [%csl Gg4][%cal Gh3g4,Rc8g4] } 6... Bg7 7. Nc3 O-O 8. Be2 Nc6 9. Be3 f5 10. exf5 (10. d5) (10. Qb3+ e6 (10... Kh8)))) (3... Qxd5 4. Nc3 Qa5 5. e4 { In contrast to the normal Scandinavian, White still has the e-pawn, and it should be pushed right away. } 5... e5 (5... e6) (5... Nc6 6. Bb5 $146 Bd7 7. d3)) 4. dxc6 Nxc6 5. g3 { With Black's two knights controlling the center already, we go for a fianchetto line. } 5... e5 6. Nc3 Bg4 7. Bg2 Be7 8. O-O O-O $14 *


