1. Nf3 d5 2. c4 d4 3. b4 c5 { Michel Gambit } (3... Nf6) (3... f6) 4. a3 (4. Bb2) (4. b5) (4. g3) (4. e3 { ➡ Reversed Blumenfeld }) (4. bxc5?! { Bad idea. Black gets a fast development, a strong center, and an initiative as compensation, and White cannot hold the extra pawn for long. } 4... Nc6 5. g3 e5 6. d3 (6. Qa4 Bd7 7. d3) 6... Bxc5 7. Bg2 h6 8. O-O Nf6 9. Ba3 Bxa3 10. Nxa3 O-O 11. Nd2 Qe7 12. Nc2 Bf5 13. Rb1 Rac8 14. Qc1 e4 15. Rb3 Rfe8 16. Re1 Qd7 17. Qb2 b6 18. dxe4 Nxe4 19. Nf3 Nc5 20. Nfxd4 Bxc2 21. Nxc2 Nxb3 22. axb3 Qd2 23. Qb1 Na5 24. e3 Qc3 25. Nd4 Qb4 26. Bd5 Rc7 27. Rd1 Nb7 28. Nb5 Rce7 29. Bxb7 Rxb7 30. Nd6 Rbb8 31. Nxe8 Rxe8 32. Rd5 g6 33. Qd3 Re7 34. Kg2 Re6 35. Rd8+ Kg7 36. Qd4+ Rf6 37. Rd7 a6 38. Rc7 Qd6 39. Rc8 Qe6 40. Rd8 Qc6+ 41. Rd5 Kh7 42. e4 Re6 43. h4 h5 44. b4 a5 45. b5 Qa8 46. f3 Re8 47. Qf6 Qb7 48. Rd6 Rb8 49. Qd4 Rf8 50. Rxb6 Qa7 51. c5 a4 52. Ra6 Qb7 53. Qxa4 Rd8 54. Qa2 Qe7 55. Ra7 { Kramnik, Vladimir - Tkachiev, Vladislav, 1-0, Wch Blitz 5th, 2009, https://lichess.org/1W4FLwvi }) *


