1. Nf3 d5 2. c4 d4 3. e3 { This is already an aggressive move. } 3... c5 { And now we are in for a ride! } (3... Nc6 { is Black's way to prevent the Blumenfeld. } 4. exd4 Nxd4 5. Nxd4 Qxd4 6. Nc3) 4. b4! { This is the Reversed Blumenfeld Gambit } 4... dxe3 (4... Nf6 5. Qa4+ (5. exd4 cxd4 6. Bb2 e5! { This looks like a gambit, but … } 7. Nxe5 Bxb4 8. Qa4+ Nfd7 9. Bxd4 O-O 10. Qxb4 Nxe5 { White should not take this knight, at least not twice. } 11. Be3 (11. Bxe5 Nc6 { [%cal Rc6b4,Rc6e5] } 12. Qc3 Nxe5 { Black is one pawn down but ahead in development. } { [%csl Be5,Bf8,Bg8,Gc3,Gc4] } 13. Be2 (13. Qxe5?? Re8! $19))) 5... Bd7 6. Qb3 dxe3 7. fxe3 cxb4 8. a3) (4... g6?!) (4... Bg4) (4... b6?! 5. bxc5 bxc5 6. Nxd4! { The point is that you clear f3 for the queen: } (6. Ne5 { Also fine, but less forcing. } 6... Bb7 (6... dxe3) 7. Qa4+ { [%cal Ge5d7,Ge5c6] } 7... Nd7 8. Na3 { [%cal Ga1b1,Gb1b7] }) 6... cxd4 7. Qf3 { And now Black has to give a piece back. } { [%cal Gf3a8] } 7... Nc6 8. Qxc6+ Bd7 9. Qf3 $16 { White is just a pawn up here, and Black has no compensation. }) (4... e6?! 5. bxc5 Bxc5 6. exd4 Bxd4 7. Nxd4 { Now White has the bishop pair. } 7... Qxd4 8. Nc3 Nc6 9. Ba3 { Be annoying. } { [%cal Ga3f8] } 9... Nge7 10. Nb5 { A very forcing move. } { [%cal Gb5d4,Gb5c7] } 10... Qe5+ { [%cal Ge5c7] } 11. Be2 O-O 12. O-O $10 { Equal position, but certainly easier to play for White. }) 5. fxe3 cxb4 6. d4 { This strong pawn center is White's compensation for the sacrificed b-pawn. } { [%csl Bc4,Bd4,Be3] } 6... Nf6 (6... e6) (6... Nh6!? $146 { Novelty! Looks like an interesting try. The point is that White's dark-squared bishop is blocked, and the knight can go to f5 or g4. } { [%csl Be3,Gf5,Gg4][%cal Rc1e3,Gh6g4,Gh6f5] } 7. a3 { Undermine this pawn before Black can stabilize it with a5. } 7... bxa3 { There is no need to take back immediately. The pawn is attacked three times. } { [%cal Ga1a3,Gb1a3,Gc1a3] } 8. Be2 { Just develop. If Black plays g6, take the pawn with the rook, castle otherwise. } 8... g6 (8... e6 9. O-O) 9. Rxa3 { Keep the pressure on the half-open file and add extra protection for e3. Also get the rook off from the a1-h8 diagonal. } { [%csl Ge3][%cal Ga3e3,Ga3a7,Bg7a1,Bf8g7] } 9... Bg7 10. O-O O-O 11. e4 { Occupy the center and free the dark-squared bishop. } { [%csl Bc1] } 11... Bg4 { This is an indirect attack on d4. } { [%cal Rg7d4,Rd8d4] } 12. Be3 f5 { Can Black launch an attack without a completed development? Maybe. } { [%cal Rh6f5] } 13. Nc3 (13. e5 f4 14. Bf2 $13 { [%csl Bd4][%cal Rh6f5,Rb8c6,Bc6d4,Bf5d4] })) 7. Bd3 g6 8. O-O Bg7 9. a3 bxa3 *


