1. Nf3 f5 { Black is hoping to transpose to a Dutch. And after 2.d4, they'd get their wish. But … } 2. d3 Nf6 3. e4 { Lisitsyn Gambit Deferred } 3... fxe4 4. dxe4 Nxe4 5. Bd3 d5 (5... Nf6 6. Ng5 { [%cal Gd3h7,Gg5h7] } 6... Nc6 (6... g6? 7. h4 { [%cal Gd3g6,Gh4h5] } (7. Nxh7 Rxh7 8. Bxg6+ Rf7 9. g4 (9. Bg5 Nc6 10. O-O $14) 9... d5) 7... d5 8. h5 Bg4 9. f3 Bxh5 10. Nc3 (10. g4 Qd6 11. gxh5 Bh6 12. Qd2 Nxh5)) 7. Nxh7 Ne5 8. Bf4 Nxd3+ 9. Qxd3 { Qg6 would be mate, and Black cannot stop that, to they have to make luft for their king. } { [%csl Bg6][%cal Gd3g6] } 9... d6 10. Ng5 Rh4 { [%cal Gh4f4] } 11. Qg6+ Kd7 12. g3 Rh6 13. Qf7 { [%cal Gg5e6,Be6f8,Bf7f8] } 13... Nh5 { [%cal Gh5f4] } 14. Be3 $16) 6. Bxe4 dxe4 7. Qxd8+ Kxd8 8. Ng5 Ke8 9. Nc3 Bf5 10. Be3 Nc6 11. O-O-O $14 { Niklasch, Oliver - Stabolewski, Andreas, 1-0, Dresden ZMD op, 2004, https://lichess.org/5ait9G1k } *


