1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 { [%cal Gd2d4] } 2... a6 { B28 Sicilian Defense: O'Kelly Variation. Named after Alberic O'Kelly de Galway who was playing it a lot between 1948 and 1951.
Introduced in Réti - Tartakower, 1919, Vienna.
White can play almost everything against this, because a6 doesn't fight for the center or develops a piece. And yet … there are surprisingly many ways for Black to equalize quickly. } 3. d4 { Normal System } (3. Nc3 { Yerevan System } 3... d6 (3... e6 4. d4 cxd4 5. Nxd4 { Transposition to: B43 Sicilian/Kan/Knight Variation }) 4. d4 (4. g3 Nc6 5. Bg2 Bg4 6. h3 (6. O-O e6) 6... Bxf3 7. Bxf3 { h3 is a liability now. } { [%csl Gh3] }) 4... cxd4 5. Nxd4 Nf6 { Transposition to: B90 Sicilian/Najdorf Variation }) (3. b4 { Wing Gambit }) (3. c4 { Maróczy Bind. This is probably the best way to maintain the initial edge for White. But this setup isn't everyone's toast. It leads to a slow and positional game.
White should get d4 in as soon as possible to cover the hole on d3. } { [%csl Bd3][%cal Gd2d4] } 3... e6 { Paulsen Line } (3... d6 { Robatsch Line }) (3... Nc6 4. d4 cxd4 5. Nxd4 e5 { Geller Line })) (3. g3 { Réti System }) (3. d3 { Quiet System }) (3. b3 { Kieseritzky System }) (3. Be2 { Aronin System }) (3. a4 { unnamed rare sideline } 3... Nc6 4. Nc3 { Everything is focused on an irrelevant square. } { [%cal Ga4b5,Gc3b5,Gf1b5] } 4... e6 5. d4 cxd4 6. Nxd4 $10) (3. c3 { Venice System } 3... d5 (3... d6 { Steiner Line }) (3... b5 { Ljubojevic Line }) (3... Nf6 { Barcza }) (3... e6 4. d4 d5) (3... g6 4. d4 cxd4 5. cxd4 d5) 4. exd5 Qxd5 (4... Nf6 { Gambit Line }) 5. d4 Nf6 (5... cxd4 6. cxd4 { Here White has an IQP position, which is probably just fine, because they can develop the knight with a tempo on the queen. } 6... e6 7. Nc3 Qd6 (7... Bb4 8. Bd3)) 6. Be2 e6 7. O-O Nc6 8. Be3 cxd4 9. Nxd4 Nxd4 10. Bxd4 Bc5 11. Bf3 Qd6 $14) 3... cxd4 4. Nxd4 (4. Bc4 { Cortlever Gambit } 4... e6 5. O-O (5. Nxd4 Nf6 6. Nc3)) (4. c3 { Smith-Morra Line. This does spice the game up! Maybe too much. } 4... dxc3 5. Nxc3 Nc6 6. Bc4 d6 7. O-O Nf6 { Transposition to: B21 Sicilian/Smith-Morra Gambit Accepted/Classical Formation }) 4... Nf6 (4... e6 { Kan Line }) (4... e5 { Taimanov Line }) 5. Nc3 e5 6. Nf3 (6. Nde2 Bc5 7. Ng3 d6 { [%cal Gf6g4,Gc5f2,Gg4f2,Gc8g4] } 8. Be2 O-O 9. O-O) 6... Bb4 7. Bc4 (7. Nxe5 O-O 8. Qd4 { [%cal Gd4b4] } 8... Bxc3+ 9. Qxc3 Nxe4 10. Qd4 Re8) *


