1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 { E40 Normal Line } 4... O-O { E46 Normal Variation } 5. Nf3 (5. Bd3 { Main move nowadays } { [%cal Gd1c2,Gc2h7] }) 5... Ne4 { This is a bit early. d5, c5 or b6 are the more stable continuations. } 6. Bd2 (6. Qc2 f5 7. Bd3 b6 8. O-O Bxc3 9. bxc3 Bb7 10. Nd2 Qh4) 6... Bxc3 7. Bxc3 Nxc3 8. bxc3 d6 9. Bd3 c6 { This is a very passive setup. Black's knight and bishop can't get into the game now. } { [%csl Gc6,Gd6,Ge6] } 10. O-O b6 11. e4 { Black should really activate the pieces from the queenside now! Bot no: } (11. a4 a5) 11... Qf6? (11... Nd7) (11... c5 { [%cal Gc8b7] }) (11... Bb7) 12. e5 { [%cal Gd3h7,Gd1d2,Gd2h6] } 12... dxe5 { Allows White's knight to get into the center and to unblock the f0-pawn. } { [%cal Gf3e5,Bf2f5] } (12... Qe7) 13. Nxe5 { [%csl Gd7][%cal Ge5d7,Rb8d7,Rc8d7,Bd7f8] } 13... Qh6 (13... Bb7 14. Re1 { [%cal Ge1e3,Ge3g3] }) 14. Ng4?! (14. Be4 { [%cal Ge4c6,Ge5c6] } 14... Bb7 15. Rb1 { [%cal Gc4c5] }) 14... Qh4 15. g3 (15. f4 f5 16. Ne5 Nd7 17. g3) 15... Qe7 16. Ne5 { This little Ng5 maneuver didn't do much. } 16... f6?? (16... c5 17. Qh5 { [%cal Gd3h7,Gh5h7] } 17... h6 { And Black is still okay. Not great, but the game would go on. }) 17. Bxh7+ (17. Ng6! { is even stronger. } 17... Qa3 (17... hxg6 18. Bxg6 Qd7 19. Qh5 Rd8 20. Rad1 Bb7 21. f4 f5 22. c5) 18. Nxf8 Qxf8) 17... Kxh7 (17... Kh8 18. Ng6+ Kxh7 19. Qh5+ Kg8 20. Nxe7#) 18. Qh5+ Kg8 19. Ng6 { [%cal Gh5h8,Gg6e7] } 19... Qe8? (19... Qd6 { could hold the game, says Stockfish } 20. Rfe1) 20. f4 f5 21. Qh8+? (21. d5 exd5 22. Rae1 Be6 23. Qh8+ Kf7 24. Qxf8+ Qxf8 25. Nxf8 { [%cal Ge1e6] } 25... Bc8 26. Nh7 $18) 21... Kf7 22. Ne5+ Ke7 (22... Kf6 23. Qh4+ g5 24. Qxg5#) 23. Qxg7+ Rf7! (23... Kd8 { And Black is still in the game! }) 24. Nxf7? (24. Qg5+ Kf8 25. Qh4 { [%cal Gg3g4,Gf1f7] }) 24... Qxf7 25. Qe5 Bd7?? (25... Nd7! { and Black is actually slightly better. } { [%cal Gd7e5] } 26. Qc7 Ba6 27. Rfe1) 26. Qc7 Na6 27. Qb7 { [%cal Gb7a6,Gb7a8] } 27... Rh8 28. Qxa6 Qh5 29. Rf2 Qh3 30. Qxa7 Rg8 31. Rg2 (31. Qxb6 Qh4 32. Qc7) 31... Qg4 32. Re1 Qf3 33. Qa3+ c5 34. d5 { [%cal Ge1e7] } 34... Kf6 35. Qb3 b5 36. cxb5 exd5 37. c4 Qxb3 38. axb3 Ra8 39. Rd2 d4 40. b4 cxb4 41. Rxd4 Be6 42. b6 Kf7 43. c5 Ra2 44. Rxe6 { 1-0 Black resigns. } 44... Kxe6 45. b7! { unstoppable pawn. } 1-0


