1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Nf3 Ne4?! { Probably too aggressive. } 5. Qc2 f5 6. g3 Nc6 (6... Bxc3+ 7. bxc3) (6... b6 7. Bg2 Bb7 8. Nd2 Bxc3 9. bxc3 Nd6 10. d5?! (10. O-O Bxg2 11. Kxg2) (10. e4 { [%cal Gc2e4,Gd2e4,Gg2e4] }) 10... Na6 11. O-O O-O 12. Ba3 (12. e4 Qf6 13. Re1 fxe4 14. Nxe4 Nxe4 15. Bxe4 { Colovic, Aleksandar - Drei, Andrea, 1-0, Cesenatico op 16th, 2012, https://lichess.org/NoS0FiSP }) 12... Qf6 { Carlsen, Magnus - Ivanchuk, Vassily, 0-1, Wch Rapid, 2012, https://lichess.org/wcBThHyB }) 7. Bg2 O-O 8. O-O Bxc3 9. bxc3 Na5 { [%cal Ga5c4] } 10. c5 d6 11. c4 b6 { The late b6. } (11... dxc5 12. Ba3 Nc6 13. Rad1 { Moiseenko, Alexander - Sulskis, Sarunas, 0-1, Kharkov Rector Cup 5th, 2003, https://lichess.org/2r744wee }) 12. Bd2 Nxd2 13. Nxd2 d5?! (13... Bb7 14. Bxb7 Nxb7 15. c6 Na5 16. d5) 14. cxd5 exd5 15. e3 { Odd position: Black's light-squared bishop is bad, the knight misplaced, and the rook on a8 not in the game. All of this can be solved, but it takes some valuable time. } 15... Be6 16. Qc3!? { This make b5 impossible for now, a move that Black would like to play after Rfc1. } { [%cal Gc3a5,Gc3c7] } (16. Rac1 { [%csl Gc7][%cal Gc2c7,Bc5b6] } 16... b5 17. Qc3 Nc6) 16... Rf7?! (16... Rc8 { This also solves the problem of the pin. } { [%cal Gg2a8] }) 17. Rfc1 Rb8?! (17... g5 { Engine suggestion. The idea is f4. } { [%cal Gf5f4] }) 18. Rab1 (18. Nf3! { [%cal Gf3e5] } 18... Nc4 19. a4 c6) 18... Re7 19. a4 Bf7 20. Bf1 h6 21. Bd3 Qd7 22. Qc2 Be6 23. Bb5 Qd8 24. Rd1 g5 25. Nf3 Rg7 26. Ne5 f4 27. Bf1 Qf6 28. Bg2 Rd8 29. e4 dxe4 30. Bxe4 Re7 31. Qc3 Bd5 32. Re1 Kg7 33. Ng4 Qf7 34. Bxd5 Rxd5 35. Rxe7 Qxe7 36. Re1 Qd8 37. Ne5 Qf6 38. cxb6 Qxb6 39. gxf4 Rxd4 40. Nf3 Nb3 41. Rb1 Qf6 42. Qxc7+ { 1-0 Black resigns. } 1-0


