1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 b6 { E12 Queen's Indian Defense } 4. Nc3 { E12 Queen's Indian Defense: Kasparov Variation } 4... Bb4 { E21 Nimzo-Indian Defense: Three Knights Variation, Duchamp Variation
Here Karpov finally had a Nimzo-Indian with b6 on the board, although by an unusual move order. He didn't play b6 in the 1985 championship. } 5. Bg5 (5. Qb3 c5 6. Bg5) 5... Bb7 6. e3 h6 7. Bh4 Bxc3+ 8. bxc3 d6 { Put the pawns on dark squares to compensate for the loss of the dark-squared bishop. } { [%cal Gb8d7] } 9. Nd2 g5 10. Bg3 Qe7 11. a4 a5 12. h4 Rg8 13. hxg5 hxg5 14. Qb3 Na6 { Prevents c5 by White, and prepares maybe O-O-O. } 15. Rb1 Kf8 (15... Nd7 16. c5 dxc5) 16. Qd1 Bc6 17. Rh2 Kg7 18. c5 bxc5 19. Bb5 Nb8 20. dxc5 d5 21. Be5 Kf8 22. Rh6 Ne8 23. Qh5 f6 24. Rh7 Ng7 25. Qf3 Kf7 26. Qh5+ Kf8 27. Qf3 Kf7 28. Rh6 Ne8 29. e4 g4 30. Qf4 Bxb5 31. Rxb5 Nd7 32. Bxc7 Nxc5 33. Qe3 Nxe4 34. Nxe4 dxe4 35. Bxa5 f5 36. Bb4 Qd7 37. Qd4 Ra7 38. Rh7+ Ng7 39. a5 Kg6 40. Qxd7 Rxd7 41. Rh4 Rgd8 42. c4 Rd1+ 43. Ke2 Rc1 44. a6 Rc2+ 45. Ke1 Ra2 46. Rb6 Rd3 47. c5 Ra1+ 48. Ke2 Ra2+ 49. Ke1 g3 50. fxg3 Rxg3 51. Kf1 Rgxg2 52. Be1 Rgc2 53. c6 Ra1 54. Rh3 f4 55. Rb4 Kf5 56. Rb5+ e5 57. Ra5 Rd1 58. a7 e3 { 0-1 White resigns. } 0-1


