1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. Nf3 { Three Knights Variation } { [%csl Bf6,Bf3,Bc3] } 4... c5 (4... b6 5. Bg5 Bb7 6. e3 h6 7. Bh4 g5 8. Bg3 Ne4 9. Qc2 Bxc3+ 10. bxc3 d6 11. Bd3 f5 12. d5 Nd7 (12... exd5 13. cxd5 Bxd5 14. Nd4 { [%cal Gd4f5] })) 5. g3 cxd4 6. Nxd4 Ne4 (6... O-O 7. Bg2 d5 8. cxd5 Nxd5 9. Qb3 { [%cal Gg2d5,Gb3d5] } 9... Nc6 10. Nxc6 bxc6 11. O-O) 7. Qd3 Bxc3+ 8. bxc3 Nc5 9. Qf3 d6 10. Bg2 Bd7 11. O-O Bc6 12. Qg4 O-O 13. Bh6 Qf6 14. Bg5 Qg6 15. Nxc6 Nxc6 16. Qh4 f6 17. Be3 Rfd8 18. Rab1 Qf7 19. Bxc6 bxc6 20. Bxc5 dxc5 { An almost symmetrical position. But White is better, because the queen is in front of the pawns and can switch targets easily. } { [%csl Gh4] } 21. Qe4 { [%cal Ge4c6] } 21... e5 { [%cal Rf7c4,Ge4c6] } 22. Rb2 { Cover d2. } { [%csl Rd2][%cal Rd8d2] } 22... Rab8 23. Rfb1 Rxb2 24. Rxb2 Qd7 25. Kg2 Re8 (25... Qc8 26. Qe3 { [%cal Ge3c5] }) 26. Qe3 { [%cal Ge3c5] } 26... Qe7 (26... Qd6) 27. a4 g6 28. a5 Rd8 29. a6 { [%cal Gb2b7] } 29... Rd7 { [%cal Gd7b7,Gb2b7] } 30. Rb8+ Kg7 31. Rc8 Qd6 32. Qe4 f5? (32... Rc7 { Black has to hold the pawn. } 33. Rxc7+ Qxc7 34. Qb1 { [%cal Gb1b7] }) 33. Qxc6 Qxc6+ 34. Rxc6 Kf7 (34... e4 { [%cal Gg7e5] } 35. f4 { [%cal Gf4e5] } 35... exf3+ 36. Kxf3 Re7 { [%cal Ge7e4] } 37. Rxc5) 35. f4 exf4 36. gxf4 Re7 37. Kf3 Ke8 38. Rxc5 Kd7 39. Re5 Rxe5 (39... Rf7 40. Rb5) 40. fxe5 g5 41. c5 h6 42. c4 h5 43. h4 g4+ 44. Kf4 Ke6 45. c6 Ke7 46. c5 (46. c7 Kd7 47. e6+ Kxc7 48. c5) 46... Ke6 47. c7 Kd7 48. e6+ Kxc7 49. e3 { Basically a waiting move. Black is now in zugzwang. } 49... Kc6 (49... Kd8 50. c6 Kc7 51. e7 { [%cal Ge7d8,Gc6d7] }) 50. Ke5! { Note that White doesn't take on f5. This pawn will play an important role later. } (50. Kxf5) 50... g3 51. e7 Kd7 52. Kf6 g2 53. c6+ Kc7 { If Kxc6 or Ke8, White will promote with a check. } (53... Kxc6 54. e8=Q+) (53... Ke8 54. c7 Kd7 55. e8=Q+ Kxc7) 54. e8=Q g1=Q 55. Qd7+ Kb6 56. c7 { 1-0 Black resigns. } { The point is that Black will run out of checks eventually. White's king can hide behind the pawn on f5. } { [%csl Bf5] } 56... Qa1+ 57. Kg6 Qg1+ 58. Kh7 { And Black has no checks anymore. } { [%csl Rf5][%cal Gc7c8,Rg1b1,Rb1f5] } 1-0


