1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e3 { Normal Line } 4... O-O 5. Ne2 { Reshevsky Variation } 5... Re8 6. a3 Bf8 7. g4?! Nxg4 8. Rg1 { The idea is simple: open the file, and attack the king. } 8... Qh4?! (8... Nxh2 { [%cal Gh2f1] } 9. Bg2 { And now Black should develop quickly and probably fianchetto the dark-squared bishop. } 9... e5 10. Qc2 { [%cal Gc2h7,Gg1h1,Gh1h7] } 10... g6 { [%cal Gf8g7] } 11. Bd2 exd4 12. exd4 Bg7 $15 { This is good for Black. }) (8... f5 9. h3 Nf6 10. Ng3?! d6 { Sowray, P. - Roberson, P., 0-1, 4NCL 2013-14, 2014, https://lichess.org/pLjNa1S2 }) 9. Rg3! { The threat of Rh3 protects the pawn on h2. } { [%cal Gg3h3] } 9... Bd6 10. h3 Nf6 (10... Bxg3? { Doesn't work because then White gets two pieces for the rook: } 11. fxg3 Qf6 12. hxg4 $14) 11. e4 { [%cal Ge4e5] } 11... Nxe4 12. Nxe4 Qxe4 13. Rg4 Qc6 14. Nc3 { Threat is Ne4, followed by d5. } { [%cal Gc3e4] } 14... Bf8? { Mistake. } (14... Be7 { The only good move in the position, says Stockfish. } 15. Rg3 (15. Ne4 { is no threat anymore, because of } 15... f5!) 15... d5) 15. c5? { Mistake. Ne4 is so much better. } (15. Ne4! { The point is that } 15... f5 { can now be answered with } 16. Nf6+! Kh8 { and } 17. Nxe8 { is great for White. } { [%cal Ge8g7,Gg4g7] } 17... d6 { [%cal Gc6e8] } (17... fxg4? 18. d5 exd5 19. cxd5 Qb6 20. Qxg4 { Threatening Qf4 } { [%cal Gg4f4,Ge8c7] } 20... Na6 $16) 18. Nxg7 fxg4 19. d5! exd5 20. cxd5 Qd7 21. Ne6 $16) 15... f5 16. Rg1 a6 17. Qh5 d6 18. Be3 Qd7 19. Be2 Qf7 20. Qh4 e5 21. dxe5 dxe5 22. Nd5 Kh8 23. Bh5 Qxd5 24. Bxe8 f4 25. Rd1 Qg8 26. Rd8 Nc6 27. Bxc6 bxc6 28. Bd2 Qf7 29. Bc3 h6 30. Bxe5 Kh7 31. Rxf8 Qxf8 32. Rxg7+ Qxg7 33. Bxg7 Kxg7 34. Qxf4 Ra7 35. Qd4+ Kf7 36. Qd8 { 1-0 Black resigns. } 1-0


