1. e4 e5 2. Bc4 f5 { C23 Calabrese Countergambit. A very aggressive opening, similar to the King's Gambit. } 3. d3 { Jänisch Variation } (3. exf5 { Accepted Variation. Not a good move for White. } 3... Nf6 { [%csl Gh5][%cal Gd7d5,Gf6h5,Rd1h5] } 4. d3 d5 5. Bb3 Bxf5) (3. d4 { Counter Counter :) Nf6 is now not good. } 3... Nc6 4. Nf3 fxe4 5. Nxe5 d5 6. Bb5 Qd6 7. c4) (3. Bxg8 { Exchange. Not good for White. } 3... Rxg8 4. Qh5+ g6 5. Qxh7 Rg7) 3... Nf6 { Preventing the check. } { [%csl Gh5][%cal Gf6h5,Rd1h5] } *


