1. e4 { [%clk 0:10:00] } 1... c5 { [%clk 0:10:00] } 2. Nf3 { [%clk 0:10:00] } 2... d6 { [%clk 0:10:03] } 3. d4 { [%clk 0:10:04] } 3... cxd4 { [%clk 0:10:07] } 4. Nxd4 { [%clk 0:10:09] } 4... Nf6 { [%clk 0:10:11] } 5. Nc3 { [%clk 0:10:13] } 5... g6 { The first time I actually got a proper Dragon on the board. Yay! } { [%clk 0:10:14] } 6. Be3 { Main move. } { [%clk 0:10:14] } 6... Bg7 { [%clk 0:10:15] } 7. Be2 { Prevents Ng4, although that's not needed yet. } { [%clk 0:10:18] } (7. f3 { is the main move. }) 7... O-O { [%clk 0:10:18] } 8. a4 { A very weird move. Not in the database, and I had no preparation for it. } { [%clk 0:10:21] } 8... a6 { With the idea to cover b5, a square under heavy pressure by White. } { [%csl Rb5][%cal Ga6b5,Re2b5,Ra4b5,Rc3b5,Rd4b5] [%clk 0:10:19] } 9. b4 { White is going for a queenside attack prior to castling! } { [%clk 0:10:22] } 9... Nc6 { I just tried to develop my pieces. } { [%clk 0:10:14] } (9... b6 { was the best option here – with the idea Bb7. I didn't even see that move. } { [%cal Gc8b7] }) 10. Nxc6 { [%clk 0:10:22] } 10... bxc6 { [%clk 0:10:19] } 11. a5 { [%clk 0:10:24] } 11... Rb8 { [%cal Gb8b4] [%clk 0:09:39] } 12. Bb6?! { [%clk 0:10:25] } 12... Rxb6 { Taking this pawn was just too tempting. } { [%clk 0:09:32] } 13. axb6 { [%clk 0:10:27] } 13... Qxb6 { My compensation was a safe backrank, one pawn, and the bishop pair. Enough, I felt, and the engine agrees. } { [%clk 0:09:37] } 14. Rb1 { [%clk 0:10:19] } 14... Nh5?! { I decided to go for White's light-squared bishop. Way too slow. } { [%clk 0:08:53] } (14... Ng4 { I was looking at this move for quite a while, but I didn't see how to continue after the exchange. } { [%cal Gg7c3] } 15. Bxg4 Bxc3+ 16. Kf1 Bxg4 17. Qxg4 { And here ended the line I was calculating. I just couldn't see the follow-up. } 17... c5! { This one I missed. } { [%cal Gb6b1] } 18. b5 axb5 { There is still some work to do, but White's weak pawns and the passive rook are pretty good for me. } { [%csl Bh1,Bc2] }) 15. Na4 { [%cal Gb6a6] [%clk 0:09:47] } 15... Qa7 { [%clk 0:08:04] } 16. c4?! { [%clk 0:09:47] } (16. Bxh5 gxh5 17. Qxh5 $10 { Not sure why my opponent didn't go for this. }) 16... Nf4 { [%clk 0:08:00] } 17. O-O { [%clk 0:09:02] } 17... Nxe2+?! { [%clk 0:08:03] } (17... f5 { is an engine suggestion. The point is probably that White cannot protect the pawn with the f-pawn. } { [%csl Gf2][%cal Ga7g1] } 18. Bf3 Bd4 19. exf5 Bxf5 20. Rb3 e5 $15) 18. Qxe2 { [%clk 0:09:01] } 18... Bd7?! { My idea was to put some pressure on the knight, but then I realized that White had c5. } { [%clk 0:08:00] } 19. Rfc1 { White gifted me a tempo, so I played c5 before they could do that. } { [%clk 0:08:16] } (19. c5! { I was very afraid of that move. } 19... a5 20. Qc2 { [%csl Gc6][%cal Gc2c6] }) 19... c5 { White gifted me a tempo, so I played c5 before they could do that. } { [%cal Gd7a4] [%clk 0:07:56] } 20. Nc3 { [%clk 0:08:09] } (20. Qc2 { [%cal Rc2a4,Gd7a4] } 20... cxb4 21. Rxb4) 20... cxb4 { [%clk 0:07:26] } 21. Rxb4 { [%clk 0:08:10] } 21... Bd4 { I thought I need this bishop on c5 to support the advance of the a-pawn. } { [%clk 0:06:43] } (21... a5 22. Rbb1 a4 23. Nb5 Qa8) 22. Nd5 { I saw that! } { [%cal Rd5e7] [%clk 0:08:05] } 22... Be6?! { [%csl Ge7][%cal Ga7e7] [%clk 0:06:31] } (22... Bc6 { was apparently better. }) 23. Nxe7+?? { Decisive blunder. } { [%clk 0:08:06] } (23. Qd2 { [%cal Rd2d4] } 23... Bc5 24. Rb3) 23... Qxe7 { [%clk 0:06:34] } 24. Rd1 { [%clk 0:08:03] } 24... Bc5 { [%clk 0:06:34] } 25. Rb3 { [%clk 0:07:12] } 25... a5 { Finally time to push the pawn and bind White's resources. } { [%clk 0:06:21] } 26. Rdb1 { [%clk 0:07:09] } 26... a4 { [%clk 0:06:08] } 27. Rb7 { [%clk 0:07:04] } 27... Qf6 { [%csl Bd4][%cal Gf6f2,Gc5f2,Bf6d4,Be6c4] [%clk 0:06:11] } 28. Qa2? { [%clk 0:07:02] } 28... a3 { [%clk 0:06:07] } 29. Kf1?? { [%clk 0:06:49] } 29... Qd4? { [%clk 0:05:58] } (29... Bxc4+! { I missed that. } { [%cal Gf6f2,Gc5f2] } 30. Kg1 (30. Qxc4 Qxf2#) 30... Bxa2) 30. Rb8 