1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 g6 { B70 Sicilian Defense: Dragon Variation } 6. Bg5 Bg7 7. f3 O-O 8. Qd2 { [%cal Rg5h6] } 8... Nc6 9. Nxc6 (9. Nb3 { is the normal move here. }) 9... bxc6 10. Bxf6?! Bxf6 { Here I had a decent position: bishop pair with open diagonals, open b-file for my rook and an almost completed development. And then … I ruined it. } 11. h4 h5 (11... Rb8 { [%cal Gb8b2] } 12. Bc4 { Now Rxb2 would get the rook trapped. } { [%cal Gc4b3] } 12... Be6 13. Bxe6 fxe6 14. Na4) 12. Be2 a5?! { My idea was trading off the light-squared bishops to slow down White's attack. That's too passive. } (12... Rb8) 13. O-O-O?! Ba6? (13... a4 14. g4 Qa5 { So simple, once you see it. :) } { [%cal Ga5h5] } 15. a3 Rb8) 14. g4 Bxe2 15. Qxe2 hxg4 16. fxg4 e6? (16... Qb6) 17. g5 Bxc3 18. bxc3 Qb6 19. h5 Rab8 20. hxg6 fxg6 21. Qh2 Qe3+ 22. Rd2 Kf7 23. Qh7+ Ke8 24. Qxg6+ Ke7 25. Rh7+ Kd8 26. Rf7 Qe1+ 27. Rd1 Qe3+ 28. Rd2 Qe1+ 29. Rd1 Qe3+ 30. Rd2 { The game is a draw. } 1/2-1/2


