1. e4 { [%eval 0.12] [%clk 0:10:00] } 1... e5 { [%eval 0.37] [%clk 0:10:00] } 2. b3 { [%eval -0.89] [%clk 0:10:06] } 2... Nf6 { [%eval -0.43] [%clk 0:10:02] } 3. Bb2 { [%eval -0.7] [%clk 0:10:12] } 3... Nc6?! { [%eval -0.12] } { My opponent didn't take the pawn and developed a piece instead. Not a bad idea overall, it's me who wants an open center, not him. } { [%clk 0:10:05] } (3... Nxe4 4. d3 Nf6 5. Bxe5 Nc6 6. Bb2 d5 7. Be2 Bb4+ 8. Nd2) 4. d3 { [%eval -0.42] [%clk 0:10:15] } (4. Nf3 { Maybe I should go for the pawn on e5 immediately and hope that he takes on e4 now? } 4... Nxe4 5. d3 Nf6 6. Nxe5 Nxe5 7. Bxe5) 4... a6?! { [%eval -0.18] } { I have no idea what this move does. I can't play Bb5 anyway, and playing b5 makes no sense. Plus it wouldn't need support by a6.. } { [%clk 0:10:03] } 5. Nf3 { [%eval -0.44] [%clk 0:10:22] } 5... d5 { [%eval -0.34] } { And we are in business. } { [%clk 0:09:57] } 6. exd5 { [%eval -0.69] [%clk 0:10:21] } 6... Nxd5 { [%eval -0.51] [%clk 0:10:02] } 7. Nxe5?! { [%eval -1.18] } { Inaccuracy. That was a bad move, and I realized it as soon as I played it. The reason is that after … } { [%clk 0:10:22] } (7. Be2 { Doesn't work here, because of } 7... Nf4 { … and I lose my beloved light-squared bishop. }) (7. g3 { Hmm, I'm not so sure about that move. But it does help my king safety and keeps the light-squared bishop. } 7... Bg4 8. Bg2 Qd7 9. h3 Bf5 10. Nxe5 { Now I can take the pawn! } 10... Bb4+ 11. Kf1) 7... Nxe5 { [%eval -0.83] } { … and … } { [%clk 0:09:49] } 8. Bxe5 { [%eval -0.86] } { … my opponent had too many good moves. Luckily, he played: } { [%clk 0:10:30] } 8... Bc5? { [%eval 0.15] } { And I was okay.
But the takeaway is that I should castle first before I open the center. } { [%clk 0:09:14] } (8... Qg5 { [%cal Gg5e5] } 9. Bb2 { [%cal Gg5g2] } (9. Qe2) 9... Bb4+ 10. c3 O-O! 11. Qd2 (11. cxb4?? { I can't take! } 11... Re8+ 12. Be2 Qxg2 { [%cal Gg2h1] } 13. Kd2 (13. Rf1? Nf4 14. Nc3 Bf5 15. Bc1 Nxd3+ 16. Qxd3 (16. Kd2? Rad8 $19) 16... Bxd3) 13... Qg5+! 14. Ke1 Bf5 15. Nc3 Nxb4 $19 { [%cal Gb4d3] }) 11... Qe7+ 12. Be2) 9. Be2 { [%eval 0.17] [%clk 0:10:32] } 9... O-O { [%eval 0.61] [%clk 0:09:13] } 10. O-O { [%eval 0.58] [%clk 0:10:37] } 10... Qg5?! { [%eval 1.1] } { This comes too late, because I have castled already. } { [%clk 0:09:01] } (10... Re8 11. d4 Bf5 12. Bf3 Bb6 13. a3 c5 14. dxc5 Bxc5 15. Bg3 Nf6 16. Bxb7 Qxd1 17. Rxd1 $10) 11. Bb2? { [%eval -0.84] } { Mistake. Best move was d4. } { [%clk 0:10:33] } (11. d4 { I discarded that move, because I wanted to stay on the a1-h8 diagonal, and I thought f6 would be an option for Black. But f6 opens the diagonal for my light-squared bishop to his king, so it's probably not a good move. } { [%cal Ge2c4] } 11... Bb6 12. Bf3 c6 13. c4 $16 { [%cal Gc4c5] }) 11... Bh3? { [%eval 0.91] } { Mistake. I'd rather defend g2 with the bishop on f1—I didn't have time for that because of that silly center maneuver– but here I can do the same from f3. } { [%clk 0:09:05] } (11... Nf4 12. g3 Re8 13. Bf3 Nh3+ 14. Kg2 Qh6 15. d4 Ng5 16. Kh1 Nxf3 17. Qxf3 Bd7 18. Kg1) 12. Bf3 { [%eval 0.56] [%clk 0:10:18] } 12... h6?? { [%eval 5.02] } { Blunder. Another pointless waiting move, like a6 earlier. Nf4 immediately would have been a little bit dangerous. } { [%clk 0:08:01] } (12... Nf4 { [%cal Rf4g2,Rh3g2,Rg5g2] } 13. Bc1 Bd6 14. Re1 c6 15. Nc3 Qg6 16. Bxf4 Bxf4 17. Ne4 Rfd8 18. c3 Re8 19. Nc5) 13. Nd2? { [%eval 1.93] } { Mistake. I should have taken d5. } { [%clk 0:10:18] } (13. Bxd5 Qxd5 14. gxh3 $18) 13... Ne3?? { [%eval 6.54] } { Blunder. Yes, it looks dangerous, because Black can recapture with a check. But it's just one check and nothing more. } { [%clk 0:07:54] } (13... Nf4 14. Ne4 Qg6 15. Ng3 Bc8 16. Qd2 Bd6 17. Rae1 c6 18. Be5 Bxe5 19. Rxe5 Qf6 20. d4) 14. fxe3 { [%eval 6.48] [%clk 0:10:09] } 14... Bxe3+ { [%eval 6.66] [%clk 0:07:58] } 15. Kh1 { [%eval 6.58] [%csl Bh3] [%clk 0:10:16] } 15... Bxd2?! { [%eval 7.23] } { Inaccuracy. Best move was Be6. } { [%clk 0:07:54] } (15... Be6 16. Ne4) 16. gxh3 { [%eval 7.02] } { This is completely winning already, and now Black missed what my strong bishop (the sting!) was threatening. } { [%cal Gb2g7,Gf1g1,Gg1g7] [%clk 0:10:17] } 16... c6? { [%eval 12.98] } { Mistake. Best move was Qa5. } { [%clk 0:07:12] } (16... Qa5 17. Bxb7 Rae8 18. Bxa6 f5 19. Bc4+ Kh8 20. Qf3 Bc3 21. Bxc3 Qxc3 22. a4 Qa5 23. Rf2) 17. Rg1 { [%eval 12.47] [%clk 0:10:23] } 17... Qe3?! { [%eval #8] } { Checkmate is now unavoidable. Best move was Rae8. } { [%clk 0:07:13] } (17... Rae8 18. h4) 18. Rxg7+ { [%eval #7] [%clk 0:10:27] } 18... Kh8 { [%eval #7] [%clk 0:07:12] } 19. Rg2+?! { [%eval 13.93] } { Mistake. I saw Be4, but I thought Black could stop that with f5. So I went for the material. } { [%clk 0:10:32] } (19. Be4 Bc3 (19... f5 { … but that doesn't work. } 20. Qh5! { The point is that Black has no checks. } 20... Rf6 { [%cal Gf6h6] } 21. Bxf6 Rg8 22. Rxg8+ Kxg8 23. Qe8+ Kh7 24. Bxf5#) 20. Bxc3 f5 21. Qh5 Rf6 22. Bxf6 Rg8 23. Rxg8+ Kxg8 24. Qe8+ Kh7 25. Bxf5#) 19... Kh7?! { [%eval #8] } { Checkmate is now unavoidable. Best move was f6. } { [%clk 0:07:18] } (19... f6 20. Qxd2) 20. Rxd2 { [%eval 12.87] } { Mistake. Basically the same as before. } { [%clk 0:10:17] } (20. Be4+ Qxe4 21. dxe4 f6 22. Qxd2 Rad8 23. Qf4 a5 24. Qf5+ Kh8 25. Bxf6+ Rxf6 26. Qxf6+ Kh7 27. Qg7#) 20... Rae8 { [%eval 18.64] [%clk 0:06:53] } 21. Be4+ { [%eval 13.38] [%clk 0:10:19] } 21... Kg8?! { [%eval #4] } { Checkmate is now unavoidable. Best move was Rxe4. } { And now even I saw the mate. } { [%clk 0:06:53] } (21... Rxe4 22. dxe4) 22. Rg2+ { [%eval #3] [%clk 0:10:15] } 22... Qg5 { [%eval #3] [%clk 0:06:46] } 23. Rx