1. e4 { [%clk 1:30:57] } 1... e5 { [%clk 1:30:32] } 2. Nf3 { [%clk 1:31:22] } 2... Nf6 { [%clk 1:31:00] } 3. Nxe5 { [%clk 1:31:44] } 3... d6 { [%clk 1:31:19] } 4. Nf3 { [%clk 1:32:09] } 4... Nxe4 { [%clk 1:31:46] } 5. Nc3 { [%clk 1:32:32] } 5... Nxc3 { [%clk 1:32:12] } 6. dxc3 { [%clk 1:32:54] } 6... Be7 { Everything normal so far. } { [%clk 1:32:36] } 7. Bf4 { Maybe not the best square for the bishop, staring at the little pawn chain? } { [%csl Bd6,Bc7][%cal Gf4d6] [%clk 1:32:48] } (7. Be3 { Main move. }) 7... Nc6 { Black announces long castling. } { [%clk 1:28:20] } (7... O-O { Main move. } 8. Qd2 Nd7 (8... Nc6 9. O-O-O Be6 10. Kb1 a5) 9. O-O-O Nc5 { The idea is simply to bring material to the queenside. } 10. h4 Bg4) 8. Qd2 { [%clk 1:33:05] } 8... Be6 { [%clk 1:28:21] } 9. O-O-O { [%clk 1:33:06] } 9... Qd7 { [%clk 1:27:59] } 10. Ng5 { That's a rare and somewhat odd move. The idea is of course to get the bishop pair. Navara has played that before. } { [%clk 1:30:33] } 10... Bxg5 { [%clk 1:25:25] } (10... Bxa2! $146 { Has not been played before; I looked it up in the chess24 database. But doesn't that bishop fall to b3? } 11. b3 a5 12. Kb2 a4 { And here White can't take! } 13. Ra1 (13. Kxa2? axb3+ 14. Kxb3? (14. Kb2 Qf5 { [%csl Bc2][%cal Ga8a2,Ba2c2,Bf5c2,Bb3c2] } 15. cxb3 Nb4! 16. Bd3 (16. cxb4? Bf6+ { [%cal Ra8a1] }) 16... Ra2+ 17. Kb1 Qa5! 18. Bb5+ Qxb5 19. Qd4 Ra1+ 20. Kb2 (20. Kxa1?? Qa5+ 21. Kb1 Qa2+ 22. Kc1 Qc2#) 20... Ra2+ 21. Kb1 Ra3 22. cxb4 Rxb3+ 23. Kc2 Rxb4 24. Qxg7 Rxf4 25. Qxh8+ Kd7 26. Nf3 Rc4+ 27. Kd2 Qd5+ $19) 14... Ne5! { [%cal Gd7a4] } 15. Qd4 c5! { [%csl Gc4,Gb4,Ga4][%cal Ge5c4,Gc5b4,Ga8a4] } 16. Qe4 f5! $19 { And this is over. White can't prevent Qa5 anymore. }) 13... axb3 14. cxb3 O-O { And now the bishop is indeed gone. But … } 15. Rxa2 Rxa2+ 16. Kxa2 Ra8+ { Only two variations: } 17. Kb2 (17. Kb1 Na5 { [%cal Ga5b3] } 18. Qd5 { [%cal Gd5f7,Gg5f7] } (18. Qc2 { [%cal Gc2h7,Gg5h7] } 18... Bxg5 19. Bxg5 Nxb3! { [%cal Gd7f5,Gf5g5,Gf5b1] } 20. Bc4 Ra1+ 21. Kb2 Rxh1 22. Bxb3 Rxh2 $10) 18... Bxg5 19. Bxg5 Nxb3 20. Bc4 c6 21. Qf3 Ra1+ 22. Kb2 Rxh1 23. Bxb3 d5 $10 { This is equal. }) 17... Nb4 18. Qd4 Ra2+ 19. Kb1 Ra1+ { [%cal Gb4c2,Gc2d4,Gc2a1] } 20. Kb2 { Draw by repetition. } 20... Ra2+ 21. Kc1? Bxg5 22. cxb4 (22. Bxg5?? Qf5 { [%cal Gf5c2] } 23. Bd3 Nxd3+ 24. Kd1 Nxf2+ 25. Ke1 Qb1+ 26. Bc1 Qxc1+ 27. Qd1 Qxd1#) 22... Qc6+ 23. Bc4 Bf6 { [%csl Ga1][%cal Gf6a1,Ga2a1,Ga1h1] } 24. Qd5 Qxd5 25. Bxd5 Ra1+ 26. Kc2 Rxh1 $19) 11. Bxg5 { [%clk 1:30:54] } 11... h6 { [%clk 1:21:06] } (11... f6 { Main move. } 12. Be3 O-O-O 13. b3 Rde8 14. f3 h5 15. h4 Bf5 16. Bf2 Re7 17. Be2 Rhe8 18. Rde1 Kb8 19. Bd1 Rxe1 20. Bxe1 Re7 21. Bf2 Ne5 { Navara, D. - Melkumyan, H., 1/2-1/2, Gibraltar Masters 2019, https://lichess.org/z8lNs5Qp }) 12. Be3 { [%clk 1:29:05] } 12... O-O-O { [%clk 1:19:42] } 13. b3 { [%csl Gb5,Ga7][%cal Gf1b5,Ge3a7] [%clk 1:28:47] } 13... a6 { [%clk 1:13:44] } 14. Be2 { [%clk 1:22:26] } 14... Bg4?! { Wasting a tempo. } { [%clk 0:55:25] } 15. f3 { [%clk 1:22:37] } 15... Bf5 { [%clk 0:55:52] } 16. Rhe1 { [%clk 1:17:45] } 16... h5?! { Playing h7-h6 and h6-h5 is wasting more time. Also there are no real targets on the kingside. And if you only have a light-squared bishop, your pawns should probably control dark squares. } { [%clk 0:53:33] } (16... Rhe8 17. Kb2 Bg6) 17. c4 { [%cal Gd2a5] [%clk 1:14:30] } (17. Bc4) 17... Qe6 { [%clk 0:51:03] } (17... Rhe8 18. Bf2 Qe6) 18. Bf1 { [%clk 1:14:01] } 18... Qg6 { [%clk 0:47:13] } 19. b4 { [%cal Gb4b5] [%clk 1:08:15] } 19... b6 { [%clk 0:38:47] } 20. Qc3 { [%cal Gc4c5] [%clk 0:57:25] } 20... a5 { [%clk 0:38:22] } (20... Kb7) 21. a3 { [%clk 0:57:28] } 21... Kb7 { [%clk 0:37:15] } 22. Kb2 { [%clk 0:49:02] } 22... Ra8?! { That rook is out of the game now. This might be the moment things went wrong for Black. } { [%clk 0:36:32] } (22... axb4 23. axb4 Ra8 { Now it would actually do something. }) 23. b5 { [%clk 0:43:34] } 23... Nd8?! { Weakens d6. We will see in a moment how. } { [%csl Bd6] [%clk 0:30:10] } (23... Nb8 24. g4 hxg4 25. fxg4 Be4 (25... Qxg4 26. Be2)) 24. g4?! { [%clk 0:40:06] } (24. g3 Re8 25. Bf2 Re6 26. Qd2) 24... hxg4 { [%clk 0:29:44] } 25. fxg4 { [%clk 0:40:25] } 25... Be4?! { Taking g4 was better. } { [%clk 0:27:14] } (25... Qxg4 26. Be2 (26. Bf2) 26... Qh3 { [%cal Gh3c3] } 27. Bf1 Qg4) 26. Bxb6 { [%clk 0:26:37] } 26... Rxh2? { [%clk 0:16:23] } (26... cxb6 27. Qg3 { And this is why 23...Nd8 was bad: Now Black can't put a rook behind the d-pawn. } { [%cal Gg3d6,Gd1d6] } 27... Qf6+ 28. Ka2 Qf3 29. Bd3 Qxg3 30. Bxe4+ Kc7 31. hxg3 Rb8) 27. Rxe4 { [%clk 0:23:15] } 27... Qxe4 { [%clk 0:16:48] } 28. Bg1 { [%cal Gd1d4,Gg1h2] [%clk 0:23:06] } 28... Qxg4 { [%clk 0:13:26] } 29. Bxh2 { [%clk 0:22:28] } 29... Qxd1 { [%clk 0:13:52] } 30. Bg2+ { [%clk 0:22:47] } 30... c6?? { The decisive blunder. } { [%clk 0:11:58] } (30... Kb8 31. Qxg7 { Here White is just a bit better, but not winning. }) 31. Bf3 { [%clk 0:17:04] } 31... Qf1 { [%clk 0:12:23] } 32. Bxd6 { [%clk 0:17:24] } 32... Qf2 { [%clk 0:10:00] } (32... Kc8 33. Bg4+ Kb7 34. bxc6+ Nxc6 35. Qb3+) 33. Qe5 { [%cal Ge5e7,Ge7c7] [%clk 0:15:46] } 33... Rc8 { [%clk 0:08:37] } 34. Qe7+ { [%clk 0:15:41] } 34... Kb6 { [%clk 0:08:33] } 35. c5+ { [%clk 0:15:52] } 35... Kxb5 { [%clk 0:08:58] } 36. Be2+ { 1-0 Black resigns. } { [%clk 0:15:35] } 1-0


