1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. d4 Nxe4 { C43 Russian Game: Modern Attack, Symmetrical Variation } 4. dxe5 { Adolf Anderssen was the first who played this in 1853 against Louis Eichborn. He won. } (4. Bd3 { Main move. } 4... d5 5. Nxe5 Nd7 6. Nxd7 Bxd7 7. O-O Bd6 8. c4 c6 9. cxd5 cxd5 10. Nc3 Nxc3 11. bxc3 O-O 12. Qh5 g6 13. Qxd5 Qc7 14. Bh6 Rfd8 15. Qg5 Qxc3 16. Rfd1 Bf8 17. Bxf8 Rxf8 18. Rac1) 4... Bc5 { [%cal Gc5f2,Ge4f2] } (4... d5 { Main move. Eichborn played this too. } 5. Nbd2 Nxd2 6. Bxd2 $10) 5. Bc4! { White can't really defend f2 without ruining their pawn structure, so a counter-attack is the best option. } (5. Be3?! Bxe3 6. fxe3 d5 7. exd6 Nxd6 $10) 5... Nxf2 6. Bxf7+ Kxf7 7. Qd5+ Kg6 8. Qxc5 $146 { That was a novelty in 2011. Nowadays it's the main move. Everyone else played the dubious 8.Rf1, and Nigel Short Bg5 } (8. Rf1?! d6 9. Rxf2 Bxf2+ 10. Kxf2 h6 $15) (8. Bg5 Qe8 9. Nh4+?? Kxg5 10. Nd2 Kh6 11. Nf5+ Kg6 12. Nh4+ { Short, Nigel D - Smeets, Jan, 1/2-1/2, Corus, 2010, https://lichess.org/wf3h1isV }) 8... Nxh1 9. Nc3 d6 (9... h6 { That's the main move now. } 10. Qc4 Kh7 11. Nd5 { [%cal Gd5c7,Gc4c7] } 11... Re8 12. Nxc7 d5 13. Qd3+ Kg8 14. Nxe8 Qxe8 15. Be3 { Van Leeuwen, Etienne - Zajontz, Rainer, 1/2-1/2, EU/C2015/ct05, https://lichess.org/Bro5R2y3 }) 10. Qc4 (10. exd6?! { Opens the e-file for Black's rook. } { [%cal Gh8e8] } 10... cxd6 11. Qc4 { [%cal Gh8e8] }) 10... h6 (10... Re8 11. Nh4+ Kh5 12. Nf3 Kg6) 11. Nd5?! (11. e6 { Locking out the light-squared bishop for now. } { [%csl Gc8] } 11... Kh7 12. Qe4+ Kg8 13. Nd5 { Threatens e7. } { [%cal Ge6e7] } 13... Nc6 14. e7 Qe8 15. Be3 (15. Nxc7 Bf5 16. Qc4+)) 11... Rf8?? (11... c6 12. Nf4+ Kh7 13. Qd3+ Kg8 14. exd6 Qa5+ 15. Bd2 Qf5 { [%cal Gf5d3] } 16. Qe3 Qxc2 $10) 12. Qe4+ Kf7?? { (2.87 → 5.82) Blunder. Bf5 was best. } (12... Bf5 13. Nh4+ Kh7 14. Nxf5 Nf2 15. Kxf2) 13. Bxh6! gxh6 14. Qh7+ Ke8 15. Nxc7+ Qxc7 16. Qxc7 Na6?! (16... Nc6 17. Qxd6 Bf5) 17. Qxd6 Bf5 18. O-O-O Rc8?! (18... Nf2 19. e6 Nc5 20. e7 Ncd3+ 21. cxd3 Rf7 22. Rd2 Nxd3+ 23. Rxd3 Bxd3 24. Qxd3 Rxe7 25. Qg6+) 19. Nd4 Rd8 20. Qxh6 Nf2 21. Qh5+ Kd7 22. e6+ { Black resigns. } 1-0


