5. Bb5 (5. Bc4 { [%cal Gc4f7] } 5... e6 6. f5 { Positional pawn sacrifice. } (6. O-O { If you know that your opponent knows the f5 line, just castle immediately. } 6... Nge7 (6... d6?! { Too quiet. } 7. d3 Nge7 8. Qe1 O-O { [%cal Gf4f5,Ge1h4] }) 7. d3 O-O 8. Qe1 d5 9. Bb3 Nd4 $13) 6... gxf5 (6... exf5 7. d3 Nge7 8. O-O O-O 9. Qe1 d6 10. Qh4 { [%cal Gf3g5,Gh4h7,Gc1g5,Gc3d5,Gc4f7] }) (6... Nge7 { Black just can and should decline the gambit. } 7. fxe6 fxe6 8. d3 d5 9. Bb3 b5! { White cannot take this pawn. } 10. Nxb5? (10. exd5 exd5 11. O-O) 10... Qa5+ 11. Nc3 d4) 7. d3 Nge7 8. O-O { [%cal Bd1e1,Be1g3] }) 5... Nd4! (5... e6 6. Bxc6 bxc6 7. e5 d5 8. exd6 Qxd6 9. d3 Nf6 10. O-O O-O { Here White doesn't have the strong king-side attack, but a slightly more comfortable overall position. }) 6. O-O Nxb5 7. Nxb5 d5 8. e5 (8. exd5 a6 9. Nc3 Nf6 { [%cal Rf6d5] } 10. d4 Nxd5 11. dxc5 Nxc3 12. Qxd8+ Kxd8 13. bxc3 Bxc3 14. Rb1 { Looks better for Black. }) 8... a6 9. Nc3 Bg4 10. d4 cxd4 11. Qxd4 Bxf3 12. Rxf3 e6 13. Qb4! { [%cal Gb4b7,Gb4f8] } 13... b5 $10 (13... Qe7?! 14. Qa4+ Qd7 15. Qxd7+ Kxd7 16. Na4! { [%cal Ga4b6,Ga4c5] }) *


