1. e4 c5 2. Nc3 Nc6 (2... d6) (2... e6) (2... a6) 3. f4 g6 { Main move, but not the only one. d4 is a good place for Black's knight. It is important to keep control over this square. } { [%csl Bd4][%cal Rf8g7,Rg7d4] } (3... e6) 4. Nf3 Bg7 { Now White has to find a place for the ls-bishop. Bc4 is the old line. } 5. Bc4 (5. Bb5 { [%cal Gb5c6] } 5... Nd4 { [%cal Rd4b5] } (5... e6 6. Bxc6 bxc6 7. e5! { [%cal Gc3e4,Ge4d6] }) 6. a4 (6. Bd3 d6 { [%cal Gc8g4] } 7. Nxd4 cxd4 8. Ne2 { [%cal Ge2d4,Gc2c3] } 8... Nf6 9. c3 dxc3 10. dxc3 $15) (6. Nxd4 cxd4 7. Ne2 Nf6 { [%csl Ge4] } 8. e5 (8. d3? Qa5+ 9. c3 Qxb5 $17)) (6. O-O Nxb5 (6... a6?! 7. Bd3) (6... e6?! 7. e5 Ne7 8. Nxd4 cxd4 9. Ne4 $14) 7. Nxb5 d5 (7... d6 8. d3 Nf6 9. Qe1 { [%cal Ge1h4,Gf4f5] }) 8. e5 (8. exd5 a6 (8... Qxd5?? 9. Nc7+) 9. Nc3 Nf6 10. d4 c4 (10... Nxd5?! 11. dxc5 Nxc3 12. Qxd8+ Kxd8 13. bxc3 Bxc3 14. Rb1) 11. Qe2 Nxd5 12. Qxc4 Be6) 8... a6 9. Nc3 Bg4 (9... d4 10. Ne4 Qd5!) 10. d4 cxd4 11. Qxd4 Bxf3 12. Rxf3 e6) 6... Nxb5 7. axb5 { [%csl Gc6,Ga6][%cal Ga1a6,Gb5a6,Gb5c6] }) 5... e6 { Main move and most effective. Stops the bishop and prepares d5. } { [%csl Rd5][%cal Rd7d5] } (5... d6) (5... Nf6? 6. e5 Ng8) 6. O-O { Calmer move. } (6. f5 { More risky. Taking the pawn offers White fantastic compensation. } 6... Nge7 (6... gxf5 { Recapturing would give up control over the center. Black's king side is now wide open. } { [%csl Gd5] } 7. d3 { Just protect the pawn on e4. } 7... Nge7 8. O-O O-O 9. Qe1 { [%cal Ge1g3,Gg3g8] }) (6... exf5 { Hardly better than gxf5 } { [%cal Gc4f7] } 7. d3 Nge7 8. O-O O-O 9. Qe1 d6 10. Qh4 { [%csl Ge7][%cal Gc1g5,Gc3d5] }) 7. fxe6 dxe6 (7... fxe6 8. d3 d5 9. Bb3 (9. exd5?! exd5 { Activates Black's other bishop. } { [%cal Gc8g4] }) 9... b5 { [%cal Gc5c4] } 10. O-O (10. Nxb5? { Loses a piece: } 10... Qa5+ 11. Nc3 d4!) 10... c4 11. dxc4 dxc4 12. Qxd8+ Kxd8) 8. d3 O-O 9. O-O) 6... Nge7 7. d3 { Not f5! } { [%cal Gd1e1,Ge1h4,Gf4f5,Gf3g5] } 7... O-O 8. Qe1 d5! 9. Bb3 Nd4 { [%cal Re7c6] } 10. Nxd4 { White has to give up their precious knight – and with that also the Ng5 plan. } 10... Bxd4+ 11. Kh1 *


