1. d4 e5 { A40 Englund Gambit Complex/General } 2. dxe5 { The only good move here. The declined variations are all at least equalizing. } (2. d5? $10 { Englund Gambit Complex/Declined } 2... Bc5 3. e4 Qh4 { Englund Gambit Complex/Declined/Diemer Counterattack } 4. Qf3 (4. Qe2)) (2. e3? { Englund Gambit/Declined/Reversed French }) (2. Nf3? { Englund Gambit/Declined/Reversed Alekhine } 2... e4 { Englund Gambit/Declined/Reversed Krebs } (2... exd4 3. Nxd4 Nf6 4. Bf4 Nc6) 3. Ng1 { Englund Gambit/Declined/Reversed Brooklyn } (3. Ne5 { Englund Gambit/Declined/Reversed Mokele Mbembe })) 2... Nc6 (2... d6 { Englund Gambit Complex/Hartlaub-Charlick Gambit }) (2... Qh4 { Englund Gambit Complex/Mosquito Gambit }) (2... f6 { Englund Gambit Complex/Soller Gambit }) (2... d5 3. e4 dxe4 4. Qxd8+ Kxd8 5. Nc3 (5. Bf4) 5... Bf5) 3. Nf3 Qe7 { Englund Gambit Complex/Englund Gambit } (3... Bc5 { Englund Gambit Complex/Felbecker Gambit }) (3... f6 { Englund Gambit Complex/Soller Gambit Deferred }) (3... Nge7 { Englund Gambit Complex/Zilbermints Gambit }) (3... h6 { Englund Gambit Complex/Zilbermints Gambit II }) 4. Nc3 (4. Qd5 { Englund Gambit Complex/Stockholm Variation }) (4. Bg5 { Go for a draw? } 4... Qc5 5. Be3 Qe7 6. Bg5 { And repeat. }) (4. Bf4 { This can be seen as a counter-gambit, because White is giving up the b2-pawn. But the compensation is much better than Black's. } 4... f6 (4... Qb4+ { The main move, because it comes with a trap. It's not the best idea for Black though. } { [%cal Rb4e1,Rb4b2] } 5. Bd2 Qxb2 6. Nc3 { The only move. } (6. Bc3?? Bb4! 7. Bxb4 Nxb4 8. Na3 Qxa3 9. Rb1 $19) 6... Bb4 (6... Nb4 { [%cal Rb4c2] } 7. Nd4 { Only move. } 7... Na6 (7... c5? 8. Rb1 Qa3 9. Ndb5 Qa5 10. a3)) 7. Rb1 Qa3 8. Rb3 (8. Nd5 { [%cal Rd5c7] }) 8... Qa5 9. e3 { There is no immediate danger now, so White can prepare castling and completing their development. } (9. a3) 9... Nge7 10. a3 Bxc3 11. Bxc3 Qa4 (11... Qc5 12. Bd3 Ng6 13. Qa1 (13. Be4 { Engine suggestion. Not sure about this. }) 13... Qe7 14. h4! Nf8 15. Nd4 Ne6 (15... Nxe5?? 16. Nf5 { [%cal Rf5g7,Rc3f6] } 16... f6 (16... Nxd3+ 17. cxd3 f6 (17... Qd8 18. Nxg7+ Ke7 19. Bf6+ Kd6 20. Nf5+ Kc5 21. Qe5+ d5 22. Qc3#) 18. Nxe7) 17. Nxe7) 16. Nf5 Qf8 17. O-O b6 18. Be4 Ba6 $16 { [%cal Ra6f1] }) 12. h4! h6 13. h5 Qe4 14. Nd2 Qh7 15. Bd3 Qg8 $18)) 4... Nxe5 5. Nd5 Nxf3+ 6. gxf3 Qd8 7. Bg5 Qxg5 8. Nxc7+ Kd8 9. Nxa8 *


