{ This study is heavily based on Peter Svidler's e-book "The Grünfeld according to Svidler"
https://chess24.com/en/learn/advanced/ebook/the-gruenfeld-according-to-svidler?ref=fuxia

All comment here are his comments unless marked otherwise. Lines that are not part of Svidler's book are marked with a ☆ }
1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 (3. g3 { King's Indian Defense/Fianchetto Variation/Immediate Fianchetto } 3... d5 { Neo-Grünfeld Defense } (3... Bg7 { Stays in the KID theory. })) (3. d5 { E60 Indian Game/Anti-Grünfeld/Advance Variation } 3... Bg7 4. Nc3 O-O 5. e4 d6 6. Bd3) (3. f3 { Indian Game/Anti-Grünfeld/Alekhine Variation } 3... d5 { Neo-Grünfeld Defense/Goglidze Attack }) (3. Nf3 d5 { Neo-Grünfeld Defense/Non- or Delayed Fianchetto } (3... Bg7 { This is technically a King's Indian Defense. } 4. Nc3 (4. g3) (4. Nbd2 { [%cal Re2e4] })) 4. cxd5 Nxd5 5. e4 Nb6 6. h3 Bg7 7. Nc3 O-O 8. Be2 Nc6 9. Be3 f5 10. exf5 Bxf5 11. Qb3+ Kh8 12. d5 Ne5 13. Nxe5 Bxe5 14. O-O) 3... d5 { D80 Grünfeld Defense. The main reference for any Grünfeld player is Peter Svidler's video series on chess24: https://chess24.com/en/learn/advanced/video/the-gruenfeld-according-to-svidler/?ref=fuxia
This study is heavily based on that series } (3... Bg7 { King's Indian Defense. We don't want that today. }) 4. Bf4 { Brinckmann Attack } (4. Nf3 Bg7 { Three Knights Variation } 5. e3 { Three Knights Variation/Burille Variation } (5. Qb3 { Russian Variation } 5... dxc4 6. Qxc4 O-O 7. e4 { Russian Variation/With e4 } (7. Bf4 c6 (7... Na6 8. e4 c5 9. dxc5 Be6 10. Qb5 Bd7 11. Qxb7 Nxc5 12. Qb4 Ne6 13. Be5 a5 14. Qa3 Qb6) 8. e4) 7... Bg4 { Russian Variation/Smyslov Variation } (7... c6 { Russian Variation/Szabo (Boleslavsky) }) (7... b6 { Russian Variation/Levenfish Variation }) (7... a6 { Russian Variation/Hungarian Variation. Main move } 8. e5 b5 9. Qb3 Nfd7 10. e6 fxe6) (7... Na6 { Russian Variation/Prins Variation } 8. Be2 c5 9. d5 e6 10. O-O exd5 11. exd5) (7... Nc6?! { Russian Variation/Byrne (Simagin) Variation } 8. Be2 Nd7) 8. Be3 Nfd7 9. Qb3 { Russian Variation/Smyslov Variation } 9... c5 { Russian Variation/Yugoslav Variation }) (5. Qa4+ { Flohr Variation } 5... Bd7 6. Qb3 dxc4 7. Qxc4 O-O 8. Bf4) (5. Bg5 { Three Knights Variation/Petrosian System } 5... Ne4 6. cxd5 Nxg5 7. Nxg5 e6 { [%cal Rd8d4,Rg7d4,Rd8g5] } 8. Nf3 exd5 9. e3 O-O 10. b4 $10) (5. Bf4 { Three Knights Variation/Hungarian Attack } 5... O-O 6. e3 { Three Knights Variation/Hungarian Variation }) 5... O-O (5... c5 6. Be2 cxd4 7. exd4 Nc6 8. O-O O-O { Three Knights Variation/Burille Variation/Reversed Tarrasch }) 6. Bd3 { Three Knights Variation/Paris Variation } (6. Bd2 { Opocensky Variation }) (6. b4 { Makogonov Variation }) (6. Qb3 { Three Knights Variation/Vienna Variation } 6... e6 { Botvinnik Variation }) 6... c6 7. O-O Bf5 { Flohr Defense } (7... Bg4 { Smyslov Defense })) (4. f3 { Lutikov Variation } 4... c5 5. cxd5 Nxd5 6. Na4 { Lutikov Variation/Murey Attack }) (4. g4 $15 { Gibbon Gambit. The idea is to push Black's knight away, so White can play e4 safely. } 4... dxc4 5. h3 (5. g5) 5... Bg7 6. e4 c5) (4. h4 $10 { Zaitsev Gambit } 4... c6 5. cxd5 cxd5 6. Bf4) (4. Qb3 { Russian Variation/Accelerated Variation } 4... dxc4 5. Qxc4 Bg7 (5... Be6 6. Qb5+ Bd7) 6. e4 O-O 7. Be2) (4. Bg5 { Stockholm Variation } 4... Ne4 (4... c5 { Played by Dubov almost exclusively. }) 5. Bh4 Nxc3 6. bxc3 dxc4 7. e3 Be6 8. Nf3 Bg7) (4. c5?! { This pawn wants to be attacked immediately. } 4... b6 5. cxb6 (5. b4) 5... axb6 { Now Black's rook prevents any checks via Qa4. } { [%cal Ra8a4] }) (4. e3 Bg7 5. Nf3 { Three Knights Variation/Burille Variation } (5. cxd5 Nxd5 6. Nxd5 Qxd5 7. Ne2 O-O 8. Nc3 Qd8 9. Be2 c5 10. d5! e6 11. e4 exd5 12. exd5 b6 (12... Qb6 13. O-O) 13. O-O Bb7 14. Bf3 Nd7) (5. b4 { Makogonov Variation? } 5... O-O 6. Qb3 c6 { Van Wely, Loek - Aronian, Levon, 0-1, Amber-rapid 17th, 2008, https://lichess.org/CY73sHQT }) (5. Qb3 e6 6. Qa3 a5 7. Nf3 c6 8. b3 Na6 9. Bd2 Ne4 10. Qb2 O-O)) (4. cxd5 Nxd5 { Exchange Variation } 5. e4 (5. Na4?! { Exchange Variation/Nadanian Attack } 5... Bg7 6. e4 Nb6 7. Be3 O-O 8. Nf3) (5. Nxd5?! Qxd5 6. e3 Bg7 7. Ne2 O-O) (5. Nf3 Bg7 6. e4 Nxc3 7. bxc3 c5) (5. Bd2 Bg7 6. e4 Nb6 (6... Nxc3 7. Bxc3 O-O 8. Qd2)) 5... Nxc3 6. bxc3 Bg7 7. Bc4 { Exchange Variation/Classical Variation } (7. Nf3 { Exchange Variation/Modern Exchange Variation } 7... c5 8. h3 { Exchange Variation/Modern Exchange Variation/Kramnik's line } (8. Rb1 O-O 9. Be2 Nc6 (9... cxd4 10. cxd4 Qa5+ 11. Bd2 Qxa2 12. O-O Bg4 13. Bg5 h6 14. Be3 Nc6 15. d5 Bxf3 16. Bxf3 Ne5 17. Rxb7 a5 { Kramnik, Vladimir - Svidler, Peter, 1/2-1/2, Zuerich Kortschnoj-B, 2001, https://lichess.org/6JfZyXzP }) 10. d5 Bxc3+ { Exchange Variation/Modern Exchange Variation/Pawn Grab line }) (8. Qb3?! { Happened to me here: https://lichess.org/nGhPVdu5/black#15 } 8... cxd4 9. cxd4 { [%cal Rf1b5] } 9... O-O 10. Be3 Nc6 11. Rd1 Bg4 $15 { [%cal Gd8a5,Gc6a5,Gc6d4] })) 7... c5 { Main move! } (7... O-O 8. Ne2 c5 { Exchange Variation/Spassky Variation } (8... Qd7 { Exchange Variation/Larsen Variation }) (8... Nc6 { Exchange Variation/Simagin's Improved Variation }) 9. O-O Nc6 10. Be3 cxd4 (10... Bg4 11. f3 Na5 (11... Bd7 12. Rb1 Qc7 { [%cal Gc7c4] }) 12. Bxf7+ { Exchange Variation/Seville Variation }) 11. cxd4 Bg4 12. f3 Na5 13. Bd3 Be6 { Exchange Variation/Spassky Variation } 14. d5 { Exchange Variation/Sokolsky Variation }) 8. Ne2 Nc6 9. Be3 O-O 10. O-O Bg4 11. f3 Na5 12. Bd3 cxd4 13. cxd4 Be6 { Transposition to to Exchange/Spassky } 14. d5 { Transposition to Exchange/Sokolksy } 14... Bxa1 15. Qxa1 f6 16. Bh6 Re8 17. Kh1 Rc8 18. Nf4 Bd7 19. e5 Nc4 20. e6 Ba4 21. Nxg6 hxg6 22. Bxg6 Ne5 23. Be4 Bc2 24. Bxc2 Rxc2 25. Qd1 Kh7 (25... Qc7) (25... Qc8)) 4... Bg7 5. e3 (5. Rc1 Nh5) 5... O-O { Brinckmann Attack/Grünfeld Gambit } 6. Rc1 { Brinckmann Attack/Grünfeld Gambit/Capablanca Variation } (6. cxd5 Nxd5 7. Nxd5 Qxd5 8. Bxc7 { Brinckmann Attack/Grünfeld Gambit/Accepted } 8... Na6 9. Bxa6 Qxg2 10. Qf3 Qxf3 11. Nxf3 bxa6 $10) (6. Nf3 { Transposition: Three Knights Variation/Hungarian Variation } 6... c5) 6... c5 7. dxc5 Qa5 { Brinckmann Attack/Reshevsky Gambit } (7... Be6 { Brinckmann Attack/Grünfeld Gambit/Botvinnik Variation }) *


