1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 d5 4. Bg5 { Stockholm Variation. } 4... Ne4 { is the main move } (4... Bg7 { Recommended by Svidler. It's a pawn sacrifice though. } 5. Bxf6 (5. e3 c5 6. Bxf6 (6. Nf3 cxd4 7. Nxd4 (7. exd4) (7. Bxf6 Bxf6 8. Nxd5 Bg7 9. Nxd4 Nc6)) (6. dxc5) 6... Bxf6 7. cxd5 cxd4 8. exd4 O-O 9. Bc4 Qb6 10. Nge2 Qxb2 11. Rb1 Qa3 12. O-O Nd7 13. Ne4 (13. Qd2 Nb6 14. Bb3 Qa5 15. Ng3 Bd7 16. Nge4 { Aronian, Levon - Carlsen, Magnus, 0-1, Wch Blitz 5th, 2009, https://lichess.org/E4YUyFAu }) 13... Nb6 14. Bb3 Bg7 15. Re1 Rd8 16. N2c3 Bf5 17. g4 Bxe4 18. Rxe4 Rac8 { Krasenkow, Michal - Svidler, Peter, 1/2-1/2, Madrid Magistral 7th, 1998, https://lichess.org/9Xo0m487 }) 5... Bxf6 6. cxd5 c6 7. e4 (7. dxc6 Bxd4 8. cxb7 Bxb7 9. Qb3 { [%cal Rb3b7] } 9... Qc7 10. e3 Bg7 11. Bb5+ (11. Nf3 O-O 12. Be2 Nd7 13. O-O Rab8 14. Qa3 Ne5 15. Rab1 (15. Rac1?! Bxf3 16. gxf3 Qb7 { [%cal Gb7f3] } 17. f4 Nf3+ 18. Bxf3 Qxf3 19. Qxe7 Rxb2 20. Ne4 Rxa2 21. Nf6+ Bxf6 (21... Kh8 22. Nd7 { Crouch, Colin S - Svidler, Peter, 1/2-1/2, Lloyds Bank op 15th, 1991, https://lichess.org/ethu8xKR } 22... Qg4+) 22. Qxf6 Qg4+ 23. Kh1 Qh3 $15)) 11... Nc6 12. Nf3 O-O 13. O-O Ne5 14. Nxe5 Qxe5 15. Qa4 (15. e4 { Papaioannou, Ioannis - Svidler, Peter, 0-1, Wch U16, 1992, https://lichess.org/VA9wxO5W })) 7... O-O 8. e5 Bg7 9. Bc4 b5 10. Bb3 b4 11. Nce2 cxd5) (4... c5 { Played by Dubov. } 5. Bxf6 (5. cxd5 Nxd5) 5... exf6 6. cxd5 Qb6 { [%cal Gb6b2] } 7. e3) 5. Bh4 (5. Bf4 Nxc3 6. bxc3 Bg7 7. e3) (5. Nxe4 dxe4 6. e3 (6. Qd2 Bg7 7. e3) 6... Bg7 7. Ne2 c5 8. Qd2) 5... Nxc3 6. bxc3 dxc4 7. e3 Be6 8. Nf3 Bg7 9. Be2 O-O 10. O-O c5 11. Rb1 cxd4 12. Nxd4 Bd5 13. Qc2 Qd7 { Threating e5. } { [%cal Ge7e5] } 14. e4 (14. Rfd1) 14... Bc6 15. Bxc4 Ba4 (15... Rc8 16. Rfd1 Qg4 17. Nxc6 (17. Bxf7+ Kxf7 18. Qb3+ e6 19. Nxc6 Nxc6 20. Rd7+ Kg8 21. Rxg7+! Kxg7 22. Qxb7+ Kf8 23. Bf6 Rab8 24. Qg7+ Ke8 25. Rf1 { Huzman, Alexander - Mikhalevski, Victor, 1-0, ISR-chT 1011, 2011, https://lichess.org/cr4dl6zy }) 17... Nxc6 18. Bg3 Rd8 $10 { [%cal Rb1b7] }) (15... b6 16. Rbd1 Ba4 17. Bb3 Bxb3 18. axb3 Qb7 19. f4 Nc6 20. e5 Nxd4 21. Rxd4 Rad8 { Vachier Lagrave, M. - Volokitin, And, 1/2-1/2, Qatar Masters Open 2014, https://lichess.org/z6xK6WLL }) (15... Bxd4 16. cxd4 Qxd4 17. Rbd1 Qxe4 18. Qxe4 Bxe4 19. Rfe1 Bf5 20. Bxe7 Re8 { Moiseenko, Alexander - Kurnosov, Igor, 1/2-1/2, Moscow Aeroflot op-A, 2009, https://lichess.org/jCSYQaru }) 16. Bb3 Bxb3 17. Qxb3 { [%cal Rb3b7] } 17... b6 *


