1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 d5 4. Bg5 { Stockholm Variation } 4... c5 { This move is played by Daniil Dubov quite often. } 5. Bxf6 (5. Nf3 { Black should take one pawn here } 5... cxd4 (5... dxc4) 6. Nxd4 Bg7 7. Bxf6) 5... exf6 6. cxd5 (6. Nxd5) (6. Nf3) 6... Qb6 7. e3 (7. Nf3) (7. dxc5) 7... cxd4 (7... a6) (7... Qxb2 8. Bb5+ Bd7 9. Bxd7+ Nxd7 10. Nge2 cxd4 (10... Qb6 11. O-O (11. Qa4 Qa6 12. Qxa6 bxa6 13. Rb1 Nb6 14. O-O Rc8 15. Rfc1 f5?! { Moiseenko, Va - Tsydypov, Z., 1-0, 39th Nezhmetdinov Mem, 2017, https://lichess.org/l6IXHsYv } (15... cxd4 { is much better, almost an only-move. } 16. Nxd4 Ba3 17. Rc2 $10)) 11... Qa6) 11. Rb1 Qa3 12. Qxd4 Qa6 13. Nb5 Qa5+ 14. Nec3 a6 15. Qe4+ Kd8 16. O-O axb5 17. Nxb5 $17 { Sammalvuo, T. - Ponomariov, R., 1/2-1/2, European Blitz 2017, https://lichess.org/tl6G6oAq }) 8. Qxd4 (8. Bb5+ Nd7 9. Qxd4 Qxd4 10. exd4 Bg7 (10... Be7 { Jojua, D. - Dubov, Daniil, 1/2-1/2, 18th ch-EUR Indiv 2017, https://lichess.org/A8uwxuw5 })) 8... Qxd4 9. exd4 Bg7 10. Nf3 O-O { Aleksandrov, A. - Dubov, Daniil, 1/2-1/2, 18th ch-EUR Indiv 2017, https://lichess.org/QpcmORXY } *


