1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 d5 4. Bf4 { Brinckmann Attack } 4... Bg7 5. e3 { This is still the main move. } (5. Nb5 Na6 { [%cal Gd5c4,Gd8d4] }) 5... O-O (5... c5 { is playable } 6. dxc5 Qa5 7. Rc1 (7. Qa4+ Qxa4 8. Nxa4 Bd7 9. Nc3 Ne4 10. Nxd5 Na6 11. f3 Nexc5 12. O-O-O (12. Rb1 e6 13. Nc7+ Nxc7 14. Bxc7 Na4 15. Bd6 (15. b3?! Nc3 16. Rc1 Nxa2 $15) 15... Nxb2 16. Ba3 Na4 17. Rxb7 Bf8 18. Bxf8 Rxf8 19. Ne2 Ke7 20. Nd4 Nc5 21. Rb4 { Novikov, Igor A - Sutovsky, Emil, 1/2-1/2, MK Cafe Cup-A, 1998, https://lichess.org/Kph1hW23 }) 12... e6 13. Nc7+ Nxc7 14. Bxc7 Rc8 15. Bd6 b5 16. b3 Nb7 (16... bxc4 17. Bxc4 Na4! 18. Rd2 Bb5 19. Rc2 Bxc4 20. bxc4 Kd7 21. c5 Rc6 22. Ne2 Nxc5 23. Rd1 { Novikov, Igor A - Yermolinsky, Alex, 1/2-1/2, New York op, 1998, https://lichess.org/b8qXcHZs } (23. Bxc5 Rhc8 24. Rd1+ Ke8 25. Rdd2 Rxc5 26. Rxc5 Rxc5+ $10)) 17. Kb1 Nxd6 18. Rxd6 Ke7 19. Rd1 a6 { Vosselman, Jan M - Malashenkov, Alexei, 1/2-1/2, BLR-NED 2014, https://lichess.org/PR6lzEHm }) 7... dxc4 8. Bxc4 O-O) 6. cxd5 (6. Rc1) (6. Nf3) 6... Nxd5 7. Nxd5 Qxd5 8. Bxc7 { Old theory that's long since been known to be harmless for Black. } 8... Na6 9. Bxa6 Qxg2 10. Qf3 Qxf3 11. Nxf3 bxa6 { Here White has half an extra pawn because the pawns on a7 and a6 aren't ideal, but on the other hand Black has the bishops and potential activity. In general, if the position opens up Black shouldn't suffer at all here - and according to the current state of theory the position is going to be opened. } 12. Rg1 (12. Rc1) 12... f6 13. Rc1 (13. Ke2) 13... Rf7 14. Ke2 Bd7 { Now Black has the additional idea of Bb5+ in many lines, while his main idea is of course ...e5, which he'll play against almost any move in this position. That opens the position and when Black's bishops start playing to their full potential it becomes obvious that Black has no problems whatsoever. } 15. Rc3 e5 16. Bd6 (16. dxe5 fxe5 17. Ng5 Bb5+ 18. Ke1 { Gyimesi, Zoltan - Luther, Thomas, 1/2-1/2, Bundesliga 0708, 2008, https://lichess.org/smx42QIX }) 16... Rd8 17. Bc5 Bb5+ 18. Kd2 f5 19. Kc1 exd4 20. Bxd4 f4 21. Ng5 fxe3 22. fxe3 Re7 $10 { Postny, Evgeny - Tseitlin, Mark D, 1-0, ISR-ch, 2010, https://lichess.org/NO0WMf77 } *


