1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Bc4 { Almost a normal Scotch gambit. } 4... Bb4+ 5. c3 dxc3 6. O-O cxb2 7. Bxb2 { [%cal Gb2g7] } 7... Bf8 8. e5 d6 9. Re1 dxe5?? { The decisive blunder. } (9... d5 { is the better move. } 10. Qxd5 (10. Bxd5 Nge7) 10... Qxd5 11. Bxd5) 10. Nxe5?? { Actually not the correct move. Black has now a chance to win again. } (10. Bxf7+ Ke7 11. Qb3 Qd7 12. Bxg8) 10... Qxd1 11. Bxf7+ Ke7? (11... Kd8 12. Nxc6+ bxc6 13. Rxd1+ Ke7) 12. Ng6+ Kxf7 (12... Kd6! { The only move that holds. } 13. Rxd1+ Kc5 14. Nxh8 Nf6) 13. Nxh8# { 1-0 White wins by checkmate. } 1-0


