1. e4 e6 2. c4 { C00 French Defense/Steiner Variation } 2... d5 (2... c5 3. Nf3 Nc6 4. d4 cxd4 5. Nxd4 { Now we have a Maróczy Bind. See https://lichess.org/study/hZMObHz5 }) 3. exd5 exd5 4. cxd5 { And now we have reached the IQP position. Acually, we have *two* IQPs. For the moment. And there is no e6 pawn for Black. This makes the f7-pawn very weak. } { [%csl Bd2,Rf7,Re6] } 4... Nf6 { [%cal Rf6d5,Rd8d5] } (4... Qxd5?! { This helps White to develop with a tempo, similar to the Scandinavian } 5. Nc3 Qd8 6. d4 { Now White controls the square in front of the IQP. This makes a push even easier. Although White doesn't have developed enough material for that. } { [%csl Bd5][%cal Rd4d5] } 6... Nf6 { Stop the pawn } { [%cal Rf6d5,Rd8d5] } 7. Nf3) 5. Bb5+ (5. Nc3 Nxd5 { Here is an opportunity to get rid of the IQP, if that's what you want. Just let Black play Nxc3 } 6. Bc4 Nb6 (6... Nxc3 7. bxc3) 7. Bb3) 5... Nbd7 6. Nc3 *


