1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. exd5 cxd5 4. c4 { 4.c4 marks the beginning of the Panov Attack, sometimes also called the Panov–Botvinnik Attack. 6…Nf6 5.Nc3 e6 is the main line here. } 4... Nf6 5. Nc3 e6 6. Nf3 Bb4 7. cxd5 { And now we have reached the IQP position. } { [%csl Bd4] } 7... Nxd5 { The well known pawn formation. Black is already blocking the IQP with a piece. } { [%csl Ra7,Rb7,Re6,Rf7,Rg7,Rh7,Ga2,Gb2,Gd4,Gf2,Gg2,Gh2] } 8. Bd2 O-O 9. Bd3 Nc6 10. O-O Be7 11. Qe2 (11. Qc2 { [%cal Rd3h7] }) *


