{ These are the basic ideas you should learn in order to get well into the game. For details see the individual chapters. }
1. e4 c5 2. b3 { B20 Sicilian Defense/Snyder Variation. Similar to the Reti Gambit against the French Defense (1.e4 e6 2.b3) and the Euwe Attack against the Caro-Kann (1.e4 c6 2.b3).
The main line here follows the moves that are played mostly. These are not the best moves. } 2... Nc6 (2... b6 { Queen Fianchetto Variation } 3. Bb2 Bb7 4. Nc3 e6 5. Nf3 a6 (5... Nc6 6. d4 cxd4 7. Nxd4 Nf6 8. Nxc6 Bxc6 9. f3 $13 (9. Bd3 Bd6 $10)) 6. d4 cxd4 7. Nxd4 (7. Qxd4 Nc6 8. Qe3 Rc8 9. a3 Nce7) 7... Qc7) (2... e6 3. Bb2 Nc6) (2... g6 3. Bb2 Nf6 4. g3 (4. e5 Nd5 5. d4 Qa5+ (5... cxd4 6. Qxd4 Qa5+ (6... Nc7 7. Nf3 (7. f4 { Bodnaruk, A. - Melia, S., 1-0, 6th Holuj-Radzikowska, 2016, https://lichess.org/Zxm7XTyl }) 7... Bg7 8. Nc3 $14 { d6, O-O, and Nc6 are equal options for Black now. } { [%cal Rd7d6,Re8g8,Rb8c6] }) 7. Nc3 Nxc3 8. Qxc3 Qxc3+ 9. Bxc3 Bg7 10. Ne2 Nc6 11. f4 O-O $14) 6. Qd2 Qxd2+ 7. Nxd2 cxd4 (7... Nb4 { [%cal Rb4c2] } 8. O-O-O { [%cal Rb4a2,Gd4c5] } 8... cxd4 9. Kb1 Bg7 10. Ngf3 N4c6 11. Re1 { [%csl Be5][%cal Gf3e5,Ge1e5,Rc6e5,Rg7e5] } 11... O-O $10) 8. Ngf3! Nc6 9. Nxd4 Bg7 { [%cal Rc6e5,Rg7e5] } 10. N4f3 { [%csl Be5][%cal Gb2e5,Gf3e5,Rc6e5,Rg7e5] } 10... Ndb4 { [%cal Rb4c2] } 11. O-O-O Nxa2+ 12. Kb1 Nab4 $15) 4... Bg7 5. Bg2 O-O 6. Ne2 Nc6 7. O-O e5 8. c4 (8. d3 { Mesropov, Konstantin - Kovchan, Alexander, 1/2-1/2, Zeleny Shum-A, 2017, https://lichess.org/dGv5OPYX }) (8. Nbc3 { Bagirov, Vladimir - Kapengut, Albert Z, 1/2-1/2, URS-ch40, 1972, https://lichess.org/c3dTR7pr }) 8... d6 $10) (2... d6) (2... Nf6 3. e5) (2... e5) 3. Bb2 d6 (3... b6 4. Na3!?) 4. Bb5 Bd7 5. f4 Nf6 6. Qe2 e6 7. Nf3 Be7 8. O-O O-O 9. d3 a6 10. Bxc6 Bxc6 *


