{ Here are the basic lines and short-term plans you should memorize. I took the most common moves for Black and the best moves (according to SF 9) for White. }
1. e4 c5 2. b3 Nc6 (2... d6 3. Bb5+ Nd7 4. Bb2 Nf6 5. d3 g6 6. Nf3 { Play a4, take d7, castle short. } { [%cal Ga2a4,Gb5d7,Be1g1] }) (2... b6 { The only line in which we castle long. } 3. Nc3 Bb7 4. Bb2 e6 5. d4 cxd4 6. Qxd4 { After Nc6 play Qd2, a3, and castle long. } { [%cal Gd4d2,Ga2a3,Be1c1] }) (2... g6 3. Bb2 Nf6 4. g3 Bg7 5. e5 Nd5 6. Bg2 { Play f4, Ne2, and castle short. } { [%cal Gf2f4,Gg1e2,Be1g1] }) (2... e6 3. Nf3 b6 4. d4 cxd4 5. Nxd4 Bb7 6. Nd2 { Play Bd3, Bb2, and castle short. } { [%cal Gf1d3,Gc1b2,Be1g1] }) (2... Nf6 3. e5 Nd5 4. Nf3 Nc6 5. Bb2 e6 6. g3 { Answer g6 with c4, otherwise play Bg2, Nc3, and castle short. } { [%cal Be1g1,Gf1g2,Gb1c3,Gc2c4] }) 3. Bb2 d6 4. Nf3 e5 5. Nc3 g6 6. Bc4 Bg7 7. h3 { Castle short, and play d3. } { [%cal Be1g1,Gd2d3,Ga2a4] } *


