{ Beutiful. Sharp. Might lead to a draw with perfect play. But that has never happened. }
1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 a6 { Kan Variation } 5. Nc3 b5 { Wing Attack } 6. Bd3 Qb6 7. Be3 Bc5 { You would expect a defensive move here, like Be2 or Nce2. But: } 8. Qg4! $10 { Kan Variation/Wing Attack/Christiansen's Dream.
What a beautiful move! } { [%cal Gg4g7] } 8... Bxd4 (8... g6? 9. Nce2 e5 { Prevent White from playing e5. } 10. Nf5! h5 (10... gxf5? 11. Bxc5 Qxc5 12. Qg7 Ke7 13. f3 Nf6 14. Qxh8 Bb7 $16)) 9. e5 { The bishop is pinned, the e-pawn blocks the bishop from protecting g7. } { [%csl Rg7][%cal Rd4e5,Rf6g7,Gg4g7,Ge3b6] } 9... Bxe3 (9... Nc6 10. Qxg7 Bxe5 11. Qxe5 Nxe5 12. Bxb6 Bb7 13. Bd4 (13. f3 Nf6 14. Bd4 d6 15. Bxe5 dxe5 16. O-O-O Nd5 $10) (13. Be4 d5 14. Bd3 Ne7 15. f4 Nxd3+ 16. cxd3 $10) 13... Nxd3+ (13... f6 14. O-O Nxd3 15. cxd3 $10) 14. cxd3 f6 $10) 10. Qxg7 Bxf2+ 11. Kf1 Kd8 (11... Nc6 12. Qxh8 { The knight on g8 is lost no matter what. That's why Kd8 immediately is slightly better. } { [%csl Rg8] } 12... Kd8 (12... Ne7 13. Ne4 Bc5 14. Nf6+ Kd8 15. Nxg8 Kc7) 13. Ne4 Be3 (13... Bd4 14. c3 Kc7 15. Qxg8) 14. Qxg8+ Kc7 15. c3 Nxe5 16. Qg3 d6 $10) 12. Be4 { The rook on h8 isn't going anywhere, let's attack the other rook too. } (12. Qxh8 Kc7 13. Qxg8 Bb7 14. Be4 Nc6 15. Qxh7 Bd4 $13) 12... b4 (12... Ra7?!) (12... Bh4) 13. Na4 Qd4 14. Bxa8 Kc7 15. Qxh8 a5 16. g3! { Get some luft to avoid the mate. } (16. Qxg8?? Ba6+ 17. c4 Bxc4#) 16... Qd2 17. Kg2 { Only move. } 17... Ba7+ 18. Kh3 Qh6+ 19. Kg2 Qd2+ { Draw! } *


