1. e4 { [%eval 0.03] } 1... c5 { [%eval 0.17] } 2. Nf3 { [%eval 0.03] } 2... e5? { [%eval 1.27] } { Jalalabad Variation } (2... g6 3. c3 Bg7 4. d4 cxd4 5. cxd4 d5 6. e5 a6 7. Nc3) 3. Nxe5 { [%eval 1.39] } 3... Qe7 { [%eval 1.34] } { There are only two good answers here: d4 and Nf3. } (3... Nc6 4. Nxc6 dxc6 5. Nc3 Nf6 6. d3 Bd6 7. f4 { [%cal Re4e5] } 7... Bc7 $16) 4. d4 { [%eval 1.33] } (4. Nf3 Qxe4+ 5. Be2 Nf6 6. Nc3) (4. f4?! d6) 4... cxd4 { [%eval 1.42] } 5. Qxd4 { [%eval 1.42] } 5... Nc6 { [%eval 1.72] } 6. Nxc6 { [%eval 1.28] } 6... dxc6 { [%eval 1.31] } { And now White can hold the extra pawn easily. } 7. Nc3 { [%eval 1.26] } 7... Nf6 { [%eval 1.67] } 8. Be2 { [%eval 1.65] } 8... Qc7 { [%eval 2.01] } 9. e5! { [%eval 1.52] } 9... Qd7 { [%eval 1.67] } 10. Qf4 { [%eval 1.35] } *


