1. e4 c5 2. Na3 { Kronberger Variation also known as Zvjaginsev Variation.
Peter Svidler told me: On December 20, 2005, Vadim Zvjaginsev played this against Alexander Khalifman in the Russian Superfinal – successfully! Impressed by that, many Russian players decided to give this opening a go in the Moscow Superblitz on January 5th 2006. The opening has been played 8 times on that day, 3 times alone by Peter Svidler, who never played it before or after that day. } 2... Nc6 (2... d6 3. d3) 3. Bb5 (3. d4? cxd4 4. Bc4 { Nemeth Gambit }) 3... Qc7 4. Nf3 g6 5. c3 a6 6. Bxc6 Qxc6 7. O-O Bg7 8. d4 d6 9. d5 Qc7 10. h3 Nf6 11. Bf4 O-O 12. Re1 b5 13. Qd2 Bb7 14. Rad1 Rfe8 15. c4 Qb6 16. Bh6 Bh8 17. b3 e6 18. Ng5 exd5 19. cxd5 Re7 20. Re3 Rae8 21. Rde1 a5 22. Nb1 b4 23. Qc2 Nd7 24. Nd2 Ba6 25. Ngf3 Ne5 26. Bg5 Nxf3+ 27. Nxf3 Rd7 28. e5 dxe5 29. Nxe5 Rxd5 30. Nxf7 Rxe3 31. Rxe3 Kxf7 32. Re7+ Kf8 33. Qe4 Rd1+ 34. Kh2 Qd6+ 35. f4 Bf6 36. Bh6+ Kg8 37. Qa8+ { Zvjaginsev, Vadim - Khalifman, Alexander, 1-0, RUS-ch Superfinal, 2005, https://lichess.org/8TeESqQp } *


