{ Rare sideline in the Smith-Morra Gambit. Playable for both sides. }
1. e4 c5 2. d4 { B21 Smith-Morra Gambit } 2... cxd4 3. Nf3 { Morphy Gambit } 3... a6 { Don't try to hold the pawn. } (3... e5?! 4. c3 { Andreaschek Gambit } (4. Nxe5? { Nah, that pawn is poisoned: } 4... Qa5+ 5. c3 Qxe5 $19) 4... Nc6 (4... dxc3 5. Nxc3 Nc6 (5... d6 6. Bc4 Nc6 7. Ng5 { [%cal Gc4f7,Gg5f7] } 7... Nh6 8. Qf3 f5 $14) 6. Bc4 Nf6 (6... Bb4) (6... d6?! 7. Ng5 Nh6 8. Qf3 f5 9. h4 f4)) 5. cxd4 exd4 6. Nxd4 Nf6 7. Nc3 Bb4 8. Nxc6 bxc6 9. Bd3) (3... d6 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Be3) (3... Qa5+?! { This does win a pawn, but White has enough compensation in form of a very fast development. } 4. c3 dxc3 5. Nxc3 Nc6 6. Bc4) 4. Nxd4 Nf6 (4... e5 { Transposition: O'Kelly Variation/Normal System/Taimanov Line } 5. Nf3 Nf6) 5. Nc3 e5 6. Nf3 Bb4 7. Bc4 d6 (7... Bxc3+?! 8. bxc3 Nxe4?? 9. Qd5) (7... Qc7 8. Qd3 (8. Bb3 d6 9. O-O Bxc3 10. bxc3 Nbd7 11. Nd2 O-O 12. Re1 Nc5 13. f3 Nxb3 14. axb3 Qxc3 15. Ba3 Be6 16. Nf1 Rfd8 17. Ne3 Rac8 18. Qe2 Rd7 19. Rad1 Ne8 20. Rd3 Qa5 21. Bb2 b5 22. Rd2 Qb6 23. Ra1 a5 24. Qf2 Ra7 25. Ba3 a4 26. bxa4 bxa4 27. Rdd1 Rc3 28. Rd3 Rxd3 29. cxd3 Rc7 30. Rc1 Rxc1+ 31. Bxc1 Nc7 32. Nc4 Qb3 33. Qb6 Qd1+ 34. Kf2 h5 35. Qxc7 Qxc1 36. Qd8+ Kh7 { Agopov, M. - Rapport, R., 0-1, 20th European Teams, 2015, https://lichess.org/tx14m2zw })) 8. O-O Qc7 9. Qd3 Bxc3 10. Qxc3 O-O $10 *


