{ Not as terrible as the engine thinks it is, also not very good. }
1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 d5?! { Nimzo-American Variation } 5. exd5 Qxd5 6. Be3 Nf6 (6... e6 7. Nc3 Bb4 8. Qg4 Nge7 9. Nxc6 { [%cal Rg4b4] } 9... Bxc3+ 10. bxc3 Qxc6 11. Qxg7 Rg8 12. Qe5 Qd5 $16) 7. Nc3 Qa5 8. Qf3 Bd7 9. O-O-O { The following moves are from a blitz game between Vassily Ivanchuk and Zsuzsa Polgar. } 9... e6 10. Nb3 Qb4 11. Be2 Be7 { White is much better here, +3.5! } 12. a3?! (12. Qg3 { [%cal Rg3g7] } 12... Ne4 13. Nxe4 Qxe4 14. Qc7) 12... Qh4 { [%csl Rg4][%cal Rf6g4,Yg4e3,Yg4f2] } 13. h3 (13. g3) 13... g6 14. g3 Qh5 15. g4 Qh4 16. Nc5 O-O-O? (16... Bc8) 17. Bb5? (17. Nb5 Bxc5 18. Bxc5) 17... Bxc5 18. Bxc5 h5 19. Kb1 hxg4 20. hxg4 Qg5? (20... Ne5 21. Qf4 Qxh1 22. Rxh1 Rxh1+ 23. Ka2 Bxb5 24. Nxb5 Rd5 25. Nd6+ { [%cal Rf4f6,Rf6d8] } 25... Kc7 26. Nxf7) 21. Be3 Qe5 22. Bf4 Qc5 23. Rxh8 (23. b4 Qf8 24. Rhe1) 23... Rxh8 24. Bf1? (24. b4 Qf8) 24... g5?? (24... Nd4 25. Qe3 Nxg4 26. Qxd4 Qxd4 27. Rxd4 e5 28. Rc4+ Kb8 29. Bc1) 25. Bd6 Qb6 26. Qxf6 { Ivanchuk, Vassily - Polgar, Zsuzsa, 0-1, Moscow blitz, 1993, https://lichess.org/n3bWaol3 } { And here, that's my guess, Ivanchuk's time run out. The position is absolutely winning for White. } *


