1. e4 c5 2. b4 { Wing Gambit } 2... cxb4 { We take this one … } 3. a3 { … but not this one. } 3... d5 4. exd5 { White takes back in almost all cases. } (4. e5?! Nc6 5. d4 Qb6 6. Nf3 (6. Be3 bxa3 (6... Bf5))) 4... Qxd5 { The crucial square here is e5. } { [%csl Be5][%cal Re5a1,Re5e1] } 5. Nf3 { [%csl Be5][%cal Rf3e5] } (5. axb4?? { If White is greedy and takes the pawn, we get their rook. } { [%csl Be5] } 5... Qe5+ { [%cal Re5e1,Re5a1] } 6. Be2 Qxa1 $18) 5... e5 (5... Bg4?! { Doesn't really work, because White has now a crazy line. } 6. axb4 Bxf3 7. Qxf3 Qxf3 { The only good move. } (7... Qe5+? { Black can't go for the rook anymore, because White's queen is out. } 8. Be2 Qxa1 9. Qxb7 Qxb1?? (9... e6 10. Bb5+ Kd8 11. O-O Qxb1 12. Qxa8 Bd6 13. Qxa7 Qxb4 14. c4 Nh6 $10 { White is up a pawn, down a piece, but their king is safer. }) (9... e5? 10. O-O Qxb1? 11. Bb5+ Kd8 12. d4 Qxc2 13. Bg5+ f6 14. Rc1 { [%cal Rc1c8] } 14... Qxc1+ 15. Bxc1 $18) 10. Qc8#) 8. gxf3 e6 $14 { Equal material, }) 6. c4 Qe6 (6... bxc3?! { Now it's difficult to hold the e-pwn. } 7. Nxc3) 7. d4 exd4+ 8. Be2 Nc6 9. O-O Bd6 $10 { Black should now castle as soon as possible } *


