. Bxd4 cxd4 12. Ne2 g6 13. h4 h5 (13... h6 14. Qb3 e6 15. Bb5 Bg7 16. Qa4 O-O 17. Bxc6 bxc6 18. Qxc6 Rb8 19. b3 { Lenderman, Aleksandr - Le Quang, Liem, 0-1, Saint Louis SPICE Cup op 7th, 2013, https://lichess.org/ED0bIR0O }) 14. Ng5 e6 15. f4 Be7 16. a3 a6 { Zhu, Yi - Nguyen, Thai Dai Van, 1/2-1/2, World Youth Open U16 2017, https://lichess.org/O0iCbnLp }) 11... e6 12. h4 Nxf3 13. Qxf3 a6 14. Qe2?! Nd4 { Katalymov, Boris N - Gusev, Vladimir A, 1/2-1/2, URS-ch sf, 1978, https://lichess.org/Dp3JkOyk }) 11. Bxe6 { [%clk 0:27:47] } 11... Bxe6 { [%clk 1:24:52] } 12. d4?! { [%clk 0:25:18] } (12. Bxc5 { White really should have taken this pawn. } 12... Bg7 $10) 12... cxd4 { [%clk 0:59:45] } 13. Nxd4 { [%clk 0:25:08] } 13... Nxd4 { [%clk 0:59:09] } 14. Bxd4 { [%clk 0:21:25] } (14. Qxd4 Qxd4 15. Bxd4 f6) 14... f6 { Looks odd, but the f-pawn is supported by the e-pawn, and f7 is a safe square for the king now that White's light-squared bishop is gone. } { [%clk 0:58:56] } 15. Qa4+ { [%clk 0:21:15] } 15... Kf7 { [%clk 0:57:46] } 16. Rd1 { [%clk 0:20:51] } (16. Be3 a6 17. Rd1) 16... Qc8 { [%clk 0:56:54] } 17. Be3 { [%clk 0:19:32] } 17... Qc4+ { Trading material is in Black's interest: The fewer pieces are on the board the stronger the bishop pair becomes. } { [%csl Be6,Bf8] [%clk 0:44:32] } 18. Qxc4 { [%clk 0:19:52] } 18... Bxc4+ { [%clk 0:44:58] } 19. Kg1 { [%clk 0:19:53] } 19... Bg7 { [%clk 0:45:21] } 20. f3 { [%clk 0:18:41] } 20... Rhd8 { [%clk 0:45:20] } 21. Kf2 { [%clk 0:18:51] } 21... f5 { [%clk 0:45:27] } 22. exf5 { [%clk 0:13:13] } 22... gxf5 { [%clk 0:45:47] } 23. Rxd8 { [%clk 0:12:25] } (23. Rc1 Rd3 { And now White would have to trade anyway to avoid an invasion on the d-file. } 24. Rhd1 Rad8 25. Rxd3 Rxd3) 23... Rxd8 { [%clk 0:46:13] } 24. Rd1 { [%clk 0:10:19] } 24... Rxd1 { [%clk 0:33:54] } 25. Nxd1 { [%clk 0:10:46] } 25... b6 { [%clk 0:34:18] } 26. a3 { The knight is just a sad piece now: has to protect b2 and can't move anywhere. } { [%csl Gd1,Be3,Bf2,Rc3][%cal Gd1b2,Rg7b2] [%clk 0:10:08] } (26. b3) 26... e5 { [%clk 0:34:37] } 27. g3 { [%clk 0:05:24] } 27... Bf8 { [%clk 0:33:30] } 28. Nc3 { [%clk 0:05:50] } 28... Bd6 { [%clk 0:33:42] } 29. f4 { [%clk 0:03:48] } 29... Ke6 { [%clk 0:33:42] } 30. fxe5 { [%clk 0:04:10] } 30... Bxe5 { [%clk 0:34:08] } 31. Bf4 { [%clk 0:04:33] } 31... Bf6 { [%clk 0:32:16] } 32. Ke3 { [%clk 0:04:45] } 32... b5 { [%clk 0:31:29] } 33. Kd2 { [%clk 0:02:25] } 33... a5 { Black's pawn are running now, supported by both bishops. } { [%csl Ra5,Rb5] [%clk 0:25:27] } 34. b3?! { This maneuver is a bit dubious, because Black will come out with a passed pawn. } { [%clk 0:02:04] } 34... Bxb3 { [%clk 0:25:26] } 35. Nxb5 { [%clk 0:02:31] } 35... Kd5 { [%clk 0:19:37] } 36. Nd6 { [%clk 0:02:11] } 36... Be7 { [%clk 0:19:44] } 37. Nxf5 { [%clk 0:01:06] } 37... Bxa3 { And here is the passed pawn. Black has all the time to push it slowly. } { [%csl Ra5] [%clk 0:20:10] } 38. Kc3 { [%clk 0:01:17] } 38... a4 { [%clk 0:17:15] } 39. Nd4 { [%clk 0:01:37] } 39... Bd1 { [%clk 0:17:36] } 40. Nb5 { [%clk 0:00:44] } 40... Be7 { [%clk 0:15:26] } 41. Kd3? { [%clk 0:00:40] } (41. Bc1) 41... Bb3 { [%clk 0:14:56] } 42. Nc3+ { [%clk 0:00:52] } 42... Kc6 { [%clk 0:12:53] } 43. Ne2 { [%clk 0:00:57] } 43... Bf7 { [%clk 0:12:50] } 44. Be5 { [%clk 0:00:45] } (44. g4) 44... a3 { [%clk 0:12:42] } 45. Bd4 { [%clk 0:00:35] } 45... Kb5 { [%clk 0:12:24] } 46. Kc2 { [%clk 0:00:34] } 46... Kc4 { [%clk 0:12:41] } 47. Bg7 { [%clk 0:00:43] } 47... Bg6+ { [%clk 0:12:55] } 48. Kc1 { [%clk 0:01:09] } 48... Bd3 { [%clk 0:11:42] } 49. Nf4 { [%clk 0:01:01] } 49... Be4 { [%clk 0:12:08] } 50. Kd2 { [%clk 0:00:34] } 50... Bb4+ { [%clk 0:12:27] } 51. Kc1 { [%clk 0:00:37] } 51... Bc3 { [%clk 0:10:01] } 52. Bxc3 { [%clk 0:01:02] } 52... Kxc3 { [%clk 0:10:29] } 53. Ne2+ { [%clk 0:01:27] } 53... Kd3 { [%clk 0:10:21] } 54. Nf4+ { [%clk 0:01:54] } 54... Kc4 { [%clk 0:10:46] } 55. Ne2 { [%clk 0:01:11] } 55... Bd3 { 0-1 White resigns. } { [%clk 0:10:42] } 0-1


