1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Nf6 { Italian Game/Two Knights Defense } 4. d3 { "Modern Bishop's Opening". Main line. } (4. d4 { "Open Variation" } 4... exd4 { Transposition: "Scotch, Scotch Gambit, Dubois Reti Defense" } (4... Bd6 { Transposition: "Scotch Gambit Declined #2" }) (4... d6 { Transposition: "Scotch Gambit Declined" }) (4... Nxe4 { "Two Knights Defense #2" } 5. dxe5) (4... Nxd4 { [%cal Gc4f7,Gf3d4,Gf3e5] })) (4. Nc3 { "Four Knights Game, Italian Variation" }) (4. O-O { (no name?) }) (4. Qe2 { (no name?) }) (4. c3 { "de Riviere Gambit" } { [%csl Re4][%cal Gf6e4] } 4... Nxe4 5. O-O d5 6. Bb5 { [%csl Ge5] } 6... Bd6) (4. Ng5 { "Knight Attack" } 4... d5 $7 (4... Bc5 { Traxler Counterattack }) 5. exd5 $7 Na5 { Polerio Defense } (5... b5 { Ulvestad Variation }) (5... Nd4 { Fritz Variation } 6. d6 (6. c3 Nf5 7. O-O h6 8. Nf3 e4) 6... Qxd6 7. Bxf7+ Ke7 8. Bb3) (5... Nxd5 6. Nxf7 { Fried Liver Attack } (6. d4 { Lolli Attack }) (6. d3 f6 { NN }))) 4... Be7 { Main line. } (4... Bc5 { Transposition: Giuocco Pianissimo }) (4... h6 5. O-O d6 6. c3 g5!?) 5. O-O (5. Bb3 O-O 6. O-O d6 7. c3 Na5 8. Bc2 c5) (5. a4 O-O 6. O-O d6) 5... O-O 6. Re1 d6 7. a4 (7. c3 Na5 8. Bb5) (7. a3 Be6) 7... Na5 (7... Be6 { The idea for Black is here to open the f-file for the rook with an exchange on e6. } 8. Nbd2 { White rather wants to get the knight out with an exchange on c4. The ls-bishop is the "bad bishop" anyway due to White's pawn structure. } 8... Qd7 { Connect the rooks and get the option to trade on e6 with the queen. } 9. c3 { Prevent Black's knight from entering the center. } { [%csl Rd4,Rb4] } 9... Rfd8 { Prepare d5. }) 8. Ba2 c5 9. h3 (9. c3) 9... Nc6 $14 *


