1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Nf6 4. Ng5 d5 5. exd5 Na5 6. d3 { "Kieseritzky Variation" } 6... h6 (6... c6 { Rare move, found only two games in the database. See [Filinkov - Kuebler] and [Hristodoulou - Dounis]. } 7. dxc6 (7. O-O $146 { Castle before it's too late. No game for that in the database. } 7... cxd5 8. Bb5+ Nc6 9. c4 a6 10. Bxc6+ bxc6 { +0.2 This is probably the line easiest to play for White. } { [%cal Gf1e1,Ge1e5,Gc4d5,Rc6d5,Gg5f3] }) 7... Nxc4 8. dxc4 Qxd1+ { Ruin castling for White. } 9. Kxd1 bxc6 $14 { +0.3 } { [%cal Gh1e1,Ge1e5,Gb1c3,Gb1d2] }) (6... Nxc4 7. dxc4 c6 8. dxc6 (8. O-O h6 9. Nf3 e4) 8... Qxd1+ 9. Kxd1 bxc6 { same as 6…c6 }) (6... Bd6 { Stop the d-pawn, and enable castling. } 7. Bb5+ c6 8. dxc6 bxc6 9. Ba4 h6 10. Ne4 { [%cal Re4d6] } 10... Nxe4 11. dxe4 Ba6 { [%csl Gf1] } 12. c3 { b4 will weaken the c6-pawn. } { [%csl Rb4,Gc6][%cal Rb2b4,Rb4a5] } 12... O-O 13. b4 Qh4 { Allowing Black to take e4 will make White's position *very* uncomfortable. } { [%csl Gf1,Ge2,Gd3,Gc4,Gb5][%cal Gh4e4] } 14. Qf3 Nc4 15. Qe2 (15. Bxc6? Rac8) 15... Bb5 16. Bxb5 cxb5) 7. Nf3 e4 8. Qe2 { [%cal Re2e8] } 8... Nxc4 9. dxc4 Bc5 10. Nfd2 O-O 11. Nb3 Bg4 12. Qf1 Bb4+ { Encourage White to mess up the pawn structure. } 13. c3 Be7 14. h3 (14. Be3) 14... Bh5 $15 *


