1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Nf6 4. Ng5 d5 5. exd5 Na5 6. d3 c6 7. dxc6 { [%cal Gc4f7,Gg5f7] } 7... Nxc4 8. dxc4 Qxd1+ 9. Kxd1 bxc6 10. Re1 { [%csl Ge5] } 10... Bd6 (10... Bg4+ 11. f3 O-O-O+ 12. Bd2 Bh5 13. Nc3 (13. Rxe5 Bd6 14. Re2 Bxh2 15. g4 Bf4 16. Kc1 (16. Ne4 Nxg4 17. Ke1 (17. fxg4 Bxg4 18. Ke1 Bxd2+ 19. Rxd2 Rde8 20. Nc3 f5 $17) 17... Be5 18. fxg4 Bxg4 19. Bc3 Bxc3+ 20. Nbxc3 Bxe2 21. Kxe2 f5 22. Nc5 g5 $15) 16... Bxd2+ 17. Nxd2 Bg6 18. b3 Rhe8 19. Rxe8 Rxe8 20. Kb2 Re2 21. Rd1 $14) 13... Bg6 14. Nge4 Rd4 15. c5 Be7 16. Re2 Rhd8 17. Ke1 Nxe4 18. Nxe4 Bxe4 19. fxe4 Bxc5 20. Be3 Rc4 21. Bxc5 Rxc5 22. c3 $10) 11. c5?! { Instead of developing pieces, White goes for a simple pawn attack. b3 would have stabilized the pawns and opened a field for the bishop } (11. b3 h6 12. Nf3 Bg4 13. h3 Bxf3+ 14. gxf3 { [%csl Gg4,Ge4][%cal Rf6g4,Rf6e4] } 14... O-O-O 15. Ke2 { +0.4 } { [%cal Ge2f1] }) 11... Bc7 12. Bf4?! (12. Nc3 O-O 13. Bd2 Nd7 14. Nf3 { +0.3 } { [%cal Ge1e5,Gf3e5] }) 12... Nd7 13. Bxe5?? { Wins a piece. Loses the game. -1.6 } (13. Be3 a5 14. f3 { [%csl Gg4] } 14... O-O 15. a4 h6 16. Ne4 { +0.5 }) 13... Nxe5 14. f4 Bg4+ 15. Kc1 O-O-O!? { Long castling is very unusual in the Two Knights Defense, but here it exploits all the weaknesses in White's position: lack of development, weak d1, and no counterplay. } 16. fxe5 Bxe5 { Rook can't take back, because of the mating threat on d1. } { [%csl Gd1][%cal Gg4d1,Gd8d1] } 17. Ne4? (17. g3 Rhe8 18. Ne4 { [%cal Ge4d6,Gd6e8,Gd6c8] } 18... Kb8 19. Rf1 { [%cal Gf1f7] } 19... Bd4 { [%cal Ge8e4] } 20. Nbd2 { [%cal Gf1f7] } 20... Bh3 { [%cal Gh3g2,Gg2e4,Ge8e4] } 21. Rd1 (21. Rxf7?? Rxe4 22. Nxe4 Be3+ 23. Nd2 Rxd2 24. Re7 Bh6) 21... Rxe4 22. Nxe4 Be3+ 23. Rd2 Rd4! 24. c3 Rxe4) 17... Bf4+ 18. Ned2 Rxd2 19. Nxd2 Rd8 20. Re7?? (20. b4 Bxd2+ 21. Kb2 a5!? 22. Re4 { [%cal Ge4g4] } 22... axb4 { [%cal Gd2c3,Ge4g4] } 23. Rxg4 Bc3+ { [%cal Gd8d1] } 24. Kb3 Bxa1 25. Rxb4) 20... Rxd2 { There is no place for the rook on e7 to hide from a discovered attack. } 21. b3 Re2+ { 0-1 White resigns. } { [%cal Ge2e7,Gf4c1] } 0-1


