1. d4 d5 (1... Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. Nc3 Nbd7 5. Bg5 c6 6. e3 Qa5) 2. c4 e6 { Queen's Gambit Declined } 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. Bg5 Nbd7 5. Nf3 (5. cxd5 exd5 6. Nxd5?? { This is called the Elephant Trap: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Queen's_Gambit_Declined,_Elephant_Trap } 6... Nxd5! 7. Bxd8 Bb4+ 8. Qd2 Kxd8) 5... c6 6. e3 Qa5 { D52 Queen's Gambit Declined: Cambridge Springs Variation.
Unpins the knight on f6, and creates a pin on the knight on c3. The knight on f3 also can't move, because the bishop on g5 is vulnerable to discovery attacks.
Note that black's queenside is difficult to develop. } { [%csl Bf6,Bc3,Bf3,Yc8][%cal Ga5e1,Ra5g5,Rd5c4,Bf3g5] } 7. Nd2 (7. cxd5 Nxd5 (7... exd5)) (7. Bxf6 Nxf6) 7... Bb4 (7... dxc4?! { Maybe too early. It might work in bullet, but in longer games it's better to keept the tension and develop instead. } 8. Bxf6 Nxf6 9. Nxc4 Qc7) 8. Bxf6 (8. Rc1 Ne4 { [%cal Ge4g5,Ge4c3] } 9. Ncxe4 (9. Ndxe4 dxe4 { [%cal Ga5g5] } 10. Bh4 Qxa2 11. Qc2 Nb6 { [%cal Gb6c4,Ga2c4] } (11... Qa5?! 12. Qxe4 Qf5 13. Qxf5 exf5 { Matlakov, M. - Carlsen, M., 0-1, World Blitz 2019, https://lichess.org/DyYXR2Yr }))) (8. Qb3?? dxc4 9. Nxc4 (9. Bxc4) (9. Qxc4 Bxc3) 9... Bxc3+ 10. Qxc3 Qxg5 $19) (8. Qc2 O-O 9. Be2 c5 10. O-O cxd4 11. Nb3 Qb6 12. exd4 dxc4 13. Bxc4 Qc7 14. Qe2 Bxc3 15. bxc3 Ne4 16. Qxe4 Qxc4 17. Rfe1 Nb6 18. Rac1) 8... Nxf6 9. Qc2 (9. Qb3 O-O $10) 9... O-O 10. Bd3 c5 11. Nb3 Qc7 12. dxc5 dxc4 13. Bxc4 Bxc5 14. Nxc5 Qxc5 $10 *


