{ There are actually THREE Exchange variations: 1. D10, the immediate exchange on move 3, 2. D13, the exchange after 3.Nf3 Nf6, and 3. D12 after 4.e3 Bf5. }
1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. cxd5 { D10 Exchange Variation } (3. Nf3 Nf6 4. cxd5 (4. e3 Bf5 5. cxd5 cxd5 6. Nc3 { D12 Exchange Variation/Schallopp Variation }) 4... cxd5 { D13 Exchange Variation } 5. Nc3 Nc6 6. Bf4 Bf5 { D14 Exchange Variation/Symmetrical Line } 7. e3 e6 8. Qb3 Bb4 { D14 Exchange Variation/Trifunovic Variation }) 3... cxd5 { We take back. Always. } (3... Nf6 { Transposition to D06 Queen's Gambit Refused/Marshall Defense/Tan Gambit. } 4. dxc6 Nxc6 { I don't think that there is enough compensation for the pawn. }) 4. Nc3 { [%cal Rc3d5] } (4. Nf3) (4. Bf4) (4. Bg5) 4... Nf6 { [%cal Rf6d5] } 5. Bf4 (5. Nf3) 5... Nc6 { Main move. } (5... Qb6 { [%cal Gb6b2] }) (5... e6 { [%csl Bc8] }) 6. e3 (6. Nf3) 6... a6 (6... Bf5) 7. Bd3 { Main move. } (7. Nf3 Bg4 (7... Bf5)) 7... Bg4 8. Nge2 (8. f3) (8. Nf3) (8. Qb3) 8... e6 9. O-O (9. Rc1) 9... Bd6 (9... Be7) (9... Bxe2) 10. f3 (10. Bxd6) (10. Qd2) 10... Bh5 (10... Bxf4!?) 11. Rc1 Bg6 (11... O-O) 12. Na4 (12. Bxd6 Qxd6) (12. Bxg6 hxg6) *


