{ Not sure what to think about this. a3+b4 structures are a thing, and White doesn't create any self-damage, but … it's so slow and the center looks a bit vacated. }
1. e4 c5 2. a3?! { B20 Mengarini Variation. Probably named after Ariel Mengarini (1919—1998), although I couldn't find a game from him in this line. } 2... g6 { While White is wasting time, Black can do the rather slow fianchetto maneuver and target that weak corner. } (2... Nc6 3. b4 cxb4 (3... Nf6 4. b5 Nd4 5. c3 Ne6 6. e5 Nd5 7. Nf3 d6 8. d4 cxd4 9. cxd4 { Dobrov, Vladimir - Sutovsky, Emil, 1-0, EU-ch Internet 3rd, 2006, https://lichess.org/gXM5EHlo }) 4. axb4 Nxb4 5. d4 { Carlsen, M. - Inarkiev, E., 1-0, World Blitz 2017, https://lichess.org/rY9iA2Ly } { The point of this pawn sacrifice is the strong center. } { [%csl Gd4,Ge4][%cal Gc2c4] }) (2... e6 3. b4 cxb4 4. axb4 Bxb4 5. c3 Be7 6. d4) 3. b4 Bg7 4. Nc3 d6 5. Rb1 Nf6 6. bxc5 dxc5 *


