1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 f5 { The Philidor Countergambit. I really don't recommend this for Black, so I just show how to play against it as White. Black is now wide open for an early attack. } { [%cal Gf1c4,Gf3g5,Gc1g5,Gd1h5,Gc4f7] } 4. Bc4 { Let Black decide if and what to take. Online most people will will play fxe4. Which is losing. } { [%cal Gc4f7,Gf3g5,Gg5f7,Gd1h5,Gc1g5] } 4... Nc6 (4... fxe4 5. Nxe5! d5 (5... dxe5? 6. Qh5+ g6 7. Qxe5+ Qe7 8. Qxh8 { [%cal Gh8g8] } 8... Be6 { [%cal Re6g8] } 9. Bxe6 Qxe6 10. Qxh7 $18) 6. Qh5+ g6 (6... Ke7?? 7. Qf7+ Kd6 8. Qxd5+ Ke7 9. Qf7+ Kd6 10. Nc3 e3 11. Ne4#) 7. Nxg6 { [%cal Gh5h8] } 7... Nf6 { [%cal Rf6h5] } 8. Qe5+ Be7 9. Nxe7 (9. Nxh8?! dxc4 10. Qg5 { [%cal Gg5g8] }) 9... Qxe7 10. Bg5 Qxe5 11. dxe5 dxc4 12. Bxf6 Rg8) (4... exd4 5. O-O fxe4 6. Nxd4) 5. Ng5 Nh6 6. d5 { [%cal Gd5c6] } 6... f4 { [%cal Rd8g5] } 7. h4 Nb8 *


