1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nf6 { B29 Nimzowitsch Variation
The two main responses here are e5 and Nc3 } 3. e5 { Advance Variation } (3. Nc3 { Closed Variation } 3... d6 4. d4 cxd4 5. Nxd4) (3. d3 { goes into a KIA setup } 3... Nc6 4. g3 d5 5. Nbd2 (5. exd5 Nxd5 6. Bg2 g6 7. O-O Bg7) 5... g6 (5... e5 6. Bg2 (6. exd5 Nxd5 7. Bg2 Be7 8. O-O O-O)) 6. Bg2 Bg7 7. O-O O-O) 3... Nd5 4. Nc3 (4. d4 cxd4 5. Qxd4 e6 6. Bc4 Nc6 7. Qe4 d6 8. exd6 Nf6 9. Qe2 (9. Qh4 Bxd6) 9... Bxd6 10. O-O O-O) (4. c4 { Very rare otb, but a common move online. } 4... Nc7 5. d4 cxd4 6. Nxd4 (6. Qxd4) 6... Nc6 (6... g6) 7. Nxc6 bxc6) 4... e6 (4... Nxc3 { Exchange Variation } 5. bxc3 d5 6. exd6 (6. d4 Nc6 7. Be2)) 5. Nxd5 (5. Ne4 f5 (5... Nc6 6. c4 Nb6) 6. Nc3 (6. exf6 Nxf6 7. Nxf6+ Qxf6 8. d4 cxd4)) 5... exd5 6. d4 Nc6 { Main Line } 7. dxc5 Bxc5 8. Qxd5 Qb6 9. Bc4 Bxf2+ 10. Ke2 O-O 11. Rf1 Bc5 12. Ng5 Nd4+ (12... Nxe5 13. Nxf7 (13. Qxe5 d5) 13... Nxf7 14. Rxf7 Qe6+ 15. Qxe6 dxe6 16. Rxf8+ Kxf8) 13. Kd1 Ne6 14. Ne4 d6 (14... Be7 15. Nd6) 15. exd6 Rd8 16. Bd3 Bxd6 17. Qh5 { [%cal Ge4d6,Gh5f7] } 17... f5 18. Rxf5 (18. Nxd6 Qxd6 19. Qxf5 Qxh2 20. Qf7+ Kh8 21. Bg5 Rg8 22. Be3) 18... Qg1+ 19. Rf1 Qxh2 20. Qf7+ Kh8 21. Nxd6 Qxd6 *


