1. d4 (1. Nf3 f5 2. d3! { This is why f5 here doesn't really work:White can now play e4 much earlier than usual, and f5 doesn't prevent that. } 2... d6 { [%cal Gc8f5] } (2... Nf6) 3. e4! { And here it comes. } 3... e5 4. Nc3 Nf6 5. exf5 Bxf5 6. d4 e4 { Looks strong, but see how White has activated both knights and bishops already. } { [%cal Rc1g5,Rf1b5] } 7. Nh4 Bg4 8. Be2 Bxe2 9. Qxe2 d5 10. Bg5 Bb4 11. Qb5+ Nc6 12. Qxb7 Nxd4 $14 13. O-O-O (13. Bxf6 gxf6 { [%cal Ge1g1,Ge1c1] })) 1... f5 { A80 Dutch Defense } 2. g3 { Fianchetto Attack } (2. Qd3 { Kmoch Attack aka Alapin Variation. Named after https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hans_Kmoch and https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Semyon_Alapin } 2... d5 (2... d6 3. g4 { Manhattan Gambit/Anti-Modern }) (2... e6 3. g4 { Manhattan Gambit/Anti-Classical Line }) (2... g6 3. g4 { Manhattan Gambit/Anti-Leningrad }) (2... Nc6 3. Qxf5 Nxd4 4. Qh5+ (4. Qd3 e5 5. Nf3) 4... g6) 3. g4 { Manhattan Gambit/Anti-Stonewall }) (2. Nf3 e5 { Omega-Isis Gambit }) (2. h3 { Korchnoi Attack } 2... Nf6 3. g4 { Janzen-Korchnoi Gambit }) (2. Nc3 { Raphael Variation } 2... d5 (2... Nf6 3. g4 { Spielmann Gambit } (3. Bg5 e6 4. e4)) 3. e4 { Kingfisher Gambit }) (2. g4 { Krejcik Gambit } 2... e5 { Hevendehl Gambit } (2... fxg4 3. e4 e5 4. Nc3 { Krejcik Gambit/Tate Gambit })) (2. e4 { Staunton Gambit } 2... fxe4 { Staunton Gambit/Accepted } (2... d6 { Staunton Gambit/Balogh Defense aka Rat Defense/Balogh Defense }) 3. Nd2 { Staunton Gambit/American Attack } (3. Nc3 Nf6 4. g4 { Staunton Gambit/Tartakower Variation } (4. Bg5 { Staunton Gambit/General Variation } 4... c6 { Staunton Gambit/Chigorin Variation } (4... g6 5. f3 { Staunton Gambit/Lasker Variation })) (4. f3 { Blackmar's Second Gambit }))) (2. Bg5 { Hopton Attack. I recommend this line for White. It is easy to play, and it keeps White's advantage for a long time. }) (2. c4 e6 { A84 Classical Variation } (2... Nf6 { Normal Variation } 3. Nc3 { Queen's Knight Variation } (3. g3 { Fianchetto Variation } 3... g6 { A86 Leningrad Variation } (3... e6 4. Bg2 { A90 Classical Variation (not to confuse with A84) } 4... Bb4+ { Nimzo-Dutch Variation } (4... Be7 { A91 Classical Variation (not to confuse with A84 or A90) } 5. Nh3 { Classical Variation/Blackburne Attack } (5. Nf3 O-O { A92 Classical Variation (not to confuse with the "Classical Variations" A84, A90 or A91) } 6. O-O d5 { Stonewall Variation/General Variation } (6... d6 { A96 Classical Variation (not to confuse with the Classical Variations A84, A90, A91, and A92) } 7. Nc3 Ne4 { Classical Variation/Huisl Variation } (7... a5 { Classical Variation/Buenos Aires Variation }) (7... Qe8 { Classical Variation/Ilyin-Zhenevsky Variation } 8. Qc2 { Classical Variation/Ilyin-Zhenevsky Variation/Alatortsev-Lisitsyn Line } (8. b3 { Classical Variation/Ilyin-Zhenevsky Variation/Modern Main Line }))) (6... Ne4 { Alekhine Variation }) 7. b3 { Classical Variation/Stonewall Variation/Botvinnik Variation } (7. Nc3 c6 { A95 Classical Variation/Stonewall Variation (not to confuse with A94 Classical Variation/Stonewall Variation) }) 7... c6 8. Ba3 { A94 Classical Variation/Stonewall Variation })) (4... d5 5. Nf3 c6 6. O-O Bd6 { Modern Stonewall Variation }) 5. Bd2 Be7 { Nimzo-Dutch Variation/Alekhine Variation }) 4. Bg2 Bg7 5. Nf3 { A87 Leningrad Variation (note the different code number) } 5... O-O 6. O-O d6 7. Nc3 c6 { Leningrad Variation/Warsaw Variation } (7... Nc6 { Leningrad Variation/Matulovic Variation })) 3... d6 4. Nf3 Nc6 { Krause Variation }) 3. Nc3 { Rubinstein Variation } (3. e4 { Bellon Gambit aka A84 Horwitz Defense/Dutch Defense/Bellon Gambit }) (3. Nf3 Nf6 4. g3 c6 5. Bg2 d5 6. O-O Bd6 { Stonewall Variation/Modern Variation })) (2. e3 Nf6) 2... Nf6 (2... g6 3. Bg2 Bg7 4. Nh3 { Leningrad Variation/Karlsbad Variation } 4... Nf6) 3. Bg2 g6 { Semi-Leningrad Variation } (3... e6 4. Nh3 { Blackburne Variation }) (3... d6 4. c4 (4. Nc3 c6 5. e4 fxe4 6. Nxe4 Nxe4 7. Bxe4 Bf5 { [%cal Bd8a5,Ba5e1,Ba5f5] } 8. Qf3 Bxe4 9. Qxe4 Qa5+ 10. c3 { Khenkin, Igor - Vasiukov, Evgeni, 1-0, Voskresensk, 1990, https://lichess.org/tLYJbPNm }) 4... c6 5. Nc3 Qc7 { Hort–Antoshin System }) 4. Nf3 (4. Nh3 Bg7 { Same as 2...g6 3.Bg2 Bg7 4.Nh3 Nf6 }) 4... Bg7 *


