1. c4 { A10 English Opening. Yes, you can play the Dutch against English! These variations reside under ECO A10, and they are rarely played. They might transpose into the Dutch main lines if White plays d4. } 1... f5 { English Opening/Anglo-Dutch Defense } 2. g3 { Statistical main line } (2. e4 { Hickmann Gambit. Similar to the Staunton Gambit. } 2... fxe4 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. g4 $15 { English Opening/Porcupine Variation }) (2. Nf3 d6 3. e4 { Chabanon Gambit }) (2. g4 { Wade Gambit }) (2. Nc3 Nf6 3. e4 { Ferenc Gambit }) (2. b3 { Suggested by Christof Sielecki in his series on the English opening on chess24.com. } 2... e5 (2... Nf6 3. Bb2 e6 $14 (3... g6 4. Bxf6 exf6 $14)) 3. Bb2 Nc6 4. e3 Nf6 $14) (2. d4 { Transposes back to normal Dutch variations. }) 2... Nf6 3. Bg2 g6 (3... e5 4. d4 Bb4+ 5. Bd2 Bxd2+ 6. Qxd2 d6 7. Nc3 O-O $14) 4. Nc3 Bg7 5. d3 O-O 6. e4 fxe4 7. dxe4 d6 8. Nge2 c5 9. O-O Nc6 10. h3 e5 11. f4 Be6 12. Nd5 Qd7 13. g4 exf4 14. Bxf4 { Seuffert, Gabriel - Deglmann, Ludwig, 1-0, Bayern-ch 77th, 2006, https://lichess.org/K1C17VHh } (14. Nexf4 { Seuffert, Gabriel - Ruettinger, Johannes, 1-0, Bayern-chI Bank Hofmann 9th, 2005, https://lichess.org/hDKSjG8e }) *


