1. Nf3 f5 { This is dubious: White hasn't played d4 yet, so they can play e4 with the support of d3. } 2. d3! { This is why f5 here doesn't really work:White can now play e4 much earlier than usual, and f5 doesn't prevent that. } 2... d6 (2... Nf6?! { Looks like a normal move in the Dutch. But … } 3. e4! { Lisitsyn Gambit Deferred } 3... d6 (3... fxe4 4. dxe4 Nxe4 5. Bd3 d5 (5... Nf6 6. Ng5 { [%cal Gg5h7,Bd3g6] } 6... Nc6 (6... g6 7. Nxh7 Rxh7 8. Bxg6+ Rf7 9. Bg5 Nc6 10. O-O))) 4. Nc3 e5 5. exf5 Bxf5 6. d4 e4 7. Nh4 Bg4 (7... Be6 8. d5 Bf7 (8... Bd7 9. g3 Be7 10. Ng2 O-O 11. Nf4 Qe8 12. Bg2 Bg4 13. Qd4 c5 14. Qe3 Na6 15. O-O Nc7 16. Nxe4 Nxe4 (16... Ncxd5?? 17. Qb3 { [%cal Gb3g8] } 17... Rf7 18. Nxd5 Nxd5 19. Qxd5) 17. Bxe4 Qf7 18. Qd3 $16) 9. Nf5 c6 10. Bg5) 8. Be2 Bxe2 9. Qxe2 { [%cal Ge2e4,Gc3e4] } 9... d5 10. Bg5 Bb4 11. Qb5+ Nc6 12. Qxb7 Nxd4) 3. e4! { And here it comes. } 3... e5 { At last Black can play e5 early, something that isn't possible in most other variations. } 4. Nc3 Nf6 (4... Nc6 5. exf5 Bxf5 6. d4) 5. exf5 Bxf5 6. d4 e4 { Looks strong, but see how White has activated both knights and bishops already. } { [%cal Rc1g5,Rf1b5] } 7. Nh4 Bg4 8. Be2 Bxe2 9. Qxe2 d5 10. Bg5 Bb4 11. Qb5+ Nc6 12. Qxb7 Nxd4 $14 13. O-O-O (13. Bxf6 gxf6 { [%cal Ge1g1,Ge1c1] }) *


