{ Here I looked at the Lichess database and took the *most common* responses from White and the *best* moves for Black. If you can memorize these lines, you should get a fine position out of the opening.
The end of a database line is marked with EODB. }
1. d4 f5 2. c4 (2. Nf3 e6 3. c4 Nf6 4. Nc3 Bb4 5. Bd2 (5. Bg5 Bxc3+ 6. bxc3 h6 7. Bxf6 Qxf6 $7 8. e3 O-O 9. Bd3 d6 10. O-O e5 11. e4 Nc6 12. d5 (12. exf5 Bxf5 $10) 12... Ne7 $15) 5... O-O 6. e3 Bxc3 7. Bxc3 Ne4 8. Bd3 b6 9. O-O (9. Bxe4 fxe4 $7 10. Nd2 d5 $10) 9... Bb7 10. Qc2 (10. Rc1 Nxc3 11. Rxc3 c5 $10 { EODB. The following moves are some rather dubious engine suggestions. Not sure about that. } 12. Bc2 Qf6 13. dxc5 bxc5 14. Ba4 Rd8 $14) (10. Bxe4 fxe4 11. Nd2 Qg5 12. Qc2 d5 $10) 10... Nxc3 $7 11. Qxc3 Bxf3 $7 12. gxf3 $7 Qh4 13. Kh1 (13. Kg2 Rf6 14. Rh1) 13... Rf6 14. Rg1 (14. d5 Rg6 $15 { EODB } 15. Be2 Rh6 16. Qe5 $7 d6 $7 17. Qg3 $7 e5 18. Rg1 g6 19. Qxh4 Rxh4 $7) 14... Qxf2 $17 { [%cal Rf2e3,Rf2f3] } 15. Raf1 { EODB } 15... Qxe3 16. d5 Rf7 { [%cal Rc3g7,Rg1g7] } 17. f4 Na6 18. Rg3 Qc5) (2. e4 { Staunton Gambit } 2... fxe4 $7 3. Nc3 Nf6 $7 4. Bg5 g6 5. Bxf6 exf6 $7 6. Nxe4 d5 7. Ng3 Qe7+ 8. Qe2 Na6 $15 { EODB } 9. Nf3 c6 10. c3) 2... Nf6 3. Nc3 { Queen's Knight Variation } 3... b6 4. Nf3 e6 5. Bg5 (5. g3 Ne4 (5... Bb7 6. Bg2 Bb4 7. O-O Bxc3 8. bxc3 Nc6 9. d5 Na5 10. Nd4 O-O (10... Nxc4 11. dxe6 Bxg2 12. Kxg2 O-O 13. Qb3 d5 14. Nxf5 { EODB } 14... Re8 15. Rd1)) 6. Nxe4 fxe4 7. Ng5 Bb4+ 8. Bd2 Qxg5 { EODB } 9. Bxb4 Nc6 10. Bc3 Bb7 11. Bg2 Ne7 12. Rc1 O-O 13. O-O $14) 5... Bb4 6. e3 Bxc3+ (6... Bb7 7. Be2 (7. Bd3 O-O 8. O-O Bxc3 9. bxc3 Qe8 10. Bxf6 Rxf6 11. Re1 d6 12. e4 Bxe4 { EODB } 13. Bxe4 fxe4 14. Rxe4 { Now we are back in the DB. } 14... Qg6 15. Qe2 Nd7 16. Re1 Re8 17. Kh1 e5 { EODB } 18. dxe5 dxe5 19. Nxe5 Rxe5 20. Rxe5 Nxe5 21. Qxe5 $10) 7... Bxc3+ 8. bxc3 O-O 9. O-O d6 10. a4 Qc8 { EODB } (10... a5 11. Rb1 Nbd7 12. Nd2 (12. Qb3 { [%cal Rb3e6] } 12... Qe8 13. Bh4 { EODB }) 12... Qe8 13. f3 (13. Bf3 Bxf3 { EODB }) 13... Qg6 14. Bf4 Nh5 { EODB })) 7. bxc3 O-O 8. Bd3 h6 $10 { EODB } *


