1. d4 f5 2. Qd3 { A80 Dutch Defense: Alapin Variation.
This is also called the Kmoch Attack after Hans Kmoch who played this move first, 1926 against Alekhine. He lost.
It is also sometimes called Manhattan Variation.
The most common response is d5 (that's what Alekhine played), the "best" according to Stockfish is e6. The second best, and rarest response is what has been played here: Nc6. } { [%cal Rd3f5] } 2... Nc6 { I found only two games with this move in the database, from 2002 and 2006. } (2... d5 3. Bf4 e6 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. e3 Bd6 6. Be2 O-O 7. Ne5 c5 8. c3 Nc6 9. Nd2 Qc7 { [%cal Rc6e5,Rd6e5,Rc7e5] } 10. Ndf3 Nd7 11. Nxd7 Bxd7 12. Bxd6 Qxd6 13. O-O c4 14. Qd2 b5 15. Ne1 g5 16. f4 g4 17. b3 Rfb8 { Kmoch - Alekhine, 1926, 0-1 https://lichess.org/W7agVaub }) 3. Nf3 { This is actually the best move, according to SF8/depth 37. The next best moves are a3 and Bf4. } (3. d5 Nb4 4. Qb3 e6 { Schmitz, Manuela - Moritz, Cornelia - 2002, 1-0 https://lichess.org/lKl3d6km }) (3. g4 fxg4 4. Bg2 d5 5. c3 Nf6 { Csukas, Tibor - Hunko, Gyorgy - 2006, 0-1 }) (3. a3 { Second best move. } 3... e6 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. e3 a5 6. Be2 g6 7. O-O Bg7 8. c4 O-O $10) (3. Bf4 { Third best move. } 3... e6 4. e3 Nf6 5. Nf3 Ne4 6. h3 Nb4 { [%cal Rb4d3] } 7. Qd1 Nd5 { [%cal Rd5f4] } 8. Bh2 b6 $10) 3... e6 4. e4?! { (0.35 → -0.23) Inaccuracy. Best move was g3. } (4. g3 Nf6 5. Bg2 Be7 6. O-O O-O 7. a3 d6 8. Rd1 Bd7) (4. c4 Nf6 5. Nc3 b6 6. e3 Bb7) 4... Nb4 5. Qe2 fxe4 6. Qxe4 Nf6 7. Qe2 c5 8. g3 cxd4 9. Nxd4 Bc5 10. Nb3 Bb6 11. Bg2 O-O 12. O-O a5 13. c3 Nc6 14. Be3 a4 15. Nd4 e5 16. Nxc6?! { (0.00 → -0.62) Inaccuracy. Best move was Nc2. } (16. Nc2 d5 17. Nba3 Ra6 18. h3 Be6 19. Rad1 e4 20. Bxb6 Qxb6 21. Nb5 Ne5 22. Ncd4 Bf7) 16... bxc6 17. c4 d5?! { (-0.57 → 0.00) Inaccuracy. Best move was e4. } (17... e4 18. Nc3 d5 19. Bxb6 Qxb6 20. Rab1 Rd8 21. Rfc1 Qb4 22. b3 axb3 23. cxd5 cxd5 24. Rxb3) 18. Nd2? { (0.00 → -1.05) Mistake. Best move was Bxb6. } (18. Bxb6 Qxb6 19. Qxe5 Re8 20. Qc3 Rb8 21. b3 axb3 22. axb3 Qxb3 23. cxd5 cxd5 24. Qc7 Qb6) 18... Bg4 19. f3 Bh5 20. Bf2 Re8 21. cxd5? { (-1.40 → -4.04) Mistake. Best move was Qd3. } (21. Qd3 Qb8 22. Qa3 Ba5 23. Rad1 Bb4 24. Qd3 Bg6 25. Qe2 a3 26. b3 Qb7 27. Rc1 Rab8) 21... cxd5