1. e4 d5 { These two moves are already the Scandinavian defense. From here on we have a few different variations, but basically White is restricted to a limited set of options. } 2. exd5 (2. b4 { Zilbermints Gambit }) (2. b3 { Unnamed Gambit }) (2. Nc3 { https://chess24.com/en/watch/live-tournaments/chinese-championship-2018/5/1/4 } 2... d4 (2... dxe4 3. Nxe4 Nd7 4. d4) (2... e6 3. d4 Bb4 (3... Nf6 4. Bg5 (4. e5 Nfd7 5. f4 c5) 4... dxe4 5. Nxe4 Be7 6. Bxf6 Bxf6) 4. e5 c5 5. a3 Bxc3+ 6. bxc3 Ne7) 3. Nce2 e5 (3... c5) 4. Ng3 Be6 5. Nf3 f6 6. Bb5+ c6) (2. e5) 2... Qxd5 { Mieses-Kotroc Variation } (2... Nf6 3. d4 { Modern Variation } (3. c4 e6 { Icelandic-Palme Gambit } (3... c6 { Panov Transfer } 4. Nc3 cxd5 5. d4 Nc6)) 3... Nxd5 { Marshall Variation } (3... g6 4. c4 b5 { Modern Variation/Wing Gambit }) (3... c6 4. dxc6 e5 { Kadas Gambit }) (3... Bg4 { Portuguese Variation } 4. f3 Bf5 5. Bb5+ Nbd7 { Portuguese Variation/Portuguese Gambit }) 4. Nf3 (4. c4 Nb4 { Kiel Variation } (4... Nb6 5. Nf3 (5. Nc3 e5 6. Nf3 Bg4) 5... g6 6. Nc3 Bg7 7. c5 Nd5 8. Bc4 c6 9. O-O O-O 10. Re1) 5. a3 N4c6 6. d5) 4... Bg4 { Modern Variation/Gipslis Variation } (4... g6 { Richter Variation } 5. c4 Nb6 6. Nc3 Bg7)) (2... c6 { Blackburne-Kloosterboer Gambit } 3. dxc6 Nxc6 { Blackburne Gambit } (3... e5 { Kloosterboer Gambit } 4. cxb7 Bxb7 5. Bb5+ Nc6 6. Nf3 Qb6 7. Qe2)) (2... e5 3. dxe6 Bxe6 { Boehnke Gambit }) 3. Nc3 (3. Nf3 Bg4 4. Be2 Nc6 5. d4 O-O-O 6. c4) (3. d4 { The point of this line is to play c4 first and Nc3 later. 3.Nf3 is just a different move order. } 3... Nc6 4. Nf3 Bg4 5. Be2 O-O-O 6. c4 Qf5 7. Be3 Bxf3 8. Bxf3 Nxd4 9. Bxd4 Qe6+ 10. Be2 Qe4 11. O-O Qxd4 12. Qa4 e6 13. Nc3 Bd6 14. Nb5 Qe5 15. Nxd6+ cxd6 16. Bf3 Kb8 17. Rfe1 Qc5 18. b4 { c4 is a poisoned pawn. If Black takes, then White wins. } 18... Qc7 (18... Qxc4? 19. Bxb7! Ne7 (19... Kxb7 { is bad: } 20. Rac1 { [%cal Ga4c6,Gc1c6] } 20... d5 (20... Qd5 21. Rc7+! Kxc7 22. Qxa7+ Qb7 23. Rc1+ Kd7 24. Qxb7+) 21. Rxc4) 20. Rac1 Qd4 21. Ba6)) (3. c4 Qe4+) 3... Qd6 { Gubinsky-Melts Defense } (3... Qa5 { Main Line } 4. b4 { Leonhardt Gambit } (4. d4 Nf6 { Mieses Variation } (4... e5 { Anderssen Counterattack } 5. Nf3 Bg4 { Anderssen Counterattack/Collijn Variation }) 5. Nf3 Bf5 { Classical Variation } (5... Bg4 6. h3 { Lasker Variation }) (5... c6 6. Bc4 Bf5 { Better than Bg4 } (6... Bg4?! 7. h3 (7. Bxf7+?? { Doesn't work: } 7... Kxf7 8. Ne5+ Qxe5+ 9. dxe5 Bxd1 10. Kxd1 { White is just down a piece. }) 7... Bh5 8. g4 Bg6 9. Ne5 { Gives White the bishop pair. } { [%cal Ge5g6,Ge5f7,Gc4f7] } 9... Nbd7 { Challenge the knight on e5 immediately, before White gets a chance to attack the bishop with another pawn, thus keeping a threat on f7. } 10. Nxg6 hxg6) 7. Bd2 { There are no discovery attacks yet for White, so Black just continues development. } 7... e6 (7... Qc7?! 8. Ne5 { [%cal Gc4f7,Ge5f7] } 8... e6 9. g4 Bg6 10. h4) 8. Nd5 (8. Qe2 Bb4 9. O-O-O Nbd7 10. a3 Bxc3 11. Bxc3 Qc7 12. Ne5 b5 13. Ba2 Be4 14. Nxd7 Qxd7 15. f3 Bd5 16. Bb1) 8... Qd8 9. Nxf6+ Qxf6 10. Qe2 { [%cal Rb8d7,Rf5g4] } 10... Bg4 11. O-O-O) 6. Ne5 c6 7. g4 { Grünfeld Variation })) (3... Qe6+ 4. Be2 Qg6 5. Nf3 (5. Bf3 e5 6. Qe2 Bd6 7. d4)) 4. d4 c6 { Schiller-Pytel Variation } (4... Nf6 5. Nf3 a6 { Bronstein Variation } 6. g3 Bg4 7. Bg2 Nc6 8. O-O O-O-O 9. d5 Ne5 10. Bf4) 5. Bc4 Nf6 6. Nge2 Bf5 7. Bf4 Qb4 { Schiller-Pytel Variation/Modern Variation } *


