1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e5 { A51 Indian Game/Budapest Defense } 3. dxe5 { Accepting is the only move with which White can hold an advantage. All declined variations are good for Black. That's what theory say at least. } (3. d5 $10 { Declined variation. } 3... c6 (3... Bb4+) (3... a5)) (3. e4 $15 exd4 (3... Nxe4) 4. Qxd4 Nc6 5. Qd3) (3. Nf3 exd4 (3... e4 4. Nfd2 c6) 4. Nxd4) (3. Nc3 exd4 4. Qxd4 Nc6 5. Qd1) (3. e3 $10 Bb4+ (3... exd4 4. exd4 d5) 4. Nc3) (3. Bg5 h6 (3... exd4) 4. Bxf6 Qxf6) 3... Ng4 { A52 Budapest Defense/General } (3... Ne4 { Fajarowicz Variation } 4. a3 (4. Qc2 { Fajarowicz-Steiner Variation }) 4... b6 { Fajarowicz Defense/Bonsdorf Variation } 5. g3 Bb7 6. Nf3) 4. Bf4 { Rubinstein Variation } (4. e4 { Alekhine Variation } 4... Nxe5 (4... d6 { Alekhine Variation/Tartakower Defense } 5. Nc3 Nxe5 6. f4 Ned7 7. Be3 Be7) 5. f4 Nec6 { Alekhine Variation/Abonyi Variation }) (4. Nf3 { Adler Variation } 4... Bc5 5. e3 Nc6) (4. e3 Nxe5 5. Be2 (5. Nh3 d6 6. Nf4) 5... Nbc6) (4. Nc3 Nxe5 5. e3 g6 6. b3) 4... Nc6 (4... g5 5. Bg3 Nc6 (5... Bg7 6. Nf3 Nc6) 6. Nf3 Bg7 7. h4) (4... Bb4+ 5. Nd2 (5. Nc3) 5... d6 6. exd6 Qf6 { [%csl Gf2,Gf4,Gb2][%cal Gf6f4,Gf6f2] } (6... Bxd6) 7. e3 g5 8. Bg3 h5 9. h3 h4 10. hxg4 hxg3 11. Rxh8+ Qxh8 12. fxg3 Qxb2 13. Nf3 Bxg4) 5. Nf3 Bb4+ (5... Bc5 6. e3 Qe7) (5... f6 6. exf6 Qxf6 { [%cal Rf6b2,Rf6f4] } 7. e3) 6. Nbd2 (6. Nc3 Bxc3+ 7. bxc3 Qe7 8. Qd5 f6 9. exf6 Nxf6 10. Qd3 d6 11. g3 O-O 12. Bg2 Bg4 13. O-O Rae8) 6... Qe7 7. e3 (7. a3 Ngxe5 8. Nxe5 (8. Bxe5 Nxe5 9. Nxe5 Bxd2+ 10. Qxd2 Qxe5) (8. axb4?? Nd3# { The Kieninger Trap! }) 8... Nxe5 9. e3 (9. Bxe5 Bxd2+ 10. Qxd2 Qxe5 11. g3 { Ernst, Sipke - Reinderman, Dimitri, 1-0, NED-ch57, 2002, https://lichess.org/C9rLZEkH } (11. e3 b6)) (9. axb4 Nd3# { The Kieninger Trap. Again. }) 9... Bxd2+ 10. Qxd2 d6 11. Be2 O-O 12. b4 b6) (7. h3 Ngxe5 8. Nxe5 Nxe5 { Still threatening mate with Nd3#. } { [%csl Bd3][%cal Re5d3,Rd3e1] } 9. e3 { [%csl Gd3][%cal Gf1d3] } 9... O-O $10) 7... Ngxe5 (7... Ncxe5) 8. Nxe5 Nxe5 9. Be2 O-O 10. O-O Bxd2 11. Qxd2 d6 $14 *


