1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e5 3. dxe5 Ng4 4. Nf3 (4. Bf4 { Rubinstein Variation }) 4... Bc5 { Attack f2, enforce e2-e3. } { [%cal Gg4f2,Gc5f2] } (4... Nc6 5. Bf4 (5. Bg5) (5. Nc3) 5... Bb4+ 6. Nbd2 (6. Nc3 Bxc3+ 7. bxc3 Qe7 8. Qd5 f6 9. exf6 Nxf6 10. Qd3 d6 11. g3 O-O 12. Bg2 Bg4 13. O-O Rae8) 6... Qe7 (6... f6) 7. e3 (7. a3 Ngxe5 8. Nxe5 Nxe5 { [%cal Ge5d3,Gd3e1] } 9. e3 Bxd2+ 10. Qxd2 d6 11. Be2 O-O 12. b4) 7... Ngxe5 8. Nxe5 Nxe5 9. Be2 O-O 10. O-O Bxd2 11. Qxd2 d6 12. b4) (4... Bb4+?! $14 5. Nc3 (5. Bd2 Bc5 { Black just lost a tempo. } (5... Qe7 6. Nc3 (6. e3 { Voloshin, Leonid - Koc, Przemyslaw, 1-0, Polanica Zdroj op, 2017, https://lichess.org/lUA3HWYC }) 6... Nxe5 7. Nxe5 (7. e3 { Valles Moreno, Ivan - Fernandez Garcia, Miguel Angel, 1/2-1/2, Boadilla del Monte Eliminatorias, 2007, https://lichess.org/ZOEtorWz }) 7... Qxe5 8. a3 { Priehoda, Vitezslav - Moravec, Michal, 1-0, CZE-chT1W 0809, 2009, https://lichess.org/OpjS3We7 }) 6. e3 Nc6 7. a3 { [%cal Gb2b4] } 7... a5 8. Nc3 O-O $14) (5. Nbd2 Nc6 6. g3 (6. a3 Be7 (6... Bxd2+?! 7. Bxd2 { Oll, Lembit - Yermolinsky, Alex, 1/2-1/2, Agzamov Memorial, 2017, https://lichess.org/Ovtso16V }) 7. b4 Ncxe5 8. e3 d6 $10) 6... O-O 7. Bg2 Ngxe5 8. O-O d6 9. Nxe5 dxe5 10. a3 Bxd2 11. Bxd2 Be6 $10) 5... Qe7 6. Bd2 Nxe5 7. Nxe5 (7. e3 { Valles Moreno, Ivan - Fernandez Garcia, Miguel Angel, 1/2-1/2, Boadilla del Monte Eliminatorias, 2007, https://lichess.org/ZOEtorWz }) 7... Qxe5 8. a3 Bd6 $16 (8... Be7 { Not a comfy place … } 9. Nd5 { [%cal Gd5e7] } 9... Bd8 10. Bc3 $16 { Priehoda, Vitezslav - Moravec, Michal, 1-0, CZE-chT1W 0809, 2009, https://lichess.org/OpjS3We7 } { [%cal Gc3e5,Ge5g7] })) 5. e3 { Now White's bishop cannot protect e5 anymore. } (5. h3?? Bxf2+ 6. Kd2 Ne3 7. Qa4 c6) (5. Nd4? { Saw this once in a game against me. I played Nxe5, which was wrong. Of course. Here is how to handle it correctly: } 5... d6 6. exd6 Qf6 { [%cal Gf6f2,Gg4f2,Gf6d4] } 7. Be3 Nc6 { [%cal Gc6d4,Gf6b2] } (7... Nxe3 8. fxe3 Qh4+ 9. g3 Qe4 { [%cal Ge4h1] } 10. Nf3 Qxe3 { [%cal Ge3f2] } 11. dxc7 Qf2+ 12. Kd2 Na6 13. Nc3 Nxc7 14. Kc1 Qe3+ 15. Qd2 O-O $15) 8. Nc3 { [%csl Be4][%cal Rc3e4,Be4f6,Be4c5] } 8... Nxd4 9. Ne4 Bb4+ 10. Bd2 Qf4! 11. Bxb4 Qxe4 { [%csl Bc2][%cal Gd4c2,Bc2e1,Bc2a1] } 12. Rc1 Nc6 13. Bd2 Qd4 { [%cal Gd4f2,Gg4f2,Gd4d6] } 14. e3 Qxd6 $17) 5... Nc6 { [%cal Gc6e5,Gg4e5] } 6. Be2 (6. Nd4 { [%cal Rd1g4] } 6... Ngxe5 7. Nc3 { Best move } (7. Nxc6 { Main move } 7... dxc6 { Best move, by far!, according to the engine. It makes sense: Black is ahead in development, so go into the end game right now. } (7... Nxc6 { Main move. Third-best. } 8. Nc3 O-O $14) (7... bxc6 { Second-best, second-main move. } 8. Nc3 O-O $10) 8. Qxd8+ Kxd8) 7... O-O 8. Be2 d6 9. O-O Re8 $10) (6. Nc3 Ngxe5 7. b3 O-O $14) 6... O-O (6... Ncxe5 7. Nc3 O-O $10) 7. O-O (7. Nd4 Ngxe5 8. Nc3 d6 9. O-O Re8 $10) 7... Re8 (7... Ncxe5 8. Nd4 { Now the knight has to move. Qh4 is also possible, looks a bit dubious. } { [%cal Re2g4] } 8... Nf6 (8... Qh4?! 9. h3 Nh6 10. Nc3 d6 $14) 9. Nc3 Re8) 8. Nc3 Ngxe5 9. Nxe5 Nxe5 10. b3 a5 *


