1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e5 3. d5 { This is a dubious idea for White: Black has now the a7–g1 diagonal for his bishop, and the pawn on d5 can be challenged easily with c6. } { [%csl Gc5][%cal Gf8c5,Ba7g1,Gc7c6,Bb8c6] } 3... c6 (3... a5 { [%cal Gf8b4] } 4. a3 (4. e3 Bb4+ 5. Bd2 d6 6. Nf3 c6 7. a3 Bxd2+ 8. Qxd2 cxd5 9. Nc3) 4... Bc5 5. Nf3 { [%cal Rf3e5] } 5... d6 6. e3 O-O 7. Nc3 c6 $10) (3... Bb4+ 4. Bd2 (4. Nd2) 4... a5 5. Qc2 d6 6. a3 Bxd2+ 7. Nxd2 Nbd7 8. e4 O-O 9. Ne2 Nh5) (3... Bc5 { Most common move order. There are also a few, rarely played Bb4 lines. } 4. Nc3 (4. e3 d6 5. Nc3 c6 6. Bd3 O-O 7. Nge2 b5! 8. cxb5 cxd5 9. O-O Nbd7 10. a4 a5 11. bxa6 Nb8 12. Na2 Nxa6) 4... d6 (4... O-O) 5. Nf3 (5. e4 Ng4 (5... O-O 6. Bd3 (6. h3 c6 (6... h6 7. a3 a5 8. Bd3 Nh7 9. Nf3 f5 { Gonzalez Rodriguez, Jorge Armando - Sanchez Quiroga, Miguel Angel, 1-0, Sitges op 26th, 2000, https://lichess.org/KDuJiRfU }) 7. Bd3 a6 (7... a5 8. Nge2 Na6 9. O-O Nh5 10. Kh2 Qh4 { Krouzel, Jaroslav - Pokorny, Zdenek, 1-0, CZE-chT2 9900, 2016, https://lichess.org/SFl0tsz3 }) 8. Nge2 cxd5 9. exd5 Ne8 { Mosnegutu, Klaus - Ciobanu, Viorel Adrian, 0-1, Centrocoop June op-A, 2017, https://lichess.org/oKSrZzw4 }) 6... Ng4 7. Nh3 Qh4 (7... h6 8. Qf3 Qf6 9. Qxf6 Nxf6 10. Ng1 Ng4 { Paravic, Ing. Zvonimir - Ketola, Ville, 0-1, CCO17/S2, 2006, https://lichess.org/88sEjIH1 }) 8. O-O h6 9. Qf3 Nf6 { Martys, Mark - Fels, Bernhard, 1/2-1/2, SH.2006.0.00060, https://lichess.org/rNOm1Luq }) 6. Nh3 O-O 7. f3 Ne3 8. Bxe3 Bxe3 { Wimmer, Herbert - Roeder, Frank, 1/2-1/2, Bayern-ch, 2017, https://lichess.org/ZF70VhL5 }) (5. e3) (5. h3) (5. Qc2) (5. Bg5) 5... O-O 6. a3 a5 7. Bg5 e4! 8. Nd4 (8. Nxe4?? Nxe4 { [%cal Gc5f2,Ge4f2] } 9. Be3 (9. Bxd8?? Bxf2#) 9... Bxe3 10. fxe3) 8... h6 9. Bxf6 Qxf6 10. e3) 4. e3 cxd5 5. cxd5 Bb4+ 6. Nc3 { The queen can still protect d5. } { [%cal Bd1d5] } (6. Bd2?! Nxd5 7. Bxb4 Nxb4 8. Nc3 Qe7 $10) 6... Bxc3+ 7. bxc3 Qa5 { [%cal Ga5d5,Ga5c3] } 8. Qb3 Nxd5 { [%cal Gd5c3,Ga5c3] } 9. Ba3 { Nasty. Blocks black from castling anytime soon. } { [%cal Ra3f8] } 9... Nc6 { [%cal Gc6e7,Gd5e7] } (9... Qxc3+?? 10. Qxc3 Nxc3 11. Rc1 { [%csl Bc8,Rc3][%cal Rc1c3,Bc3c8] }) 10. Rc1 Nde7 11. Nf3 d5 $10 *


