1. Nc3 { A00 Van Geet Opening. This a bit dubious already: The knight does not prevent d5 or e5, so Black can claim the center. } 1... d5 (1... e5 { Reversed Nimzowitsch } 2. a3 { Battambang Variation } (2. e3 d5 3. Qh5 Be6 { Hulsemann Gambit } (3... Nf6 { Liebig Gambit }) (3... Be7 4. Qxe5 { [%cal Ge5d5] } 4... Nf6 { [%cal Rd8d5,Rf6d5] } 5. Nb5 { [%cal Gb5c7,Ge5c7] } 5... Na6 6. Nd4) (3... Qd6 4. d4 exd4 5. exd4)) (2. b3 d5 3. e4 dxe4 4. d3 { Gladbacher Gambit }) (2. f4 { Transposition: Bird Opening/From's Gambit/Bahr Gambit } 2... exf4 3. e4 { Transposes back to Van Geet Opening/Nowokunski Gambit }) (2. d4 exd4 3. Qxd4 Nc6 4. Qa4 { Reversed Scandinavian }) (2. Nf3 Bc5 { Billockus-Johansen Gambit } (2... Nc6 3. d4 { Napoleon Attack } 3... exd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6) (2... d6 3. d4 Nd7 4. e4 { Transposition to Philidor Defense/Hanham Variation }))) (1... c5 { A Pseudo-Sicilian } 2. Nf3 (2. e4 { Transposes to a Sicilian Defense/Closed Variation }) (2. b4 { Düsseldorf Gambit } 2... cxb4) (2. d4 cxd4 3. Qxd4 Nc6 4. Qh4 { Novosibirsk Variation }) (2. Rb1 { Twyble Attack }) 2... Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 { Van Geet Opening/Sicilian Two Knights }) (1... Nc6 2. d4 d5 3. e4 { Transposition: Nimzowitsch Defense/Scandinavian Variation/Bogoljubov Variation. The main line in the Nimzowitsch Defense. } 3... e5 { Nimzowitsch Defense/Heinola-Deppe Gambit or Van Geet Opening/Berlin Gambit } 4. dxe5 d4 5. Nd5) (1... f5 { Asking for a Dutch. } 2. e4 (2. d4 { Transposition to Dutch Defense/Raphael Variation }) 2... fxe4 3. d3 { Kluever Gambit } (3. Nxe4 Nf6 4. Nxf6+ exf6 5. d4)) (1... b5 { Laroche Gambit } 2. Nxb5 d5 3. d4) (1... g6 2. h4 { Myers Attack } (2. e4 { Transposition to B06 Modern Defense }) (2. d4 { Transposition to A40 Modern Defense })) (1... e6 2. e4 { Transposition to French Defense/Queen's Knight } (2. d4 d5 { Transposition to Horwitz Defense })) (1... d6 2. f4 (2. d4 g6 3. e4 Bg7 { Transposition to Modern Defense/Standard Defense }) (2. e4 { Transposition to Pirc Defense }) 2... e5 3. fxe5 Nc6 { Hergert Gambit } 4. exd6 Bxd6) (1... Nf6 2. g4 { Tübingen Gambit } (2. Nf3 d5 (2... Nc6 3. e4 d5 4. exd5 Nxd5 5. d4) 3. d4 Bf5 (3... c5 4. Bf4 Nc6) (3... c6 4. Bf4 Bf5) 4. Bf4 e6 5. e3 Bd6 6. Ne5 Nbd7) (2. e4 { Transposition to Alekhine Defense } 2... d5 { Alekhine Defense/Scandinavian Variation } (2... e5 { Transposition to Vienna Game/Falkbeer Variation }) (2... d6 3. d4 { Transposition to Pirc Defense }) (2... g6?! 3. e5 Nh5 4. d4) 3. e5) (2. d4 { Transposition to Indian Game } 2... d5 { Transposition to Veresov Attack } (2... g6 3. e4 d6 { Transposition to Pirc Defense })) (2. f4?! d5) 2... Nxg4) 2. e4 { Transposition to Scandinavian Defense. A good version for Black! } (2. f4 { This is a position that might also arise from a Bird Opening. } 2... d4 (2... e5 { Damhaug Gambit }) (2... g5 { Warsteiner Gambit }) 3. Ne4 e5 { Pfeiffer Gambit } (3... f5 4. Nf2 Nf6 5. Nf3 c5 6. b4 { Jendrossek Gambit }) (3... c5 { Melleby Gambit }) 4. Nf3 { Pfeiffer Gambit/Sleipner Countergambit }) (2. e3 e5 3. d4 Bb4 { Sleipnir Gambit }) (2. d3 Nf6 3. g3 { Venezolana Variation }) (2. d4 { Transposition to Veresov Attack. See my study https://lichess.org/study/WHwhHyO8 }) 2... d4 (2... c6 { Transposition to Caro-Kann Defense } 3. h3 { Caro-Kann Variation/St. Patrick's Attack }) (2... dxe4 3. Nxe4 (3. f3 { Dougherty Gambit }) (3. d3 { Dunst-Perrenet Gambit }) (3. Bc4 { Hector Gambit }) 3... e5 { Grünfeld Defense } (3... Nd7 4. Bc4 (4. d4 Ngf6 5. Nxf6+ Nxf6 6. Nf3) (4. Nf3 Ngf6 5. Nxf6+ Nxf6 6. Bc4 Bf5) 4... Ngf6 (4... e6 5. Nf3 Ngf6) (4... Ndf6 5. Ng3 (5. Ng5 e6))) 4. f4 { Grünfeld Defense/Steiner Gambit }) 3. Nce2 e5 4. Ng3 Be6 { It is important for Black to occupy this diagonal before White does it. } { [%cal Re6a2] } (4... Nc6 5. Bc4 { And this bishop is now very annoying for a while. }) 5. Nf3 f6 6. Bb5+ c6 7. Ba4 Na6 8. Bb3 Bxb3 9. axb3 d3 10. O-O *


