{ This is from a game I had recently: https://lichess.org/8Q8Hqjuc/black

The quest here is to find a way to avoid the draw. }
1. e4 c6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 dxe4 4. Nxe4 Bf5 { I could go for another line, but I think Bf5 is the most principled. } (4... Nd7 { Karpov variation. I played that for a long time. It's okay, but … not very ambitious. }) (4... Nf6 5. Nxf6+ gxf6 { Bronstein-Larsen Variation. Very sharp, almost too much for my taste. } (5... exf6 { Tartakower Variation. Doesn't fit my style. I got beaten up in this line a few times. })) 5. Ng3 Bg6 6. h4 h6 7. Nf3 { [%csl Be5][%cal Rf3e5,Be5g6] } 7... Nd7 { [%csl Be5][%cal Gd7e5,Rf3e5] } (7... e6 8. Ne5 Bh7 9. Bd3 Bxd3 10. Qxd3 Nd7 11. f4 (11. Bf4 Nxe5 12. Bxe5 Qa5+ 13. c3 Nf6 14. O-O (14. Bxf6 gxf6 15. Ne4 Be7 16. Nd2 O-O-O $13) 14... Be7 (14... Ng4))) 8. h5 Bh7 9. Bd3 Bxd3 (9... Ngf6 { Odd sideline. Bent Larsen played this a few times. I don't like it. } 10. Bxh7 Nxh7 { That's … not a good knight. } { [%csl Bh7] }) 10. Qxd3 e6 (10... Ngf6 11. Bd2 e6 { Transposes back to the main line. }) 11. Bd2 Ngf6 12. O-O-O Be7 { B19 Caro-Kann Defense: Classical Variation, Lobron System } (12... Qc7 { Kramnik, Vladimir - Leko, Peter, 1/2-1/2, World Championship, 2004, https://lichess.org/Rr9gKbh8 }) (12... Bd6 13. Ne4 Bc7 14. Nxf6+ Nxf6 15. c4 (15. Qb3) 15... b5 16. cxb5 Qd5 { [%cal Gd5a2,Gd5b5] }) 13. Ne4 Nxe4 (13... O-O 14. Nxf6+ Nxf6 15. g4 { Transposes back to the main line. It's just one move faster. }) (13... Qc7 { This might be playable. } 14. Nxf6+ Nxf6 15. Qe2 { [%cal Rg2g4] } (15. Ne5 { [%csl Rf7][%cal Re5f7] } 15... Bd6 16. f4 O-O-O { White is a bit better here than in the other lines, but it's still playable for Black. } { [%csl Gc5][%cal Gc6c5,Bd8d3,Bd6c5] }) 15... O-O-O!?) (13... Qb6 { Huebner, Robert - Larsen, Bent, 1/2-1/2, Bugojno, 1982, https://lichess.org/KY9MtC4c }) 14. Qxe4 Nf6 15. Qd3 O-O 16. g4?! (16. Kb1 c5) 16... Nxg4 (16... Qd5 { Not better: } 17. g5 Qxa2 { Threatening mate. } { [%cal Ga2a1] } 18. c3 hxg5 (18... Ng4 { [%cal Gg4f2] } 19. Rdg1 Nxf2 20. Qe3 Bxg5 (20... Ba3 21. Qxf2 (21. bxa3? { Now Black has perpetual checks. } { [%csl Gd1,Gd3][%cal Gf2d1,Gf2d3] } 21... Qxa3+ 22. Kb1 Qb3+) 21... Qxb2+ 22. Kd1 hxg5 23. Qe3 { [%cal Ge3g5,Gg5g7] } 23... Qb3+ 24. Ke1 Be7 $18) (20... Qa1+ 21. Kc2 Qa4+ 22. Kb1 Bxg5 23. Nxg5 Nxh1 24. Ne4 { Threat: 24. Rxg7+ Kxg7 25. Qxh6+ Kg8 26. Nf6# } { [%cal Rg1g7] } 24... f6 { Now f6 is protected by the rook. } { [%cal Gf8f6] } 25. Nd6 { [%cal Re3e6] } 25... Kh8 26. Qxe6 Ng3 27. Bxh6! { [%cal Ge6g4] } 27... Qa5 (27... gxh6? 28. Qe3 { [%csl Gh6,Gg3] } 28... Qa5 29. Qxh6+ Kg8 30. Rxg3+ $18)) (20... Nxh1? 21. gxh6 g5 (21... Qa1+ 22. Kc2 Qa4+ 23. Kb1 Qb5 24. Ne5 { Spasov, Vasil - Debray, Christopher, 1-0, Cappelle op 27th, 2011, https://lichess.org/j49Z7YOe }) 22. Nxg5 Ba3 23. bxa3 Qa1+ 24. Kc2 Qa2+ 25. Kd1 Qb1+ 26. Ke2 Qb5+ $18) 21. Qxf2 f6 $16) 19. Bxg5 { [%cal Gh5h6] } 19... Nd5 20. Rdg1 $16) 17. Rhg1 (17. Qe2 Kh8 18. Rhg1 Nf6) 17... Nxf2 (17... f5 { maybe? } 18. Qe2 { [%cal Ge2e6] } 18... Kh8 (18... Qd5?! 19. c4! Qd6 20. Ne5 { [%cal Ge5g4] } 20... Nxe5 (20... Qxd4? 21. Nxg4 fxg4 22. Rxg4 Qxf2 23. Qxe6+ { Leko, Peter - Topalov, Veselin, 1-0, Amber-blindfold 18th, 2009, https://lichess.org/witP8zxu }) 21. dxe5 Qc5 22. Bxh6 $16) 19. Ne5 Nxe5 20. dxe5 Qe8 21. Rg6 $14 { Yee, Soon Wei - Thejkumar, MS., 1/2-1/2, Asia Cities-ch 17th, 2011, https://lichess.org/IISkZBS8 } { White is still better. }) 18. Qe3 (18. Qe2 Nxd1 19. Bxh6 Bf6 20. Bxg7 Bxg7 21. h6 Qf6 22. Rxg7+ Kh8 23. Ng5 Qxh6 24. Rh7+ Qxh7 25. Nxh7 Kxh7 26. Qh5+ { And perpetual checks follow. }) 18... Nxd1 19. Qxh6 Bf6 { My opponent resigned here. Maybe "because" the engine says Black is winning (-4 in depth 23)? It's actually a forced draw: } 20. Bf4 { Threat is Be5 } { [%cal Rf4e5] } (20. Kxd1? Bxd4 21. Nxd4 Qxd4 { [%cal Ga8d8] } 22. Qg5 Qxb2 $19) 20... Bxd4 21. Be5 { Podvoysky, Evgeny Borisovich - Kazantsev, Renal Aleksandrovic, 1/2-1/2, RUS/C10/sf2 (RUS), 2010, https://lichess.org/IsPQxRyu } 21... Be3+ 22. Qxe3 Nxe3 23. Rxg7+ Kh8 24. Rxf7+ Kg8 25. Rg7+ { And that's a draw by repetition. } 0-1


