1. g4 c6 { This is a Caro-Kann inspired line that leads to a less tactical game. Note that White has no Qb3 nonsense, because our light-squared bishop is still on c8. } { [%cal Gc8b7] } 2. Bg2 (2. c4 d5 3. cxd5 cxd5 4. Bg2 Nc6 5. Qb3 d4 { Prevents Nc3. } { [%csl Gc3] } (5... e6 { [%cal Gf8b4] } 6. Nc3)) 2... g6 { And now we fianchetto our dark-squared bishop. The question to White is: What about king safety? Castling short isn't so attractive anymore after g4, and castling into that juicy diagonal? } { [%cal Gg7b2] } (2... d5 3. h3 e5) 3. d4 { Probably White's best move. } (3. c4 { The main move online. This is strategically dubious. } 3... Bg7 4. Nc3) 3... Bg7 *


