5c0S }) (4... Bb4 5. Bg2) 5. Bg2 d6 6. d3 a6 7. O-O O-O 8. Bg5 h6 9. Bxf6 Qxf6 10. Nd5 { [%cal Gd5c7] } 10... Qd8 $10) 4... Bb4 { C49 Four Knights Game/Double Spanish } (4... Bc5 { C48 Four Knights Game/Spanish Variation/Classical Variation } 5. Nxe5 Nd4 6. Ba4 O-O { C48 Four Knights Game/Spanish Variation/Classical Variation/Marshall Gambit }) (4... Nd4 { C48 Four Knights Game/Spanish Variation/Rubinstein Variation } 5. Nxe5 (5. Nxd4 { C48 Four Knights Game/Spanish Variation/Rubinstein Variation/Accepted }) 5... Qe7 6. f4 { C48 Four Knights Game/Spanish Variation/Rubinstein Variation #2. Again weird naming. }) (4... a6 5. Bxc6 { C48 Four Knights Game/Ranken Variation }) 5. O-O O-O 6. d3 { C94 Four Knights Game/Double Spanish, with 5.O-O } (6. Bxc6 { C49 Four Knights Game/Nimzowitsch (Paulsen) }) (6. Nd5 Nxd5 7. exd5 e4 { C49 Four Knights Game/Gunsberg Counterattack }) 6... d6 { C49 Four Knights Game/Spanish Variation/Symmetrical Variation #3 } (6... Bxc3 { C49 Four Knights Game/Spanish Variation. Weirdly, the same name as the plain 4.Bb5 – but a different ECO code. } 7. bxc3 d6 8. Re1 { C49 Four Knights Game/Janowski Variation }) 7. Bg5 (7. Ne2 { C49 Four Knights Game/Spanish Variation/Symmetrical Variation #4 }) 7... Bxc3 (7... Ne7 { C49 Four Knights Game/Spanish Variation/Symmetrical Variation #2 }) 8. bxc3 Qe7 9. Re1 Nd8 10. d4 Bg4 { C49 Four Knights Game/Spanish Variation/Symmetrical Variation } *


