1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3 Nf6 { C46 Four Knights Game } 4. Bb5 { C48 Spanish Variation } 4... Bb4 { C49 Double Spanish } (4... Bc5 { C48 Classical Variation } 5. Nxe5 Nd4 6. Ba4 O-O { C48 Classical Variation/Marshall Gambit }) (4... Nd4 { C48 Rubinstein Variation } 5. Nxe5 { Black can get that pawn. } (5. Nxd4 { C48 Rubinstein Variation/Accepted }) (5. Bc4 Nxf3+ 6. Qxf3) 5... Qe7 6. f4 { C48 Rubinstein Variation #2. Again weird naming. } (6. Nf3 Nxb5 7. Nxb5 Qxe4+ { Got the pawn back. And black has the bishop pair. } 8. Qe2 Qxe2+ 9. Kxe2 Nd5 10. c4 a6)) (4... a6 5. Bxc6 { C48 Ranken Variation } 5... dxc6 6. Nxe5 Nxe4 7. Nxe4 Qd4 8. O-O Qxe5 9. d4 Qf5 10. Ng3) 5. O-O O-O 6. d3 { C94 Double Spanish, with 5.O-O } (6. Bxc6 { C49 Nimzowitsch (Paulsen) }) (6. Nd5 Nxd5 7. exd5 e4 { C49 Gunsberg Counterattack }) 6... d6 { C49 Symmetrical Variation #3 } (6... Bxc3 { C49 Spanish Variation. Weirdly, the same name as the plain 4.Bb5 - but a different ECO code. } 7. bxc3 d6 8. Re1 { C49 Janowski Variation }) 7. Bg5 (7. Ne2 { C49 Symmetrical Variation #4 }) 7... Bxc3 (7... Ne7 { C49 Symmetrical Variation #2 }) 8. bxc3 Qe7 (8... h6 9. Bh4) 9. Re1 Nd8 10. d4 Ne6 (10... Bg4 { C49 Symmetrical Variation }) 11. Bc1 { C49 Symmetrical Variation, Metger Unpin } 11... Rd8 *


