1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3 Nf6 { C46 Four Knights Game } 4. Nxe5 { C46 Four Knights Game/Halloween Gambit, also known as the Müller–Schulze Gambit or Leipzig Gambit. A good resource is https://timkr.home.xs4all.nl/tour/breeze.htm } 4... Nxe5 5. d4 Ng6 (5... Nc6 6. d5 Ne5 (6... Bb4?! { "Pinksi's Move" after the Polish IM Jan Pinski. Allows White to get an almost equal game. } 7. dxc6 bxc6 $10 { This is an equal position that can also arise from a 4 Knights/Scotch. Example: } { Nakamura, Hi - Carlsen, M., 0-1, Zurich CC Blitz 2014, https://lichess.org/qustMeqJ } (7... Nxe4 $10 8. Qd4 Qe7 9. Be3 (9. Qxg7 { The line suggested by Pinski. } 9... Nxc3+ 10. Be3 Nd5+ (10... Ne4+ { looks better }) 11. c3 Rf8 12. cxb4 Nxe3 13. fxe3 Qxb4+) 9... f5 (9... O-O 10. Bd3 Nxc3 11. bxc3 Ba5 12. O-O Bb6 13. Qf4 Bxe3 14. fxe3 dxc6) 10. cxd7+ Bxd7 { Sigfusson, Sigurdur - Bellin, Robert, 0-1, Reykjavik IM, 2007, https://lichess.org/8dJjMWuD })) 7. f4 Ng6 8. e5 Ng8 9. d6 (9. Qe2 { This is a line in which White actually can get the piece back! } 9... Bb4 10. f5 N6e7 11. f6 gxf6 12. exf6 Nxf6 13. Qe5 O-O 14. Qxf6 Nxd5 15. Qd4 Re8+ 16. Kd1 Nxc3+ 17. bxc3 d5 18. Bh6 (18. cxb4?? { Can't take the bishop: } 18... Re4 19. Qf2 Bg4+ 20. Kd2 Qg5+ 21. Kd3 Qg6 22. Kd2 Qh6+ 23. Kd3 Qc6 24. h3 Bd1 25. Qc5 Qg6 26. Kc3 a5 $19) 18... Bf8 19. Bxf8 Qg5 20. h3 (20. Bb4?? Bg4+ 21. Qxg4 Qxg4+)) 9... cxd6 10. exd6 { [%cal Gc3b5,Gb5c7] } 10... Qf6 11. Nb5 (11. Qe2+ Kd8 12. Ne4 Qe6 13. Be3 { Threat: Ng5. } { [%csl Gg5][%cal Ge4g5,Bg5e6,Bg5f7] } 13... h6 { Engine suggestion. But the eval jumps from -1.2 to -0.1 here. Needs further analysis. } 14. O-O-O Nf6 $16) 11... Rb8 { C46 Plasma Variation }) 6. e5 Ng8 (6... Bb4 { Recommended by Eric Schiller } 7. exf6 Qxf6 $10 { The engine sees this as equal with a tiny advantage for White. }) 7. Bc4 (7. Qf3 c6 8. Bc4 { [%cal Gc4f7,Gf3f7] } 8... f5 (8... d5) 9. h4 (9. Ne2) (9. O-O) 9... d5 10. exd6 Bxd6 11. h5) 7... d6 (7... Bb4 8. Qf3 f5 { C46 Oldtimer Variation }) (7... d5 { This line was recommended by Max Euwe. } 8. Bxd5 c6 $15) 8. Qf3 f6 9. exd6 (9. h4 dxe5 10. h5 N6e7 11. Be3 Nf5 12. O-O-O Nxe3 13. Qxe3 Bd6 14. dxe5 fxe5 15. f4 Nf6 16. h6 g6 17. Rhe1 Ng4 18. Qf3 Rf8 19. Bb5+ c6 20. Ne4 Rxf4 21. Nxd6+ Kf8 22. Qc3 Qe7 23. Rf1 Rxf1 24. Rxf1+ Nf6 25. Ne4 Bf5 26. Nxf6 cxb5 27. Nd5 Qd6 28. g4 Qxd5 29. gxf5 Qg2 30. Qb4+ Kg8 31. Qb3+ Kf8 32. Qxb5 gxf5 33. Rxf5+ Kg8 34. b4 Rc8 35. Qd3 Qh1+ 36. Kb2 Qxh6 37. Qd5+ Kh8 38. Qxb7 Re8 39. Qd7 Rf8 40. Rxe5 Qf4 41. Qd6 Rf7 42. b5 Kg7 43. a4 h6 44. a5 Kh7 45. b6 axb6 46. axb6 Kg7 47. Re6 { Guzman, Carlos M - Larsson, Mats, 1-0, ST.2006.0.00001, https://lichess.org/yEfZ87Xk }) 9... Bxd6 10. O-O Qd7 11. Re1+ Kd8 $17 *


