1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. d4 Bb4?! { (-0.14 → 0.43) Inaccuracy. exd4 is the normal continuation here for a good reason. Bb4 invites White to play this gambit. } (4... exd4 5. Nxd4 Bb4 6. Nxc6 bxc6 7. Bd3 O-O 8. O-O d5 9. Qf3 Re8 10. Bg5 Bxc3 11. bxc3) 5. Nxe5 { C47 Four Knights Game: Scotch Variation, Krause Gambit. The d4-pawn is left hanging. But Nxe5 is actually the best move for White here. } { [%csl Gd4] } 5... O-O (5... Qe7 { Leonhardt Defense. The common – and best – continuation. }) 6. Bd3 (6. Qd3 { Main move in this position. }) 6... Nxd4 7. O-O d6 8. Nc4 { The only move. Nf3 would get pinned by Bg4. } 8... Bxc3 { Bg4 was better. But I couldn't find any game with that move in the database. } 9. bxc3 Ne6 { Prevents Bg5. } { [%csl Rg5][%cal Re6g5] } 10. Ne3 (10. e5 { This would have been the best move, according to SF depth 39. Followed by Qf3 and Re1. } 10... dxe5 11. Nxe5 { Opens the center for the bishop pair. }) 10... Re8 11. c4 Nc5 { [%cal Rc5e4,Rf6e4,Re8e4] } 12. f3 Nfd7 13. Rb1 Ne5?! { (0.00 → 0.59) Inaccuracy. Best move was b6. } (13... b6 14. Bb2 Bb7 15. Qe1 Qg5 16. Nd5 Rac8 17. Bd4 Qg6 18. Nf4 Qg5 19. Be3 Qf6 20. Nd5) 14. Bb2 f6 15. Qd2 Be6 16. Rbe1 Qd7 17. f4 Nexd3 18. cxd3 f5 19. Rf3 Re7 20. Rg3 Rf7?! { (0.81 → 1.55) Inaccuracy. Best move was fxe4. } (20... fxe4 21. f5 Bxf5 22. Nd5 Bg6 23. Nxe7+ Qxe7 24. dxe4 Rd8 25. Qd5+ Kh8 26. e5 c6 27. Qd4) 21. exf5 Bxf5 22. Rg5 Bxd3 23. Ng4 Bg6? { (1.83 → 3.21) Mistake. Best move was Kf8. } (23... Kf8 24. Nh6 Ne4 25. Rxg7 Rxg7 26. Qxd3 Rg6 27. Rxe4 Rxh6 28. Qd4 Rg6 29. Qh8+ Rg8 30. Qf6+) 24. f5 Rxf5? { (3.03 → 5.16) Mistake. Best move was Re8. } (24... Re8 25. fxg6 Rxe1+ 26. Qxe1 hxg6 27. Qb1 Qe7 28. Nh6+ Kf8 29. Nxf7 Qe3+ 30. Kh1 Ne4 31. h3) 25. Nh6+! gxh6 26. Qd4 Ne6 27. Qh8+? { (5.58 → 3.87) Mistake. Best move was Rxe6. } (27. Rxe6 hxg5 28. Re1 Re5 29. Rxe5 Kf8 30. Re2 Qf7 31. Rf2 Qxf2+ 32. Kxf2 Ke7 33. Qg7+ Ke6) 27... Kf7 28. Rxf5+ Bxf5 29. Qf6+ Kg8 30. Qxf5? { (3.28 → 2.20) Mistake. Best move was Qh8+. } (30. Qh8+) 30... Nf8?? { (2.20 → 5.76) Blunder. Best move was Qf7. } (30... Qf7 31. Qxe6 Qxe6 32. Rxe6 Rf8 33. Re7 Rf7 34. Re8+ Rf8 35. Rxf8+ Kxf8 36. Kf2 Ke7 37. Kf3) 31. Qd5+ Qf7 32. Re7 { White wins. } 1-0


