1. e4 e5 2. Ne2 { C20 Alapin Opening. This is of course not a very good move: It doesn't attack anything, and the light-squared bishop is blocked, which means White has to waste an extra tempo to get it out.
On the other hand, White can play an early f4, like a King's Gambit without the pawn sacrifice. Or the knight goes to g3 where it protects e4. } { [%csl Bf1][%cal Gf2f4,Ge2f4,Re2g3] } 2... Nf6 { Attacks e4. } { [%cal Rf6e4] } (2... Nc6 3. Nbc3 Bc5 4. f4 (4. Na4 Be7 (4... d6 5. Nxc5 dxc5 6. d3 Be6 7. Be3 Qd6 8. Nc3 O-O-O 9. Be2 f6 10. O-O g5 { Shanava, K. - Beradze, I., 1/2-1/2, Georgian Cup 2016, https://lichess.org/E9yClm2T }) 5. d4 exd4 (5... d6 6. d5 Nb8 7. c4 Na6 8. Ng3 Bg5 9. c5 Nxc5 10. Bxg5 Qxg5 { Shanava, K. - Demchenko, A., 0-1, TCh-TUR 1st League 2017, https://lichess.org/ylvG0fm0 }) 6. Nxd4 Nf6 7. Nxc6 bxc6 8. e5 Nd5 9. c4 Nb6 10. Nc3 O-O { Castaldo, Folco - Huebner, Robert, 1/2-1/2, Porto San Giorgio op 18th, 2006, https://lichess.org/REfTKjtl }) 4... d6 5. Na4 Bg4 6. Nxc5 dxc5 7. d3 Qh4+ 8. g3 Qh5 9. Kf2 Bf3 10. Rg1 Nd4 { Schramm, C. - Naiditsch, A., 0-1, Bundesliga 2016-17, https://lichess.org/B8p0uZSP }) (2... Bc5) (2... d5 3. exd5 Nf6 4. d4 exd4 5. Qxd4 Qxd5 6. Nbc3 Qxd4 7. Nxd4 Bc5 8. Ndb5 Na6 9. Bf4 O-O { Ivanchuk, V. - Carlsen, M., 0-1, GCT Blitz YourNextMove, 2017, https://lichess.org/caoLToDP }) (2... c6 3. Ng3 d6 4. d3 Nd7 5. Nd2 Nc5 6. Nb3 Ne6 7. Ne2 Nc5 8. Nc3 Ne6 9. g3 Nf6 10. Bg2 Be7 { Palac, Mladen - Zelcic, Robert, 1/2-1/2, CRO-ch, 2011, https://lichess.org/LVoJLbXy }) 3. d4 { We have a similar position in the Petrov Defense/Modern Attack, but with a knight on f3. https://lichess.org/study/yVVpkkLT/5Fs3l7mt
And this is already the first opportunity for Black to make the wrong decision. Nxe4 is the only good move. } (3. Nbc3 Nc6 (3... d5 4. exd5 Nxd5 5. g3 Nxc3 6. Nxc3 Bd7 7. d4 exd4 8. Qxd4 Nc6 9. Qe3+ Qe7 10. Bg2 O-O-O { Bachmann Schiavo, Axel - Melkumyan, Hrant, 0-1, Dos Hermanas Internet f 9th, 2008, https://lichess.org/JLCml5WU }) 4. g3 (4. f4 d5 5. fxe5 Nxe4 6. d4 Be7 7. Nxe4 dxe4 8. c3 f6 9. Nf4 Bf5 10. exf6 Bxf6 { Kornev, Alexei - Bakalarz, Mieczyslaw, 1-0, EU-ch 6th, 2005, https://lichess.org/PbE4ScuD }) 4... Bc5 5. Bg2 { This position happens usually in a Vienna opening. } 5... a6 6. d3 d6 7. O-O O-O 8. h3 Be6 9. Kh2 d5 10. Bg5 d4 { Bachmann Schiavo, Axel - Khachiyan, Melikset, 0-1, Edmonton 2nd, 2007, https://lichess.org/Qn1aiiuL }) (3. f4 Nxe4 (3... exf4 4. Nxf4 d5 5. Nxd5 Nxd5 (5... Nxe4) 6. exd5 Qxd5 7. Nc3)) 3... Nxe4 (3... exd4?! { Gives White the tempo back. } 4. e5 Ne4 (4... Ng4?! 5. Nxd4 { The only move! } (5. Qxd4? { [%cal Gd4g4] } 5... d6 { [%cal Rc8g4] } 6. exd6 { [%cal Gd4g7,Rc8g4] } 6... Bxd6! 7. Bf4 (7. Qxg7? Be5! 8. Qg5 Qxg5 9. Bxg5 Bxb2 $19 { And now it's over. }) 7... O-O $15) 5... Nxe5 { Black is one pawn up here, but White can develop the bishops faster. The engine thinks this is already enough compensation. } { [%cal Gc1f4,Gf1c4] } 6. Qe2 Qe7 7. Nc3) 5. Nxd4 d6 6. Nf3 $10) (3... d5 4. exd5 exd4 5. Qxd4 Nxd5 6. Nbc3 Be6 7. Nf4 Nc6 8. Bb5 Nxf4 9. Qxd8+ Rxd8 10. Bxf4 Bd6 { Ivanchuk, V. - Anand, V., 1-0, GCT Blitz YourNextMove, 2017, https://lichess.org/hUFNYRh6 }) 4. f3 Nd6 5. dxe5 Nf5 *


