1. e4 e5 2. Ne2 Nf6 (2... Nc6 3. Nbc3 Bc5 4. f4 d6 5. Na4 Bg4 6. Nxc5 dxc5 7. d3 Qh4+ 8. g3 Qh5 9. Kf2 Bf3 10. Rg1 Nd4 11. h3 O-O-O 12. c3 Nxe2 13. Bxe2 Bxe2 14. Qxe2 Qxh3 15. f5 Nf6 16. Bg5 Ng4+ 17. Kf3 Nh2+ 18. Ke3 f6 19. Bh4 g5 20. fxg6 hxg6 21. Kd2 g5 22. Rh1 gxh4 23. Rxh2 Qxg3 { Schramm, C. - Naiditsch, A., 0-1, Bundesliga 2016-17, https://lichess.org/B8p0uZSP }) (2... c6 { Transposes to a rather uncommon Caro-Kann. }) (2... d5 { Less ambitious than it looks. } 3. exd5 Nf6 4. d4 exd4 5. Qxd4 Qxd5 { Almost symmetrical position, White is still one tempo ahead. } 6. Nbc3 (6. Qxd5 { Best move. } 6... Nxd5) 6... Qxd4 7. Nxd4 Bc5 8. Ndb5 Na6 9. Bf4 O-O 10. f3?! Re8+ 11. Be2 Be6 12. O-O-O Bxa2 13. Rhe1 Nh5 14. Bd2 Be6 15. Ne4 Be7 16. Nd4 Bd7 17. Bxa6 bxa6 18. Bg5 Bxg5+ 19. Nxg5 Nf6 20. Nb3 h6 21. Ne4 Nxe4 22. Rxd7 Nf6 23. Rdd1 Kf8 24. Nc5 Rxe1 25. Rxe1 Re8 26. Rxe8+ Kxe8 27. Nxa6 Kd7 28. Nc5+ Kd6 29. Nd3 c5 30. Kd2 c4 31. Nf4 Kc5 32. h4 a5 33. g4 Nd5 34. Ne2 g6 35. c3 Kd6 $10 { Still fairly equal here. } 36. f4? h5 37. g5? a4 38. Ke1 Ne3 39. Ng3 Ng2+ { Ivanchuk, V. - Carlsen, M., 0-1, GCT Blitz YourNextMove, 2017, https://lichess.org/caoLToDP }) 3. d4 (3. f4) 3... d5 4. exd5 exd4 5. Qxd4 Nxd5 6. Nbc3 Be6 7. Nf4 Nc6 8. Bb5 Nxf4 9. Qxd8+ Rxd8 10. Bxf4 Bd6 11. Bxd6 Rxd6 12. Ne4 Rd5 13. Bxc6+ bxc6 14. Nc3 Rd6 15. O-O Ke7 16. Rfe1 Rd2 17. Rac1 Rhd8 18. f3 Kf8 19. Ne4 R2d4 20. b3 Bf5 21. Ng3 Bg6 22. Nf1 c5 23. Re5 R4d5 24. Re3 f5 25. f4 Rd4 26. g3 Bf7 27. Re5 R8d5 28. Rce1 c4 29. Kf2 g6 30. Rxd5 Rxd5 31. b4 a5 32. a3 axb4 33. axb4 Rd6 34. Re5 Bd5 35. c3 Be4 36. Rc5 Rd1 37. Rxc7 Rc1 38. Ne3 Rxc3 39. Nxc4 Rc2+ 40. Ke3 Rxh2 41. b5 Rh3 42. Kd4 Rxg3 43. Ke5 Rb3 44. Kf6 Ke8 45. Rxh7 Kd8 46. Nd6 Bd3 47. Nb7+ Kc8 48. Nc5 Rc3 49. Nxd3 Rxd3 50. Kxg6 Rd5 51. b6 Rb5 52. b7+ Kb8 53. Rd7 { Ivanchuk, V. - Anand, V., 1-0, GCT Blitz YourNextMove, 2017, https://lichess.org/hUFNYRh6 } *


[Event "London"]
[Site "London"]
[Date "1874.??.??"]
[Round "1"]
[White "Porges, Moritz"]
[Black "Steinitz, Wilhelm"]
[Result "1-0"]
[WhiteElo "2678"]
[BlackElo "2650"]
[Variant "Standard"]
[ECO "C20"]
[Opening "King's Pawn Game: Alapin Opening"]
[StudyName "Alapin Opening: 1.e4 e5 2.Ne2"]
[ChapterName "Porges - Steinitz, 1874, Debut of this opening"]
[ChapterURL "https://lichess.org/study/3xZzsUd5/5XctFcOv"]
[Annotator "https://lichess.org/@/fuxia"]

{ It wasn't Alapin who played this opening first, it was Moritz Porges in 1874. This was the era of romantic chess, and this game is no exception to that. Enjoy!
http://www.porges.net/FamilyTreesBiographies/MoritzPorges1857-1909.html }
1. e4 e5 2. Ne2 Nf6 { Is still the main move nowadays. } 3. Ng3?! { A very dubious move that hasn't been tried again i high level chess. } (3. Nbc3 { is the main line } 3... Nc6 4. g3 Bc5 5. Bg2 { And now the game transposes into a known line: the Vienna Game/Mieses Variation. }) 3... Bc5 4. Bc4 { This reminds us of the Italian game. The difference is of course that White is one tempo down and the knight is a little bit off. } 4... O-O 5. d3 { [%cal Gc1g5] } 5... d5 { Very aggressive. The engine wants to prepare this with c6, but Steinitz just wants to get his light-squared bishop into the game. } 6. exd5 Ng4? { [%cal Rg4f2,Rc5f2] } (6... Nxd5 7. O-O { would have been a more solid continuation. }) 7. Ne4 { Suddenly this knight makes sense! } { [%cal Ge4c5,Be4f2] } (7. O-O { is not an option, because of } 7... Qh4! { [%cal Rg4h2] } 8. h3 Nxf2 9. Rxf2 Qxg3 { And this is completely winning for Black. } { [%csl Bf2][%cal Rc5g1] }) 7... Bb6 (7... Bb4+ 8. Nbc3) 8. h3 f5! { Counter-attack } 9. Bg5 (9. Ng5 { was also possible. } 9... Bxf2+ 10. Ke2 f4 { [%cal Rd8g5] } 11. Ne6 { [%cal Ge6d8] } 11... Qh4 12. Qf1) 9... Qe8 10. hxg4 fxe4 { [%cal Rf8f2,Rb6f2] } 11. d6+ (11. Bh4 { was the best continuation. } { [%cal Gh4f2] }) 11... Kh8 { The only move. And now White has to get some pressure off the f-pawn. } { [%cal Rf8f2,Rb6f2] } (11... Be6 12. Be3) 12. f3 (12. Be3 { was much better. } 12... Bxe3 13. fxe3 Qg6 { [%csl Ge4][%cal Gg6e4] } 14. dxc7 $10) 12... exf3 13. gxf3 Nc6? (13... e4! { was better. } { [%cal Re4f3,Rf8f3] } 14. dxe4 Qe5 { [%cal Re5g5] } 15. Bh4) 14. Kd2 (14. Bd5) 14... Qg6 15. Be7 Nxe7? (15... Bxg4! 16. Bd5 (16. fxg4 Rf2+ { [%cal Rb6e3,Be3c1] } 17. Kc3 Bd4+ 18. Kb3 cxd6 { [%cal Rc6a5] })) 16. dxe7 Qg5+ 17. Kc3 Qxe7?? (17... Re8) 18. Rxh7+ Kxh7 19. Qh1+ { [%cal Gc4g8] } 19... Kg6 20. Qh5+ Kf6 21. Qh4+ { 1-0 Black resigns. } { [%csl Ge6,Gf7,Be7][%cal Gc4f7,Gg4f5,Gh4h6,Bh4e7] } 1-0


