1. e4 { [%clk 0:15:17] } 1... c6 { [%clk 0:15:18] } 2. d3 { Breyer Variation } { [%clk 0:15:19] } 2... d5 { [%clk 0:15:21] } 3. Nd2 { Avoids the queen trade. } { [%clk 0:15:27] } (3. Nf3 dxe4 4. dxe4 Qxd1+ 5. Kxd1) 3... e5 { [%clk 0:15:27] } (3... dxe4 4. dxe4 { [%csl Gd2] }) 4. Ngf3 { [%clk 0:15:34] } 4... Bd6 { [%clk 0:15:35] } 5. g3 { [%clk 0:15:35] } 5... Nf6 { [%clk 0:14:45] } 6. Bg2 { [%clk 0:15:41] } 6... O-O { [%clk 0:14:53] } 7. O-O { [%clk 0:15:46] } 7... Re8 { [%clk 0:15:01] } 8. h3?! { There is no need to protect g4. The knight on f4 is protected twice, and the queen can just step aside in case of Bg4. The pawn on h3 is now weak, it needs extra protection. } { [%clk 0:15:08] } (8. Re1 { Main move. } 8... Nbd7 9. c3 a5 10. Qc2 $10) (8. d4 { is a rare, but interesting try. } 8... exd4 9. exd5 cxd5 10. Nb3 { This reminds of a reversed Panov/Fianchetto, but with the c-pawn still in the original position. Very playable. } { [%cal Gb3d4,Gf3d4,Gd1d4] }) 8... Nbd7 { [%clk 0:15:04] } 9. Re1 { [%clk 0:14:44] } 9... a5 { [%clk 0:13:47] } 10. d4 { A difficult position. It's not so easy to calculate all the possible captures. } { [%clk 0:12:12] } 10... exd4 { [%clk 0:13:31] } (10... Nxe4 { Probably the best try. } 11. Nxe4 (11. Nxe5) (11. dxe5) 11... dxe4 12. Nxe5 (12. Ng5 Nf6 13. dxe5 Rxe5 14. Bf4 Rd5 $15) (12. Rxe4?! f5! 13. Re1 e4 $17) (12. dxe5? exf3 13. Qxd6 fxg2 $19) 12... f5 13. Nc4 Bc7 $15) (10... dxe4) 11. Nxd4 { [%clk 0:12:11] } 11... dxe4 $146 { Novelty. Bc5 was played in Tzermiadianos - Papaioannou, 1995, 0-1 } { [%clk 0:13:30] } 12. Nxe4 { [%clk 0:11:25] } 12... Nxe4 { [%clk 0:13:39] } 13. Rxe4 { [%clk 0:10:46] } 13... Rxe4 { [%clk 0:12:26] } 14. Bxe4 { [%clk 0:10:55] } 14... Nf6 { [%clk 0:12:28] } 15. Bg2 { [%clk 0:10:54] } 15... Qe7 { [%clk 0:11:59] } 16. Qe2 { [%clk 0:09:30] } 16... Qxe2 { [%clk 0:11:57] } 17. Nxe2 { [%clk 0:09:39] } 17... Bf5 { [%clk 0:11:30] } 18. Nd4 { [%clk 0:08:42] } 18... Bg6 { [%clk 0:10:52] } 19. Be3 { [%clk 0:07:41] } 19... R