1. d4 d5 (1... Nf6 2. Nf3 e6 (2... g6 3. Bf4 { A48 "London System" } 3... Bg7 4. e3 O-O 5. Be2 d6 6. h3 { [%cal Gf4h2] } 6... c5 7. c3) 3. Bf4 { A46 "Indian Game: London System" } 3... c5 4. e3 Nc6 5. c3) 2. Nf3 (2. Bf4 { D00 "Mason Attack". Technically not classified as London System, but the resulting position for White is the same. } 2... e6 3. e3 c5 4. c3 Nc6 5. Nf3 Nf6 6. Nbd2 Bd6 7. Bg3 { Offer a bishop trade on g3 to get the semi-open h-file. } 7... O-O 8. Bd3 { [%cal Gd3h7,Gh1h7] } 8... b6 9. Ne5 Bb7 { [%cal Gf2f4,Ge1g1,Gd1f3] }) 2... Nf6 3. Bf4 c5 4. e3 Nc6 5. c3 Qb6 { [%cal Rb6b2] } 6. Qb3 c4 7. Qxb6 axb6 { Continue with normal development here: bring the knight from b1 to c2 (via a3) or d2, bishop to e2 and castle, perhaps go Ne5 to distract Black's development. } { [%csl Gc7,Ge5,Gg3,Ge2,Gd2,Ga3,Gc2,Rh6][%cal Gf3e5,Gb1d2,Gb1a3,Gf1e2,Gf4g3,Gf4c7,Ga3c2,Rh7h6] } 8. Na3 { Prevent b5, perhaps occupy it with the knight. } { [%csl Gb5] } 8... Na7 9. Nd2 Bf5 { Prepare f3, g4. } 10. f3 e6 { [%cal Rf8a3] } 11. b4 { Play b4 when your knight is attacked. } 11... h5 { [%csl Rg4] } (11... cxb3 12. axb3 { [%csl Gb5,Ga3][%cal Ga1a3,Gf1b5] } 12... Nc6 13. b4 { [%cal Ra8a3,Ba3a1] } 13... Be7 14. g4 { That's why Black should play h5 first. } 14... Bg6) *


