1. d4 d5 2. Bf4 { D00 Queen's Pawn Game: Mason Attack } 2... e6 3. e3 c5 4. c3 Nc6 5. Nf3 { The different move order doesn't qualify this as a London System, but de facto it is one. } 5... Bd6 6. Bg3 Nge7 7. Bd3 { This is too early. Now the white queen cannot go to b3 anymore due to the possible fork c5-c4. } (7. dxc5 Bxc5 8. Bd3 (8. b4 Bb6 9. a3)) 7... Bxg3 8. hxg3 Qb6 { White's queen wants to go to b3, the normal move, but it can't. Qc2 is another option. } { [%csl Rc4][%cal Rb6b2] } 9. b3?! { Weakens c3. } { [%cal Rb6a5,Ra5e1] } 9... h6 { Prevent knight attacks. } { [%csl Rg5] } 10. Nbd2 Bd7 { Prepares long castling, which will not happen in this game anyway. } 11. Rc1 { Now the rook does the work of the b2-pawn: protect c3. } 11... Rc8 12. g4 { [%csl Gf5][%cal Re7f5] } 12... e5?! { (-0.02 → 0.63) Inaccuracy. Best move was cxd4. } (12... cxd4 13. exd4 e5 14. Nxe5 Nxe5 15. dxe5 Qa5 16. Nb1 Qxa2 17. O-O O-O 18. Re1 Rfe8 19. c4) 13. Nxe5 Nxe5 14. dxe5 Nc6 15. Be2 { Too passive. Also it smothers the own queen. } (15. Bf5 Bxf5 16. gxf5 Nxe5 17. Nf3 Qd6 18. c4 Rd8 19. cxd5 Qxd5 20. Qxd5 Rxd5 21. Nxe5 Rxe5 22. g4 $14) 15... Nxe5 16. Rh5 (16. g5! { [%cal Gh1h8] }) 16... Qe6 17. Nf3 f6?! { (0.00 → 0.71) Inaccuracy. Best move was Nxg4. } (17... Nxg4 18. Rxd5 Rc7 19. Qd3 O-O 20. Rd1 Nf6 21. Re5 Qb6 22. Nd2 Bc6 23. Bf3 Bxf3 24. Nxf3) 18. g5?! { (0.71 → 0.00) Inaccuracy. Best move was Nxe5. } (18. Nxe5 fxe5 19. e4 dxe4 20. Bc4) 18... g6?! { (0.00 → 0.74) Inaccuracy. Best move was Nxf3+. } (18... Nxf3+ 19. Bxf3 fxg5 20. Qxd5 b5 21. Rh1 Ke7 22. Rd1 Qxd5 23. Bxd5 b4 24. c4 Rhf8 25. f3) 19. Rh1?! { (0.74 → 0.16) Inaccuracy. Best move was Rxh6. } (19. Rxh6 Kf7 20. b4 b6 21. Nxe5+ Qxe5 22. Bf3 Qxg5 23. Rxh8 Rxh8 24. Qxd5+ Qxd5 25. Bxd5+ Be6) 19... fxg5 20. Nxg5 Qf6 21. Nf3 Bc6 22. Nxe5 Qxe5 23. Rh3 Kf7 24. Bd3 (24. f4 Qe4 25. Rg3 { [%cal Ge2d3,Gd3g6,Gg3g6] }) 24... Rce8 25. Qg4 Qe6 26. Qh4 Kg7 27. Rg3 g5 28. Kd2 Kf6 29. Qh5 Ke7 30. Rh1 Kd8 31. Qg6 Qxg6 32. Bxg6 Ref8 33. f3 Ke7 34. Rgh3 Kf6 35. Bc2 Kg7 36. R3h2 Rf6 37. Re1 h5 38. e4 dxe4 39. Bxe4 Rd6+ 40. Kc2 Re6 41. Rhh1 Bxe4+ 42. fxe4 h4 43. Kd3 Kg6 44. Kc4 Rhe8 45. Kd3 Rd8+ 46. Kc2 b5 47. Rhf1?! { (-1.18 → -1.85) Inaccuracy. Best move was Re2. } (47. Re2 c4 48. Rd1 Rxd1 49. Kxd1 Rd6+ 50. Ke1 Rd3 51. e5 Kf7 52. bxc4 bxc4 53. e6+ Ke7) 47... Ra6 48. Ra1 Re8 49. Rfe1 b4?! { (-1.76 → -0.98) Inaccuracy. Best move was Rae6. } (49... Rae6 50. a4 b4 51. cxb4 cxb4 52. Kd3 Rd8+ 53. Ke3 Red6 54. Kf2 Rd2+ 55. Re2 R8d3 56. Rc1) 50. Re3 Rf8 51. Re2 Rf4?! { (-1.16 → -0.50) Inaccuracy. Best move was Rd8. } (51... Rd8 52. Rf2 g4 53. Rf4 Rad6 54. Rf2 Rf6 55. Rxf6+ Kxf6 56. a3 bxc3 57. Kxc3 Ke5 58. Rh1) 52. Kd3 Rd6+ 53. Kc4 bxc3 54. Kxc3 Rd4 55. e5 Rde4 56. Rae1 Rxe2 57. Rxe2 Kf7 58. e6+ Ke7 59. Re5 Rg4 60. Re2 a5 61. a4 Rg3+ 62. Kc4 g4 63. Kb5 Rxb3+ 64. Kxa5?? { (-0.37 → -5.11) Blunder. Best move was Kxc5. } (64. Kxc5 g3 65. Kd5 Rb6 66. Re4 Rd6+ 67. Kc5 Rd2 68. Kb5 Rxg2 69. Rxh4 Kxe6 70. Rg4 Kf5) 64... Rb8?? { (-5.11 → -0.08) Blunder. Best move was g3. } (64... g3) 65. Re4 Rb4 66. Re5 Rb2 67. Rh5 Kxe6 68. Rxh4 g3 69. Rg4 Rb3 70. Rg5?? { (-0.08 → -3.54) Blunder. Best move was Ka6. } (70. Ka6 Kf5 71. Rc4 Rb2 72. Rxc5+ Kg4 73. Rc4+ Kg5 74. a5 Rxg2 75. Rc3 Kg4 76. Ka7 Re2) 70... c4 71. Rc5?? { (-3.47 → -7.10) Blunder. Best move was Ka6. } (71. Ka6 c3 72. a5 Kd6 73. Rg6+ Ke5 74. Ka7 Kd4 75. Rxg3 c2 76. Rxb3 c1=Q 77. a6 Kc5) 71... c3 72. Ka6 Kd6 73. Rc8 Kd5?! { (-8.94 → -8.16) Inaccuracy. Best move was Ke5. } (73... Ke5 74. Ka7) 74. a5 Kd4 75. Ka7 Rb2 76. a6 Rxg2 77. Rd8+ Ke5 78. Re8+ Kd6?? { (-9.19 → -6.02) Blunder. Best move was Kf6. } (78... Kf6 79. Re1 Rb2 80. Ka8 c2 81. a7 g2 82. Re6+ Kf5 83. Re1 Rb4 84. Re5+ Kg4 85. Re1) 79. Rc8?? { (-6.02 → -13.06) Blunder. Best move was Rd8+. } (79. Rd8+ Ke5) 79... Rc2 80. Rg8?? { (-6.63 → -51.58) Blunder. Best move was Rd8+. } (80. Rd8+) 80... g2 81. Ka8 Ra2 82. a7?! { (-20.33 → Mate in 10) Checkmate is now unavoidable. Best move was Rg3. } (82. Rg3 Rxa6+) 82... c2 83. Rd8+ Ke7 { White resigns. } 0-1


