1. d4 (1. Nf3 d5 2. d4 (2. c4 d4 (2... dxc4 3. e3 (3. Na3 a6 4. Nxc4 b5) 3... Be6)) 2... c5 (2... Nf6 3. c4 dxc4 4. e3) 3. c4 dxc4) (1. c4 d5 (1... e5) (1... c5) 2. cxd5) 1... d5 2. c4 dxc4 { In general not such an aggressive opening. Black doesn't try to hold on the pawn. } 3. e4 { Most principled and most popular now. This is the line why we don't see the QGA on the top level that often anymore. } (3. Nf3 Nf6 (3... a6 4. e3 b5 5. a4 Bb7 6. b3 e6 7. bxc4 bxc4 8. Bxc4 Nf6) (3... c5 4. d5 (4. e3 cxd4 5. Bxc4 Qc7 6. Bb3 dxe3 7. Bxe3) 4... Nf6 5. Nc3 e6 6. e4 exd5 7. e5) 4. e3 (4. Nc3 c6 (4... a6)) 4... e6 5. Bxc4 c5 6. O-O a6 7. dxc5 (7. Bb3) (7. a4) (7. Qe2) (7. Bd3) (7. Nc3 b5 8. Be2 Bb7 9. dxc5 Qxd1 10. Rxd1 Bxc5) 7... Bxc5 8. Qxd8+ Kxd8) (3. e3 e5 (3... Nf6 4. Bxc4 e6 5. Nf3) (3... c5 4. Bxc4 cxd4 5. exd4 Qc7 6. Qd3) 4. dxe5 (4. Bxc4 exd4 5. exd4 Nf6 6. Nf3 Be7) 4... Qxd1+ 5. Kxd1) 3... Nf6 { Provokes e5. } (3... e5 4. Nf3 exd4 5. Bxc4 Nc6 (5... Bb4+ 6. Nbd2 Nc6) 6. O-O Be6 7. Nbd2 (7. Bb5 Bc5) (7. Bxe6 fxe6) 7... Qf6) (3... c5 4. d5) (3... Nc6) 4. e5 (4. Nc3 { Not a good move, because it allows Black to play e5. } 4... e5 { [%cal Rd8d1] }) 4... Nd5 5. Bxc4 Nb6 6. Bd3 Nc6 7. Ne2 Bg4 8. f3 (8. Be3 Qd7 9. Nbc3 O-O-O 10. Be4 e6) *


