1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 c5 4. cxd5 cxd4 { D32 Tarrasch Defense/Schara Gambit. Black gives up the d-pawn in favor of the initiative. White has to play very accurately now. } 5. Qa4+ (5. Qxd4 Nc6 { Use the pin to get a development move with a tempo. White's queen wants to stay connected to d5, so … } 6. Qd1 exd5 7. Qxd5 (7. Nxd5? Nf6 8. Nxf6+ Qxf6 { [%cal Gf8b4] } 9. Nf3 (9. a3 Be7! 10. Nf3 O-O 11. e3 Rd8 { Hard to find a good square for the queen. } { [%csl Rc2,Rb3,Ge6,Gf5][%cal Gc8e6,Bf5c2,Be6b3] } 12. Qa4 Bh3! 13. Qf4 (13. gxh3?? Qxf3 14. Rg1 Bh4 15. Rxg7+ (15. Qxh4?? Qd1#) 15... Kxg7 16. Qg4+ Qxg4 17. hxg4 Ne5 $19) (13. Rg1? Be6)) 9... Bb4+ 10. Bd2 (10. Nd2 Bf5 $17) 10... Qxb2) 7... Be6 8. Qxd8+ Rxd8 { White can protect only one of both squares. } { [%cal Gc6d4,Gc6b4] } 9. Bg5 (9. a3?? Nd4 { The king can't go to the d-file. } { [%cal Gd4c2,Ge6b3,Gd4b3] } 10. f4 Nc2+ 11. Kf2 Nxa1 $19) (9. e3 Nb4?! 10. Bb5+ Ke7 11. Kf1 Nf6 12. Nf3 Nc2 13. Rb1 Ne4 14. Be2 (14. Nxe4 Rd1+ 15. Ke2 Rxh1 16. Ng3 Bxa2 17. Nxh1 Bxb1 18. Bd3 g6! 19. Nd2 (19. Kd2?? Bh6 20. Bxc2 Rd8+ 21. Nd4 Rxd4+ 22. Kc3 Rd8 23. Bxb1 Rd1) 19... Nxe3 20. Nxb1) 14... f5)) 5... Bd7 (5... Nd7 { Best move according to SF8. Rarely played. The VHSG player might not be prepared. } 6. Qxd4 exd5 7. Nxd5 Ne7 8. Qe3 { Pins the knight. } { [%cal Re3e8] } 8... Nc5! 9. Nc3 Ne6 10. Qd2 Bd7 $14) (5... b5 6. Qxd4 (6. Nxb5 Bd7 7. d6 Bxb5 8. Qxb5+ Nd7) 6... Nc6 7. Qd1 exd5 8. e4 (8. Qxd5 Bd7)) 6. Qxd4 exd5 7. Qxd5 { [%cal Rd5b7] } 7... Nc6 (7... Nf6 { [%cal Gd5b7] } 8. Qxb7 Nc6) 8. Nf3 (8. Bg5 Nf6 9. Qd2 h6 10. Bxf6 Qxf6 11. e3 O-O-O 12. O-O-O? Bg4 13. Nd5 Rxd5! 14. Qxd5 Ba3! { [%cal Gh8d8,Gf6b2,Ga3b2] } 15. Qb3 Bxd1 16. Qxa3 Qxf2 { [%cal Gf2f1] } 17. Qd3) 8... Nf6 9. Qd1 Bc5 10. e3 Qe7 11. Be2 O-O-O { [%cal Gd7h3] } 12. O-O g5 13. b4 Bxb4 14. Bb2 { [%cal Rb2h8] } 14... g4 15. Nd4 h5 16. Ncb5 { [%cal Rb5a7] } 16... Kb8 17. Qa4 a6 18. Nxc6+ Bxc6 19. Bxf6 Qe4 { [%cal Ge4g2] } 20. f3 Qxe3+ 21. Kh1 Bd2 22. Qb3 Qxe2 23. Nd4 Rxd4 24. Bxd4 Re8 25. Rf2 Qe1+ 26. Rf1 (26. Rxe1?? Rxe1+ 27. Rf1 Rxf1+ 28. Bg1 gxf3 29. gxf3 Bxf3+ 30. Qxf3 Rxf3 31. Bc5 $19) 26... Qe2 27. Rf2 Qe1+ $10 *


