1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. Nc3 e6 5. e3 a6 { D45 Semi-Slav Defense: Accelerated Meran Variation } 6. b3 Bb4 7. Bd2 Nbd7 8. Bd3 O-O 9. O-O Qe7 10. Bc2!? { (Svidler) Normally, Black wants to play Bd6 in these positions, aiming to play e6-e5, but now White can play e4 with the normal reply dxc4 bxc4 e5. Not possible due to the bishop on c2: } 10... Rd8 (10... Bd6 11. e4 dxc4 12. e5 { loses a piece }) 11. a3 Bxa3 12. Rxa3!? Qxa3 13. c5 { All of Black's pieces are very passive now. } 13... b6 14. b4 Ne4?! { (0.00 → 0.77) Inaccuracy. Best move was Qb2. } (14... Qb2?! 15. Na4 (15. Nb1 Ne4 16. Ng5! Nxg5? { Traps the queen } (16... Ndf6 17. Nxe4 Nxe4 18. Be1 e5 19. f3) 17. Bc3 Qa2 18. Bb3) 15... Qa3 16. Nc3) 15. Nxe4 dxe4 16. Bxe4 Rb8?! (16... bxc5 17. bxc5 a5 18. Qc2 Ba6) 17. Bxh7+ (17. Qc2 f5 18. Bc3 { [%cal Gf1a1,Ga1a3] } 18... bxc5 19. Bxf5 exf5 20. Ra1) 17... Kxh7 18. Ng5+ Kg8 19. Qh5 Nf6 20. Qxf7+ Kh8 21. Qc7 Bd7 22. Nf7+ Kh7 23. Nxd8 Rc8 24. Qxb6 Nd5 25. Qa7 (25. Qb7 Rxd8 26. e4 Bc8 27. Qf7 Nc3 28. Bg5 Rxd4 29. h3 Nxe4 30. Qh5+ Kg8 31. Qe8+ Kh7 32. Bc1 Qxb4 33. Qxc8 Nxc5 34. Qxc6 { Might lead to a draw }) 25... Rxd8 26. e4 Qd3 27. exd5 Qxd2 28. Qc7 Qg5 29. dxc6?! { (1.06 → 0.14) Inaccuracy. Best move was d6. } (29. d6 Qf6 30. h3 Be8 31. Re1 Bd7 32. Rd1 Qf8 33. Ra1 Qe8 34. Rxa6 Rc8 35. Qa5 e5) 29... Bc8 30. h3 Qd5 31. Rd1 e5? { (0.47 → 1.87) Mistake. Best move was Rf8. } (31... Rf8 32. Rd3 Qe4 33. Rg3 Qxd4 { equal position }) 32. Rd3 exd4 33. Qe7 Bf5?? { (1.87 → 11.93) Blunder. Best move was Rg8. } (33... Rg8 34. Qh4+ Kg6 35. Rxd4 Qe5 36. c7 Re8 37. Rd6+ Kf7 38. Rd8 Qa1+ 39. Kh2 Qe5+ 40. f4) 34. Rg3 Bg6 35. Qh4+ { Black resigns. } 1-0


