1. e4 e6 2. d3 { C00 French Defense/King's Indian Attack.
It is important to get the center set up first in order to avoid an early queen trade. } (2. Nf3 { is playable. } 2... d5 3. exd5 (3. e5 c5 4. c3 d4) 3... exd5 4. d4) 2... d5 3. Nd2! { This is played to avoid a queen trade after dxe4 } 3... Nf6 (3... dxe4 4. dxe4 { [%cal Rd8d2] }) 4. g3 { White needs more protection for e4, Black tries to open the center immediately. } (4. Ngf3 b6 5. g3 dxe4 6. dxe4 Bb7 7. Qe2 Nc6 8. c3 { saves some important squares. } { [%csl Gd4,Gb4][%cal Rc6b4,Rc6d4] } (8. Bg2 { is too slow and leads to an uncomfortable position: } 8... Nb4 { [%cal Rb4c2] } 9. Qc4 { [%cal Rb4c2,Gc4c2] } 9... Ba6 10. Qb3 Nxe4! 11. Nxe4 Qd5 12. Qxd5 exd5 { [%cal Rb4c2,Rd5e4] } 13. Nc3 Nxc2+ 14. Kd1 Nxa1) 8... a5 9. Bg2 Ba6 10. Nc4 e5 11. O-O Bc5 12. Nh4 O-O 13. Nf5) 4... c5 (4... dxe4 5. dxe4 e5 6. Ngf3 { [%cal Gf3e5] } (6. Bg2) 6... Nc6 7. Bg2 Bc5 { [%cal Rf6g4,Rg4f2,Rc5f2] } 8. O-O O-O 9. c3 { Block Black's knight. } { [%csl Gb4,Gd4][%cal Rc6b4,Rc6d4] } 9... a5 { Prevent b4. } { [%csl Rb4] } 10. Qc2 { [%cal Gc2e4] } 10... Be6 { [%cal Re6c4] } 11. Ng5 { [%cal Gg5e6] } 11... Bd7 12. Nc4 h6 (12... Qe7) (12... Re8) 13. Nf3 $7 { [%csl Be5][%cal Gc4e5,Gf3e5,Rc6e5] } 13... Qe7 { Protect e5. } 14. Ne3 (14. a4 { Horvath, Gabor - Simonyi, Zoltan, 0-1, HUN-chT2 Erkel 1112, 2011, https://lichess.org/MOCvU82O }) 14... Be6 15. Nh4 Rfd8 16. Nhf5 (16. Nef5?! { Now White's knights don't help in the center anymore. } 16... Qd7 $15) 16... Qf8 $10 { De Toledo, Charles Mann - Balutescu, Mihail Goanga, 1/2-1/2, WS/MN/110, 2014, https://lichess.org/ySIA4hlF }) 5. Bg2 Nc6 6. Ngf3 Be7 7. O-O O-O 8. e5 Nd7 9. Re1 b5 10. Nf1 b4 11. h4 a5 12. Bf4 a4 13. a3 bxa3 14. bxa3 Na5 *


