1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Bc5 4. b4 Nxb4 { This is rarely played. From here on I followed Stockfish's recommendations. The depth, evaluation and alternative moves are given in the comments. } 5. c3 { depth 42 -0.17 } (5. O-O { -0.18 }) (5. d4 { -0.31 }) (5. Nxe5?? { Taking that pawn is not a good idea. The game is basically over already. } 5... Qf6! { [%cal Gf6a1,Rc5f2,Rf6f2] } 6. O-O { Sadly, this is the best move in this position. } (6. Bxf7+? { Don't try to make it even sharper. } 6... Kf8 7. O-O { depth 32: -2.42, still
the best move! Ng4 Qxa1 - 2.43, Qf3 Nc2+ -3.12 } (7. d4? { Futile attempt to go all in. } 7... Bxd4 { [%cal Gd4a1,Rd4e5] } 8. f4 { Bxa1 is also an option, but the knight is currently stronger than the rook. } 8... Bxe5 9. fxe5 Qh4+ { [%cal Gh4e4] } 10. Kd2 Kxf7 11. Rf1+ Kg6! 12. Qf3 Nh6 { depth 34: -3.45 } 13. g3 { depth 33: -3.59, Qf4: -3.84, Na3: -3.85 } 13... Qg4 { depth 36: -3.64, Qh5: -3.08, Qxh2: -2.87 } 14. Qe3 { depth 31: -3.80, Qf4: -3.85, Bb2: -3.99 } 14... d5 { depth 40: -4.14, Qh5: -4.11, Rd8: -4.00 } (14... Qh5 15. Nc3 d6 16. Rb1 Ng4 { [%cal Gg4e3] } 17. Qe2 Nc6 18. exd6 Nd4 19. Qg2 Qa5 20. e5 Qxe5 21. Nd5 Re8 22. Nf4+ Kg5 23. Qd5 Ne3 24. Qxe5+ Rxe5) (14... Rd8 15. a3 Nc6 16. Bb2 d6 17. exd6 cxd6 18. Nc3 Ne5 19. Kc1 Be6 20. Rf4 Qh3 21. Nd5 Nhg4 22. Qe2 Qxh2 23. Qxh2 Nxh2 24. Nc7 Nd3+ 25. cxd3 Rac8) 15. exd6 Qh5 { [%cal Gh5h2,Bh2d2] } 16. h4 Rd8 17. Kc3 Rxd6 18. Qg5+ (18. Kxb4? { Yes, White gets the piece back. But Black gets a devastating attack! } 18... Rb6+ 19. Kc3 Qa5+ 20. Kd3 (20. Kd4?? Rd6+ 21. Kc4 Be6#) 20... Rd6+ 21. Ke2 Bg4+ 22. Rf3 Rf8 23. Nd2 Qb5+ 24. c4 Bxf3+ 25. Nxf3 Qxc4+ 26. Ke1 Re8 $19 { -5.63 }) 18... Qxg5 19. Bxg5 a5 20. Kb2 Bh3 21. Rf3 Bg2 22. Rc3 Bxe4 23. Nd2 Bc6 24. Re1 Nf7) 7... Qxe5) 6... Qxe5 7. c3 { depth 30: -1.19, Nc3: -3.28, d4: -3.75 } 7... Nc6) 5... Nc6 { depth 32 -0.09 Practically the only move. Protects also e5. } { [%cal Gc6e5] } (5... Na6? { Mistake. Now e5 *is* vulnerable. +1.45 }) (5... b5 { The counter gambit. Really bad either. +2.10 }) 6. O-O { depth 33 -0.16 } (6. d4 { A bit too early. -0.31 }) (6. Bb3 { Too passive. -0.73 }) 6... Bb6 { depth 33: -0.34 } (6... d6 { -0.31 }) (6... Qe7 { -0.31 }) 7. d4 { depth 32: -0.20, a4: -0.35, h3: -0.67 } 7... d6 { depth 32: -0.30, exd4: -0.10,
