1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. e4 d6 5. Nf3 O-O 6. Be2 (6. h3 { Loses a tempo, but the engine likes it. } 6... e5 7. d5 Nfd7 8. Be2 a5 { Now we have a strong deviation from the main line. } 9. h4 Nf6 { This is an engine move. The knight has moved back and forth now, and black is seriously behind on development. I'd rather not play this line. }) 6... e5 { The engine wants to play 7. d5 immediately, but the main line is castling first. } 7. O-O Nc6 { The idea is to move the knight to e7, but is very slow. } 8. d5 Ne7 9. Ne1 { Get the knight to the queen side to support an attack there, and make room for the f-pawn that has to step up soon. } 9... Nd7 { Makes room for the black f-pawn for an attack on the king side. } 10. Be3 { Support the c4-c5 attack. } 10... f5 { Threatens f5 to attack the bishop on e3. } 11. f3 { Create a fallback space for that bishop. } 11... f4 12. Bf2 g5 *


