1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Bc4 Nf6 { Dubois Réti Defense, the main line. } 5. e5 { Advance Variation } (5. O-O { Slower, but playable. It does take the tension out of the game, and with accurate play, the game will probably end in a draw. } 5... Nxe4 6. Re1 d5 7. Bxd5! Qxd5 8. Nc3 Qh5 9. Nxe4 Be6 10. Bg5 { Prevents O-O-O. } { [%cal Gg5d8] } 10... Bd6 11. Nxd6+ cxd6 12. Bf4 { [%cal Gf4d6,Gf3d4] } 12... Qd5 13. c3 Rc8 (13... dxc3?? 14. Qxd5 { [%cal Ge1e8] }) 14. b3 O-O 15. Nxd4 Nxd4 16. Qxd4 Qxd4 17. cxd4 d5 18. Rac1 Rxc1 19. Rxc1 $10) (5. Ng5?! { Leads to complications … for White! } 5... d5 6. exd5 Na5 (6... Qe7+ 7. Kf1 Ne5 { [%cal Ge5c4] } 8. Qxd4 Nxc4 9. Qxc4 h6 10. Nf3 $15 { Nothing achieved. Black is even slightly better. }) 7. Qxd4 Nxc4 8. Qxc4 Qxd5 9. Qe2+ Be7 10. O-O $10 { No attack, equal position. }) (5. Nxd4 Nxe4 6. Nxc6 (6. O-O d5 7. Bb5 Bd7 8. c4 (8. Re1?! { Too early! Black gets a nice attack now. } 8... Bd6! { [%cal Rd6h2] } 9. Nc3 (9. f3? Nxd4 10. Bxd7+ Kxd7! 11. fxe4 Qh4 { [%cal Rh4h2,Rd6h2] } 12. e5) 9... O-O)) 6... bxc6 7. O-O d5 8. Re1 Bc5 9. Be3 Bxe3 10. Rxe3 O-O 11. Bd3) 5... d5 (5... Ng4 { [%cal Rg4e5] } 6. O-O Be7 (6... Ngxe5? 7. Nxe5 Nxe5 8. Re1 { [%cal Gf2f4] } 8... Qe7 (8... d6 9. f4 Be7 10. fxe5 dxe5 11. Rxe5 O-O) 9. f4 { Black's best option is giving up the queen. } 9... Nxc4 10. Rxe7+ Bxe7 11. Qxd4 { [%cal Gd4c4,Gd4g7] } 11... d5 12. Qxg7 Rf8 $16) 7. Re1) 6. Bb5 Ne4 (6... Nd7) 7. Nxd4 Bd7 { Threatening Nxe5. } { [%cal Rc6e5] } (7... Bc5) 8. Bxc6 bxc6 (8... Bxc6 9. Nxc6 bxc6 10. O-O) *


