1. b4 { A00 Polish Opening/General. Also known as Sokolsky Opening (after https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alexey_Sokolsky who wrote a book about it) or Orangutan Opening (see the game [Tartakower - Maroczy]).
This is not a good opening. I don't recommend playing it, but you should know how to play against it. } 1... e5 { [%cal Rf8b4] } (1... b5?! { Symmetrical Variation }) (1... c6 { Outflank Variation } 2. Bb2 a5 3. b5 cxb5 4. e4 { Schühler Gambit } { [%cal Rf1b5] } 4... b4 5. a3 Nf6 6. e5 Nd5 7. axb4 Nxb4 { Timmermans, M. - Smeets, J., 1-0, ch-NED Internet 2016, https://lichess.org/XDqH83QT }) (1... c5?! { Birmingham Gambit } 2. bxc5 e5) (1... f5?! { Dutch Defense } 2. Bb2 Nf6) (1... Nc6?! { Grigorian Variation }) (1... Nh6?! { Karniewski Variation }) (1... Nf6 2. Bb2 (2. Nf3 { Zukertort System }) 2... g6 { King's Indian Variation } (2... d5 3. e3 e6 4. b5 { Schiffler-Sokolsky Variation }) (2... e6 3. b5 (3. a3 c6 4. d3 a5 5. bxa5 d5 6. e4 { Orangutan-Hartlaub Gambit }) 3... a6 $10 { Queenside Defense } (3... b6 $10 { Queen's Indian Variation }) 4. a4 axb5 5. axb5 Rxa1 6. Bxa1 $10 { Rooks Swap Line }) 3. e4?! { King's Indian Variation/Schiffler Attack } (3. c4 Bg7 4. e3 d6 5. Nf3 O-O 6. d4 $10 { King's Indian Variation/Sokolsky Attack })) (1... d5 2. Bb2 (2. Nf3 { Transposition: Zukertort Opening/Santasiere's Folly } 2... Bg4 3. Bb2 Nd7 4. e3) 2... Qd6?! { German Defense } (2... c6 3. a4?! { Myers Variation }) (2... Bf5 { Baltic Defense }) 3. a3 e5 4. e4?! dxe4 5. f3?! $17 { Orangutan-Diemer Gambit }) 2. Bb2 { [%cal Rb2e5] } (2. a3 { Bugayev Attack }) 2... Bxb4 (2... f6 3. b5 { Bugayev Advance Variation } (3. e4?! { Tartakower Gambit } 3... Bxb4 4. Bc4 Nc6 $15 5. f4 Qe7 6. f5 g6 $17 { Tartakower Gambit/Brinckmann Variation })) (2... c5?! { Wolferts Gambit }) (2... d6 $10 { Czech Defense }) 3. Bxe5 Nf6 4. c4 O-O 5. Nf3 d5 6. e3 (6. a3) 6... Bf5 (6... Re8) (6... Nc6) (6... Nbd7) 7. Bb2 (7. Nc3) 7... Nbd7 $10 *


