1. d4 { [%clk 0:30:00] } 1... d5 { [%clk 0:30:00] } 2. c4 { [%clk 0:29:58] } 2... e6 { [%clk 0:30:00] } 3. Nf3 { I tried not to play the Nimzo. } { [%clk 0:29:54] } 3... Nc6 { [%clk 0:30:00] } 4. e3 { I know this is "correct", but I still don't like how that move blocks my black bishop. } { [%clk 0:29:21] } 4... Be7 { [%clk 0:30:00] } 5. g3 { [%clk 0:29:15] } 5... a6 { [%clk 0:30:00] } 6. Nbd2 { Should have played b3 here, so the white bishop doesn't have to protect c4 anymore. Nbd2 does that too, but it blocks my black bishop even more. } { [%clk 0:29:12] } 6... Nf6 { [%clk 0:30:00] } 7. Bg2 { [%clk 0:29:10] } 7... h6 { [%clk 0:30:00] } 8. cxd5 { Create a target for my white bishop. Black cannot defend d5 with the c-pawn, which is blocked by its knight. } { [%clk 0:28:53] } 8... exd5 { [%clk 0:29:59] } 9. O-O { [%clk 0:28:48] } 9... Bf5 { [%clk 0:29:59] } 10. Ne5 { [%clk 0:28:29] } 10... Qd6 { [%clk 0:29:59] } 11. f4 { I needed a second protection for that knight. But this move was too passive. Ndf3 would have been better, g4 even more aggressive. } { [%clk 0:28:20] } (11. g4 Bc8 12. f4 g5 13. e4 dxe4 14. Nxe4) 11... h5 { [%clk 0:29:59] } 12. h4 { I was a little bit afraid of black's h4, so I played it myself. Missed Ndf3 again, and Qb3 didn't even come to my mind. Still have to learn to look at the whole board, not just one particular situation. } { [%clk 0:28:08] } 12... Rb8 { [%clk 0:29:59] } 13. Re1 { e3 isn't hanging, but it isn't protected either. Black's Ng4 might be a real threat. } { [%clk 0:27:33] } 13... g6 { [%clk 0:29:59] } 14. e4 { Decided to open the position. A little bit too early, made my position worse. } { [%clk 0:27:15] } 14... dxe4 { [%clk 0:29:59] } 15. Nxe4 { [%clk 0:27:12] } 15... Bxe4 { [%clk 0:29:59] } 16. Bxe4 { [%clk 0:27:10] } 16... Qxd4+ { [%clk 0:29:58] } 17. Qxd4 { [%clk 0:26:44] } 17... Nxd4 { [%clk 0:29:58] } 18. Be3 { [%clk 0:26:19] } 18... Ne6 { Now I'm a pawn down, but I have the bishop pair. } { [%clk 0:29:58] } 19. Bf3 { [%clk 0:26:03] } 19... Bb4 { [%clk 0:29:58] } 20. Red1 { [%clk 0:25:53] } 20... Be7 { [%clk 0:29:58] } 21. Rac1 { [%clk 0:25:41] } 21... c6 { [%clk 0:29:58] } 22. Rd3 { With the idea of Rb3 and then Bxc3. Too slow. } { [%clk 0:25:27] } 22... O-O { [%clk 0:29:58] } 23. Rcd1 { [%clk 0:25:19] } 23... Rbd8 { [%clk 0:29:58] } 24. Bb6 { [%clk 0:24:52] } 24... Rc8 { [%clk 0:29:58] } 25. Nd7 { Trying to get a rook on the 7th rank. } { [%clk 0:24:34] } 25... Rfe8 { [%clk 0:29:58] } 26. Nxf6+ { [%clk 0:24:13] } 26... Bxf6 { [%clk 0:29:57] } 27. b3 { [%clk 0:24:02] } 27... Be7 { [%clk 0:29:57] } 28. Rd7 { [%clk 0:23:33] } 28... Rb8 { [%clk 0:29:57] } 29. Ba7 { Should have moved my king to a safe place first. } { [%clk 0:23:19] } 29... Rbc8 { [%clk 0:29:57] } 30. Rxb7 { [%clk 0:23:14] } 30... Kf8 { [%clk 0:29:57] } 31. Bb6 { [%clk 0:21:56] } 31... Bc5+ { [%clk 0:29:57] } 32. Bxc5+ { [%clk 0:21:18] } 32... Nxc5 { [%clk 0:29:57] } 33. Rb6 { Funny that this a pretty safe place for the rook. :) } { [%clk 0:21:00] } 33... a5 { [%clk 0:29:57] } 34. Rxc6 { [%clk 0:20:50] } 34... Rxc6 { [%clk 0:29:57] } 35. Bxc6 { [%clk 0:20:49] } 35... Re6 { [%clk 0:29:56] } 36. Bd5 { [%clk 0:20:40] } 36... Rd6 { I saw that coming, but I wanted to exchange material, because I'm a pawn up, and my pawns are placed on both sides of the board. } { [%clk 0:29:56] } 37. Bf3 { [%clk 0:20:19] } 37... Rxd1+ { [%clk 0:29:56] } 38. Bxd1 { [%clk 0:20:17] } 38... Ke7 { [%clk 0:29:56] } 39. Kf2 { Should have played Bc2 first to prevent the following knight move. } { [%clk 0:20:15] } 39... Ne4+ { [%clk 0:29:56] } 40. Kf3 { Nc3 is now possible. But it didn't happen. Phew! } { [%clk 0:20:13] } 40... Nd6 { [%clk 0:29:56] } 41. Bc2 { [%clk 0:19:57] } 41... Kf6 { [%clk 0:29:56] } 42. Be4 { [%clk 0:19:54] } 42... Nf5 { [%clk 0:29:56] } 43. Bxf5 { [%clk 0:19:51] } 43... gxf5 { [%clk 0:29:56] } 44. Ke3 { [%clk 0:19:46] } 44... Kg6 { [%clk 0:29:56] } 45. Kd4 { [%clk 0:19:44] } 45... Kf6 { [%clk 0:29:56] } 46. Kd5 { [%clk 0:19:42] } 46... Ke7 { [%clk 0:29:55] } 47. a3 { [%clk 0:19:28] } 47... Kf6 { [%clk 0:29:55] } 48. b4 { [%clk 0:19:25] } 48... Ke7 { Black had just given up here. } { [%clk 0:29:55] } 49. bxa5 { [%clk 0:19:21] } 49... Kf8 { [%clk 0:29:55] } 50. Kd6 { [%clk 0:19:17] } 50... Kg8 { [%clk 0:29:55] } 51. Ke7 { [%clk 0:19:13] } 51... Kh8 { [%clk 0:29:55] } 52. Kxf7 { [%clk 0:19:11] } 52... Kh7 { [%clk 0:29:55] } 53. a6 { [%clk 0:19:06] } 53... Kh6 { [%clk 0:29:55] } 54. a7 { [%clk 0:19:04] } 54... Kh7 { [%clk 0:29:55] } 55. a8=Q { [%clk 0:19:00] } 55... Kh6 { [%clk 0:29:55] } 56. Qh8# { 1-0 White wins by checkmate. } { [%clk 0:18:58] } 1-0


